window.CHAMP_FULL.masteryi = {"aatrox":{"tldr":"A genuine race: you concede the level 1-5 lane to Aatrox's sweetspot Qs and drain, then flip the lane the instant your on-hit item lands and Alpha Strike starts dodging his combo.","winCon":"Farm safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos through his strong early, never duel him before your first on-hit item, then once Kraken/BORK is online, Q-cancel into his W pull or Q3 knockup so he whiffs his combo and your true-damage on-hit out-DPSes a drain bruiser with no kite. Bring anti-heal to cut his passive and World Ender lifesteal.","enemyWin":"Aatrox wins by punishing levels 1-5: he lands outer-edge sweetspot Qs and W chains while you have only Alpha Strike to escape, out-trades you with passive drain, and at 6 his World Ender combat stats let him all-in you before your item spike lands. If he denies your CS and stays ahead, his healing simply out-paces your early on-hit damage.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Aatrox","rating":"6/10","why":"He has Q range and a sweetspot you can't answer; you only have short-range autos, so respect his Q1 edge and just last-hit."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Aatrox","rating":"6/10","why":"His E dash plus a second Q sweetspot lets him trade and drain through your Wuju autos before you have E to add true damage."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Aatrox","rating":"6/10","why":"Full Q combo online with W pull threat; one chained Q-W catches you with no Highlander to break it yet."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Aatrox","rating":"5/10","why":"Your E Wuju Style true damage and W Meditate sustain come online, shrinking his trade lead but his sweetspots still out-poke you."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"His World Ender all-in answers your Highlander, but R's slow immunity plus Alpha Strike dodging his Q3 knockup makes it a genuine coin-flip."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken/BORK on-hit DPS lands; Alpha Strike now goes untargetable through his W pull and you out-damage a drain bruiser in an extended fight."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At 2+ items with anti-heal your on-hit true damage and Highlander resets shred his healing faster than he can drain — you win every extended fight."}],"breakdown":{"early":"You are flatly weaker levels 1-3. Aatrox out-ranges your autos with Q, his sweetspot edge chunks you and heals him on hit, and your only escape is Alpha Strike on cooldown. Do not contest — last-hit with autos, use Q to safely poke the wave and reset your attack timer, and concede aggression. Standing in his Q1 arc to CS is the single biggest way to lose this lane.","mid":"Levels 4-5 stabilize you: Wuju Style adds true damage to short autos and Meditate lets you cancel a trade and heal through his drain. At 6, Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity finally let you stick or escape — but his World Ender does the same for him, so it's a true skill window, not a free spike.","late":"Once you have Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King plus a second item, the lane flips hard. Your on-hit DPS, Alpha Strike untargetability, and Highlander resets out-fight a drain bruiser who has no way to kite you. Anti-heal (Bramble/Executioner's) is what closes the gap by gutting his passive and R lifesteal.","wave":"Best wave: a wave you can freeze just outside tower so he can't all-in without diving, letting you scale safely. Worst wave: a wave shoved at you under no pressure where he free-pokes with sweetspot Q while you're forced to walk up and CS. Crash timing: crash and reset right before your first on-hit item completes so you come back with the spike and can start contesting trades.","cooldowns":"Track his Q sweetspot rhythm and especially his W (Umbral Dash chain-pull) — Meditate or Alpha Strike timing should answer the W catch, and his R (World Ender) is the all-in you must respect from 6 until your item lands.","trading":"Early, you lose every prolonged trade and break even at best on a quick Alpha-Strike-and-back. Post-item, your trade is to Q into his combo (going untargetable through the knockup/pull), auto with Wuju + on-hit, and reset Highlander if he dies.","spikes":"Aatrox: levels 2-3 (Q ranks) and 6 (World Ender). Master Yi: 6 (Highlander), and decisively your first on-hit item, then again at 2 items + anti-heal.","feeding":"If you fall behind, his drain snowballs and you can't fight him at all — but Yi farms from range with Alpha Strike better than most, so abandon the lane, freeze/farm safe, and look to side-lane or jungle camps to hit your item timing anyway.","carry":"If you get ahead, your snowball is among the steepest in the game: Highlander resets let you chain kills through teamfights, Alpha Strike dodges peel CC, and on-hit true damage melts even his tankier builds. Take the lead to other lanes the moment your item is up.","difficulty":"It's a 5/10 because the lane is two different games — a losing early you survive, then a winning late you must reach. Difficulty is all in patience: the kill pressure is on Aatrox until your item, and Yi players throw by trying to fight him at level 3."},"focus":{"text":"Aatrox's W (Umbral Dash chain-pull) sets up his sweetspot Q knockup combo — the catch that kills you before your item. Dodge the W zone or Alpha Strike out of it, and respect his R all-in.","letters":["W","R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Q, don't fight","d":"Use Alpha Strike to last-hit safely and reset your attack timer while you're weak levels 1-5. Concede the early lane and reach your on-hit item even — that's the whole game."},{"t":"Dodge his combo with Q","d":"Time Alpha Strike's untargetability to break his W pull or Q3 knockup. Going untargetable mid-combo wastes his entire damage rotation and flips the trade once you're itemized."},{"t":"Buy anti-heal","d":"Bramble Vest or Executioner's Calling early gates his passive drain and World Ender lifesteal, which is the single highest-value purchase in this specific lane."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't stand in his Q arc","d":"Sweetspot Q edges chunk you and heal him; CSing inside the Q1 arc is how you lose lane before you ever scale."},{"t":"Don't all-in pre-item","d":"Before Kraken/BORK, a prolonged fight always favors his drain — Meditate buys time but doesn't win the trade. Never extend without your spike."},{"t":"Don't waste Q as escape into his R","d":"If you blow Alpha Strike to engage and he ults, you have no second escape and World Ender combat stats run you down — save Q to dodge his lockup, not to chase."}],"tradeGood":"Post-item: Q into his combo to go untargetable through the W pull/Q3 knockup, then Wuju-auto with on-hit and anti-heal while he can't kite you, resetting Highlander on the kill.","tradeBad":"A level 2-3 extended brawl where he lands a sweetspot Q and chain-pulls you — his drain out-sustains your autos and you have no Highlander to break it.","ahead":"Press a lead by forcing fights only once your first on-hit item is up — shove the wave with Alpha Strike, then look to all-in when his W or R is down. Your Highlander resets mean a single kill snowballs into roams: take Alpha Strike DPS to grouped fights and dodge their key CC with untargetability. Keep anti-heal updated so his drain never claws the lead back.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Aatrox - Track: Aatrox's W (Umbral Dash chain-pull) sets up his sweetspot Q knockup combo — the catch that kills you before your item. Dodge the W zone or Alpha Strike out of it, and respect his R all-in.. - Farm safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos through his strong early, never duel him before your first on-hit item, then once Kraken/BORK is online, Q-cancel into his W pull or Q3 knockup so he whiffs his combo and your true-damage on-hit out-DPSes a drain bruiser with no kite. Bring anti-heal to cut his passive and World Ender lifesteal.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A genuine race: you concede the level 1-5 lane to Aatrox's sweetspot Qs and drain, then flip the lane the instant your on-hit item lands and Alpha Strike starts dodging his combo."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing early lane by farming with Alpha Strike instead of dueling, then flip the matchup the instant your first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) lands. From there, Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges his combo and your on-hit true damage out-DPSes a drain bruiser who cannot kite you."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Aatrox owns levels 1-3 (Q range/sweetspots), it's a skill coin-flip at 4-6 as your Wuju/Meditate/Highlander come online versus his World Ender, then you take over decisively at first item and dominate at 2+ items with anti-heal."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Back off and just CS through levels 1-5 — you lose any extended trade to his drain. Only start trading once your on-hit item completes, and only by Q-cancelling his combo; never extend while his Q sweetspot and W are up."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave neutral or slightly frozen outside your tower early so he can't free-poke or all-in without diving. Crash and reset right as your first item finishes so you return with the spike, then you can start shoving to deny him roam tempo."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability is your key tool — time it to phase through his W (Umbral Dash) pull and his Q3 knockup so his whole combo whiffs. Meditate's damage reduction blunts a single sweetspot Q, and Highlander's slow immunity ignores his Q/W slows once you commit. Anti-heal directly counters his passive and R lifesteal."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the on-hit attack-speed flip (or Conqueror if you want more early trade staying power vs his drain). Secondary Triumph/Legend: Alacrity from Precision, then Resolve with Conditioning/Second Wind, or Bone Plating to eat his early Q-W burst. Run Second Wind specifically vs his poke."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite if you intend to flip the lane and have anti-heal value at 6; Flash + Teleport is the safer, more standard pick since you're conceding early and want to reach items and rejoin the map after a back."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Open Doran's Blade with anti-heal early — Executioner's Calling or Bramble Vest is mandatory here. Build Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first for the on-hit spike, then Wit's End (great vs his AD and tankiness) or Terminus, Berserker's Greaves, and a defensive component (Bramble/armor) versus his physical damage."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Your only real pre-6 all-in is if he whiffs a sweetspot Q and burns W with no jungler near. Your true all-in window is first on-hit item onward, ideally when his W or R is on cooldown — that's when Q-cancel plus on-hit DPS wins decisively."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're extremely gankable levels 1-5 with only Alpha Strike to escape, and his W sets up easy gank-pulls — ward and play safe. Once you have Highlander and an item, you become the better dive target FOR your jungler: collapse on Aatrox and your resets snowball the whole map."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi throw here is trying to fight Aatrox at level 2-3 because the matchup reads EVEN — it isn't even yet. Players also waste Alpha Strike to chase instead of saving it to dodge his combo, and skip anti-heal, letting his drain erase their item lead."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're losing, stop contesting entirely: freeze/farm safe, use Alpha Strike to soak CS from range, and hit your item timing off side camps if needed. Don't give him kills — a behind Yi who still scales beats an ahead Aatrox who can't kite at two items."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Once ahead, close with your item spike up: all-in when his W/R is down, take Highlander resets through fights, and keep anti-heal current so his drain never recovers. Move your DPS to grouped objectives and let untargetability dodge their peel."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A true 50/50 (49.55%) two-act lane — concede the early to his sweetspots, then out-scale him hard at first item with Alpha Strike dodging his combo and anti-heal gutting his drain."}]},"akali":{"tldr":"Akali edges this lane because her Twilight Shroud blanks your Alpha Strike target-lock and her R re-engage punishes you the second Highlander drops — survive to your on-hit first item and the duel flips.","winCon":"Concede the early game, farm with Alpha Strike from max range, and dodge her shuriken pokes until you hit your on-hit spike (Kraken/BORK). Once itemized, force extended fights where Wuju Style true damage and Highlander resets out-DPS her burst-then-vanish pattern.","enemyWin":"Akali pokes you down with E shuriken and Q+passive procs, drops Twilight Shroud the instant you Alpha Strike in so your blink fizzles, then bursts you with Shadow Dance once you're low and slow without Highlander up. Roaming on her R mobility, she snowballs mid/jungle while your weak early lane can't punish her absence.","diff":"TRICKY","tone":"#ff8b3d","diffRating":"7/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Akali","rating":"6/10","why":"Akali's auto + Q with passive marks out-trades your short-range Wuju autos, and you have no E true damage yet to punish back."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Akali","rating":"6/10","why":"At 2 points in Q she pokes you off the wave; your Alpha Strike resets your attack timer but can't close distance through her early kite."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Akali","rating":"7/10","why":"Akali hits her E shuriken dash for repositioning and her trade pattern outpaces yours — you still have no escape but Q and no Meditate sustain online."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate healing come online, letting you out-sustain her energy-gated pokes in short trades if you Alpha onto her after she E's."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity let you stick to her through Shadow Dance; if she ults in to burst, you chase-reset and Meditate the return."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King on-hit DPS lets you melt her squishy build in an extended duel, with Alpha Strike dodging her R re-engage."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Akali","rating":"6/10","why":"Akali's AP item scaling and Twilight Shroud reset reclaim the late skirmish — her Shroud blanks your target-lock and she kites your on-hit with R double-dash."}],"breakdown":{"early":"You are flatly behind levels 1-3 — Akali's Q with passive mark out-trades your short Wuju autos and you have no Wuju Style true damage or Meditate sustain yet. Do not contest; farm with Alpha Strike from max range and tank the shuriken poke only when you must last-hit. Your only goal is to reach level 4-5 even in CS without burning Flash to a roam-into-gank.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are your stabilization. Wuju Style true damage and Meditate healing let you take short trades and out-sustain her energy-gated poke, and level 6 Highlander is your first real spike — its slow immunity and move/attack speed let you stick through her Shadow Dance burst instead of getting kited to death. Bait her E or R, then commit.","late":"At 2+ items the duel is yours in an extended fight: Kraken/BORK on-hit plus Wuju true damage shreds her squishy AP build, and Alpha Strike's untargetable blink dodges her R re-engage. But Akali is a hard SCALER — once she completes AP items her Shroud reset and double-dash R let her reclaim the very late game, so close before she gets there.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push you control, so you fight her on YOUR side near your turret where her roam value drops and a gank on her is lethal. Worst wave: a wave shoved under her turret early, where her shuriken poke and Shroud zone you off CS while she's safe. Crash timing: crash the wave just before your back at first-item so you reset on tempo and return with your on-hit spike before she does.","cooldowns":"Track Twilight Shroud (W) above all — its cooldown is long, and Alpha Strike can't lock onto her inside it, so the window AFTER she's used Shroud is when you commit. Also count her Shadow Dance (R) charges.","trading":"Short-trade only when her Q/E is on cooldown or her energy is low: Alpha Strike in, get a Wuju Style + Double Strike proc, and disengage before she can E-reposition and shuriken back. Never sit in her Q+passive auto rhythm.","spikes":"Akali spikes at level 6 (Shadow Dance) and at her first AP item; you spike at level 6 (Highlander) and harder at your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK), flipping the duel until her 2+ item AP scaling reclaims it.","feeding":"If you fall behind, your weak early gets weaker and a fed Akali simply Shrouds your engage and one-shots you — abandon the lane, farm side waves safely with Alpha Strike, and scale to your on-hit items without dying.","carry":"If you get ahead, Highlander's kill-reset chains you through her team — Alpha Strike onto the squishiest target, dodge her R with the untargetable blink, and snowball the on-hit DPS lead across the map.","difficulty":"It's a 7/10 because Akali has every tool that beats Master Yi early — ranged poke that out-trades your weak laning phase, a vanish (Shroud) that hard-counters your only target-lock engage, and burst mobility (R) that punishes you the moment Highlander expires."},"focus":{"text":"Twilight Shroud — Akali's W vanish/zone. Alpha Strike cannot select her as a target inside the Shroud, so it eats your only gap-closer and escape; bait or wait it out before you commit.","letters":["W"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike","d":"Use Q to last-hit from max range early so you scale safely without eating her Q+passive auto trades. Concede the lane, not the gold."},{"t":"Save Q to dodge her R","d":"Alpha Strike makes you untargetable mid-blink, which dodges Akali's Shadow Dance burst and her shuriken — hold it for her commit, not for poke."},{"t":"Fight after Shroud is down","d":"Once she's spent Twilight Shroud, she can't vanish your target-lock — that post-Shroud window plus level 6 Highlander is your green light to all-in."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't trade autos early","d":"Her Q with passive mark beats your short-range Wuju autos levels 1-3; standing in her rhythm just bleeds you out before you scale."},{"t":"Don't Alpha into the Shroud","d":"Blinking onto her while Twilight Shroud is up wastes your engage AND your escape — you'll surface untargeted, slowed, and get bursted."},{"t":"Don't chase without Highlander","d":"If R is down, her E/R mobility kites your on-hit and she resets the fight; never commit to a kill when you can't sustain the chase with Highlander's slow immunity."}],"tradeGood":"After Akali burns Twilight Shroud or her E, Alpha Strike in for a Wuju Style true-damage Double Strike proc and peel off before she can reposition.","tradeBad":"Standing in her Q+passive auto rhythm levels 1-3, or Alpha Striking onto her while Shroud is up — both eat your damage and your escape for nothing.","ahead":"Press a lead by forcing the wave to your side and inviting her to trade where your jungler can punish a committed Akali. With Highlander's reset chaining, every pick you take snowballs your on-hit DPS, so dive her under tower once your first item is up — just always hold Alpha Strike for her R re-engage. Roam with your refreshed cooldowns to deny her own roam value, since out-of-lane is where she does her real damage.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Akali - Track: Twilight Shroud — Akali's W vanish/zone. Alpha Strike cannot select her as a target inside the Shroud, so it eats your only gap-closer and escape; bait or wait it out before you commit.. - Concede the early game, farm with Alpha Strike from max range, and dodge her shuriken pokes until you hit your on-hit spike (Kraken/BORK). Once itemized, force extended fights where Wuju Style true damage and Highlander resets out-DPS her burst-then-vanish pattern.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Akali edges this lane because her Twilight Shroud blanks your Alpha Strike target-lock and her R re-engage punishes you the second Highlander drops — survive to your on-hit first item and the duel flips."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing early lane by farming with Alpha Strike, then reach your on-hit first item where Wuju Style true damage and Kraken/BORK procs let you out-DPS her in any extended fight. Win the duel by dodging her R with Alpha's untargetable blink and chaining Highlander resets before her AP scaling reclaims the late game."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Akali owns levels 1-3, it's roughly even at 4-5 as Wuju/Meditate come online, you claim level 6 (Highlander) and first item (on-hit spike), then she reclaims 2+ items with AP scaling and Shroud resets."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only when her Shroud, E, or energy is down — Alpha in, proc Wuju Style true damage and Double Strike, then disengage. Back off entirely while her Q+passive rhythm is up or she has R charges and you don't."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave on your side with a slow push so you fight near your turret, lower her roam value, and set up ganks; avoid shoving it under her tower where her poke and Shroud zone you off CS."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable blink dodges Akali's Shadow Dance and shuriken, but it CANNOT target her inside Twilight Shroud — Shroud hard-counters your engage. Highlander's slow immunity beats her E slow so you can stick through her kite; Meditate out-sustains her energy-gated poke between trades."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the attack-speed ramp that powers your on-hit duel (Conqueror is the alternative into her sustained-damage profile), with Triumph and Legend: Alacrity; secondary Resolve (Second Wind + Overgrowth) to blunt Akali's AP shuriken poke in lane."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite is fine if you're confident in the post-6 all-in, but Teleport is the safer pick here — it lets you farm the losing early lane, reset on your on-hit spike, and not lose tempo when she roams."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush an on-hit core — Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first, then Wit's End for the magic resist and on-hit magic damage that directly answers her AP. Add Terminus or Mercury's Treads boots; Wit's End's MR is your main defensive layer against her burst."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Your real all-in windows are level 6 with Highlander up AND after she's spent Twilight Shroud, and again at your first on-hit item when your DPS outraces her burst. Outside those, you don't have the kill pressure."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Your early lane can't punish her roams, so ping and track her — a fed Akali on R mobility ganks bot freely. Conversely, she's very gankable for YOUR jungler before 6 since she has no escape once E is committed; set up a slow push and call your jungler to cash your weak lane in."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic error is Alpha Striking onto Akali while her Shroud is up — you waste your only engage and escape, surface untargeted and slowed, and die. The second is contesting trades levels 1-3 instead of just farming to your item spike."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're losing, stop interacting: farm side waves with Alpha Strike, take only safe CS, and scale to Kraken/BORK + Wit's End. A behind Master Yi who reaches two items is still a threat in side lanes; a dead one is not."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"When ahead, use Highlander's kill-reset to chain through her team — Alpha onto the squishiest carry, dodge her R, and dive Akali under tower at first item. Roam with refreshed cooldowns to deny her own snowball."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"TRICKY (46.43% WR) — Akali's Shroud and poke beat you out of lane, but survive to your on-hit spike and the extended-fight duel is yours until her AP scaling reclaims the very late game."}]},"akshan":{"tldr":"A range-vs-scaling standoff: Akshan kites and pokes you for thirteen levels, but if you farm safely behind Meditate to your on-hit spike, Highlander turns his squishy frame into a free reset.","winCon":"Survive the early kite by farming with Alpha Strike and topping off poke with Meditate, then hit your first on-hit item and use Highlander's slow immunity to close the gap his E swing can't recreate. Once you tag him with on-hits he has no Meditate-style sustain to answer your burst, so a single caught Akshan dies in one Alpha-Strike reset.","enemyWin":"Akshan poisons your laning with Avengerang (Q) poke through minions and refunds his trades by swinging out on E before you can stick, denying you CS and HP until his roams snowball the map. If he gets ahead and you have no slow-immunity window up, he simply out-ranges every approach and revives off his passive when you do commit.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Akshan","rating":"7/10","why":"Akshan's Avengerang (Q) out-ranges your auto and passes through the minion line, so he pokes free while you can only farm."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Akshan","rating":"6/10","why":"At 2 points in Q his poke chunks you each wave and Alpha Strike into a single ranged target just bounces you into his W/auto follow-up."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Akshan","rating":"6/10","why":"Level 3 he can chain Q poke into an E swing reposition, leaving you no all-in answer before Wuju Style and Meditate are online."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"With Wuju Style (E) true damage and Meditate (W) sustain up, you neutralize his poke and trade evenly if he steps in, but he can still swing away on E."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Highlander gives slow immunity to threaten an all-in, but Akshan's camouflage passive and E swing let him reset distance, so it's a coin-flip on whether you stick."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) lets Alpha Strike plus a Wuju'd auto string melt his squishy frame faster than he can swing out."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"At 2+ items a single Highlander-refreshed Alpha Strike kills him in one rotation and resets onto the next target; he has no sustain or armor to survive your DPS."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are Akshan's. His Avengerang (Q) is a ranged, minion-piercing poke that out-ranges your auto, so every time you walk up to last-hit you eat a Q for free. Do not Alpha Strike a lone Akshan to trade — it dumps your only escape into a target that just W-autos or swings out on E, and you come out behind on HP.","mid":"Levels 4-6 stabilize the lane. Wuju Style (E) gives true damage for short punishes and Meditate (W) lets you channel his poke back to full between waves, so his Q chip stops mattering as much. Level 6 Highlander is your first real spike — the slow immunity and move speed let you threaten an actual all-in or dodge a gank, but his E grapple swing can still reset the distance, so pick the commit when his E or Flash is down.","late":"At 2+ items the lane inverts hard. Once Kraken/BORK plus Wit's End or Terminus are online, one Alpha Strike into a Wuju'd auto string outright deletes Akshan's squishy body, and any kill or assist refreshes Highlander to chain the next pick. He has no Meditate-equivalent sustain and stacks no armor, so he cannot survive your sustained DPS the way a tank can.","wave":"Best wave: a thick wave you can freeze just outside your tower, forcing Akshan to over-extend into your jungler if he wants to deny you. Worst wave: a pushed wave that lets his Q poke you under turret while he sits at max range and farms safely. Crash timing: crash the wave right before your first on-hit item completes so you can recall, buy the spike, and return to a fresh wave already itemized.","cooldowns":"Track his E (grapple swing) — it's both his trade-engage and his escape, so when it's on cooldown after a swing or a hookshot to a ward, that's your window to all-in with Highlander up.","trading":"He pokes with Q from range and swings out on E; you cannot win a poke war. Your trade is reactive — wait for him to step in or E toward you, pop Wuju Style and Alpha Strike onto him, and burst before his E comes back up.","spikes":"Akshan spikes at levels 1-3 (raw Q range) and at his lethality first item for roam pressure; you spike at level 6 Highlander, and decisively at your first and second on-hit items.","feeding":"If you fall behind, his lethality build one-shots your squishy frame from range and your Alpha Strike won't close the gap before he E-swings away or revives off passive — farm side waves, take Wit's End/armor, and look to teamfight where his single-target poke matters less.","carry":"If you get ahead, you out-scale the entire map: ping into any fight, Alpha Strike onto the carry, and let Highlander resets turn one pick into a team wipe — Akshan's roams can't match a fed on-hit Yi cleaning teamfights.","difficulty":"It rates a true 5/10 EVEN because two opposite frustrations cancel out: he can poke and kite you all lane but can't actually kill a Meditate-healing, slow-immune Yi, and you out-scale him hard but can almost never catch a mobile ranged champ to express it before items."},"focus":{"text":"Akshan's E grapple swing is the whole matchup — it's how he engages his poke trades AND how he escapes your Alpha Strike, so all-in only when it's on cooldown.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm behind Meditate","d":"Use Alpha Strike to safely last-hit and channel Meditate (W) between waves to erase his Avengerang (Q) poke; your goal levels 1-5 is simply to reach your on-hit item even in HP."},{"t":"All-in when his E is down","d":"His grapple swing is his only escape from your closure — when he's used it to swing in or to a ward, commit Highlander plus Alpha Strike and he can't reset the distance."},{"t":"Build to your spike","d":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King, then Wit's End for the magic-damage-and-attack-speed swing; the moment that first on-hit item completes, the lane flips to yours."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't Alpha Strike to poke","d":"Blinking onto a lone Akshan to trade early just burns your only escape into a ranged target who W-autos or E-swings out, leaving you stranded and chunked."},{"t":"Don't chase without slow immunity","d":"Outside of Highlander you'll never catch him — his E swing plus camouflage passive resets the gap, and you'll walk into a turret dive or his revive."},{"t":"Don't force lane while he roams","d":"Don't tunnel on the 1v1 — Akshan's strength is leaving lane to gank; ping his roams, shove, and follow or match rather than over-extending into a poked wave."}],"tradeGood":"Wait for Akshan to step in or E toward you, then pop Wuju Style (E) for true damage and Alpha Strike onto him to burst before his swing comes back up.","tradeBad":"Never Alpha Strike a full-HP Akshan at range to start a trade — you spend your only escape onto a kiter who just swings away and pokes you down.","ahead":"Press the lead by shoving him off the wave and walking at him the moment his E swing is on cooldown, then convert every kill into a Highlander reset that chains into the next pick. Once you're itemized, group and let your Alpha-Strike DPS hunt his squishy carries in skirmishes — your snowball outpaces his roam pressure. Track his recalls and deny his lethality items by collapsing on him with your jungler whenever his E is spent.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Akshan - Track: Akshan's E grapple swing is the whole matchup — it's how he engages his poke trades AND how he escapes your Alpha Strike, so all-in only when it's on cooldown.. - Survive the early kite by farming with Alpha Strike and topping off poke with Meditate, then hit your first on-hit item and use Highlander's slow immunity to close the gap his E swing can't recreate. Once you tag him with on-hits he has no Meditate-style sustain to answer your burst, so a single caught Akshan dies in one Alpha-Strike reset.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A range-vs-scaling standoff: Akshan kites and pokes you for thirteen levels, but if you farm safely behind Meditate to your on-hit spike, Highlander turns his squishy frame into a free reset."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a poke-heavy early lane by farming with Alpha Strike and out-sustaining Avengerang chip with Meditate, then reach your on-hit item where a single Highlander-refreshed Alpha Strike deletes his squishy frame. Your win condition is the scaling clock — keep the lane even in CS and HP and you auto-win past two items."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Akshan owns levels 1-3 on raw Q range, the lane evens out 4-6 as Wuju Style and Meditate come online, and it tilts to you at first item and becomes decisively yours at 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Never start the trade — back off his Q poke, then counter-trade only when he steps in or E-swings toward you by popping Wuju Style and Alpha Strike; once his E is on cooldown and Highlander is up, you can hard-commit."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Freeze just outside your tower when you can to deny his max-range poke and bait his jungler; if you're forced to push, crash right before your on-hit item so you back, buy the spike, and return itemized to a fresh wave."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable blink dodges nothing of his (his kit is skillshot/auto), but Highlander's slow immunity is what lets you ignore his slows and close the gap his E swing tries to recreate; Meditate's damage reduction and heal is what neutralizes his Avengerang poke war."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo primary (Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand) for the on-hit attack-speed ramp, secondary Resolve with Second Wind and Overgrowth to blunt his ranged Q poke through the early lane."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ghost is standard for sticking to a kiter once you have Highlander up; take Ignite only if you're confident in early kills, but Ghost composes better with his E-swing escape."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King, then Wit's End for magic damage and attack speed (great against his squishy frame); take Terminus if you need armor/MR shred, Berserker's Greaves for boots, and consider a defensive third item only if his lethality build is one-shotting you."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You can actually all-in at level 6 with Highlander up the moment his E grapple swing is on cooldown, and freely once your first on-hit item completes — before that, any commit just gets kited."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Your jungler swings this lane hard: Akshan's poked-down, escape-on-E frame is easy to collapse on, and a single gank that catches his E down snowballs you to the item spike. Conversely, ward his roam paths because his strength is leaving to gank other lanes."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi mistake here is Alpha-Striking onto a full-HP Akshan to 'trade' early — it burns your only escape into a ranged kiter and you lose the HP race; the second is chasing him without Highlander slow immunity and eating a dive or his revive."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're behind, stop forcing the 1v1 — farm side waves, build Wit's End and an armor/MR component to survive his lethality burst, and shift your value to teamfights where his single-target poke matters far less than your reset DPS."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"When ahead, shove and walk him down whenever his E is spent, convert kills into Highlander resets, and group to let your Alpha-Strike DPS hunt his carries before his roams can swing other lanes."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A genuine 5/10 EVEN — he kites and pokes you all lane but can't kill a Meditate-and-Highlander Yi, and you hard out-scale him but can rarely catch him before items; whoever respects the matchup's clock wins."}]},"ambessa":{"tldr":"A scaling lane that's yours to lose: eat Ambessa's level 1-3 dash pressure, hit your first on-hit item, and Alpha Strike straight through her chain CC to out-DPS and reset on her.","winCon":"Survive Ambessa's early dash-and-W aggression by farming with Alpha Strike and last-hitting with Wuju autos, then take over the moment Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King is online. Use Alpha Strike's untargetability to dodge her W lockdown mid-combo, then E true damage and Highlander resets to win every extended fight and snowball.","enemyWin":"Ambessa wins by exploiting levels 1-3 — her dashes close on you, her W deals heavy damage, and her chain CC pins you while you have only Alpha Strike to escape, so she snowballs a lead before you itemize. If she gets ahead and finishes a bruiser item, she can dash-CC you the instant Alpha Strike is on cooldown and burst you before Meditate or Highlander bail you out.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"4/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Ambessa","rating":"6/10","why":"At level 1 her dashes and W out-damage your two short-ranged Wuju autos, and with only Alpha Strike for an escape you can't contest her step-up."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Ambessa","rating":"6/10","why":"Level 2 she can dash in, land her W damage and chain her CC for a full trade while your Q is purely a farm tool and Wuju Style true damage isn't unlocked yet."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Ambessa","rating":"5/10","why":"Level 3 she still edges it on raw combo damage, but once you have a point in E her Wuju-true-damage autos start punishing any over-extend she makes for a last hit."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Levels 4-5 even out as Wuju Style true damage and Meditate's damage reduction and heal let you survive her combo and trade the chunk back instead of just farming."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity let you stick to her or kite her dashes, and Alpha Strike's untargetable frames dodge her W lockdown when she commits."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"With Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King online your on-hit DPS jumps and you win any extended fight where you Alpha Strike through her chain CC and reset Highlander on the kill."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At two-plus items you out-DPS and out-sustain her bruiser kit — E true damage shreds her resists, Meditate out-heals her trade, and Highlander chains kills through the rest of the map."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Ambessa and you must respect that. Her dashes close the gap your short range can't answer, her W deals real damage, and her chain CC pins you while Alpha Strike is your only escape — so don't try to fight her, just farm. Use Alpha Strike to safely last-hit a clustered wave and pick off cannon, take your Wuju autos only when she's committed to a minion, and concede any all-in. The single rule of this phase is: do not die before your items come online.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are where you stabilize. A point in Wuju Style gives your autos bonus true damage that ignores any armor she builds, and Meditate's damage reduction plus heal lets you tank a chunk of her combo and sustain back instead of recalling. Level 6 is your first real spike: Highlander's bonus move and attack speed plus slow immunity let you stick to her or peel away from her dashes, and Alpha Strike's untargetable window can eat her W when she over-commits. Start taking short trades into her cooldowns here.","late":"Two-plus items is where you flip to dominant. Once Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King stacks with Wuju Style, your on-hit DPS out-races her bruiser damage, your E true damage ignores the armor she stacks, and Meditate out-heals her trade. The fight pattern is simple: Alpha Strike in to dodge her chain CC, E on, out-DPS her, and reset Highlander on the kill to chain into the next pick. She has no way to disengage your Highlander stick.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push that lets you shove level 6+ and Alpha Strike a fat wave for free resets while looking for an all-in. Worst wave: an over-extended push at levels 1-3 with no vision — that's exactly where her dashes plus a jungler delete you. Crash timing: crash the wave just before your first item back so you reset on the on-hit spike and return to a fresh wave with your DPS online.","cooldowns":"Track her W cooldown above all — it's her main damage and the core of her chain-CC combo. When her W and her dash are down she has no kill threat, and that's your window to step up and trade or all-in.","trading":"Early, you don't trade — you farm and let her waste cooldowns. From level 6 you trade on her cooldowns: wait for her to dash or W a minion, Alpha Strike in untargetable, E for true damage, and walk out before her combo comes back up. Post-first-item every extended trade is yours because your on-hit DPS and Meditate sustain out-grind her.","spikes":"Ambessa spikes hardest at levels 2-3 and on her first bruiser item, where her dash-W-CC combo can chunk or kill you. Your spikes are level 6 (Highlander) and your first on-hit item (Kraken / BORK) — and unlike hers, your spike only grows: at two items you out-scale her permanently.","feeding":"If you fall behind, this lane gets dangerous fast — a fed Ambessa can dash-CC you the moment Alpha Strike is on cooldown and burst you before Meditate saves you. Stop trading, farm side waves with Alpha Strike from max safety, buy an early defensive component, and play for the scaling team fight where your on-hit DPS still comes online regardless of lane gold.","carry":"Ahead, you are one of the highest-carry champions in the game. Use Highlander's reset to snowball: kill her, refresh your ult and cut your cooldowns, then group or invade with your jungler. Alpha Strike lets you dive a backline through her CC, and your reset chain turns one kill into a 1v9.","difficulty":"It's only a 4/10 because the danger is front-loaded and finite. The hard part is a weak, gankable levels 1-3 against a mobile chain-CC bruiser — survive it without dying and the matchup is heavily in your favor, since your Alpha Strike untargetability is a clean answer to her one win condition (landing CC on you) and you out-scale her."},"focus":{"text":"Ambessa's W — it's her primary burst damage and the anchor of her chain-CC combo. Bait it or save Alpha Strike's untargetable window to dodge it, and once it's down she has no kill pressure on you.","letters":["W"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm, don't fight, 1-3","d":"Last-hit with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos and concede all early aggression — your entire game plan is reaching your first on-hit item alive against her front-loaded combo."},{"t":"Alpha Strike her CC","d":"Hold Alpha Strike for her commit: blink in untargetable the instant she dashes or W's so you dodge her chain CC, then E true damage and out-DPS her."},{"t":"Buy anti-armor and on-hit early","d":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King, and let Wuju Style's true damage ignore any armor or bruiser HP she stacks — your DPS only scales harder from there."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't trade levels 1-3","d":"Her dash-W-CC combo out-damages your two short-range autos and you have no escape but Alpha Strike — eating her full combo for one trade just hands her the snowball she needs."},{"t":"Don't Alpha Strike into her CC","d":"If you blink in while her W and chain CC are up, the untargetable frames end and she locks you down — wait for those cooldowns or commit only when she's already used them."},{"t":"Don't over-extend without vision","d":"A weak early Yi pushed up with no wards is a free double kill for Ambessa plus jungler — her dashes guarantee the gank connects before Highlander even exists."}],"tradeGood":"From level 6 on, wait for her to dash or W the wave, Alpha Strike in untargetable to dodge her remaining CC, E for true damage, and walk out before her combo refreshes.","tradeBad":"A level 1-3 stand-and-auto trade where she lands her full dash-W-chain-CC combo and you have nothing but Alpha Strike to escape — that's the exact exchange that loses you the lane.","ahead":"Press a lead by using Highlander's kill resets to snowball faster than she can stabilize — every kill refreshes your ult and cuts your cooldowns, so chain from her into her tower, her jungler, or a roam. Shove the wave with Alpha Strike, then look for the all-in the instant her W or dash is on cooldown. Once you're two items up she physically can't disengage your Highlander stick or out-trade your on-hit DPS, so force the side-lane 1v1 repeatedly.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Ambessa - Track: Ambessa's W — it's her primary burst damage and the anchor of her chain-CC combo. Bait it or save Alpha Strike's untargetable window to dodge it, and once it's down she has no kill pressure on you.. - Survive Ambessa's early dash-and-W aggression by farming with Alpha Strike and last-hitting with Wuju autos, then take over the moment Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King is online. Use Alpha Strike's untargetability to dodge her W lockdown mid-combo, then E true damage and Highlander resets to win every extended fight and snowball.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A scaling lane that's yours to lose: eat Ambessa's level 1-3 dash pressure, hit your first on-hit item, and Alpha Strike straight through her chain CC to out-DPS and reset on her."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive Ambessa's front-loaded levels 1-3 by farming with Alpha Strike instead of fighting, then take over once Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King is online. Use Alpha Strike's untargetable frames to dodge her W and chain CC, then out-DPS her with Wuju true damage and chain Highlander resets through the fight."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Ambessa owns levels 1-3, it evens out at 4-5 as Wuju Style and Meditate come online, and from level 6 / first item onward it tilts hard to Master Yi and only grows at two-plus items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Don't trade at all levels 1-3 — farm and let her burn cooldowns. From level 6, trade only when her W and dash are down: Alpha Strike in, E, leave. Post-first-item, take every extended fight because your on-hit DPS and Meditate out-grind her."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave neutral or slightly toward you early so you're never pinned under tower for her dive; never hard-shove and over-extend without vision at levels 1-3. From 6+ shove with Alpha Strike and crash before your item back to reset on the spike."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable blink is the whole matchup — it dodges her W damage and chain CC if timed on her commit. Wuju Style's true damage ignores the armor and bruiser HP she builds, Meditate out-sustains her W trade, and Highlander's slow immunity ignores her slows so she can't kite you with her dashes."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo primary (on-hit stick beats Conqueror here given her resists) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, and Cut Down or Coup de Grace; secondary Resolve (Conditioning/Overgrowth) or Precision-into-Resolve for the early survivability — she's AD, so lean armor/HP shards plus an attack-speed and adaptive shard."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ghost is standard for sticking and chasing with Highlander; take Ignite only if you're confident in your level 6+ all-in and want kill pressure, but against her early dominance Ghost or even Teleport for safe scaling is the more reliable pick."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first for the on-hit DPS spike, then Wit's End or Terminus into her if she's building resists; Berserker's Greaves, and since she's AD lean toward Plated Steelcaps and a defensive component (Tabi/early Steelcaps) to survive the early lane before your DPS comes online."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You can genuinely all-in at level 6 once Highlander is up and her W/dash are on cooldown, and reliably from your first on-hit item onward — Alpha Strike in untargetable, E true damage, and out-DPS her, resetting Highlander on the kill."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Her dashes make ganks land easily, so a level 1-3 gank on a pushed-up Yi is lethal — ward and play safe. Your own jungler is huge here: a single early kill or summoner burned flips the scaling clock fully in your favor, and post-6 your Highlander lets you collapse on dives."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi error is trying to fight Ambessa at levels 1-3 or Alpha Striking into her live W and CC — both feed her the snowball. The other mistake is greeding waves with no vision and dying to her dash-plus-jungler before your items exist."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're behind, stop trading entirely — farm side waves with Alpha Strike from max safety, buy a defensive component early, and play for the scaling team fight where your on-hit DPS still comes online regardless of lane gold. Don't force a 1v1 a fed Ambessa can dash-CC and burst."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If ahead, abuse Highlander resets — kill her, refresh ult, cut cooldowns, and chain into her tower, jungler, or a roam. Shove with Alpha Strike and force repeated side-lane 1v1s she can't disengage, turning one kill into a 1v9."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED (57.14% WR) — a front-loaded, survivable early against a mobile chain-CC bruiser, then a hard Yi takeover; Alpha Strike cleanly answers her one win condition and you out-scale her permanently from two items."}]},"aurora":{"tldr":"A real coin-flip: Aurora pokes and roots me off the lane before I scale, but if I survive to my on-hit item spike I Alpha Strike her burst and run her down.","winCon":"Farm safe through her early poke with Alpha Strike and Meditate, hit your first on-hit item (Kraken or BORK), then use Alpha Strike to dodge her root/burst and out-DPS her in the extended fight, resetting Highlander off the kill.","enemyWin":"Aurora chunks you down with Q poke and her spirit/exile damage before level 6, then roots you the moment you commit and blinks away with E so you can never land a clean Alpha Strike — she wins if the lane stays a ranged poke war.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Aurora","rating":"6/10","why":"She free-pokes you with Q while your only damage is short-range autos, and you have no way to close — you can only farm with Alpha Strike."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Aurora","rating":"6/10","why":"Her spirit/exile W and Q burst out-trade your level-2 autos, and one root locks you for free poke before Wuju Style true damage is online."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Aurora","rating":"6/10","why":"She still out-ranges you and her root punishes any step-up; Alpha Strike resets your attack timer but can't be cast on her from poke range."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain finally let you survive her poke and take a short trade if you catch her without E."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Highlander gives you the move/attack speed to close the gap and Alpha Strike's untargetable frames dodge her root-into-burst — but if she blinks with E first you whiff."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken/BORK on-hit DPS plus Highlander resets mean once you stick to her, Alpha Strike eats her combo and you kill her before she re-blinks."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"At 2+ items your on-hit shred out-races her squishy AP burst — Alpha Strike dodges her root and one reset chains her death across the map."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Aurora. She has the range, the Q poke, and her spirit/exile W to chip you while you have only short autos and no gap-closer except Alpha Strike, which you can't reach her with from poke distance. Don't try to trade — last-hit with Alpha Strike when minions cluster, eat the poke, and use Meditate behind the wave to undo her chip damage.","mid":"Levels 4-6 stabilize you. Wuju Style adds true damage to short autos and Meditate's heal/damage-reduction lets you sit in lane through her poke. Level 6 Highlander is your first real spike — the move and attack speed let you actually close the gap and the slow immunity means she can't peel you with slows, only her hard root. Look for a single all-in window where her E blink is on cooldown.","late":"At 2+ on-hit items the lane flips. Your DPS out-races her squishy AP burst, Alpha Strike's untargetable window dodges her root-into-burst combo, and every kill refreshes Highlander and shaves your cooldowns so you chain-fight. She becomes a target you delete, not a laner who zones you.","wave":"Best wave: a slow-pushed wave stacked on your side so she has to walk into autos range to CS, letting Highlander + Alpha Strike all-in catch her against your minions. Worst wave: a thin wave under her tower where she free-pokes you with Q and has nothing to dodge through. Crash timing: crash the wave into her tower right as you hit your first on-hit item so you reset, buy your spike, and return before she can punish the shove.","cooldowns":"Track her E blink above all — it is her get-out-of-jail. Count it the moment she uses it to reposition or dodge; the ~window it's down is your only clean all-in. Secondarily track her root, which is what catches you after Alpha Strike.","trading":"You never win a poke trade — your trade is the all-in. Bait or wait out her E blink, hit her with Highlander move speed, Wuju-Style autos and Alpha Strike to reset your timer, and Meditate only if you need to survive her returning burst. If E is up, do not engage; she just blinks and re-pokes.","spikes":"Aurora spikes at 6 (full combo: poke into root into ult zone) and at her first AP item. You spike at 6 (Highlander mobility) and harder at your first on-hit item, overtaking her at 2 items.","feeding":"If you fall behind you become a free poke target with no escape but Alpha Strike — she roots and bursts you on every approach. Farm with Alpha Strike under tower, take Meditate sustain, and play for jungle ganks or scaling rather than forcing a lane you can't reach.","carry":"If you get ahead, your snowball is one of the steepest in the game: Highlander resets let you Alpha Strike from kill to kill, and your itemized on-hit DPS lets you split or flank, force her to use E defensively, then collapse the instant it's down.","difficulty":"It's a true 5/10 EVEN — not because the lane is easy, but because her early dominance and your late dominance cancel out. The skill test is surviving her poke phase without dying or falling so far behind that you never reach the item spike that wins it."},"focus":{"text":"Her E blink — it's both her escape from your gap-close and her dodge for Alpha Strike. Every clean all-in you get is in the window after she's spent it; track it religiously.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike","d":"Use Q to last-hit caster minions and stay topped up — it's your only safe income while she out-ranges you, and the untargetable frames dodge her poke."},{"t":"Wait out her E blink","d":"Only commit Highlander + Alpha Strike when her E is on cooldown; if it's up she just blinks your all-in and re-pokes you for free."},{"t":"Meditate behind the wave","d":"Channel W out of her Q range to undo her poke chip so you arrive at your item spike healthy instead of forced to base."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't poke-war","d":"You have short autos and she has ranged Q and spirit damage — every trade at range is a trade you lose, so never approach without a commit plan."},{"t":"Don't Alpha Strike into her root","d":"If you blink to her while her root is up she catches you the instant the untargetable frames end and bursts you — bait the root or all-in when it's down."},{"t":"Don't force lane behind","d":"If you're down CS or HP, don't keep walking into her poke trying to reach her — farm under tower and scale; the lane is yours at 2 items."}],"tradeGood":"After she's blinked with E, hit her with Highlander move speed, Wuju Style true-damage autos and an Alpha Strike reset so she can't escape or re-poke before you've chunked her.","tradeBad":"Walking up to auto her while her E blink and root are both available — she roots you, blinks back, and pokes you down for free.","ahead":"Press a lead by forcing her to hold E defensively: shove the wave, threaten the all-in, and the moment she blinks to safety you've removed her only escape, so collapse with Highlander before it's back. Use your reset snowball to roam — a kill on her mid or bot refreshes Highlander and lets you Alpha Strike straight into the next fight. Build a second on-hit item over defense since her squishy AP frame can't survive your sustained DPS once you stick.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Aurora - Track: Her E blink — it's both her escape from your gap-close and her dodge for Alpha Strike. Every clean all-in you get is in the window after she's spent it; track it religiously.. - Farm safe through her early poke with Alpha Strike and Meditate, hit your first on-hit item (Kraken or BORK), then use Alpha Strike to dodge her root/burst and out-DPS her in the extended fight, resetting Highlander off the kill.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A real coin-flip: Aurora pokes and roots me off the lane before I scale, but if I survive to my on-hit item spike I Alpha Strike her burst and run her down."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive Aurora's early poke phase with Alpha Strike farming and Meditate sustain, then reach your first on-hit item spike intact. Once itemized, use Alpha Strike's untargetable frames to dodge her root-into-burst and out-DPS her squishy AP frame, chaining Highlander resets to snowball."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Aurora owns 1-5 (poke + root, you can't reach her), even at 6 (Highlander vs her ult combo), and you take over from your first item onward, dominating at 2+."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Never trade at range — your only trade is the committed all-in. Engage only when her E blink is down; if it's up, farm and wait. Use Meditate to reset her poke chip between waves."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave on your side or slow-pushed so she must step into auto range to CS, giving you all-in setups against your minions. Crash into her tower as you hit your item spike to reset cleanly. Avoid letting the wave sit under her tower where she free-pokes."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges her root and burst if timed onto her cast, but it can't be aimed at her from poke range and is wasted if she E-blinks first. Highlander's slow immunity neuters any slow component of her kit, leaving only her hard root to catch you. Meditate's damage reduction blunts her poke but is interrupted if you're rooted mid-channel."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the on-hit attack-speed ramp that wins extended fights; Triumph and either Legend: Alacrity or Bloodline; Coup de Grace as the finisher. Secondary Resolve for Second Wind (huge vs her poke) plus Overgrowth or Bone Plating. Against her AP, value the sustain and consider an early MR component."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite if your jungler camps and you want the level-6 kill pressure; Flash plus Teleport is the safer default here, since TP lets you base off her poke, buy your item spike, and return to lane without bleeding XP."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Open Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit spike that flips the lane, then Wit's End for the MR and on-hit magic damage that directly answers her AP poke and burst. Berserker's Greaves; consider Mercury's Treads if her root chains are catching you. Terminus or Maw of Malmortius as a later anti-AP layer if she's ahead."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You can all-in only when her E blink is on cooldown, ideally at 6+ with Highlander up, and decisively once you have your first on-hit item — that's when your sustained DPS beats her burst before she can re-blink."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Your jungler is your unlock — a single gank that forces her E or lands a kill gets you to your item spike ahead. She's immobile-ish once E is down, so a tracked blink makes her very gankable. Conversely, respect enemy ganks early since Alpha Strike is your only escape and her root will hold you for the collapse."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi mistake here is trying to fight her in lane instead of farming — you walk up, eat the root and poke, fall behind, and never reach the items that actually win the matchup. The lane is won by patience, not early aggression."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Farm with Alpha Strike under tower, take Meditate sustain, give up nothing you can't dodge, and play for scaling and cross-map plays. Your power is in the item spike, not the lane bully — get there alive and the game is still winnable."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Force her to spend E defensively, collapse the instant it's down, and use Highlander resets to roam — every kill refreshes your ult and shaves cooldowns, so one lead Alpha Strikes into the next pick across the map."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A genuine EVEN (49.52%): Aurora's early poke-and-root cancels Master Yi's itemized snowball — survive to your on-hit spike and the lane is yours, lose the early phase and it's hers."}]},"camille":{"tldr":"A true coinflip: Camille bullies my weak early with E-hookshot stun trades, but once I hit Kraken/BORK I out-DPS her in the very extended fights her R tries to force.","winCon":"Survive levels 1-5 by farming with Alpha Strike and short Wuju autos, dodge her E commitment, then spike on Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King and use Alpha Strike's untargetable frames to negate her R-isolation while I out-sustain her W heal and reset Highlander off the kill.","enemyWin":"Camille wins by punishing my levels 1-5 with E-stun all-ins and W true-damage cone trades, snowballing item leads, then using R to lock me in a 1v1 and finishing before my on-hit items come online; if she's fed she also reclaims the late game as a scaling duelist.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Camille","rating":"6/10","why":"Camille's level-1 Q proc and auto reset out-trade my short-range Wuju autos before I have any escape but Alpha Strike."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Camille","rating":"6/10","why":"With E available she can hookshot-stun me into a W-cone combo and I have no Highlander to disengage."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Camille","rating":"5/10","why":"Level 3 I get Wuju Style true damage for a short burst, but her E-stun all-in still wins if she lands it."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Levels 4-5 my Wuju Style and Meditate sustain answer her W heal, so trades come down to whether she lands E."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"5/10","why":"Highlander lets me cancel her engage and dodge ganks, finally matching her tempo and chasing her off the wave."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"On Kraken/BORK my on-hit DPS plus Alpha Strike's untargetable frames blank her R-isolation in an extended fight."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Camille","rating":"6/10","why":"At 2+ items Camille's defensive E shield, true-damage scaling and R reset reclaim the duel as a hard scaler."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Camille. Her Q true-damage proc and auto-reset out-trade my short Wuju autos, and once she has E she can hookshot-stun me into a full W-cone before I own Highlander to escape. I don't fight here — I farm with Alpha Strike from max range and take CS off the back of the wave.","mid":"Levels 4-5 stabilize as Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain let me answer her W heal in short trades, and level 6 Highlander is my first real spike: the move speed and slow immunity let me cancel her E engage and dodge jungle ganks. The lane is genuinely even from here until items decide it.","late":"At first item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) my on-hit DPS jumps and Alpha Strike's untargetable frames let me dodge the burst window of her R, so I win the very extended fights she tries to force. At 2+ items Camille's E shield and true-damage scaling claw the duel back — she's the harder scaler, so I want the game decided before her third item.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push that lets me crash a big wave and recall on my item spike with Alpha Strike clearing the back line safely. Worst wave: a wave shoved under her tower early, where she can E-gapclose onto me with no minions to body-block and zone me off CS. Crash timing: crash levels 5-6 to hit base, buy your on-hit component, and return with Highlander up so she can't punish the wave reset.","cooldowns":"Track her E (Hookshot/Wall Dive) above all — it's her engage, her stun, and her gap-close; when it's down she cannot start a fight on me.","trading":"Short trades only until items: hit her with a Double-Strike-empowered Alpha Strike + Wuju auto and walk, never standing for her W-cone return; after first item I can extend any trade because my on-hit out-paces her heal.","spikes":"Camille spikes at level 2 (E) and on first item; I spike at level 6 (Highlander) and harder on Kraken/BORK, with the lane tilting back to her at her 2-3 item mark.","feeding":"If I fall behind, her E-stun-to-R isolation kills me before Meditate matters and she snowballs lane and roams; I give up plates and farm safely under tower with Alpha Strike rather than contest.","carry":"If I get ahead, Highlander resets chain me through teamfights — Alpha Strike dodges her R lock, my on-hit melts her, and the kill refreshes R to keep me untouchable as I clean up.","difficulty":"It rates a 5/10 because the verdict is EVEN: she clearly owns levels 1-5 and reclaims the very late game, but my level 6 and first-item windows are real, so the lane is decided by whether I survive her early E all-ins and reach my spike even."},"focus":{"text":"Camille's E (Hookshot / Wall Dive) — it's her stun, her engage and her gap-close all in one; the entire lane is about baiting it out and farming safely while it's on cooldown.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike","d":"Use Q from max range to last-hit the back of the wave so I take CS without stepping into her E range during levels 1-5."},{"t":"Hold Q for her R","d":"Save Alpha Strike's untargetable frames for the moment she ults to isolate me — blinking out blanks her burst window and resets my attack timer for the counter-DPS."},{"t":"Spike then extend","d":"Once Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King is online, lengthen fights — my on-hit out-paces her W heal and Highlander resets chain me through the kill."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't trade pre-6","d":"Never stand in her W-cone for a return; she out-trades my short autos with the true-damage proc before I have Highlander to disengage."},{"t":"Don't Meditate mid-stun","d":"Channeling W while her E-stun or R is on me just gets me killed — the channel doesn't break CC and I drop the move speed I need to escape."},{"t":"Don't force the late game","d":"Don't drag the game past her third item expecting to win the duel — she's the harder scaler, so close on my first-item lead instead."}],"tradeGood":"A Double-Strike Alpha Strike onto her plus a Wuju-Style true-damage auto, then walk out before her W-cone can return — and after first item, extend that into a full on-hit burst while her E is down.","tradeBad":"Standing to fight inside her W-cone after she lands E, where the stun, true damage and her heal win every time before Highlander exists.","ahead":"Press a lead by crashing the wave on my item spike and looking for plays the moment her E is down — she has no answer to my on-hit DPS without it. Use Highlander's reset to chain through skirmishes, and hold Alpha Strike to dodge her R so any all-in she throws just feeds my snowball. Roam with R's bonus move speed once I've shoved, because a fed Yi 2v1s her jungler far better than she does.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Camille - Track: Camille's E (Hookshot / Wall Dive) — it's her stun, her engage and her gap-close all in one; the entire lane is about baiting it out and farming safely while it's on cooldown.. - Survive levels 1-5 by farming with Alpha Strike and short Wuju autos, dodge her E commitment, then spike on Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King and use Alpha Strike's untargetable frames to negate her R-isolation while I out-sustain her W heal and reset Highlander off the kill.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A true coinflip: Camille bullies my weak early with E-hookshot stun trades, but once I hit Kraken/BORK I out-DPS her in the very extended fights her R tries to force."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Concede levels 1-5 by farming with Alpha Strike and refusing every trade her E sets up, then reach my first on-hit item even. From Kraken/BORK onward I out-DPS her in extended fights and Alpha Strike's untargetable frames neutralize her R-isolation, so the kill resets Highlander and I snowball before her scaling reclaims the game."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Camille owns 1-3 (E-stun trades), it evens out at 4-5 (Wuju/Meditate online), I take 6 and first item (Highlander + on-hit), then she reclaims 2+ items as the harder scaler."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Pre-6: only short Alpha-Strike-plus-auto pokes, never a stand-and-fight inside her W-cone; bait her E and trade while it's on cooldown. Post-first-item: extend every trade because on-hit beats her heal, but still respect her R cooldown for the all-in."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave slightly toward my side levels 1-5 so she can't freeze and zone me, then slow-push and crash on my item spike; never shove deep into her tower before 6 where her E gap-close has minions to dive through."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges her R burst and can blink me out of her E follow-up; Wuju Style true damage ignores any armor she builds; Meditate out-sustains her W heal but does NOT break her E-stun, so never channel it under CC."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (her short fights favor ramping on-hit AS) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand or Coup de Grace primary; secondary Resolve — Conditioning/Overgrowth, or Second Wind + Unflinching to weather her early poke. Take bonus armor shards since her core damage is AD."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite to punish her into a kill on my level-6/first-item spike; take Flash + Teleport instead if you want to play safe early and stabilize the lane through her dominant first three levels."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Open Doran's Blade plus a Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King rush for the on-hit spike, then Wit's End or Terminus for resist plus more on-hit; Berserker's Greaves; since she's pure AD, prioritize armor and consider Death's Dance — bring an early Bramble Vest or Executioner's if she rushes the lane."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"All-in only when her E is on cooldown and I have Highlander up, or right after my first item lands; the ideal window is dodging her R-engage with Alpha Strike and turning the extended fight my on-hit wins."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Pre-6 I'm extremely gankable with no escape but Q, so ward her E-gapclose paths and don't overextend; post-6 Highlander's move speed and slow immunity let me dodge ganks, and a fed Yi answers a 2v1 dive far better than she does."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi error here is fighting back during levels 1-5 — trying to trade her E-stun-plus-W-cone with short Wuju autos — and dying before the item spike that actually wins the lane."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If I'm behind, farm under tower with Alpha Strike, give up plates rather than her E-to-R kill, build a defensive item early, and scale to the on-hit spike where I can still out-DPS her in a teamfight even from a deficit."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If ahead, crash waves and hunt plays whenever her E is down, chain Highlander resets through skirmishes, and roam with R move speed — my snowball is one of the steepest in the game once the on-hit items are online."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A genuine coinflip (51% / EVEN): she owns the first five levels and the very late game, I own level 6 and first item — survive her E all-ins, hit my spike, and the snowball is mine."}]},"cassiopeia":{"tldr":"Survive Cassiopeia's poke and grounding through laning, then run her down at first item — Alpha Strike dodges her R and your on-hit DPS deletes a no-escape mage before she out-kites you late.","winCon":"Concede levels 1-3 to her poison poke, farm safely with Alpha Strike, then spike on Kraken/BORK and use Q to gap-close untargetable past her Q/W and turn every all-in into a Highlander reset chain. Kill her repeatedly before her 2+ item kiting and grounding become enough to hold you off.","enemyWin":"Cassiopeia wins by chunking you with Noxious Blast and chaining Twin Fangs every time you walk up, then landing W Miasma to ground you out of dash range and R Petrifying Gaze to face-stun you mid-Alpha-Strike commit — if she keeps poison stacks on you and never lets you itemize, she out-DPSes and kites you for the whole game.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"4/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Cassiopeia","rating":"6/10","why":"At level 1 she pokes free with Noxious Blast while you have only short-range autos and Alpha Strike to farm — you can't trade through her poison so you concede and last-hit."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Cassiopeia","rating":"6/10","why":"A second point in Q or E gives her the prime-and-Twin-Fang loop that refunds mana on poisoned targets, out-chunking your weak level-2 autos before Wuju Style is online."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Cassiopeia","rating":"5/10","why":"With Wuju Style true damage up you can answer a short Alpha-Strike-in trade, but her sustained poison still edges any extended exchange — roughly even and farm-focused."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style and Meditate let you out-sustain her chip in short trades, but mistiming a walk-up into Miasma grounding flips the trade — it comes down to dodging her W."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's move speed and slow immunity let you ignore her Miasma slow and chase through poison, and Alpha Strike's untargetable frames dodge her R face-stun on the all-in."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken/BORK on-hit DPS plus Alpha Strike resetting your attack timer lets you burst her down before her poison ramps — she has no escape once you're in range with R up."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Cassiopeia","rating":"6/10","why":"At 2+ items her no-boots move speed, Miasma grounding and Twin Fang DPS reclaim the kite — if you didn't snowball the lead, she out-scales and zones you off the fight."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Cassiopeia and you must accept it. She throws Noxious Blast on your last-hits to chip you for free while you have nothing but short autos and Alpha Strike, and once she has two points across Q and E her Twin Fang loop refunds itself on poisoned targets and out-trades your weak base damage. Do not contest — farm with Alpha Strike on the wave (it's also your only safe poke), eat the poison, and stay above half HP so a jungle gank or a missed W can't convert into a kill.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you stabilize: Wuju Style's true damage ignores any MR she builds and Meditate sustains back the poison chip between trades, so short Q-in-auto-auto-out exchanges become even. Level 6 is your real shift — Highlander gives move speed and slow immunity that beats her Miasma slow, and Alpha Strike's untargetable window lets you blink past her R Petrifying Gaze to start the all-in. Only commit with R up and only when her W or R is on cooldown.","late":"At first item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) you flip the lane: your on-hit DPS plus Alpha Strike resetting your attack timer melts a squishy no-escape mage faster than her poison can ramp, and a kill refreshes Highlander to chain to the next. But she is a hard scaler — at 2+ items her boots-free move speed, repeated Miasma grounds and Twin Fang DPS let her kite you off a fight if you didn't already snowball. Close the game on your item lead; don't let it reach her three-item kite.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push into her so you can Alpha-Strike the caster minions to refund Q and crash a wave that locks her under tower for a gank. Worst wave: a wave frozen in the middle of the lane where she free-pokes you with Noxious Blast and you can't safely walk up to last-hit. Crash timing: crash the wave just before level 6 and on your first-item recall so you reset on time and arrive with Highlander up for the all-in.","cooldowns":"Track W Miasma above all — it grounds you out of Alpha Strike/Highlander dash range and chains her poison; if it's on cooldown, that's your window to commit. Secondarily watch R Petrifying Gaze for the face-stun.","trading":"Prime trade: wait for her to throw Q or step up, Alpha Strike onto her (untargetable through her cast), E Wuju Style autos for true damage, then disengage on Highlander move speed before her Twin Fang chain ramps. Never auto-walk into her — every step without Q up just eats poke.","spikes":"Hers: level 2-3 Twin Fang loop, level 6 Petrifying Gaze, and 2+ items where her poison DPS and grounding peak. Yours: level 6 Highlander, then first on-hit item where your sustained DPS overtakes her, then any kill that resets Highlander.","feeding":"If you fall behind, her poison out-ranges your farm and she perma-zones you off the wave — you become a useless early Yi with no items. Freeze near your tower, farm Alpha Strike onto the back minions to stay safe, and call your jungler; do not try to force trades to catch up, because a single Miasma-ground into R deletes you.","carry":"If you're ahead, Master Yi is one of the highest-snowball carries in the game: a fed Yi with Highlander up Alpha-Strikes onto a target, dodges the CC, and resets R on the kill to chain across the whole team. Press your item lead into mid/bot the moment your lane wave is crashed.","difficulty":"It's only 4/10 because the lane is genuinely Yi-favoured (58% WR) — her poke is annoying but she's a squishy melee-range mage with no hard CC except a dodgeable R, and Alpha Strike answers her one lockdown tool. The skill is purely in surviving the weak early without feeding and timing the all-in around her W."},"focus":{"text":"W Miasma — it grounds you (cancels Alpha Strike and Highlander dash/escape) and refreshes her poison; you can only safely all-in when it's down. Her R Petrifying Gaze is the only thing that hard-stops an Alpha Strike commit, so respect both.","letters":["W","R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike, concede early","d":"Levels 1-3 use Q on the wave to last-hit safely and refund its cooldown off minions while staying out of her Noxious Blast range — don't try to trade until Wuju Style and Highlander are online."},{"t":"All-in when Miasma is down","d":"Her W is your green light: with R up, Alpha Strike onto her (untargetable through her cast), E for true damage, and chase through her slow on Highlander's slow immunity."},{"t":"Snowball before she scales","d":"You're on a clock — close the lane and roam on your first-item spike, because at 2+ items her kite and grounding reclaim the matchup if it goes even."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't walk up without Q ready","d":"Every step toward her without Alpha Strike available just feeds free Noxious Blast pokes and Twin Fang chains — Q is your engage AND your only escape, so never burn it just to farm when you might need to commit or flee."},{"t":"Don't Alpha Strike into her R","d":"If Petrifying Gaze is up she'll face-stun you the instant your untargetable frames end and chain-poison you to death — bait or wait out her R before committing."},{"t":"Don't duel her at 2+ items even","d":"If the lane reached two items with no lead, she out-kites and grounds you; group with your team and use your snowball elsewhere instead of forcing a losing 1v1."}],"tradeGood":"Punish her W cooldown: Alpha Strike in untargetable, E Wuju Style for true damage that ignores her MR, weave Double Strike, then peel off on Highlander move speed before her Twin Fang chain ramps.","tradeBad":"Never walk straight at her with Q on cooldown — you eat Noxious Blast plus a Miasma ground and a chained Twin Fang burst with no escape and no untargetable to answer her R.","ahead":"Press a lead by crashing the wave and immediately roaming or forcing all-ins the moment her W or R is down — a fed Yi with Highlander up resets the ult on every kill and chains them. Build into your on-hit spike fast (Kraken/BORK) so your DPS stays ahead of her poison, and deny her farm by perma-shoving so she never catches up to her scaling window. Take Drake/Herald fights where you can Alpha Strike onto her backline and reset across the team.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Cassiopeia - Track: W Miasma — it grounds you (cancels Alpha Strike and Highlander dash/escape) and refreshes her poison; you can only safely all-in when it's down. Her R Petrifying Gaze is the only thing that hard-stops an Alpha Strike commit, so respect both.. - Concede levels 1-3 to her poison poke, farm safely with Alpha Strike, then spike on Kraken/BORK and use Q to gap-close untargetable past her Q/W and turn every all-in into a Highlander reset chain. Kill her repeatedly before her 2+ item kiting and grounding become enough to hold you off.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Survive Cassiopeia's poke and grounding through laning, then run her down at first item — Alpha Strike dodges her R and your on-hit DPS deletes a no-escape mage before she out-kites you late."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Master Yi wins by surviving a weak, poke-heavy early lane and farming with Alpha Strike, then spiking on his first on-hit item and using Q's untargetable frames to dodge her R/grounding and out-DPS a squishy no-escape mage. Every kill resets Highlander, so one won all-in snowballs into a lane and then a map lead before her 2+ item kite comes online."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Cassiopeia owns levels 1-3 (free poison poke), it's even at 4-5 with Wuju Style/Meditate, then favor flips hard to Yi at level 6 and first item, before she reclaims the 2+ item late as a hard scaler."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only when her W Miasma is on cooldown and you have Q up — Alpha Strike in, E true-damage autos, leave on Highlander move speed. Back off entirely when her R is up or your Q is down; never auto-walk into her poison."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Don't freeze — you want the wave pushing so you can shove and roam on your spike, but early just safe-farm with Alpha Strike on the caster line. Slow-push into a crash before 6 and on first recall so you arrive with R up; avoid a mid-lane freeze that lets her free-poke."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike makes you untargetable, dodging her R Petrifying Gaze and avoiding her Q/W lands during the blink — it's your single best tool here. Highlander's slow immunity ignores her Miasma slow, but the Miasma GROUND still cancels your dash, so time the all-in around her W. Wuju Style's true damage ignores any MR/Seeker's she builds, and Meditate out-sustains her chip in short trades but is interrupted by her R stun."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (uncaps your attack speed for on-hit DPS) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand or Coup de Grace; secondary Resolve (Conditioning/Overgrowth) or Sorcery (Nimbus Cloak/Transcendence) for the early survivability you need vs an AP poke lane. Take Second Wind in the minor tree to sustain through her poison."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite to convert your level 6/first-item all-in into a kill and cut her Meditate-less sustain — Ignite's Grievous Wounds is mostly for her healing-less kit but the kill pressure closes the lane. Take Teleport instead only if you want to play for scaling map presence rather than solo-killing her."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit spike that out-DPSes her poison, then Wit's End for MR and on-hit magic damage that directly answers her AP — Terminus is a strong third for resist shred plus dual resists. Build Mercury's Treads for tenacity vs her R stun and Miasma slow, and add Maw/Wit's End MR if she's snowballing."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You can actually all-in at level 6 with Highlander up and her W on cooldown, and decisively at first item — Alpha Strike in untargetable, E for true damage, and chase through her slow. Avoid committing while her R Petrifying Gaze is available, since the face-stun the moment your blink ends is a death sentence."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Your weak early makes you gank-prone — she has no escape but her poison can hold you long enough for a gank to land, so ward early. Conversely, once you hit 6, a gank converts instantly because she's a squishy with no mobility; coordinate a dive on her after a wave crash and you delete her, then reset Highlander to keep moving."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players try to trade or all-in too early (levels 1-3) and feed Noxious Blast/Twin Fang chains, or they burn Alpha Strike to farm and then get caught by Miasma+R with no escape. They also Alpha Strike straight into an up R and die the instant the untargetable frames end."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're behind, stop forcing it — freeze near tower, farm the back of the wave with Alpha Strike to stay out of poison range, and ping your jungler. Build defensively (Wit's End, Merc Treads) and look to scale to your item spike or to fights elsewhere on the map rather than soloing a fed Cassiopeia who will kite and ground you."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"When you win a trade, immediately crash the wave and roam or dive her again on her cooldowns — your kills reset Highlander so chain them. Rush your on-hit item, deny her farm by perma-shoving, and take your DPS lead to Drake/Herald fights where you can Alpha Strike the backline before her scaling ever arrives."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED, 4/10 difficulty — concede the early poke, dodge her W/R with Alpha Strike and Highlander, and out-DPS a no-escape mage on your first-item spike before her 2+ item kite reclaims the late game."}]},"chogath":{"tldr":"A scaling tank with no kite is exactly the body my on-hit kit wants — survive his Rupture-and-Feast early bullying, hit my first item, and Alpha Strike through his CC to out-DPS him before he Feasts the lane back at two items.","winCon":"Farm safely through levels 1-5 with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, dodging his Rupture (Q) and never eating a Feast (R) execute, then snowball off my first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) where I shred his giant single health bar faster than he can sustain. I want this won and a kill banked before two items, because his Feast HP and true-damage R reclaim a pure scaling 1v1.","enemyWin":"Cho'Gath wins by landing Rupture (Q) to knock me up and stacking Feast on a freezing wave, then either executing me with R when I'm below the threshold or simply out-scaling into a 30+ stack bag of HP my single-target on-hit can't chew through. If he denies my early farm and reaches two items even, his percent-HP true-damage Feast ignores my Meditate and ends extended fights.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"4/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Cho'Gath","rating":"6/10","why":"Level 1 he has Rupture (Q) and longer range to poke me off a minion while my only tool is a 4-second farming Alpha Strike — I have no trade and just last-hit."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Cho'Gath","rating":"6/10","why":"At 2 he adds Feral Scream (W) silence to lock my Q out, and a Q-into-W combo chunks me hard since I still have no escape but a single-target Alpha Strike."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"With three points I can put one in Wuju Style (E) for true damage on short autos, but his Rupture range still keeps the lane his unless he misses Q."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage plus Meditate (W) sustain let me out-trade his poke in short bursts and heal through Rupture chip while his Feast stacks are still small."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Highlander (R) gives me move/attack speed and slow immunity to close his Rupture gap, and I can Alpha Strike the instant he casts Feast to dodge the execute entirely."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King on-hit shreds his one big health bar far faster than Feast pads it, and a kill resets Highlander to chain him down."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Cho'Gath","rating":"6/10","why":"Two-item Cho'Gath is the scaling tank he wants — Feast becomes a percent-HP true-damage execute that ignores my Meditate and a 6th stack of raw HP my single-target DPS can't out-pace, so the long 1v1 reclaims to him."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are Cho'Gath's — respect them. He has Rupture (Q) range and Feral Scream (W) silence while my only level-1 tool is a 4-second-cooldown Alpha Strike I should be using to farm, not to fight. Last-hit at max range, never walk into Q range for a caster minion, and use Meditate only to top off the chip from his poke. Concede all aggression here; a Q-W combo into my no-escape early frame is how I get solo-killed or set up for a gank.","mid":"Levels 4-5 I stabilize: a point in Wuju Style (E) gives my autos bonus true damage and Meditate (W) sustains me through his Rupture chip, so I can take short favourable trades when his Q is on cooldown. Level 6 is my swing — Highlander (R) hands me the speed and slow immunity to chase him down past Rupture and, crucially, the awareness that I can pop Alpha Strike (Q) the moment he begins his Feast cast to go untargetable and eat zero of the execute.","late":"At my first item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) my on-hit DPS spikes and I start winning extended fights, because his single giant health bar is exactly what on-hit shreds. But understand the clock: at two items a fully-stacked Cho'Gath reclaims the pure 1v1. His Feast is percent-current-HP TRUE damage — it ignores my Meditate heal and my armor entirely, and a 6th-stack bag of raw HP out-paces single-target on-hit. I must have a lead banked before then or I pivot to teamfighting where I reset off his squishies, not solo-dueling him.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push into him so I out-range his Q on the relto last-hit and deny his Feast stacks. Worst wave: a freeze on my side of the lane where his Rupture-Feral Scream combo can zone me off CS and set up a gank I can't Alpha Strike out of. Crash timing: crash the big wave just before my first-item back so I recall on a hard shove, deny him free Feast farm, and return on a reset on-hit spike.","cooldowns":"Track Rupture (Q) above all — it's the knockup that opens every trade and the only thing that lands his combo; when it's on cooldown (~6-7s early) the lane is mine to step up in.","trading":"Trade in short bursts only when his Q is down: walk in with Wuju Style up, get my on-hit autos off, and disengage before his Rupture comes back. Never sit in a prolonged exchange where Feral Scream silence can lock my Q escape.","spikes":"My spikes are Level 6 (Highlander) and first item (Kraken/BORK on-hit); his spikes are Level 6 (Feast becomes a kill threat), his first big HP item (Heartsteel/Bami stacking real EHP), and two-item full Feast stacks.","feeding":"If I fall behind, his Feast execute threshold rises and his HP bar balloons until my on-hit literally can't out-damage it in the time before his W silence cancels my chase. Stop forcing the 1v1 — farm side waves, take resets off his team's squishies in fights, and let my scaling claw back through items, not through duelling the tank.","carry":"If I'm ahead I shred him 1v1 with itemized on-hit while Alpha Strike dodges his Feast cast, then carry the map: a single kill resets Highlander, so I chain that into his backline and snowball before his Feast stacks make him relevant.","difficulty":"It's only 4/10 because the early bullying is real but the lane fundamentally favours me — he's an immobile, slow body with no kite, which is precisely what my on-hit hyper-carry farms up and runs down; the danger is purely his Feast execute and his scaling, both of which I can play around."},"focus":{"text":"Feast (R) — his single-target percent-HP TRUE-damage execute. It ignores my Meditate and armor, and a stacked Cho'Gath uses it to delete me below the threshold; learn to Alpha Strike the cast to go untargetable and dodge it entirely.","letters":["R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Alpha Strike his Feast cast","d":"The instant he starts the Feast (R) animation, blink with Alpha Strike (Q) to go untargetable and eat zero of the execute — this single interaction is the whole matchup at 6+."},{"t":"Farm safe, scale to first item","d":"Concede levels 1-3 and last-hit at max range with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos; my Kraken/BORK on-hit spike is what flips the lane, so survive to it intact."},{"t":"Trade only when Rupture is down","d":"Step up for short on-hit bursts with Wuju Style (E) active when his Q is on cooldown, then disengage before it and Feral Scream (W) come back to lock me down."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't fight before Wuju Style/6","d":"Levels 1-2 I have no real trade and no escape but Q — eating a Rupture-Feral Scream combo into my weak early frame is how I get solo-killed or ganked."},{"t":"Don't 1v1 a stacked Cho'Gath at two items","d":"His Feast becomes percent-HP true damage that ignores my Meditate, and his raw HP out-paces single-target on-hit — pivot to teamfighting and reset off his squishies instead."},{"t":"Don't let him freeze and Feast-farm","d":"A freeze on his side denies my CS, fattens his health bar with free Feast stacks, and sets up ganks my Alpha Strike can't save me from — shove or crash to break it."}],"tradeGood":"Step in with Wuju Style (E) true damage active while his Rupture (Q) is on cooldown, land a quick on-hit burst, and walk out before his silence comes back.","tradeBad":"A prolonged exchange where Feral Scream (W) silences my Alpha Strike escape and a Feast (R) execute lands while I'm under the threshold.","ahead":"Once I've banked a kill and my first on-hit item, I press by shoving him in and forcing short trades he can't win — my itemized DPS chews his single health bar while Alpha Strike dodges his Feast cast. Every kill resets Highlander, so I chain pressure across the map rather than parking on the immobile tank. I want the game decided before two items, because that's the window where his Feast stacks and true-damage execute reclaim the pure 1v1.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Cho'Gath - Track: Feast (R) — his single-target percent-HP TRUE-damage execute. It ignores my Meditate and armor, and a stacked Cho'Gath uses it to delete me below the threshold; learn to Alpha Strike the cast to go untargetable and dodge it entirely.. - Farm safely through levels 1-5 with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, dodging his Rupture (Q) and never eating a Feast (R) execute, then snowball off my first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) where I shred his giant single health bar faster than he can sustain. I want this won and a kill banked before two items, because his Feast HP and true-damage R reclaim a pure scaling 1v1.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A scaling tank with no kite is exactly the body my on-hit kit wants — survive his Rupture-and-Feast early bullying, hit my first item, and Alpha Strike through his CC to out-DPS him before he Feasts the lane back at two items."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a weak, gankable early lane against his Rupture-Feral Scream poke by farming with Alpha Strike and never eating a Feast execute, then snowball off my first on-hit item where I shred his single giant health bar faster than he sustains. The lane is mine if I bank a lead before two items, because a stacked Cho'Gath's true-damage Feast reclaims the pure scaling 1v1."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Cho'Gath owns 1-3 (Q range, W silence, my no-escape frame); it evens at 3-5 as Wuju Style and Meditate come online; I take 6 (Highlander) through first item (on-hit spike); he reclaims 2+ items via full Feast stacks and the true-damage execute."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only in short on-hit bursts when his Rupture (Q) is on cooldown and Wuju Style (E) is active; back off the instant it's back up. Never sit in a long exchange where Feral Scream (W) can silence my Q escape, and never commit a kill attempt while his Feast (R) is up and I'm below the execute threshold."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Slow-push or keep the wave neutral so I out-range his Q to last-hit; deny him a freeze on his side, which fattens his health bar with free Feast stacks and sets up ganks. Crash the big wave before my first-item back to recall on a shove and return on an on-hit reset."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike (Q) goes untargetable mid-blink, so casting it on his Feast (R) animation dodges the execute outright — the single most important interaction in the lane. His Feral Scream (W) silence cancels my Q if I'm caught flat-footed, and his Feast is TRUE damage that bypasses my Meditate (W) heal and any armor I build."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the extended on-hit DPS that out-paces his health bar (Conqueror is fine if I want trade healing); secondary Triumph and Legend: Alacrity, with Second Wind and Overgrowth in Resolve to survive his Rupture poke and his HP scaling."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite — Ignite's Grievous Wounds cuts his Feast/passive sustain and gives me the kill pressure to actually convert my first-item spike before he stacks out of reach; take Teleport instead only if I expect to be zoned off lane and need to stay even on farm."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Open Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for on-hit that shreds his single health bar, then Wit's End or Terminus for more on-hit plus resistances; rush Bramble Vest into the build for the Grievous Wounds that blunts his sustain, and take boots based on his team (Mercs if he's the only threat doesn't matter — Tabis aren't needed since he's the tank, so Mercury Treads vs his CC)."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"I can all-in starting at 6 with Highlander up and Alpha Strike off cooldown to dodge his Feast — best executed when his Rupture is down and my on-hit item is online. Before 6, only all-in if my jungler is here to body-block his single-target combo."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"I'm extremely gankable pre-6 with only Alpha Strike to escape, so his jungler camping a Rupture setup can end my lane — ward the river entrance and hug the wave. Post-6 Highlander's speed and slow immunity make me hard to collapse on, and my reset DPS turns a successful counter-gank into a snowball."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi error here is forcing early trades or all-inning a Cho'Gath who still has Feast up and a kill threshold on me — I get executed out of my own combo. The second is dueling a fully-stacked Cho'Gath at two-plus items instead of pivoting to teamfights where I reset off his squishies."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If I'm behind, stop forcing the 1v1 — his Feast threshold and HP bar only grow. Farm side waves with Alpha Strike, take Bramble Vest for the anti-sustain, and look for resets off his team's carries in fights rather than the tank; my scaling claws back through items, not through out-dueling him."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Ahead, I shove him in, win short trades his health bar can't refund, and chain Highlander resets off kills across the map before his Feast stacks matter. Close the game before two items — that's the window where my snowball is uncatchable and his scaling hasn't arrived."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED, 4/10 to pilot — an immobile scaling tank is exactly what my on-hit kit farms and runs down; respect his early Rupture poke and his Feast execute, win it before two items, and the lane is mine."}]},"darius":{"tldr":"A pure scaling race: Darius owns every melee all-in from level 1 to 9, but if you farm safe and hit your on-hit spike, Alpha Strike dodges his pull-into-execute and you out-DPS him into the late game.","winCon":"Concede the early lane — never stand in his Q sweet-spot or trade into Hemorrhage stacks — and just farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos until Kraken/BORK comes online. Once itemized, fight in the open where Q can blink out of his Apprehend and Wuju true damage shreds his stacked health.","enemyWin":"Darius wins by catching you with E pull → empowered Q → W slow before you have items, stacking five Hemorrhage bleeds and finishing with a Noxian Guillotine reset that no amount of Meditate sustain survives pre-spike.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Darius","rating":"8/10","why":"His Hemorrhage bleed and high base AD crush your short-range, no-item level-1 autos in any standing fight — last-hit at max range only."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Darius","rating":"8/10","why":"With both Q and W he can E-pull you onto an empowered outer-edge Q and slow you so Alpha Strike's blink can't reach safety — never path through his pull range."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Darius","rating":"7/10","why":"Three points of Hemorrhage and full bleed-stack potential mean any extended trade favors him; only fast-tap Alpha Strike a wave for free farm, then disengage."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Darius","rating":"6/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain stabilize your trades, but he still out-bullies you and can freeze the wave to deny you XP."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity let you ignore his W slow and reposition out of E range, while his Noxian Guillotine reset still threatens a real kill if you misjudge."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King flips the DPS race — Alpha Strike dodges his E pull, then on-hit and Wuju true damage out-trade his stacked health bar."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At 2+ items you out-DPS and reset Highlander through any all-in, and Alpha Strike's untargetable blink simply dodges his Guillotine timing in an open fight."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong entirely to Darius and you must accept it. His Hemorrhage passive bleeds you for free every time you walk up, his base AD beats yours, and his E pull onto an empowered Q (the outer edge of his axe does bonus physical damage) chunks you before you can do anything back. You have no escape but Alpha Strike, and if he slows you with W mid-blink you can get caught and killed. Farm at max range with autos and tap the wave with Q only when he can't punish you.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you stabilize — Wuju Style's bonus true damage and Meditate's damage reduction plus heal let you take a short trade and sustain back up. Level 6 Highlander is your first real spike: the bonus move and attack speed plus slow immunity means his W slow no longer locks you for the E-pull combo, and you can finally walk away from a freeze or dodge a gank. You are still not all-inning him here — you're surviving to your items.","late":"At 2+ on-hit items (Kraken Slayer / BORK + Wit's End or Terminus) the lane inverts. Your on-hit DPS plus Wuju true damage out-trades his health stacking, and Alpha Strike makes you untargetable through his Apprehend and his Guillotine cast. Reset Highlander off a kill and you snowball into a 1v9 duelist he can't catch.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push or frozen wave on YOUR side that he has to walk up to, so he eats jungle gank pressure to reach you. Worst wave: a wave he can freeze just outside his tower, starving you of the XP and gold you need to scale. Crash timing: shove and crash right before your item completes or your jungler arrives, then reset to buy your spike on time.","cooldowns":"Track his E Apprehend (the pull) above all — it is the trigger for his entire kill combo and is on a long cooldown; the moment it's down, his all-in is dramatically weaker and you can step up to farm.","trading":"Pre-items there is no good extended trade — only the fast Alpha-Strike-the-wave-and-leave pattern. Post-items, bait his E, dodge or eat it, then Q in, pop Wuju, and out-DPS him in a sustained fight where his bleed can't outrace your on-hit damage.","spikes":"Darius spikes at level 1, level 6 (Guillotine), and Stridebreaker. You spike at level 6 (Highlander), first on-hit item, and decisively at 2+ items where you overtake him permanently.","feeding":"If you fall behind, his Guillotine execute threshold grows with his stacks and you become a free reset for him every time you're in lane — give up the lane, farm side waves safely under tower, and scale, because your item spike still arrives and his does not improve.","carry":"If ahead, you don't need to win lane outright — once you have items, roam with Highlander's move speed to snowball other lanes, then come back and split-push where his lack of mobility means he can never catch you off Alpha Strike.","difficulty":"It rates a 5/10 EVEN because the skill ceiling is in lane discipline, not mechanics — Darius hard-stomps the first nine levels and one greedy trade ends you, but the matchup is genuinely even because your scaling is just as inevitable as his early bully if you farm patiently."},"focus":{"text":"His E Apprehend pull — it yanks you onto his empowered Q and is the trigger for the whole pull → Q → W slow → Guillotine combo; bait it or stay out of range and his kill pressure collapses.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm, don't fight, levels 1-9","d":"Last-hit with autos and tap the wave with Alpha Strike at max range. Your entire lane is surviving to items — concede every all-in he offers."},{"t":"Save Alpha Strike as your dodge","d":"Post-6, hold Q to blink out of his E pull or to go untargetable through his Guillotine cast rather than spending it on the wave when he's looking to all-in."},{"t":"Buy your on-hit spike on time","d":"Crash the wave and back the moment Kraken or BORK is affordable — that item is the exact point the lane flips, so don't delay it for a few extra creeps."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Never stand in his Q sweet-spot","d":"The outer edge of Darius's axe does bonus damage and heals him; trading inside it pre-items hands him the lane and a likely kill."},{"t":"Don't trust Meditate to save you early","d":"Channeling Meditate while five Hemorrhage stacks are ticking just keeps you still for his empowered Q and Guillotine — the bleed and execute out-damage the heal pre-spike."},{"t":"Don't all-in before your first item","d":"You lose every even-gold melee fight to him through level 9; commit only after Kraken/BORK or with a jungler, never on equal items alone."}],"tradeGood":"Post-item, bait his E, then Alpha Strike in, pop Wuju Style, and grind him down in a sustained fight where on-hit plus true damage outpaces his bleed.","tradeBad":"Walking into his E-pull range pre-6 and eating empowered Q into a W slow — that's the trade that stacks five bleeds and ends in a Guillotine reset.","ahead":"If you get a lead, lean on Highlander's bonus move speed to roam and snowball other lanes rather than dueling him repeatedly, since you don't need this lane to carry. When you do return, split-push and force him to choose between farm and chasing — his zero mobility means he can never catch you once Alpha Strike is up, and your reset-fueled DPS ends any 1v1 he commits to.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Darius - Track: His E Apprehend pull — it yanks you onto his empowered Q and is the trigger for the whole pull → Q → W slow → Guillotine combo; bait it or stay out of range and his kill pressure collapses.. - Concede the early lane — never stand in his Q sweet-spot or trade into Hemorrhage stacks — and just farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos until Kraken/BORK comes online. Once itemized, fight in the open where Q can blink out of his Apprehend and Wuju true damage shreds his stacked health.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A pure scaling race: Darius owns every melee all-in from level 1 to 9, but if you farm safe and hit your on-hit spike, Alpha Strike dodges his pull-into-execute and you out-DPS him into the late game."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a brutal level 1-9 by farming at max range with autos and Alpha Strike, never trading into Hemorrhage stacks or his empowered Q. Hit your first on-hit item, then use Q's untargetability to dodge his pull-and-execute combo and out-DPS his stacked health in extended fights."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Darius owns 1-5 hard, the lane goes even-to-Yi-favoured at 6 (Highlander vs Guillotine), tilts to you at first item, and is firmly yours at 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Pre-items: never trade beyond a single Alpha-Strike tap on the wave. Post-6 with items: only commit after baiting his E, and only when Highlander or a jungler backs the all-in."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave on your side or slow-pushing so he must walk up into gank range; deny him the freeze just outside his tower that would starve your scaling. Crash right before your item or jungler timing."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike makes you untargetable, which dodges his E Apprehend mid-pull and lets you blink through his Noxian Guillotine cast; Highlander's slow immunity nullifies his W slow so he can't set up the pull; Wuju Style's true damage ignores any armor he builds; anti-heal on his side hurts your Meditate, but post-items your on-hit damage outraces his Hemorrhage bleed."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo primary for the on-hit DPS scaling that wins extended fights, with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity and Cut Down; secondary Resolve (Conditioning/Overgrowth) or Bone Plating + Second Wind to blunt his early all-in damage. Take Cut Down because he stacks health."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite for kill threat and to cut his Meditate-style sustain — wait, his lifesteal/heal-cut — Ignite reduces his healing and secures the level-6 kill; take Teleport instead only if you want to guarantee scaling and not lose lane state on a bad back."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first for on-hit burst against his health bar, into Wit's End or Terminus for resists plus on-hit, then Plated Steelcaps to reduce his auto/Q damage; build Berserker's Greaves only if you're already ahead. Cut Down/anti-heal items help versus his sustain."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You can only truly all-in after your first on-hit item when his E is on cooldown, or at 2+ items in an open fight where Alpha Strike dodges his execute — never on equal gold pre-spike."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Darius is gank-prone because of his zero mobility, so a tracked enemy E means your jungler can dive him; conversely, you are extremely gankable pre-6 with no escape but Q, so ward his pull angle and respect early jungle pressure that lets him land the full combo."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players try to trade or all-in too early because they know they out-scale — but you lose every even-item fight through level 9, and one greedy walk-up into his E feeds him the snowball that delays your scaling past relevance."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If losing, abandon the lane: farm side waves under tower, take Teleport value, and stack on-hit items, because your spike still arrives on schedule while his only gets marginally bigger — patience converts a lost lane into a won game."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If ahead, roam with Highlander move speed to spread the lead, then split-push where his lack of mobility can't answer you, resetting Highlander off every pickup to chain fights across the map."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A genuine 49.81% EVEN — Darius wins the first nine levels and one mistake, you win every minute after your second item; whoever respects the timeline wins."}]},"drmundo":{"tldr":"A scaling drag race where Mundo's percent-HP cleavers out-poke my weak early lane, but my on-hit DPS plus Grievous Wounds out-duels his regen the moment I hit my first item — as long as I bought anti-heal.","winCon":"Survive Mundo's Infected Cleaver poke through the early levels with Alpha Strike farming, then hit my first on-hit item with Grievous Wounds and out-DPS his sustain in an extended fight before he completes his HP-stacking tank build. My Wuju Style true damage and on-hit shred punish a champion who stacks raw health, not armor.","enemyWin":"Mundo wins by spamming his percent-HP cleaver to chip me down before I'm itemized and by reaching two tank items plus Maximum Dosage, where his R heals back most of my full combo and he becomes an unkillable raid boss I can no longer solo-kill. If I never buy anti-heal, his passive regen and R simply out-sustain everything I do.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Dr. Mundo","rating":"6/10","why":"Mundo's Infected Cleaver is a thrown percent-HP skillshot that chips me from range while I have only Alpha Strike and no item spike to fight back."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Dr. Mundo","rating":"6/10","why":"A second cleaver rank carves a real chunk and his passive heals any last-hit poke I land back, so I can't grind him this early."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Dr. Mundo","rating":"5/10","why":"His cleaver poke still out-ranges my short auto range, but Wuju Style coming online lets me start punishing the windows he walks up in."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage plus Meditate sustain stabilize me into short trades, but a cleaver to the face still out-trades any commit without an item."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Highlander lets me dodge ganks and run him down, but Maximum Dosage instantly heals most of my burst, so a clean solo-kill needs his R down."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King online plus Grievous Wounds lets my on-hit DPS out-duel his regen while his tank build is still unfinished."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"My on-hit and Wuju true damage shred HP stacks faster than armor, but Warmog's plus a tank item and R uptime can claw the 2v2/sidelane back to even."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Mundo and it's all about the cleaver. Infected Cleaver is a thrown percent-HP magic skillshot, so there's nothing I can dodge or out-stat early — he chips me for free while I have only Alpha Strike to blink between minions and farm. Don't try to grind him; his passive regen heals any last-hit poke I land back, so I sidestep cleavers, farm with Q and Wuju autos, and concede the aggression. Falling to a cleaver-and-E combo at level 1-2 is how this lane goes wrong before it starts.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are where I stabilize. Wuju Style's bonus true damage and Meditate's channel sustain come online, so I can take short trades when he steps up to E-smash, then Meditate off the cleaver chip. Level 6 Highlander is my anti-gank and run-down tool, but it does NOT make me a kill threat yet — Maximum Dosage instantly heals a chunk the moment I commit, so any all-in here only works on his R cooldown with Grievous Wounds already applied. Buy anti-heal as my first completed component; without it the mid-game is unwinnable.","late":"My first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) flips the lane: my DPS now beats his regen in an extended fight, and because Wuju Style and on-hit shred raw HP rather than armor, I punish exactly what he stacks. The clock is the catch — once he finishes Warmog's plus a tank item and has R up, he soaks my full combo, heals most of it back, and turns into an unkillable side-lane raid boss. I win by snowballing the first-item-through-two-item window and ending before his HP scaling and Maximum Dosage uptime make every duel a stalemate.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push that lets me crash and shove him under tower so I freeze him off farm while he's the weak early-laner. Worst wave: a thin or frozen-on-his-side wave where his cleavers poke me for free with no minions to Alpha Strike onto. Crash timing: crash the wave right as my first on-hit item completes so I reset, buy Grievous Wounds, and return with a fresh wave to all-in on his R cooldown.","cooldowns":"Track Maximum Dosage (R) above all — every all-in I take must land while his R is on cooldown, because it instantly heals back most of my burst. Secondarily watch Infected Cleaver (Q): after he throws it for poke, that's the safe window to step up and trade.","trading":"He pokes with cleaver from range; I answer by sidestepping it and only committing when he walks into my auto range to E-smash. My ideal trade is a short Wuju Style burst after his cleaver is on cooldown, then Meditate to heal the exchange. I never trade into a cleaver-to-the-face when his R is up.","spikes":"My spikes: level 6 Highlander (anti-gank, not a kill), and especially my first on-hit item with Grievous Wounds (the lane flips here). His spikes: rank 2-3 Infected Cleaver early, level 6 Maximum Dosage, and Warmog's plus a tank item where he becomes unkillable.","feeding":"If I fall behind, his cleaver percent-HP poke scales with my max HP and his sustain snowballs — I become a free farm target who can't ever close the gap. Don't keep face-checking cleavers trying to make a play; farm safe, scale to items, and let my late-game on-hit DPS bail me out.","carry":"If I'm ahead, I'm one of the fastest snowballers in the game: Highlander resets on kills/assists let me chain-fight, my on-hit DPS deletes squishies, and Mundo can't peel me off his carries. Use the lead to take Alpha-Strike-resetting fights around objectives and end before his tank items come online.","difficulty":"It rates a 5/10 because it's a true scaling coinflip, not a beatdown: Mundo out-pokes and out-sustains my weak early lane, but I out-DPS his regen once itemized — the whole lane hinges on me surviving early, buying anti-heal, and timing all-ins on his R, which is execution I control."},"focus":{"text":"Maximum Dosage — his R instantly heals back most of my burst, so every all-in must land while it's on cooldown or my whole combo gets undone.","letters":["R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Buy anti-heal first","d":"Grievous Wounds (Executioner's Calling into Mortal Reminder, or anti-heal on-hit) is mandatory — without it his passive regen and Maximum Dosage out-sustain every trade I take."},{"t":"All-in on his R cooldown","d":"Only commit a full Alpha Strike plus Wuju Style burst when Maximum Dosage is down; with R up he instantly heals most of it back and my commit is wasted."},{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike early","d":"Concede levels 1-3, sidestep cleavers, and use Q to last-hit safely — I scale to my on-hit spike instead of grinding a sustain war I can't win yet."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't grind his health bar early","d":"His passive regen heals any chip I land before items, so dumping autos into his HP pre-item just trades my position for nothing."},{"t":"Don't face-check cleavers","d":"Infected Cleaver is a thrown percent-HP skillshot scaling with my max HP — eating them for free is how I lose lane before I'm itemized."},{"t":"Don't duel him into two tank items","d":"After Warmog's plus a tank item with R up, he soaks my full combo and heals it back; that fight is a stalemate I should never start."}],"tradeGood":"After he throws Infected Cleaver and steps in to E-smash, I burst him with Wuju Style true damage on-hits, then Meditate to heal the cleaver chip — winning the exchange on his Q cooldown.","tradeBad":"A committed all-in while Maximum Dosage is up, where he face-tanks my whole combo and instantly heals most of it back.","ahead":"Press a lead by crashing the wave the moment my first on-hit item and Grievous Wounds come online, then all-in on his R cooldown where my DPS out-races his regen. Use Highlander resets from any kill to snowball into roams and objective fights before his tank items land. The win is ending the game in that first-item-through-two-item window — every minute I wait, Warmog's and Maximum Dosage pull the lane back toward him.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Dr. Mundo - Track: Maximum Dosage — his R instantly heals back most of my burst, so every all-in must land while it's on cooldown or my whole combo gets undone.. - Survive Mundo's Infected Cleaver poke through the early levels with Alpha Strike farming, then hit my first on-hit item with Grievous Wounds and out-DPS his sustain in an extended fight before he completes his HP-stacking tank build. My Wuju Style true damage and on-hit shred punish a champion who stacks raw health, not armor.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A scaling drag race where Mundo's percent-HP cleavers out-poke my weak early lane, but my on-hit DPS plus Grievous Wounds out-duels his regen the moment I hit my first item — as long as I bought anti-heal."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"I survive Mundo's percent-HP cleaver poke through a weak early lane by farming with Alpha Strike, then flip the lane at my first on-hit item with Grievous Wounds applied. Because Wuju Style and on-hit shred raw HP instead of armor, I punish exactly what he stacks — but only if I close before his second tank item."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Mundo owns 1-3 on cleaver poke; even at 4-6 as my Wuju/Meditate and his R/Highlander cancel out; I take first item, and 2+ items is mine until Warmog's plus R uptime claw it back."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only after his Infected Cleaver is on cooldown and he steps into auto range; back off whenever Maximum Dosage is available, since it erases any burst I land."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Slow-push to crash and freeze him off farm under tower while he's the weak early-laner; avoid thin waves where his cleavers poke me with no minions to Alpha Strike onto."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable blink dodges ganks but does nothing about his cleaver (a skillshot, not lockdown); Wuju Style true damage ignores armor though he stacks HP, so anti-heal — not armor pen — is what actually beats his Maximum Dosage and passive regen."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for max on-hit uptime in extended duels (Conqueror is fine into his tankiness too), Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve with Second Wind and Overgrowth to blunt his magic-damage cleaver poke. Second Wind specifically counters his percent-HP chip."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite — Ignite's Grievous Wounds is huge against his Maximum Dosage and passive regen and turns my level 6 all-in into a real kill threat; take Teleport only if I expect to get poked out of lane and need to scale safely."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush an on-hit core — Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for percent-HP shred — and buy Grievous Wounds (Executioner's into Mortal Reminder) early, not late. Wit's End for the magic resist vs his magic-damage cleavers; boots Mercury's if his R-fueled fights or jungle CC are a problem, else Berserker's."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"My only real solo-kill windows are level 6+ with Ignite up, or at my first on-hit item — both ONLY when Maximum Dosage is on cooldown and Grievous Wounds is on him."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"I'm gankable early before Highlander, so I respect cleaver-poke-plus-jungle setups; once I have R, Alpha Strike plus Highlander's slow immunity let me dodge most ganks, and a jungler with hard CC plus my burst is the cleanest way to kill a Mundo who out-sustains a 1v1."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players grind his health bar pre-item and face-check cleavers trying to make early plays, then commit an all-in into Maximum Dosage and watch their whole combo get healed back. Skipping anti-heal is the cardinal sin."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If I'm behind, stop dueling — farm safe with Alpha Strike, scale to my on-hit items, and let my late-game DPS out-carry. Group with my team for picks rather than trying to solo a Mundo who only gets tankier."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Crash the wave at my first item, all-in on his R cooldown, and use Highlander resets to chain kills into roams and objectives — end the game before Warmog's and Maximum Dosage make every duel a stalemate."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A genuine 52% EVEN scaling race: Mundo out-pokes and out-sustains my weak early, I out-DPS his regen once itemized — buy anti-heal, time my all-ins on his R, and close before his second tank item."}]},"fiora":{"tldr":"A losing duel until you're itemized: Fiora's parry blanks your spike and her vitals shred you early, but survive to two items and Highlander resets flip the extended fight your way.","winCon":"Farm safely with Alpha Strike and concede early aggression, then power-spike on Kraken/BORK and win extended fights where you Alpha Strike to dodge her W parry timing and out-DPS her with on-hit plus Wuju true damage. Use Highlander resets to chain kills the moment a fight breaks your way.","enemyWin":"She parries your committed Alpha Strike or your E Wuju auto, stuns you out of the trade, and walks you down with Q resets while her passive vitals chunk percent-max-HP true damage through your sustain. If she gets ahead before your second item, she out-duels you forever.","diff":"TRICKY","tone":"#ff8b3d","diffRating":"7/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Fiora","rating":"7/10","why":"She out-trades you at level 1 with Q dashes and vital procs while your only tool is a weak Alpha Strike that resets nothing on a single target."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Fiora","rating":"7/10","why":"A second point in Q gives her more dash spacing and DPS; you still have no Wuju true damage and lose any auto exchange."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Fiora","rating":"6/10","why":"She can W-parry your Alpha Strike or your first Wuju auto, eat the trade, and stun you for a vital-stacked all-in."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Fiora","rating":"6/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain finally let you trade short bursts, but her vitals still out-tick your heal."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity let you stick to her and Alpha Strike out of her W stun window for your first real even fight."},{"label":"First item","side":"Skill","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken/BORK on-hit racing her Black Cleaver-into-bruiser duel — whoever lands their key cast (your Alpha-dodge vs her parry) takes it."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"With two on-hit items plus Wuju true damage you out-sustain her vitals through Meditate and reset Highlander on the kill to snowball."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are Fiora's hard. Her Q dashes let her trade and reposition while her passive vitals deal percent-max-HP true damage that ignores your bulk, and your Alpha Strike only reduces its cooldown when it hits multiple targets, so against one champion it's a weak poke with no reset. Don't contest — last-hit with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos from max range and give up the early CS war if needed.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you stabilize: Wuju Style adds true damage and Meditate gives you a sustain answer to her vitals, so you can take short auto trades and reset. Level 6 Highlander is your first genuine spike — the move and attack speed plus slow immunity let you stick to her, and you can hold Alpha Strike to blink out of her W stun window instead of eating it.","late":"At two-plus on-hit items (Kraken/BORK into Wit's End or Terminus) the lane inverts. Your on-hit DPS plus Wuju true damage out-races her single-target vital duel, Meditate out-sustains her percent-HP chip, and any kill resets Highlander to let you chain onto her team. This is the window you've been farming toward.","wave":"Best wave: a slow-pushed wave near your tower from levels 1-3 so you out-farm her without trading into vitals. Worst wave: a wave shoved to her tower early where she Q-dashes onto you and freezes you out of farm and XP. Crash timing: crash the wave just before your level 6 / first-item back so you reset with Highlander and your on-hit spike online, then return to a long wave.","cooldowns":"Track her W (Riposte) above all — it's her parry/stun on a long cooldown; once it's down your Alpha Strike commit and Wuju autos are safe. Secondarily watch her Q dash for engage/disengage spacing.","trading":"Early, you lose any trade she initiates because vitals tick true damage faster than you sustain. Post-6 you Alpha Strike in only after baiting or eating her W, burst with Wuju autos under Highlander, then Meditate or disengage before her vitals stack.","spikes":"Her spikes: levels 1-3 vital snowball and W-parry windows, plus first item (Black Cleaver/bruiser). Your spikes: level 6 Highlander, then Kraken/BORK first item, then decisively at two-plus on-hit items.","feeding":"If you die early she fast-stacks vitals and items and becomes an unkillable single-target duelist who deletes you before Highlander matters; you fall off the map because Yi behind has no waveclear or escape beyond Alpha Strike.","carry":"If you reach two items even, you 1v9 — Alpha Strike dodges enemy CC, on-hit melts her and her squishies, and Highlander resets chain you through the whole team in fights and around objectives.","difficulty":"It's a 7/10 because her parry directly counters your single committed cast, her vitals ignore your defensive stats, and you have the game's weakest early laner — you must survive a losing lane and trust your scaling rather than fight for it."},"focus":{"text":"Fiora's W Riposte — her parry that blocks and can stun your committed Alpha Strike or your first Wuju auto; bait it or wait it out before you ever commit.","letters":["W"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm, don't fight, levels 1-3","d":"Use Alpha Strike and max-range Wuju autos to last-hit and concede the early aggression — her vitals win every trade you take before you're itemized."},{"t":"Bait or count her W","d":"Never commit Alpha Strike or Wuju autos into an up Riposte; force it out, then burst in the window before it comes back."},{"t":"Spike then re-engage","d":"Hit level 6 and your first on-hit item before you look for fights — Highlander resets and Kraken/BORK DPS are what flip this lane."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't commit into Riposte","d":"If she parries your Alpha Strike or key auto she stuns you and stacks vitals for a free kill — your one escape is on cooldown when you need it most."},{"t":"Don't trade autos early","d":"Her passive vitals deal percent-max-HP true damage that ignores your stats and out-ticks Meditate before items, so straight auto duels pre-6 just feed her."},{"t":"Don't chase across vitals","d":"Don't run her down through a fresh vital proc when she Q-dashes away — you eat true damage for nothing and she resets the duel on her terms."}],"tradeGood":"Post-6: bait her W, Alpha Strike in to dodge follow-up and burst with Wuju true-damage autos under Highlander, then disengage before her vitals re-stack.","tradeBad":"A committed Alpha Strike or Wuju auto into an available Riposte — she parries, stuns you, and converts it into a vital-stacked kill while your escape is down.","ahead":"If you scrape a lead, build your second on-hit item immediately — your duel power scales harder than hers per item, so widen the gap before she catches up. Use Highlander resets to snowball: take a kill, reset cooldowns, and shove to dive or roam mid while Alpha Strike keeps you safe from collapse. Don't overstay against a fed Fiora top — convert the lead into objectives and side-lane pressure where your on-hit out-DPSes her single-target duel.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Fiora - Track: Fiora's W Riposte — her parry that blocks and can stun your committed Alpha Strike or your first Wuju auto; bait it or wait it out before you ever commit.. - Farm safely with Alpha Strike and concede early aggression, then power-spike on Kraken/BORK and win extended fights where you Alpha Strike to dodge her W parry timing and out-DPS her with on-hit plus Wuju true damage. Use Highlander resets to chain kills the moment a fight breaks your way.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A losing duel until you're itemized: Fiora's parry blanks your spike and her vitals shred you early, but survive to two items and Highlander resets flip the extended fight your way."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing early lane by farming with Alpha Strike and conceding aggression, then spike on level 6 Highlander and your first on-hit item. Win the extended fight at two-plus items where on-hit plus Wuju true damage and Meditate sustain out-race her single-target vital duel, resetting Highlander on kills to snowball."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Fiora owns 1-5 (vitals + Q spacing + W parry), you claim level 6 (Highlander), it's a coin-flip at first item, and you take over decisively at two-plus on-hit items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Pre-6: don't trade, just farm — her vitals out-tick you. Post-6: only commit when her W Riposte is down; bait it, Alpha Strike in, burst under Highlander, then leave before vitals re-stack."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Slow-push or hold near your tower early to out-farm without trading into vitals; never let her freeze you off CS and XP. Crash before your level-6/first-item back so you reset on-spike, then return to a fresh long wave."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable blink is your only escape and your dodge — hold it to blink out of her W stun window rather than commit it where she can parry it. Her vitals deal true damage that ignores your armor/HP, so Meditate sustains but doesn't negate them until you out-damage with on-hit."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo primary for stacking on-hit attack speed in extended fights (Conqueror is fine if you prefer ramp); Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand or Coup de Grace. Secondary Resolve — Second Wind and Overgrowth (or Bone Plating) to survive her early vital poke; she's AD so favor armor/HP on runes and shards."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite if you want to contest kills post-6 and apply anti-heal versus her vitals/sustain; Teleport is the safer pick to mitigate a losing early lane and stay even in farm — Ignite only if your jungler commits to your side."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first for your on-hit spike, then Wit's End (her vitals are physical but her kit is AD — Wit's End/Terminus add resist and true/on-hit) or Terminus into a second on-hit; Berserker's Greaves; add Plated Steelcaps and an armor item (she's full AD) if she's snowballing."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You can only all-in post-6 with Highlander up, her W Riposte down, and your first on-hit item online — and ideally with jungle help; before that, any all-in feeds her vitals."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're extremely gankable early with no escape but Alpha Strike, so a camping enemy jungler ends this lane — ping for vision and play safe. Post-6 Highlander's slow immunity and Alpha's untargetability make you hard to gank, and your jungler's CC sets up the kills you need since you bring none yourself."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players commit Alpha Strike or auto-trade into her early to 'contest' the lane — that feeds vitals and walks into Riposte; the mistake is fighting before items instead of farming to your spike."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If behind, abandon the duel: farm safely with Alpha Strike, take side waves you can clear, and look to teamfights where Alpha dodges CC and your on-hit melts squishies — don't try to out-1v1 a fed Fiora top."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If ahead, rush your second on-hit item and use Highlander resets to chain kills — dive or roam off a reset, take objectives, and pressure side lanes where your scaling out-duels her single-target kit."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"TRICKY (46.73%): a losing early duel you farm through, but level 6 Highlander and your two-item on-hit spike let Yi reclaim and snowball if he survives — respect her W and her vitals."}]},"galio":{"tldr":"A coinflip scaling lane: Galio bullies me early with Q poke and an unkillable W taunt, but once I get my on-hit item online I out-DPS him in any extended fight he can't kite.","winCon":"Survive the early Q poke, farm safely with Alpha Strike, and reach my first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) where my sustained DPS plus Wuju Style true damage shreds his magic-resist-stacked body faster than his W can tank it. Save Alpha Strike to go untargetable through his W taunt and answer ganks with Highlander.","enemyWin":"Galio wins by poking me down with Q and his passive-empowered autos before I scale, then landing W to taunt me out of an all-in and lock me in place while his jungler arrives. If he denies me items and zones the wave, my weak early curve never gets to spike.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Galio","rating":"6/10","why":"Galio's Q is a free poke I can't answer at level 1 — I have short range, no Wuju true damage, and only Alpha Strike to trade with."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Galio","rating":"6/10","why":"His passive empowers his next auto with magic damage on top of Q, so every short trade chunks me harder than my level-2 autos chip him."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"With E Wuju Style up I can sneak true-damage autos after an Alpha Strike, but his Q range still wins the poke war if I overstay."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Galio","rating":"5/10","why":"He gets W taunt + damage reduction, so any all-in I attempt gets me locked in place; I farm and concede the poke."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Galio","rating":"5/10","why":"Galio's level-6 R is a global engage threat that swings teamfights, while my Highlander only stabilizes my own lane survival."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken/BORK on-hit DPS plus Wuju true damage now out-races his W damage reduction in an extended fight."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"At 2+ items I Alpha Strike through his W taunt to dodge the lock, then on-hit DPS shreds his MR stacking and Highlander resets chain him down."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Galio owns levels 1-3 outright. His Q out-ranges me and his passive empowers an auto for bonus magic damage, so every time I step up for a trade I lose the exchange. I have no Wuju true damage yet and Alpha Strike is my only tool, so I use it to safely last-hit and accept that I'm farming, not fighting.","mid":"At 4-5 my short trades get real once Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain are online — I can Alpha Strike in, get a couple of E-empowered autos, and W to heal off his Q poke. But at 6 his W taunt and global R make committing to an all-in a trap; I respect the taunt and keep scaling rather than forcing.","late":"This is where the lane flips. With my first on-hit item my sustained DPS plus true damage cuts through his magic-resist stacking, and Meditate out-sustains his Q chip. At 2+ items I out-DPS him in any drawn-out fight, Alpha Strike through his W to dodge the taunt, and reset Highlander off kills to snowball the map.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push you control so you can freeze near your tower and deny his Q poke angles while you scale. Worst wave: a wave shoved into his tower early where he free-pokes you with Q under turret and sets up a gank. Crash timing: crash the big wave right before your first on-hit item completes, recall, and come back with the spike to start trading even.","cooldowns":"Track his W (Justice Punch / the taunt) above all — it's his only hard lock on me. Note when he uses it on the wave or a trade; that's your window to step up safely.","trading":"Short, item-gated trades: pre-item you only trade when Wuju Style is up and he's wasted W on the wave; post-item you commit through extended fights where your DPS compounds and his damage reduction runs out.","spikes":"Galio spikes at 6 (R global pressure) and whenever his W is up. I spike at my first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) and again hard at 2 items, where the lane verdict actually lives.","feeding":"If I fall behind, his Q poke keeps me out of XP range and his W sets up every gank. A fed Galio becomes an unkillable MR wall who taunts me out of every fight — so I farm side lanes, scale, and avoid giving the early lead that makes his W a death sentence.","carry":"If I'm ahead, I'm a 1v9 on-hit duelist: Alpha Strike dodges his taunt, true damage ignores his MR stack, and every kill refreshes Highlander to chain the next one across the map.","difficulty":"It's a true 5/10 EVEN — Galio wins clearly early but has almost zero scaling answer to an itemized on-hit Yi, so the lane is decided entirely by whether I survive to my items, which a careful Yi reliably does."},"focus":{"text":"Galio's W — the taunt with damage reduction. It's the only ability that locks me down long enough to die or eat a gank; time it and Alpha Strike through it once I have the option.","letters":["W"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike","d":"Use Q to safely last-hit and chip the wave from range while staying out of his Q poke — survive to your on-hit item, that's the whole game."},{"t":"Bait his W, then commit","d":"Wait until he's used the taunt on the wave or a bad trade, then step up; without W he can't lock you and your DPS wins the exchange."},{"t":"Stack on-hit, then dodge the taunt","d":"Once you have Kraken/BORK, Alpha Strike's untargetable window lets you blink through his W to dodge the lock entirely, then true-damage DPS shreds his MR."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't all-in before items","d":"Pre-item, walking up to fight feeds his W taunt and passive-empowered autos — you have no kill pressure and lose every committed trade."},{"t":"Don't waste Alpha Strike on poke","d":"Q is your only escape and your taunt-dodge; don't burn it just to harass — save it for his W or to bail from a gank."},{"t":"Don't fight on a wave shoved to his turret","d":"Under his tower he free-pokes with Q and his jungler collapses while W holds you in place; manage the wave back to even ground."}],"tradeGood":"Post-item: Alpha Strike in through or after his W, land E-empowered true-damage autos in an extended fight where his damage reduction expires before your DPS does, then disengage with Highlander move speed.","tradeBad":"A pre-item all-in where you walk straight into his W taunt — you get locked, eat his passive autos and Q, and hand him a lead that makes the lane miserable.","ahead":"Press a lead by recognizing the lane flips at your first item — once you're itemized, force extended fights where his W damage reduction can't out-tank your sustained DPS, and use Alpha Strike to negate the taunt. Every kill resets Highlander, so chain them: shove, dive a low Galio through his MR with true damage, then roam with the move-speed buff to snowball other lanes before his global R can stabilize the map.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Galio - Track: Galio's W — the taunt with damage reduction. It's the only ability that locks me down long enough to die or eat a gank; time it and Alpha Strike through it once I have the option.. - Survive the early Q poke, farm safely with Alpha Strike, and reach my first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) where my sustained DPS plus Wuju Style true damage shreds his magic-resist-stacked body faster than his W can tank it. Save Alpha Strike to go untargetable through his W taunt and answer ganks with Highlander.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A coinflip scaling lane: Galio bullies me early with Q poke and an unkillable W taunt, but once I get my on-hit item online I out-DPS him in any extended fight he can't kite."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Master Yi wins this lane on the scaling axis: survive Galio's dominant early Q-and-W phase by farming with Alpha Strike, then reach his first on-hit item where sustained DPS plus Wuju Style true damage out-races Galio's magic-resist stacking and W damage reduction. The whole matchup is decided by whether Yi gets to his items intact — and a disciplined Yi does."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Galio owns 1-5 (Q poke, passive autos, W taunt, R global), the lane is a coinflip around 6, and Yi takes a decisive lead from first item onward through 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Pre-item, only trade when Wuju Style is active and his W is on cooldown from the wave; otherwise farm. Post-item, commit to extended fights where your DPS compounds — never trade into an available W taunt."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave near your side or frozen early to deny his Q poke angles and stay safe from ganks; push only to crash right before your item spike completes, then recall and return with the power to trade."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable blink lets Yi go through Galio's W taunt window to dodge the lock; Wuju Style's true damage ignores Galio's stacked magic resist; Meditate out-sustains his Q poke and passive chip in a drawn-out fight."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (fastest on-hit ramp vs a tank), Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve with Conditioning + Overgrowth, or Second Wind + Overgrowth vs his Q poke. Conqueror is fine if you prefer the bruiser path, but LT scales harder into his MR wall."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to punish his low early mobility and cut his W-sustained fights, or Flash + Teleport if you'd rather guarantee you scale safely and TP back to lane after recalls — Ignite is the higher-tempo pick into an EVEN lane you snowball."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit spike that flips the lane, then layer Wit's End or Terminus for MR shred and magic resistance to answer his AP poke. Berserker's Greaves; consider Mercury's Treads vs his W taunt CC. Wit's End is especially strong here — it both fuels your DPS and tanks his magic damage."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Only all-in after your first on-hit item, and only when his W taunt is on cooldown — then commit to an extended fight or a dive where his damage reduction expires before you do, using Alpha Strike to dodge his lock."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Galio's W taunt is a perfect gank setup, so ward early and expect collapses if you over-push; conversely your Highlander move speed and reset make you the better dive target post-6 — coordinate your jungler to come when his W is down."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players force early all-ins into Galio thinking they can fight, walk into the W taunt, and feed the lead that makes his MR wall unkillable — patience to the item spike is the entire skill of this matchup."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If behind, farm side waves, dodge his Q angles, and never fight into his W — your scaling is so steep that simply reaching 2 items reclaims relevance even from a deficit; play for cross-map fights, not lane duels."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If ahead, force extended fights and dives where his W can't save him, true-damage through his MR, and chain Highlander resets into roams — close before his global R lets his team stabilize."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"EVEN (5/10) — Galio bullies the early lane but has no answer to an itemized on-hit Yi; survive to your items and the lane is yours, matching the 51.85% win rate."}]},"gangplank":{"tldr":"A patience lane: eat Gangplank's barrel poke for ten minutes, then Alpha Strike onto him at your first on-hit item and run him out of the lane before his global gold turns him into a late-game monster.","winCon":"Survive the barrel-poke phase by farming with Alpha Strike and dodging Powder Kegs, then hit your Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King spike and force extended fights where Alpha Strike's untargetable blink lets you sit on him while Wuju Style true damage shreds his squishy frame. Close the game before he gets two or three crit items, because his global R and barrel-chain DPS reclaim the map if it goes long.","enemyWin":"Gangplank keeps you out of all-in range with constant Parrrley and Powder Keg chip, denies your engage timing, and uses W (Remove Scurvy) to cleanse any slow so he can never be locked down. If he reaches Trinity-Essence-Reaver crit power and you haven't ended, his barrels delete you before Meditate can heal and his global ult lets him out-influence the map regardless of your lane.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Gangplank","rating":"6/10","why":"He drops a Powder Keg behind the wave and Parrrleys it for free poke while your only level-1 tool, Alpha Strike, can't trade through ranged chip."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Gangplank","rating":"6/10","why":"Two Parrrley points let him zone you off melee CS from outside your auto range, and you have no Wuju Style true damage yet to punish him."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"You can use Alpha Strike to dodge a primed Powder Keg's detonation, but he can still kite with Parrrley between barrels, so it's a farming standoff."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain come online, so a fast Alpha-Strike-plus-E burst trades back his Parrrley poke, but he removes your follow-up with W cleanse."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's move and attack speed lets you stick to him through a barrel chain, and he has no hard CC to peel the dive once you commit Alpha Strike."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken Slayer / BORK on-hit DPS plus Wuju true damage burns through his thin HP bar far faster than his barrels and crit autos can kill you back."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Gangplank","rating":"6/10","why":"He reclaims it as a hard scaler: Trinity-Essence Reaver crit barrels delete you in one chain and his global R lets him swing fights across the map you can't reach."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Gangplank. He sits at barrel-and-Parrrley range and chips you for every last hit while your short range and lack of true damage mean Alpha Strike trades poorly into a kiting ranged-ish laner. Don't fight here — use Alpha Strike on the caster minions to farm safely and accept losing some CS rather than walking into a primed Powder Keg.","mid":"Levels 4-6 even out. Wuju Style gives you true-damage autos and Meditate out-sustains his single-target poke, so you can answer with a quick Alpha-Strike-into-E burst when his barrels are down. Level 6 Highlander is your real shift — the move and attack speed let you actually stick to him through a barrel chain, and he has no point-and-click lockdown to stop the dive.","late":"At one on-hit item you flip the lane: Kraken Slayer / BORK plus Wuju true damage out-DPS his crit autos and barrels in any extended fight, and Alpha Strike dodges his keg detonations while you reset Highlander off kills. But Gangplank out-scales you — once he has Trinity Force, Essence Reaver and a crit item his barrel chains one-rotation you and his global R out-influences the map, so you must convert your item window into a closed game.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push where you can free-farm under tower while sidestepping barrels, then crash and roam once you have item and Highlander. Worst wave: a thin wave shoved into his side early where he pokes you off CS with Parrrley and primes kegs in the open. Crash timing: crash the wave into his tower right as you hit your first on-hit item so you can recall, buy, and return with the level/item edge before he stacks gold.","cooldowns":"Track Powder Keg (E) charges and his W, Remove Scurvy — if his barrels are on cooldown and his W slow-cleanse is down, that's your only safe all-in window because you can finally land a slow that sticks.","trading":"Don't trade in the poke phase; let him push his Parrrley resource into your wave and farm. Post-item, wait for his barrel chain to whiff or detonate, then Alpha Strike in (untargetable through the burst), E for true damage, and out-DPS — short windows where his kegs are down, not drawn-out pre-6 brawls.","spikes":"Master Yi: level 6 Highlander, then first on-hit item (Kraken / BORK) is the real flip. Gangplank: Sheen/Trinity Force and his first crit item, scaling hard into Essence Reaver and a second crit component where his barrels start one-shotting.","feeding":"If you fall behind, his barrels gain the damage to delete you through Meditate and you become global-R fodder. Stop forcing trades, farm Alpha Strike under tower, and ask your jungler for one early gank to reset the lane — a fed Gangplank is a lost game because his scaling and map pressure compound.","carry":"If ahead, you snowball faster than almost anyone: Highlander resets on kills, so a won fight in lane turns into a tower, then a roam to mid or dragon. Buy on-hit, hit two items quickly, and use Alpha Strike's untargetability to dive his backline before he reaches the crit power that lets him out-scale you.","difficulty":"It's a true 5/10 EVEN — not hard to execute, but it's a discipline check. The early poke phase punishes greedy Yi players who try to fight before items, and the lane is a race: you must win your item window and close before his global scaling takes over."},"focus":{"text":"Powder Keg (E) — his barrels are his entire poke and burst engine; a primed keg chain plus Parrrley detonation is what chunks you out of all-in range and one-shots you once he has crit items. Time your Alpha Strike to dodge the detonation and only commit when his charges are spent.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike pre-item","d":"Use Q to last-hit safely from outside barrel range instead of walking up to melee CS into a primed Powder Keg — surviving the poke phase even on CS is winning."},{"t":"Dodge kegs with Alpha Strike","d":"Save Q's untargetable blink to phase through his Powder Keg detonation and Parrrley burst, then land on him for the on-hit trade once the keg is spent."},{"t":"All-in at first item","d":"The moment Kraken Slayer / BORK comes online, force the extended fight — your on-hit plus Wuju true damage out-DPS his crit autos before he scales, and Highlander resets if you get the kill."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't brawl levels 1-3","d":"You have no true damage or escape but Q and he kites with Parrrley — forcing an early all-in just feeds him the gold to scale into a monster."},{"t":"Don't rely on a slow to catch him","d":"His W (Remove Scurvy) cleanses slows and CC, so don't commit expecting to chase — wait until W is on cooldown before you all-in."},{"t":"Don't let it go to three items","d":"Gangplank out-scales you hard; if you can't close the lane, his Trinity-Essence-crit barrels one-rotate you and his global R wins the map — never play for late."}],"tradeGood":"Once you have an on-hit item, Alpha Strike through his Powder Keg detonation (untargetable), E for Wuju true damage, and out-DPS him in a short extended fight while his barrels are on cooldown.","tradeBad":"A level 1-3 walk-up to melee CS where he Parrrley-pokes you and detonates a primed Powder Keg on your face before you ever land a hit.","ahead":"Snowball through fights, not farm: every kill resets Highlander, so a won lane trade becomes a tower dive, then a roam to mid or dragon before Gangplank's global R can answer. Buy purely for on-hit DPS and rush your two-item spike so you can dive his backline with Alpha Strike's untargetability while he's still assembling the crit items that would out-scale you. The clock is your enemy — convert the lead into objectives and end before his scaling flips the matchup back.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Gangplank - Track: Powder Keg (E) — his barrels are his entire poke and burst engine; a primed keg chain plus Parrrley detonation is what chunks you out of all-in range and one-shots you once he has crit items. Time your Alpha Strike to dodge the detonation and only commit when his charges are spent.. - Survive the barrel-poke phase by farming with Alpha Strike and dodging Powder Kegs, then hit your Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King spike and force extended fights where Alpha Strike's untargetable blink lets you sit on him while Wuju Style true damage shreds his squishy frame. Close the game before he gets two or three crit items, because his global R and barrel-chain DPS reclaim the map if it goes long.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A patience lane: eat Gangplank's barrel poke for ten minutes, then Alpha Strike onto him at your first on-hit item and run him out of the lane before his global gold turns him into a late-game monster."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive Gangplank's barrel-poke phase by farming with Alpha Strike, then hit your first on-hit item and force extended fights where Q's untargetable blink dodges his burst and Wuju Style true damage shreds his thin HP bar. You must win your item window and close the game — he out-scales you hard, so the lane is a race against his global gold."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Gangplank owns 1-3 (poke), it evens at 4-6 (Wuju, Meditate, Highlander), you take over at first on-hit item, and he reclaims the late game at 2+ crit items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Don't trade pre-item — farm and dodge. Post-item, only commit when his Powder Keg charges and W cleanse are down, then Alpha Strike in through the burst, E, and out-DPS in a short window."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Farm safely under tower or on a slow push while sidestepping barrels; crash the wave into his tower right as you hit your first on-hit item, recall, and return with the level/item edge before he banks more gold."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike (Q) goes untargetable to phase through his Powder Keg detonation and Parrrley burst. His W (Remove Scurvy) cleanses your slows, so you can't kite-chase him — wait for it to be down. Meditate (W) out-sustains his single-target Parrrley poke once you have it. Highlander (R) gives the move/attack speed to stick through a barrel chain, and he has no hard CC to peel the dive."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (you want sustained on-hit attack speed for the extended fights, not Conqueror burst here) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve with Second Wind and Overgrowth to blunt his constant Parrrley poke through the early lane. Health and attack-speed shards."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite — Ignite's Grievous Wounds cuts his passive heal and your kill pressure spikes hard at level 6 and first item, where you want to convert a won trade into a kill. Take Teleport only if you're inexperienced and need to mitigate losing the poke phase."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for your on-hit spike, then Wit's End (the magic-resist node matters less here since he's AD — prefer Terminus for armor shred and resistances against his crit autos). Berserker's Greaves. Go Plated Steelcaps into his crit-auto and barrel AD damage; build Death's Dance later to survive his barrel burst windows."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Level 6 with Highlander up and his kegs spent, and decisively at first on-hit item when his W (Remove Scurvy) and Powder Keg charges are on cooldown so your trade can't be cleansed or pre-empted by a detonation."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're gankable early before items — ward up and play safe until 6. Post-6 Highlander's slow immunity and speed make you a strong follow-up to ganks; a single early gank that resets the lane is huge because it denies Gangplank the gold he needs to out-scale you. Beware his global R answering your dives elsewhere on the map."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Trying to fight before the on-hit item spike — Yi players see EVEN and force level-1-to-5 all-ins, eat barrel poke, and feed him the gold to become an unkillable late-game scaler. The lane is patience then explosion, not constant aggression."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Farm with Alpha Strike under tower, take Grievous Wounds and Second Wind to survive poke, and don't force anything — wait for your item spike to claw back relevance and ask your jungler to reset the lane. A fed Gangplank snowballs the map, so deny him kills above all."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Use Highlander's kill-reset to chain a won trade into a tower dive then a roam; rush two on-hit items and dive his backline with Q's untargetability before he reaches crit-item scaling. Turn the lead into objectives and end fast."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A true 5/10 EVEN and a race — lose the poke phase gracefully, win your first-item window hard, and close before Gangplank's global crit scaling reclaims the game."}]},"gnar":{"tldr":"Gnar pokes and kites you in mini form early, but once you hit Highlander and your first on-hit item you Alpha Strike onto him and delete the squishiest \"kiter\" in the top lane.","winCon":"Survive Gnar's mini-form boomerang poke to level 6, then use Alpha Strike to close the gap and dodge his Rage-bar CC while Wuju Style true damage shreds a champion who builds almost no armor. The moment Kraken/BotRK comes online, force every fight while he's in mini form and burst him before he can transform.","enemyWin":"Gnar wins by chunking you with Boomerang Throw and hop-resets in mini form, never letting you touch him before level 6, and timing his mega-form GNAR! AOE stun on your all-in so his jungler collapses while you're locked down post-Alpha Strike.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"4/10","carryRating":"9/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Gnar","rating":"6/10","why":"Mini Gnar's Boomerang Throw out-ranges you and Hyper passive auto-chunks you with no way to retaliate at melee range."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Gnar","rating":"5/10","why":"He can hop with E onto the wall/minions to space your autos while Boomerang pokes you off the wave; you have only Q to farm safely."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Gnar","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage gives short trades back, but Gnar's range still lets him win the poke war before you scale."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Meditate sustains his Boomerang poke and your Alpha Strike resets dodge his hop, but he can still kite with E hops if you mistime."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity let you stick to mini Gnar through his hops and run him down in extended trades."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken/BotRK on-hit plus Wuju true damage two-shots a Gnar who builds zero armor; Alpha Strike untargetability dodges his GNAR! stun."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At 2+ items you Alpha Strike on, ignore his Rage CC through the reset, and Highlander chains the kill into the next fight before he transforms."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Gnar: Boomerang Throw out-ranges your autos and his Hyper passive (every third attack) chunks you for free while you can only farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos. Do not walk up to trade — you have no range and no gap-closer worth burning yet. Soak XP, last-hit with Q, and concede the poke; your job is to reach level 6 at even-ish HP, not to win a war you can't win.","mid":"Levels 4-5 stabilize as Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain let you punish any Gnar who walks up to last-hit, healing back his Boomerang chip. Level 6 is your pivot: Highlander's bonus move speed, attack speed and slow immunity finally let you stick to mini Gnar through his E hops — Alpha Strike in, Wuju true-damage autos, and he can't kite a slow-immune Yi.","late":"At first item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) plus Wuju true damage, you out-DPS a Gnar who itemizes for damage and almost no armor. At 2+ items it's a stomp: Alpha Strike untargetability dodges his GNAR! AOE stun, you out-trade through his Rage CC, and Highlander resets chain you straight into the next pickoff.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push that lets you shove Gnar under tower so he can't safely poke with Boomerang, then dive on your item spike. Worst wave: a thin wave in the open mid-lane where mini Gnar free-pokes you with Boomerang and hops away. Crash timing: crash the wave just before your level-6/first-item spike so you have priority to Alpha Strike all-in or back off if his Rage bar is full.","cooldowns":"Track his Rage bar above all — mega transform is the real threat. Also count Boomerang Throw (W in mini = his slow/poke engine) and his E hop, which is his only repositioning to escape your Highlander stick.","trading":"Pre-6: never trade at range, only step on him if he over-extends to CS and you can land Wuju autos then Meditate the return poke. Post-6: Alpha Strike in on Highlander, true-damage burst, and disengage with bonus move speed before mega Gnar comes up.","spikes":"Gnar spikes at level 1-3 (range advantage) and any moment his Rage bar fills for the GNAR! stun. You spike at level 6 (Highlander), and decisively at first on-hit item — that's when the lane flips and stays flipped.","feeding":"If you fall behind, mini Gnar's poke compounds and a full Rage bar plus jungler equals a free kill; you become a farming bot who can't all-in. Play for cross-map Alpha Strike farming and scale — you out-item him eventually since his teamfight falls off and yours doesn't.","carry":"Ahead, you're one of the highest-snowball champs in the game here: Alpha Strike dodges his only CC, Wuju true damage ignores his lack of armor, and Highlander resets turn one kill into a 1v9. Roam with Highlander move speed and take over the map.","difficulty":"It's only 4/10 because Gnar can't actually kill you if you respect levels 1-3 — his poke is annoying, not lethal, and you out-scale him hard. The whole difficulty is patience: not dying to early Boomerang chip and not eating a full-Rage GNAR! stun on a bad all-in."},"focus":{"text":"Gnar's Rage bar into mega-form GNAR! — the AOE knockback/stun is the only thing that catches you after Alpha Strike and lets his jungler collapse. Never all-in while his bar is full; bait the transform, then commit.","letters":["R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Concede levels 1-3","d":"Last-hit with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, soak XP, and accept the Boomerang poke. Reaching level 6 healthy is the whole early game — don't trade into his range."},{"t":"All-in on your item spike","d":"The moment Kraken/BotRK finishes, Alpha Strike onto mini Gnar and burst him with Wuju true damage before he can hop or fill his Rage bar to transform."},{"t":"Dodge GNAR! with Alpha Strike","d":"Time your Q for when mega Gnar throws his AOE stun — you become untargetable mid-blink, eat nothing, and still apply on-hits on the way out."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't all-in into full Rage","d":"If his Rage bar is near full, a transform GNAR! stun catches you after Q and feeds the gank. Bait the transform or wait it out first."},{"t":"Don't waste Q to farm if a fight is coming","d":"Alpha Strike is your only gap-closer and dodge tool; if you blow it on a caster minion, Gnar pokes you out and you have no engage or escape."},{"t":"Don't trade at range pre-6","d":"You have zero range and his Boomerang plus Hyper autos win every poke exchange before level 6 — stepping up just hands him free chip."}],"tradeGood":"Post-6/first item: Alpha Strike onto mini Gnar, dump Wuju Style true-damage autos with Highlander attack speed, and disengage before mega comes up — he can't out-trade true damage with no armor.","tradeBad":"Walking up to auto a mini Gnar at range pre-6, or committing Alpha Strike into a full Rage bar so the GNAR! stun catches you and his jungler finishes you off.","ahead":"Once you've banked a lead, Alpha Strike onto Gnar every time his Rage bar is empty and run him down with Highlander before he can hop to safety — he has no sustain and no armor to survive your true damage. Use the kill resets and bonus move speed to roam mid or to his jungler, snowballing other lanes since Gnar's lane pressure evaporates the moment you're itemized. Force him to either give up CS under tower or die to your dive.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Gnar - Track: Gnar's Rage bar into mega-form GNAR! — the AOE knockback/stun is the only thing that catches you after Alpha Strike and lets his jungler collapse. Never all-in while his bar is full; bait the transform, then commit.. - Survive Gnar's mini-form boomerang poke to level 6, then use Alpha Strike to close the gap and dodge his Rage-bar CC while Wuju Style true damage shreds a champion who builds almost no armor. The moment Kraken/BotRK comes online, force every fight while he's in mini form and burst him before he can transform.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Gnar pokes and kites you in mini form early, but once you hit Highlander and your first on-hit item you Alpha Strike onto him and delete the squishiest \"kiter\" in the top lane."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive Gnar's mini-form Boomerang poke to level 6 by farming with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, then flip the lane on your first on-hit item by closing the gap with Q and shredding a no-armor target with true damage. Use Alpha Strike's untargetability to dodge his GNAR! stun and Highlander resets to chain kills into a map takeover."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Gnar owns 1-3 (range + Hyper poke), it evens out 4-5 (Wuju + Meditate), and you take over hard from level 6 (Highlander stick) through first item and beyond (true-damage burst + Alpha Strike CC dodge)."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Pre-6: only step on him if he overextends to CS; otherwise farm and Meditate the poke. Post-6: trade exclusively when his Rage bar is NOT full — Alpha Strike in, Wuju autos, disengage before mega transform."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave on your side or shove him under tower so Boomerang can't free-poke you; freeze if behind to deny his range advantage, slow-push into your item spike to set up a dive."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike untargetability dodges mega Gnar's GNAR! AOE stun and his Boomerang return; Wuju Style true damage ignores his (minimal) armor entirely; Highlander slow immunity nullifies mini Gnar's Boomerang/E slows so he can't kite you; Meditate out-sustains his early Boomerang chip."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (you need the attack-speed cap broken to out-DPS through his hops) — Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve with Conditioning + Overgrowth, or Precision/Sorcery with Coup de Grace and Manaflow/Transcendence isn't needed — take Resolve to survive the poke lane. Standard AD page; no AP adjustment needed since Gnar is AD."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to convert your item-spike all-ins into kills and shut off any Gnar lifesteal/cleanse value; take Teleport instead only if you expect to get poked out of lane repeatedly and want to reset and scale safely."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first (on-hit spike that flips the lane), then Wit's End or Terminus for more on-hit/sustain; Berserker's Greaves. Gnar is AD, so a Wit's End / situational armor item like a defensive third is overkill — prioritize damage and consider one anti-poke/sustain item if his early chip is heavy."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Level 6 with Highlander up and his Rage bar empty; the moment your first on-hit item completes; and any time mega Gnar has just reverted to mini form (his CC is on the longest internal cooldown) — Alpha Strike in then."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"This lane is gank-prone for you pre-6 since you have no escape but Q — ward and don't overstep into a full Rage bar plus jungler. Post-6 Highlander makes you nearly un-gankable and lets you dive Gnar with your own jungler; a full Rage bar is the only thing that turns your dive into his kill."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Trying to 'win' levels 1-3 by trading into Gnar's range and getting poked to half HP, then having no all-in pressure; and committing Alpha Strike into a full Rage bar so the GNAR! stun lands and the gank kills you. Patience pre-6 and Rage-bar tracking are everything."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Farm with Alpha Strike from max range, take every safe cross-map CS, and scale — your 2-item power dwarfs his, and his teamfight (one transform window) falls off while yours (resets) only grows. Don't force the lane; let items reset the matchup."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Use Highlander move speed to roam after kills, Alpha Strike onto Gnar whenever his Rage is empty, and convert resets into a 1v9 — once you're 2 items up he literally cannot itemize enough armor to survive your true damage."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED 4/10 difficulty, 9/10 carry — a patient early laner who out-scales and out-DPSes a squishy kiter; respect levels 1-3 and the Rage bar, then take over the game."}]},"gragas":{"tldr":"A scaling lane I lose at level 1 and own by my first item — survive Gragas's body-slam-and-cask burst, then out-DPS his even-AP-brawl kit once Kraken/BORK come online.","winCon":"Concede the early levels, farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos through his Barrel Roll poke, and use Highlander at 6 to negate gank pressure; once I hit my first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) I out-DPS his bruiser stats in any extended fight and reset Highlander off the kill. The whole lane is a race to my item spike before he can collect enough early leads to deny it.","enemyWin":"Gragas wins by bullying levels 1-5 — Barrel Roll poke plus a Body Slam (E) into his Drunken Rage empowered auto chunks me before I scale, and his second-cast E stun catches me right after my Alpha Strike to combo me out. If he banks an early lead or his jungler punishes my weak early, his W damage reduction and Q sustain let him out-brawl me before I ever reach the items that flip the lane.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"4/10","carryRating":"9/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Gragas","rating":"6/10","why":"I have only Alpha Strike and short range with no Wuju true damage or sustain yet, while his Barrel Roll out-pokes me from range and a level-1 Body Slam empowered-auto chunk wins any walk-up."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Gragas","rating":"6/10","why":"At 2 his Q+E lets him Body Slam in, drink Drunken Rage for the empowered max-HP auto, and detonate the cask before my single Alpha Strike can out-trade it."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Gragas","rating":"5/10","why":"He still out-ranges and out-trades me with Barrel Roll poke, but once I have Wuju Style my E true-damage autos start punishing him if he steps into Body Slam range to commit."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Meditate sustain and Wuju Style true damage stabilize my short trades against his Q poke, but his E-into-auto burst still wins any committed all-in he opens."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity let me ignore his Barrel Roll slow and dodge ganks, and Alpha Strike's untargetable frames can blink his Body Slam stun or his Explosive Cask knockback."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King flips my on-hit DPS so I out-damage his even-AP brawl in an extended fight, and Highlander resets to chain the kill."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At two items my on-hit shred plus Wuju true damage out-DPS his W damage reduction and Q sustain, and Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges his cask-into-E lockdown while I reset through the fight."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are Gragas's and I don't fight them. I have one ability (Alpha Strike), short range, no Wuju true damage and no Meditate sustain, so his Barrel Roll out-pokes me and a Body Slam into a Drunken Rage empowered auto chunks me for free. I farm with Alpha Strike on the wave and Wuju autos on last-hits, soak the Q poke, and refuse every walk-up trade — eating his poke is cheap, eating his E combo is how I die. I never use Alpha Strike to engage here, only to farm or to blink out if he commits.","mid":"At 4-5 I stabilize: Wuju Style's true damage ignores his armor for real short trades and Meditate channels back a chunk of his Barrel Roll poke between exchanges. Level 6 is my first real spike — Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity mean his Q slow can't kite me and I can dodge jungle ganks, and Alpha Strike's untargetable window can blink his Body Slam stun. I'm still not all-inning a healthy Gragas; I'm answering aggression and farming to my item.","late":"At first item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) the lane flips and at two items I own it. My on-hit DPS shreds through his W damage reduction and out-sustains his Q heal, Wuju true damage punishes whatever armor he builds, and Alpha Strike's untargetability lets me dodge his cask-into-E lockdown mid-fight. Highlander resets on the kill so I chain from him onto his team. He stays an even-AP brawler with displacement, but he can no longer out-DPS me in an extended fight.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push into him from level 6+ so I have a big wave to all-in into once my item is online and his E is down. Worst wave: a shoved-in wave levels 1-3 that lets him Body Slam onto me with the cannon for the empowered-auto combo. Crash timing: crash hard right before my first item completes so I can recall, buy the on-hit spike, and return to a fresh wave with my power online.","cooldowns":"Track Body Slam (E) above all — it's both his engage and his only gap-closer, and the second cast is the stun that catches me after Alpha Strike. When his E is down he has no reliable way to lock me, so that's my window. Also note Explosive Cask (R), his displacement that can interrupt my reset.","trading":"Early I take no trades — I soak Q poke and farm. From level 6 I trade only when his Body Slam is on cooldown: Alpha Strike in, stack on-hits with Wuju Style up, and disengage before his cask comes back. Once I have my item I look for the extended fight, because the longer it goes the more my on-hit DPS and Highlander resets out-value his burst-and-sustain pattern.","spikes":"Gragas spikes early — level 2 (Q+E body-slam combo) and his first AP item make him the bully. My spikes are level 6 (Highlander) and especially first item (Kraken/BORK), with two items being the point I become dominant. The lane is a race between his early-item brawl power and my on-hit scaling.","feeding":"If I fall behind, his W damage reduction and Q sustain let him out-brawl me indefinitely and his E catches my Alpha Strike, so I stop fighting entirely. I farm side lanes safely, use Alpha Strike only to escape, rush my on-hit item, and let my scaling claw the game back — Yi's curve recovers from a deficit better than almost anyone if I just stay alive and stack items.","carry":"Ahead, I'm a 1v9 threat: I shove, take Wuju-empowered objectives fast, and look for any extended fight where Alpha Strike dodges his cask and E while I out-DPS his whole team. Every kill refreshes Highlander and cuts my cooldowns, so one pick snowballs into a chain reset across the map.","difficulty":"Only 4/10 because the verdict is FAVOURED and my scaling is overwhelming — but it's not free. The early lane is genuinely Gragas's, his E is a point-and-click-style stun that punishes a sloppy Alpha Strike, and one early death can deny my item timing. The skill is patience: surviving a losing early without throwing, not the late game where I auto-win."},"focus":{"text":"Body Slam (E) — it's Gragas's engage AND the second-cast stun that catches me right after Alpha Strike's untargetable frames end. Bait it or wait it out; when his E is down he can't lock me, and that's my entire trading and all-in window.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm the losing early","d":"Use Alpha Strike to clear the wave and Wuju autos to last-hit while soaking his Barrel Roll poke — eating Q chip is cheap, and I just need to reach my first on-hit item healthy."},{"t":"Fight on his E cooldown","d":"Only commit a trade or all-in when his Body Slam is down, because that's his only stun and the only tool that catches me after Alpha Strike's untargetable window."},{"t":"Blink the lockdown with Q","d":"Time Alpha Strike to go untargetable through his Body Slam stun or Explosive Cask knockback, then re-engage and let my on-hit DPS and Highlander resets win the extended fight."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't all-in before your item","d":"Pre-Kraken/BORK I lose the brawl to his W damage reduction and Q sustain — engaging a healthy Gragas levels 1-5 just feeds him the lead that denies my scaling."},{"t":"Don't waste Q as your engage early","d":"Alpha Strike is my only escape; if I blow it to chase a chunk, his Body Slam stun catches me on the way out and his combo deletes me."},{"t":"Don't fight on a shoved-in wave","d":"A wave crashing into me lets him Body Slam in with minion and cannon damage for the empowered-auto combo — keep the wave neutral or pushing toward him before level 6."}],"tradeGood":"Post-item, with his Body Slam on cooldown: Alpha Strike in with Wuju Style active, stack on-hits in an extended fight while Highlander out-paces his Q slow, and reset onto him as he tries to cask away.","tradeBad":"A level 1-3 walk-up into his minion line, where he Body Slams onto me, drinks Drunken Rage for the empowered max-HP auto, and detonates Barrel Roll before my single Alpha Strike can answer.","ahead":"With a lead I press by shoving the wave and converting it into objective and map pressure — my Wuju autos melt towers and dragons. I look for any extended fight where Alpha Strike dodges his cask-into-E and my on-hit DPS out-trades him, knowing every kill refreshes Highlander and slashes my cooldowns to chain onto the next target. I don't dive a healthy Gragas under tower for a coin-flip; I let my item lead do the work and only commit when his Body Slam is down.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Gragas - Track: Body Slam (E) — it's Gragas's engage AND the second-cast stun that catches me right after Alpha Strike's untargetable frames end. Bait it or wait it out; when his E is down he can't lock me, and that's my entire trading and all-in window.. - Concede the early levels, farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos through his Barrel Roll poke, and use Highlander at 6 to negate gank pressure; once I hit my first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) I out-DPS his bruiser stats in any extended fight and reset Highlander off the kill. The whole lane is a race to my item spike before he can collect enough early leads to deny it.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A scaling lane I lose at level 1 and own by my first item — survive Gragas's body-slam-and-cask burst, then out-DPS his even-AP-brawl kit once Kraken/BORK come online."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"I survive a weak early against his poke and body-slam burst, farm to my first on-hit item, and from there out-DPS his even-AP brawl in any extended fight. Highlander resets on kills to chain through him and his team, so one won fight snowballs the whole game."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Gragas owns 1-3 (poke + E combo), it's even at 4-5 (Wuju + Meditate stabilize me), and it tips to me at 6 (Highlander) and decisively at first item and beyond."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Take no trades levels 1-5; soak Q poke and farm. From 6, trade only when his Body Slam is on cooldown. Post-item, seek the extended fight — the longer it runs, the more my on-hit DPS and resets out-value his burst-and-sustain."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave neutral or slow-pushing toward him early so he can't body-slam me on a crashing wave with cannon damage. Crash right before my item completes to recall and return with my spike to a fresh wave."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable frames can dodge his Body Slam stun and Explosive Cask knockback if timed on the cast. Wuju Style's true damage ignores any armor he builds, and Highlander's slow immunity hard-counters his Barrel Roll slow and lets me stick to him. Meditate out-sustains his Q poke between trades but gets out-damaged if he all-ins through it."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the attack-speed ramp and extended-fight DPS that wins this on-hit lane; Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand secondary. Vs AP Gragas take Conditioning or Second Wind in Resolve, and Magical Footwear / Cosmic Insight from Inspiration. Conqueror is the safer pick if I expect to get poked out early."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite to convert my item-spike kill pressure and cut his Q/W sustain in the all-in. Take Teleport instead if I expect to get zoned off the wave early and need to scale safely or impact the map — reasonable into a heavy-poke Gragas."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit spike that flips the lane; follow with Wit's End or Terminus to shred his magic resist and add true/magic on-hit against an AP brawler. Berserker's Greaves; build Mercury's Treads instead if his Drunken Rage burst and Cask CC are landing. Since his damage is magic, a defensive Wit's End / Maw line over pure armor."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"From level 6 onward, only when his Body Slam (E) is on cooldown — that's the one window he can't stun me out of Alpha Strike. The real all-in arrives at first item: Highlander up, Wuju Style active, his E down, in an open lane where I can extend the fight."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"My early is weak and gankable, so I track his jungler hard and play safe until 6 — a gank into his E combo before my item can throw the lane. After 6, Highlander's move speed and slow immunity make me very hard to gank, and post-item I'm the one who wants my jungler to set up an extended fight I'll win."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players try to trade or all-in too early because the lane is 'favoured' on paper — but it's only favoured once I'm itemized. Forcing fights levels 1-5 feeds his early-brawl power and denies my own scaling. The other mistake is blowing Alpha Strike to chase instead of saving it to dodge his E."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Stop fighting completely — his W damage reduction, Q sustain, and E stun beat a behind Yi every time. Farm side waves, use Alpha Strike only to escape, rush the on-hit item, and trust that my curve recovers from a deficit better than his does. Take neutral objectives my team sets up rather than coin-flip skirmishes."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Ahead, shove and convert into towers and objectives with my fast Wuju auto-DPS, then look for any extended fight where Alpha Strike dodges his cask-and-E and Highlander resets let me chain kills across the map. One pick becomes three because the reset cuts every cooldown."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED, 55% — a scaling lane I lose early and dominate once itemized; play patient, survive his body-slam burst to my first on-hit item, and out-DPS his even-AP brawl every fight after."}]},"garen":{"tldr":"Garen bullies your weak early levels and his Q-silence can clip you out of Alpha Strike, but once Wuju true damage and your first on-hit item land, Meditate out-sustains his short trades and you out-DPS his disengage in any extended fight.","winCon":"Concede levels 1-3 to Garen's silence-empowered Q and farm with Alpha Strike, then once Wuju Style true damage and your first on-hit item come online, Meditate out-sustains his burst-and-regen and you out-grind his spin in a long duel. Stick on him with Highlander, save Alpha Strike to dodge his Q so you never get silenced mid-combo, and reset off the kill to snowball the side lane.","enemyWin":"Garen wins by landing his Q-empowered silencing auto the instant you commit — the silence cancels your Alpha Strike or Wuju combo and lets his passive regen erase whatever you chipped. If he chunks you before 6 his Demacian Justice missing-HP true-damage execute caps you regardless of your sustain, and stacked armor blunts your physical autos early.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"4/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Garen","rating":"6/10","why":"With only Alpha Strike you can't fight his Q-empowered silencing auto, and his passive regen heals off any auto you trade — last-hit and concede."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Garen","rating":"6/10","why":"His Decisive Strike silence stops you from leaping out or starting a combo, and you still lack Wuju Style true damage to punch through his early armor."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Garen","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage comes online for short pokes that ignore his armor, but his Courage shield and regen still out-sustain your chip, so it's a coinflip wash."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Meditate now out-heals his poke-and-regen pattern between trades, but his Q silence still cancels any all-in, so neither side can commit cleanly yet."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's attack speed plus Wuju true damage lets you out-DPS his short trade, and the slow immunity ignores his Decisive Strike slow so he can't kite you off."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King makes your on-hit DPS beat his front-loaded burst, and Alpha Strike saved for his Q means you dodge the silence and finish the duel."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At two items your sustained on-hit damage and Highlander resets shred his single spin-and-disengage rotation, and Meditate plus Alpha Strike untargetability out-last his regen in any extended fight."}],"breakdown":{"early":"These three levels are Garen's and you respect them. At level 1 you have only Alpha Strike and no Wuju true damage, so his Q-empowered auto silences you, chunks you, and his passive regen heals back anything you land the second he breaks vision — just farm. By 2-3 his Decisive Strike silence is the real problem: it cancels your Alpha Strike mid-leap or stops a Wuju combo before it starts, and his early armor blunts your physical autos. Use Alpha Strike to last-hit safely and never walk into his minion wave for a trade.","mid":"Levels 4-5 stabilize as Wuju Style adds true damage that ignores his armor and Meditate's channel lets you out-sustain his poke-and-regen between trades, turning the lane into a wash. Level 6 is your first real swing: Highlander's bonus attack speed and slow immunity mean his Decisive Strike slow can't peel you, so you out-DPS his short trade and Wuju true damage outpaces his Courage shield. Bait his Q out before you commit — once the silence is on cooldown the all-in is yours.","late":"This is your lane. Once your first on-hit item lands (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) your sustained DPS beats his single front-loaded burst, and at two items you simply out-grind his spin-and-disengage. Alpha Strike's untargetability lets you dodge his Q-silence and even his Demacian Justice cast, Meditate out-heals his passive regen, and every kill resets Highlander to chain through the map. Force the long side-lane 1v1 his kit can't win.","wave":"Best wave: a slow-push you freeze just outside your tower so Garen can't all-in without diving and you farm safely with Alpha Strike. Worst wave: a fast-pushed wave shoved to his tower at levels 1-3, which lets him Q-silence you against the wall with no escape. Crash timing: crash the wave right as you hit your first on-hit item so you can recall, then return on the bounce with the item advantage to start trading.","cooldowns":"Track his Decisive Strike (Q, ~8s at rank 1) — it's both his burst and the silence that cancels your Alpha Strike. When it's down, his short trade and his only answer to your combo are gone, and that's your all-in window.","trading":"Early he wins the short trade: he Q-silences, lands the empowered auto, and regens off your chip. From 6 on you flip it — bait his Q, then engage with Highlander up so Wuju true damage and on-hit DPS grind him down before he can disengage.","spikes":"Garen spikes at level 6 (Demacian Justice execute) and whenever Courage is up for a trade. You spike at level 6 (Highlander), and hard at your first on-hit item and again at two items where your sustained DPS overtakes his burst-and-regen for good.","feeding":"If you fall behind, his Demacian Justice executes you through any resists and his regen means you can never poke him out — he roams and snowballs other lanes while you're stuck farming under tower. Avoid this by never trading into his Q early and never all-inning below his R execute threshold.","carry":"Once ahead your snowball is brutal: Highlander refreshes on kills and cuts your cooldowns, so you Alpha Strike onto the next target, reset, and chain fights across the map. Use your lead to roam to skirmishes the moment Garen recalls or shoves.","difficulty":"It's only a 4/10 because the lane is genuinely FAVOURED — but it's not a free 3/10 because his Q silence directly counters your one escape/engage tool and his true-damage R can punish a sloppy early-game HP bar, so the difficulty is in surviving and timing, not in winning the scaled fight."},"focus":{"text":"Garen's Decisive Strike (Q): the empowered auto silences you for ~1.5s, which cancels Alpha Strike mid-leap or stops your Wuju combo before it starts. Bait it out before every commit and use it being on cooldown as your all-in trigger.","letters":["Q"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike levels 1-3","d":"You can't fight his Q-empowered auto early, so use Alpha Strike to last-hit from range and let Wuju Style come online before you ever trade."},{"t":"Bait his Q before you all-in","d":"His Decisive Strike silence is the only thing that cancels your combo — make him use it on a minion or a feint, then engage with Highlander up while it's on cooldown."},{"t":"Save Alpha Strike to dodge, not engage","d":"Becoming untargetable mid-leap lets you dodge his Q-silence and even his Demacian Justice cast, so hold it for the moment he commits rather than burning it to start."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't trade autos into his armor early","d":"At levels 1-3 his Courage tenacity, early armor, and passive regen win the short exchange and erase your chip — you only lose HP for nothing."},{"t":"Don't all-in below his R threshold","d":"Demacian Justice is missing-HP true damage that ignores your resists, so never commit a low-HP fight expecting Meditate to save you — he just executes you."},{"t":"Don't get silenced against the wave","d":"Never push into him at levels 1-3; if his Q catches you in his minions with no Alpha Strike up, you eat the full trade with no escape."}],"tradeGood":"Post-6, bait his Decisive Strike, then engage with Highlander active so Wuju Style true damage and on-hit autos out-DPS his front-loaded burst while his slow can't kite you.","tradeBad":"A level 1-3 auto-trade into his armor and Q-silence, where his empowered strike and passive regen win the exchange and your physical damage barely dents him.","ahead":"Press a lead by forcing repeated long duels in the side lane where his single spin-and-disengage rotation can't out-DPS your sustained on-hit damage and Highlander resets. The moment Garen recalls or shoves to roam, you roam too — Highlander's cooldown reduction and refresh-on-kill let you Alpha Strike into skirmishes and chain resets faster than he can stack Courage. Build the on-hit item that out-trades his regen first (anti-heal is rarely needed since his sustain is regen-based, so prioritize raw DPS) and snowball before he can reach his tanky power spikes.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Garen - Track: Garen's Decisive Strike (Q): the empowered auto silences you for ~1.5s, which cancels Alpha Strike mid-leap or stops your Wuju combo before it starts. Bait it out before every commit and use it being on cooldown as your all-in trigger.. - Concede levels 1-3 to Garen's silence-empowered Q and farm with Alpha Strike, then once Wuju Style true damage and your first on-hit item come online, Meditate out-sustains his burst-and-regen and you out-grind his spin in a long duel. Stick on him with Highlander, save Alpha Strike to dodge his Q so you never get silenced mid-combo, and reset off the kill to snowball the side lane.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Garen bullies your weak early levels and his Q-silence can clip you out of Alpha Strike, but once Wuju true damage and your first on-hit item land, Meditate out-sustains his short trades and you out-DPS his disengage in any extended fight."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive Garen's silence-empowered early game by farming with Alpha Strike, then take over once Wuju Style true damage and your first on-hit item let Meditate out-sustain his burst-and-regen. Stick with Highlander, dodge his Q with Alpha Strike's untargetability, and out-grind his single disengage in extended duels."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Garen owns levels 1-3, it evens out at 4-5 as Wuju and Meditate come online, and it tilts to you from level 6 onward and hard from your first on-hit item."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Back off every short trade levels 1-3 — his Q-silence, armor, and regen win them. From 6 on, only trade after baiting his Decisive Strike, then commit with Highlander up."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave slow-pushing or frozen near your tower early so he can't pin you against minions for a Q-silence; once you hit your on-hit item spike, crash and recall to return with the lead."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges his Q-silence and Demacian Justice cast; Highlander's slow immunity ignores his Decisive Strike slow so he can't kite you; but his Q-silence directly cancels your Alpha Strike or Wuju combo if you don't bait it, and his R's true damage ignores any resists you build."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the attack-speed ramp that powers your extended-trade win condition, with Triumph and Legend: Alacrity; secondary Resolve (Conditioning or Second Wind vs his early poke) plus a Bone Plating-style mitigation to blunt his level-6 burst, or Cut Down if you want extra damage into his tankier build."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite to convert your post-6 all-in into a kill and shut off any chance his passive regen out-sustains you in the duel; take Teleport only if your team needs map presence, but Ignite is the higher-tempo pick for this winnable lane."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush an on-hit core — Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King — then Wit's End or Terminus for the extra on-hit/MR; berserker's greaves; defensively his armor matters more than his MR so you don't need early MR, and anti-heal is low value since his sustain is passive regen, not lifesteal — prioritize raw DPS to beat his disengage."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You can actually all-in from level 6 once Highlander is up and his Decisive Strike is on cooldown, and decisively at your first on-hit item — engage when his Q is down, your Alpha Strike is up to dodge his recommit, and his HP is above his own R-execute trap."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're gankable early since Alpha Strike is your only escape and his Q-silence sets up any gank — ward his river entrance levels 1-5. After 6, Highlander's mobility and slow immunity make you hard to collapse on, and you can punish his ganks for other lanes by farming the open side."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi mistake here is fighting too early — trading autos into his armor and Q-silence levels 1-3, or all-inning at low HP expecting Meditate to out-sustain his Demacian Justice, which it can't because the execute is true damage."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're behind, farm safely under tower with Alpha Strike, never trade into his Q, and stay above his R-execute threshold; your curve is so steep that reaching two items still flips the duel even from a deficit, so prioritize scaling over heroics."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Once ahead, chain Highlander resets — Alpha Strike a target, reset off the kill to cut your cooldowns, and roam to skirmishes the instant Garen leaves lane, building DPS faster than he reaches his tanky spikes."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED 53.31% — a steep-curve scaling lane: survive his silence-and-execute early game and your on-hit DPS out-grinds his single disengage from your first item on."}]},"graves":{"tldr":"A ranged skirmisher who blinds your autos and bursts you before you scale — survive Graves's lane, hit your first on-hit item, and the late game flips to you.","winCon":"Concede the early game, farm safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos through his poke, and reach your first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer or BORK) plus Highlander — once you out-DPS his tankier ADC build in an extended fight you reset kills and take over. Punish every Graves E dash that lands him out of position with no auto reloaded.","enemyWin":"Graves wins by abusing his range, shotgun burst, and Smoke Screen to chunk and blind you every time you walk up, denying CS and snowballing his lead before you itemize. If he keeps you under 6 and behind on items, his early kill pressure and self-peel (E armor stacks + smoke zone) mean you never get to your scaling.","diff":"TRICKY","tone":"#ff8b3d","diffRating":"7/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Graves","rating":"7/10","why":"Graves's shotgun auto and Q out-range you and out-trade your single melee auto; you have no Wuju or Highlander yet, so you only walk up to last-hit."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Graves","rating":"7/10","why":"With two abilities online he can E in for a Q burst and back off before your Alpha Strike resets, and his Smoke Screen blind blanks your auto window."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Graves","rating":"6/10","why":"His level-3 power spike (E + Q + auto) bursts a huge chunk; you still lack Highlander and lose any extended trade he chooses to take."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain let you survive his poke and answer short trades, but his range still controls when fights happen."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander gives slow immunity and burst MS to ignore his smoke slow and stick through an Alpha Strike, flipping any extended trade or gank in your favor."},{"label":"First item","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) closes his early DPS lead, but he builds tankier than a normal ADC (E armor, defensive items) so the fight is genuinely even."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"At two on-hit items Alpha Strike dodges his Q/R burst and your on-hit true damage shreds his bruiser-ADC armor faster than he can kite, and a kill resets Highlander to chain."}],"breakdown":{"early":"This is the worst part of the lane for you. Graves out-ranges you with shotgun autos and Q, and a single E-Q-auto combo at level 3 deletes a third of your bar while you have no Wuju true damage or Highlander to answer. Just farm: use Alpha Strike to last-hit from range, take Meditate-able poke, and never walk into a fight he initiates.","mid":"Levels 4-5 stabilize you as Wuju Style's bonus true damage and Meditate's sustain let you trade back the chip damage. Level 6 is your first real moment — Highlander's slow immunity ignores his Smoke Screen slow and the burst MS lets you stick through Alpha Strike, so you can finally answer his aggression and survive ganks.","late":"At 2+ on-hit items you flip the lane. Alpha Strike makes you untargetable through his Q line and R cone, your on-hit true damage and BORK/Kraken procs eat his bruiser-ADC armor faster than he can kite, and a single reset on Highlander lets you chain through him and anyone who collapses.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push you control so you fight near your tower and force him off CS into Alpha Strike range. Worst wave: a wave shoved INTO his tower early, where his range and turret let him zone you off farm and set up a jungle gank. Crash timing: crash the wave right before your first item back so you reach base, buy your on-hit spike, and return without missing a cannon.","cooldowns":"Track Smoke Screen (W) above all — its blind negates your autos and Alpha Strike on-hit DPS and the zone denies you vision to chase; also watch E (Quickdraw) since when it's down he has no dash to escape your gap-close.","trading":"Never trade auto-for-auto into his shotgun while he can see you. Wait for his E to be on cooldown or for him to step up past minions, then Alpha Strike in with Wuju active for a burst he can't kite out of, and disengage before his W comes back up.","spikes":"Graves spikes hardest at level 3 (E+Q+auto) and at his first ADC item. Your spikes are level 6 (Highlander), first on-hit item, and decisively at 2+ items where you out-DPS his tankier build.","feeding":"If you fall behind, his lead compounds fast — he zones you off every wave with range, you miss your item timings, and you become a free kill for his jungler. Play for CS under tower, ask for jungle help, and stall to your scaling rather than forcing trades you lose.","carry":"If you get ahead you become a 1v9 on-hit duelist: Alpha Strike dodges his burst, Highlander resets on kills, and your true damage ignores the armor he stacks, so you split-push and win every skirmish he can't kite.","difficulty":"It's a 7/10 because Graves is exactly Yi's nightmare archetype — ranged, bursty, and packing a blind — so you lose the entire early game and most of the mid, and your only path is disciplined farming until your item scaling drags the lane back."},"focus":{"text":"Smoke Screen (W) — its blind shuts off your basic attacks and Alpha Strike on-hit damage, and the zone denies the vision you need to chase, so it neutralizes your entire kit during a fight.","letters":["W"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike","d":"Use Q to last-hit safely from outside his shotgun range and to reduce its cooldown off minions, so you never walk into a free poke trade just for a CS."},{"t":"Wait for his E to commit","d":"Only Alpha Strike in when Quickdraw is on cooldown — without his dash he can't peel or escape your gap-close, turning his aggression into your kill."},{"t":"Scale to your items","d":"Concede the lane and prioritize your first on-hit spike (Kraken or BORK) plus level 6 Highlander; the lane is yours once you out-DPS his tankier build."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't fight in his Smoke","d":"Never commit an Alpha Strike or auto chain inside Smoke Screen — the blind zeroes your on-hit damage and the zone hides him so you can't follow up."},{"t":"Don't walk up early","d":"Don't trade autos before level 6 and Wuju online; his shotgun burst and Q out-trade your single melee hit and you have no sustain answer yet."},{"t":"Don't chase past your wave","d":"His E dash and burst let him reset distance and turn a chase into a kill on you, especially if his jungler is unaccounted for."}],"tradeGood":"Alpha Strike in with Wuju Style active right after his E and W are on cooldown, burst him with on-hit true damage, and Highlander-disengage before his shotgun reloads.","tradeBad":"Walking up to auto-trade into his shotgun and Smoke Screen blind before level 6, where his range and burst win every exchange and you can't even hit back.","ahead":"Press a lead by forcing fights in the open where Alpha Strike negates his burst and your true damage ignores his stacked armor — never inside his smoke. Use Highlander resets to chain through him and any collapsing teammate, then take a side lane to split, since he can't kite a fed Yi who out-ranges his cooldowns with untargetable Q. Deny his items with kills and the lane tilts permanently into your scaling window.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Graves - Track: Smoke Screen (W) — its blind shuts off your basic attacks and Alpha Strike on-hit damage, and the zone denies the vision you need to chase, so it neutralizes your entire kit during a fight.. - Concede the early game, farm safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos through his poke, and reach your first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer or BORK) plus Highlander — once you out-DPS his tankier ADC build in an extended fight you reset kills and take over. Punish every Graves E dash that lands him out of position with no auto reloaded.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A ranged skirmisher who blinds your autos and bursts you before you scale — survive Graves's lane, hit your first on-hit item, and the late game flips to you."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a brutal early lane by farming with Alpha Strike and Meditate, then hit your first on-hit item plus Highlander to out-DPS Graves's tankier ADC build in extended fights. Once you're untargetable through his burst and reset on kills, you reclaim the lane and snowball it into the map."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Graves owns levels 1-3 hard, the lane evens at 4-5 as Wuju and Meditate come online, you take level 6 with Highlander, it's a coin-flip at first item, and you decisively own the 2+ items window."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only when his E (Quickdraw) and W (Smoke Screen) are on cooldown and he's stepped past his minions; back off entirely while he can blind you or kite with his dash, and never auto-trade into his shotgun range pre-6."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave slow-pushing or near your tower so you farm safely in Alpha Strike range and force him into your gap-close; avoid shoving into his turret early where his range plus tower zone you off CS and bait jungle ganks."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike makes you untargetable through Graves's Q line and R cone, but his Smoke Screen blind negates your autos and Q's on-hit damage; Highlander's slow immunity ignores his smoke slow, and his E armor stacks are bypassed by your Wuju/BORK true damage."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the attack-speed scaling that fuels your on-hit comeback (Conqueror if you want trade sustain), with Triumph and Legend: Alacrity; secondary Resolve (Second Wind + Overgrowth) to survive his AD poke, or Bone Plating into his burst."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Teleport is safest here — TP lets you farm cautiously, recover from his early zoning, and rejoin lane on tempo; take Ignite only if you're confident in a level-6 Highlander all-in and your jungler camps the lane."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for your on-hit spike, then Wit's End or Terminus for more on-hit and resistances; buy Ninja Tabi/Plated Steelcaps against his all-AD burst and add a Maw or armor-shred item versus his bruiser-ADC build."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Your real all-in windows are level 6 with Highlander up and at 2+ items — only commit when his E and W are down, ideally with jungle help, so he can't kite or blind his way out."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"This lane is gank-dependent for you: pre-6 you're easily collapsed on, so ward his jungle entrances, but post-6 Highlander's MS and slow immunity make you a strong dive partner — a single jungle gank that burns his E flips the lane to your scaling."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi mistake here is walking up to trade or chase into Smoke Screen, eating the blind and burst for free; the second is forcing fights before your first item instead of just farming to your scaling spike."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're behind, abandon the trade game entirely — farm under tower with Alpha Strike, soak XP, ping for jungle help, and stall to your item timings, since your kit only needs to reach 2 items to matter again."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"When ahead, force open-ground fights where Q dodges his burst and true damage shreds his armor, chain Highlander resets through him and his team, then split-push a side lane he can't 1v1 a fed Yi in."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"TRICKY 7/10 — Graves's range, burst, and blind own the early and most of the mid, but Highlander at 6 and your on-hit scaling at 2+ items drag this 47% lane back into a winnable late game."}]},"gwen":{"tldr":"Gwen pokes you out early and Hallowed Mist denies your all-in, but once you hit your on-hit spike you out-DPS her in any extended fight and Alpha Strike lets you ignore the mist by dodging out of it — survive lane and this becomes a kill lane.","winCon":"Concede the first few levels, farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, and stack on-hit (Kraken/BORK + Wit's End) so that when you finally catch Gwen outside her Hallowed Mist your true-damage E and Highlander resets melt her before she can scale. The whole lane is \"don't die before item one, then run her down whenever her W is down.\"","enemyWin":"Gwen wins by zoning you off CS with Q true-damage snips and using Hallowed Mist to negate every all-in you attempt, then out-scaling you into a teamfight monster where her untargetability and AP burst beat your on-hit DPS at full builds.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"4/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Gwen","rating":"6/10","why":"Gwen's Q snips you for true damage from range while your only level-1 tool is a single-target Alpha Strike, so she controls the first wave and pokes freely."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Gwen","rating":"6/10","why":"With E dash + attack speed online she can short-trade and reposition, and you still lack Wuju Style true damage to punish her back."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"You get Wuju Style for true-damage autos but she gets her full poke kit; trades are a coin-flip decided by whether she has E up to dash away."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Meditate now out-sustains her Q poke and Wuju Style true damage lets your short bursts hurt, so the lane stabilizes in your favour as long as you respect her mist."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity let you stick to her and answer ganks; her ult is still down so your 6 spike lands first."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken/BORK on-hit DPS plus Alpha Strike resetting your attack timer means an extended fight outside Hallowed Mist kills her before she can react."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Gwen","rating":"6/10","why":"At full AP-bruiser items Gwen's untargetability, true-damage Q snips and burst out-scale your on-hit profile, so she reclaims the late game if she survived lane even."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are Gwen's: she snips you with Q true damage from range while you have no minion-cleared Alpha Strike and a single-target Q that barely trades. Do NOT walk up to last-hit into her Q range — use Alpha Strike to grab CS from a safe spot and soak XP. Accept the chip; you cannot win an all-in here and dying once snowballs her scaling.","mid":"Levels 4-6 flip toward you. Wuju Style adds true damage that ignores her bruiser resists, Meditate sustains through her Q poke, and at 6 Highlander gives you slow immunity and the speed to actually stick to her. This is your first window to threaten kills — but only when her Hallowed Mist is on cooldown, because inside the mist she is untargetable and your DPS is wasted.","late":"At 2+ items the lane has been decided in lane, but in teamfights Gwen reclaims scaling: her untargetability inside mist, true-damage Q snips and AP burst out-scale your on-hit profile. Close the game on your item-one/two lead; if it goes long, fight her where she has no mist to hide in and force the duel before her late-game items come online.","wave":"Best wave: a wave crashing into your side so you can farm safely under tower with Alpha Strike and dodge her Q poke. Worst wave: a slow-pushing Gwen wave that lets her zone you off CS and snip you with Q every time you step up. Crash timing: shove hard right before your first on-hit item completes so you can recall, buy your spike, and return for a level/item-advantaged all-in while her mist is down.","cooldowns":"Track Hallowed Mist (W) above all — it is her get-out-of-jail untargetability. Also count her E dashes; with E down she has no escape from Highlander.","trading":"Short-trade with E Wuju Style true-damage autos when her W and E are both on cooldown, then disengage with Highlander move speed before she can dash back. Never sit in an extended trade while she has Hallowed Mist up — she just steps in and your damage hits nothing.","spikes":"Gwen spikes at her item-one (Riftmaker/Nashor's) and scales every item after. You spike at Highlander (6) and harder at your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) — your goal is to make your spike land during a window where hers hasn't.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Gwen's untargetability makes her nearly impossible to punish and she just scales past you — your weak early already conceded tempo, so a death here is doubly costly. Farm side lanes with Alpha Strike, take camps to catch up, and avoid extended fights until your on-hit comes online.","carry":"Ahead, you become a 1v9: Highlander resets on kills let you chain through her team, Alpha Strike dodges incoming CC mid-fight, and your on-hit DPS shreds anyone outside her mist. Use your lead to take Gwen's tower, roam to other lanes, and snowball before her scaling matters.","difficulty":"Only 4/10 because the verdict is FAVOURED — your scaling out-paces hers in the early-to-mid window and Alpha Strike's blink answers her mist. The difficulty that exists is entirely the early lane and the discipline to never commit into an up Hallowed Mist."},"focus":{"text":"Hallowed Mist (W) — her untargetability bubble. Every all-in you attempt fails if she drops it, because Alpha Strike and your autos can't hit her inside it; only commit when it is on cooldown or after you've baited it out.","letters":["W"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Bait or wait out Hallowed Mist","d":"Only commit your all-in when her W is on cooldown or she has already used it — force her to drop the mist with a fake threat, then engage into the window where she's targetable."},{"t":"Farm safe early with Alpha Strike","d":"Use Q to last-hit from a safe distance and soak XP instead of walking into her Q true-damage poke range; surviving levels 1-3 even is a win for you."},{"t":"Spike on on-hit, then run her down","d":"Rush Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King plus Wit's End — once it's online, fight her in any extended exchange outside her mist and let Highlander resets chain your kills."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't all-in into an up Hallowed Mist","d":"If you blow Alpha Strike and autos while she's untargetable in the mist, you deal zero damage and eat her counter — the single biggest way to throw this lane."},{"t":"Don't fight her at full items if it went even","d":"At 2+ items her untargetability and AP burst out-scale your on-hit; if you didn't get a lead, don't duel her late — force the game to close earlier or fight her with your team where she can't hide."},{"t":"Don't trade autos into her Q poke early","d":"Stepping up to contest CS levels 1-3 just feeds her true-damage Q snips; you have no kill pressure yet, so eating poke for a worthless trade only helps her scale."}],"tradeGood":"An extended fight at your first on-hit item, with her Hallowed Mist on cooldown — Alpha Strike resets your attack timer and Wuju true damage shreds her bruiser resists before she can dash out.","tradeBad":"A committed all-in while Hallowed Mist is up — she steps into the mist, becomes untargetable, and your blown Alpha Strike plus autos hit nothing while she punishes the whiff.","ahead":"Press by taking her tower the moment you hit your on-hit item spike, then roam with Highlander's move speed to snowball other lanes while her scaling is still online. Keep dueling her only outside her mist — your lead means you delete her in any targetable window, and every kill refreshes Highlander to chain into her jungler or mid. Deny her farm so her hard-scaling never catches up, and close the game before her full build flips the late-game advantage back to her.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Gwen - Track: Hallowed Mist (W) — her untargetability bubble. Every all-in you attempt fails if she drops it, because Alpha Strike and your autos can't hit her inside it; only commit when it is on cooldown or after you've baited it out.. - Concede the first few levels, farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, and stack on-hit (Kraken/BORK + Wit's End) so that when you finally catch Gwen outside her Hallowed Mist your true-damage E and Highlander resets melt her before she can scale. The whole lane is \"don't die before item one, then run her down whenever her W is down.\"","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Gwen pokes you out early and Hallowed Mist denies your all-in, but once you hit your on-hit spike you out-DPS her in any extended fight and Alpha Strike lets you ignore the mist by dodging out of it — survive lane and this becomes a kill lane."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a poke-heavy early lane by farming with Alpha Strike, then hit your on-hit item spike (Kraken/BORK + Wit's End) and out-DPS Gwen in any extended fight where her Hallowed Mist is down. Your win condition is timing your spike into a window before hers and using Alpha Strike's blink to ignore the mist by repositioning out of it."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Gwen edges levels 1-3 with Q poke; even at 4-5 as Wuju Style comes online; you take over from 6 (Highlander) through your first on-hit item; she reclaims the 2+ items late game as a hard scaler."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only when her Hallowed Mist AND E dash are on cooldown, with short Wuju-Style true-damage bursts; back off the instant she has mist available, because she just steps in untargetable and negates the whole exchange."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Let the wave settle on your side early so you can farm under tower and dodge Q poke; shove hard right before your first on-hit item completes to recall, buy your spike, and return level/item-ahead while her mist is down."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike makes you untargetable mid-blink, so you can use it to dodge incoming CC or to reposition out of where she expects you — but it cannot hit her while she sits inside Hallowed Mist. Wuju Style's true damage ignores her bruiser armor/MR, and Meditate out-sustains her Q true-damage poke in extended exchanges."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (faster on-hit ramp into her bruiser resists) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Coup de Grace primary; secondary Resolve (Conditioning/Overgrowth) or Sorcery (Nimbus Cloak/Transcendence) — take Second Wind in the runes shard to ease her Q poke, and lean magic-resist shards vs her AP."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to convert your mid-game spike into kills and cut her sustain/scaling; take Teleport instead only if you expect to get poked out of lane and need to recover tempo."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King into Wit's End (the magic resist matters vs her AP and the on-hit shreds her), then Terminus; finish with Mercury's Treads for her CC/magic damage and consider a defensive third item like Maw if she's fed."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You can actually all-in at level 6 with Highlander up and again every time her Hallowed Mist is on cooldown after your first on-hit item — never outside those windows."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Your weak early makes you gankable, so ward and play safe pre-6; post-6 Highlander's slow immunity and speed make you hard to gank and great to gank WITH — call your jungler in when her mist is down to convert a 2v1 into a kill she can't escape."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi mistake here is forcing an all-in into an up Hallowed Mist — blowing Alpha Strike and autos while she's untargetable, then dying to the counter; the second is contesting CS into her Q poke early when you have no kill pressure."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you fall behind, farm side waves with Alpha Strike and take jungle camps to hit your on-hit spike anyway; avoid solo duels (her untargetability punishes desperation) and look to fight her 2v1 or in skirmishes where her mist can only save her, not win."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Ahead, take her tower on your item spike, roam with Highlander speed, and chain Highlander resets through her team — deny her farm so her hard scaling never arrives and end before her full build reclaims the late game."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED for Master Yi (4/10 difficulty, 8/10 carry) — eat the early poke, hit your on-hit spike, fight her outside Hallowed Mist, and close before her late-game scaling flips it back."}]},"heimerdinger":{"tldr":"Heimerdinger walls you off the wave with turrets and pokes you out before you ever hit the on-hit spike that wins fights — you lose lane, so play for the map and the late game.","winCon":"Survive the poke phase by farming with Alpha Strike from max range and only committing when his E grenade and at least one turret are down, then hit Kraken/BORK and look to all-in through Highlander or simply roam to a winnable lane. You don't out-trade Heimer — you out-scale him and out-roam him, so cap your losses, hit two items, and force fights away from his turret nest where Alpha Strike resets carry the teamfight.","enemyWin":"He builds a three-turret nest on the wave so you physically can't walk to CS without eating stacked turret fire, chunks you with W rockets, and lands the E (CH-3X) stun the moment you commit — Alpha Strike's untargetability ends and his point-and-click grenade catches you, letting turrets and his jungler delete you. If he keeps you off the wave and denies your item spikes, you never come online.","diff":"HARD","tone":"#ff5d6c","diffRating":"8/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Heimerdinger","rating":"6/10","why":"He places his first turret on the wave and starts last-hitting from safety while you have only short-range autos and no way to contest the zone."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Heimerdinger","rating":"7/10","why":"His second turret plus a W rocket volley out-trades any walk-up, and you can't dive the nest at level 2 without his E grenade locking you for turret focus."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Heimerdinger","rating":"8/10","why":"The full three-turret nest goes up and walls you off the minions entirely — this is his hardest zone and you simply concede CS rather than feed."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Heimerdinger","rating":"7/10","why":"Even with Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain online, his turret DPS plus rocket poke out-damages your short trades and Meditate just makes you a stationary turret target."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Heimerdinger","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander lets you finally dodge ganks and run him down, but his R upgrades a turret or grenade into a super-version and the CH-3X stun still catches you the instant Alpha Strike ends."},{"label":"First item","side":"Heimerdinger","rating":"6/10","why":"Your Kraken/BORK on-hit spike arrives, but his Liandry's/Rylai's-backed nest still kites you and the E stun resets the whole turret focus before you can finish him."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"At two items Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges the grenade and your on-hit DPS shreds his squishy body and turrets — but you must catch him away from a fresh nest or he resets the kite."}],"breakdown":{"early":"You are completely zoned levels 1-3. Heimer drops a turret directly on the wave and last-hits from behind it while you have no range and no escape but Q. Use Alpha Strike to snipe last-hits from max distance, never walk into turret range to auto a minion, and accept missing CS rather than taking turret-plus-rocket damage that hands him a level lead.","mid":"Levels 4-6 do not flip this lane the way they do versus melee. Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain help you survive but his three-turret nest plus W rocket poke still out-damages your short trades, and Meditate channels you into a stationary target the turrets melt. Level 6 Highlander is your first real relief — it lets you dodge the jungle gank he's set up, not win the 1v1.","late":"At 2+ items you finally have a path: Alpha Strike becomes untargetable through his E grenade and your on-hit DPS (Kraken/BORK procs) shreds both turrets and his low-health body. But it only works if you catch him without a fresh nest down — into a full three-turret setup he still kites and resets, so pick him in the river, in your jungle, or sidelane him after he places turrets and walks off.","wave":"Best wave: a wave pushing toward you so you Alpha Strike-farm under tower away from his turret zone and deny him free siege. Worst wave: a slow-push that lets him stack a full three-turret nest on top of your minions and zone you off every CS. Crash timing: shove hard right before you recall or roam so the wave crashes into his tower, resets the turret zone, and denies him a free siege window while you're gone.","cooldowns":"Track his E, the CH-3X stun grenade (the slow-moving missile) — it's his only hard lockdown and the thing that catches you the instant Alpha Strike's untargetability ends; also count his turret placements since the third turret is what fully walls the wave.","trading":"There is no good walk-up trade here — every step toward him eats stacked turret beams plus a rocket. Your only real trade is an all-in committed through Alpha Strike to dodge the grenade, and only once a turret is on cooldown or destroyed and his E is down.","spikes":"His spikes: second turret (lvl 2), full nest (lvls 3-4), level 6 super-turret/grenade upgrade, and Liandry's+Rylai's first item. Yours: level 6 Highlander for gank-dodging, and your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) — but neither out-races his nest, so your real flip is 2+ items in open ground.","feeding":"If you fall behind here it spirals fast — a fed Heimer turret nest is uncontestable, he shoves you under tower permanently, and his roams/poke let his team snowball. The instant you're down, stop forcing the 1v1, farm safely under tower with Alpha Strike, and ask your jungler to dive the nest with you rather than soloing into the turrets.","carry":"If you get ahead anyway, you carry by leaving lane — Highlander move speed lets you roam to squishier lanes where Alpha Strike resets chain kills, and in teamfights you flank so the grenade can't pre-fire on you and your on-hit DPS deletes him and his backline before the turrets matter.","difficulty":"It's an 8/10 because Heimer attacks the exact axis Yi is weakest on: a ranged zoner who out-poke and out-zones your weak early, walls you off CS so you can't even scale on schedule, and has a point-and-click stun that punishes the one window (post-Alpha Strike) where you're vulnerable. You can't dodge a nest and you can't trade through it."},"focus":{"text":"His E, the CH-3X stun grenade — it's his only hard lockdown and it catches you the exact moment Alpha Strike's untargetability ends, setting up the turret-plus-jungler kill. Bait it or wait it out before you ever commit.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Alpha Strike-farm from range","d":"Use Q to snipe last-hits from max distance so you never step into turret range for a minion; conceding a few CS beats eating stacked beams and a rocket."},{"t":"Save Q to dodge the grenade","d":"Don't waste Alpha Strike on the wave when you intend to all-in — its untargetability is your only way to blank the CH-3X stun, so commit Q the moment he throws E."},{"t":"Scale, then leave","d":"Hit level 6 and your first on-hit item, then roam with Highlander move speed or sidelane away from his nest — you win the game on the map, not in this lane."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't dive the nest","d":"All-inning into a full three-turret setup with his E up gets you stunned and melted; the turrets out-DPS you and the grenade ends your only escape."},{"t":"Don't Meditate in turret range","d":"Channeling W to sustain while standing in the nest just makes you a stationary target the turrets and rockets chew through faster than you heal."},{"t":"Don't force the 1v1 behind","d":"A fed Heimer turret zone is uncontestable solo — stop walking up, farm under tower with Q, and bring your jungler to the dive instead of feeding picks."}],"tradeGood":"After he throws E into the wave or it's on cooldown, flash-or-walk in committing Alpha Strike to blank any follow-up, pop Wuju Style and Highlander, and burst him before a new turret can stack — ideally once a turret is already destroyed.","tradeBad":"Never walk up to auto a minion or poke him inside the three-turret nest while his E is available — you eat stacked beams plus a rocket plus a stun for zero payoff.","ahead":"Pressing a lead means refusing to give it back to his nest — shove the wave in, then roam with Highlander move speed to a squishy lane where Alpha Strike chains resets, since you snowball far harder off other lanes than off sieging his turrets. When you do return, only fight him in open ground away from a fresh nest, and itemize anti-heal/penetration so he can't simply rebuild turrets and out-sustain your dive. In teamfights, flank from the side so the grenade can't pre-aim you and your on-hit DPS erases him before the turrets become relevant.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Heimerdinger - Track: His E, the CH-3X stun grenade — it's his only hard lockdown and it catches you the exact moment Alpha Strike's untargetability ends, setting up the turret-plus-jungler kill. Bait it or wait it out before you ever commit.. - Survive the poke phase by farming with Alpha Strike from max range and only committing when his E grenade and at least one turret are down, then hit Kraken/BORK and look to all-in through Highlander or simply roam to a winnable lane. You don't out-trade Heimer — you out-scale him and out-roam him, so cap your losses, hit two items, and force fights away from his turret nest where Alpha Strike resets carry the teamfight.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Heimerdinger walls you off the wave with turrets and pokes you out before you ever hit the on-hit spike that wins fights — you lose lane, so play for the map and the late game."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"You do not win this lane in lane — you survive a hard-counter poke matchup by Alpha Strike-farming, capping your CS losses, and hitting your two-item on-hit spike intact. From there you win by roaming with Highlander and fighting Heimer in open ground where Q dodges his grenade and your on-hit DPS shreds his squishy body."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Heimer owns 1 through First-item hard (turret nest + poke + the E stun); the lane only tilts toward you at 2+ items in open ground, and even then only away from a fresh three-turret setup."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only as a committed all-in through Alpha Strike after his E is down and a turret is destroyed or on cooldown; never take a walk-up auto trade inside the nest, and back off the instant a fresh turret is placed."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave pushing toward you so you farm under tower with Q and deny his free siege; shove and crash into his tower right before you recall or roam to reset his turret zone. Never let him slow-push a stacked nest onto your minions."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability is your one tool — it blanks his CH-3X (E) stun and dodges turret/rocket damage mid-blink. Wuju Style's true damage ignores any armor he stacks but is wasted poking the nest; Meditate sustains short fights but channels you into a stationary turret target. Highlander dodges the jungle gank his zoning sets up, not the 1v1."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (his short trades let your attack-speed ramp matter once you reach him) into Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve with Second Wind (eats his W rocket poke) and either Bone Plating or Overgrowth. Consider Conqueror if you expect to fight at 2+ items more than skirmish early. Doran's Shield start over Blade for the poke sustain."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Teleport — you will lose CS and need TP to stay even in gold and to roam/recover from his zone; Ignite is too greedy in a lane you can't win early. Flash is non-negotiable to escape the post-Alpha-Strike grenade."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for your on-hit spike, then Wit's End for the magic resist that directly answers his AP poke and rockets, into Terminus or Mercurial. Mercury's Treads over Berserker's for the magic-resist and tenacity versus his E stun; consider Hexdrinker/Maw components early if his poke is oppressive."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Only when his E grenade is on cooldown AND a turret is destroyed or expired AND you have Highlander up — realistically that's level 6+ with a jungler, or at 2+ items catching him away from a placed nest. Never into a fresh full nest."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"This lane lives and dies by ganks. His zoning is built to set up the enemy jungler diving you under turret, so ping early and hug tower. Your own jungler is your best path to a lead — Heimer is immobile and his nest takes setup, so a level-3/6 dive with you committing Alpha Strike on the grenade can crack the lane open."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi mistake here is trying to all-in through the nest at 6 the way you would versus a melee — you get stunned and melted. The other is wasting Alpha Strike to farm and then having no untargetability when he throws the grenade."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Stop forcing it: farm under tower with Q, take every safe TP/roam to reclaim gold elsewhere, build a defensive component (Wit's End/Hexdrinker) early, and let your team play around the map while you quietly reach two items. Do not solo-dive a fed nest."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Shove and leave — Highlander move speed makes you the best roamer on the map, so cash your lead in other lanes where Alpha Strike resets chain kills, then close games in teamfights by flanking the backline rather than sieging his turrets head-on."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A genuine hard counter (41.86% WR): Heimer zones, pokes, and stuns the exact windows Yi is weakest in. Concede the lane, scale to 2+ items, and win on the map and in open-ground fights — not in front of his nest."}]},"illaoi":{"tldr":"One of Yi's worst lanes: her tentacle field out-damages and out-heals everything you can do before items, and even Alpha Strike's untargetability can't save you from her on-timer slams once she rips your spirit.","winCon":"Survive a miserable early lane by farming Alpha Strike off the wave from outside her tentacle range, then stall to two on-hit items (BORK/Kraken into Wit's End) and only ever fight her in the OPEN lane far from her tentacles, where your DPS finally out-paces her healing.","enemyWin":"She lands Test of Spirit (E), forcing you to flee through your own tentacle slams or get vesseled, then anchors the wave inside a ring of tentacles and out-sustains your entire combo. At 6 her Leap of Faith lights the whole field and her healing simply eats your on-hit DPS in the all-in.","diff":"HARD","tone":"#ff5d6c","diffRating":"8/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Illaoi","rating":"6/10","why":"She plants a Tentacle (Q) and zones the wave; your level-1 autos are short-range and you can't trade into the slam, so you concede the brush and last-hit from the edge."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Illaoi","rating":"7/10","why":"A landed Test of Spirit (E) plus one tentacle slam already out-damages your entire level-2 kit, and Alpha Strike's untargetability does NOT cleanse the spirit — you just run from your own slams."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Illaoi","rating":"7/10","why":"You have Q + Wuju Style true damage but it's worthless inside her field; her tentacles out-trade you and her self-heal undoes any chunk you land off a single Alpha Strike."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Illaoi","rating":"7/10","why":"Wuju true damage and Meditate sustain are online but Meditate channel is a death sentence near her tentacles — every slam interrupts the heal and she free-hits the stationary channel."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Illaoi","rating":"8/10","why":"Highlander lets you dodge ganks but does nothing for the 1v1; her Leap of Faith (R) spawns a full ring of tentacles and her healing flat-out out-paces your level-6 on-hit damage."},{"label":"First item","side":"Illaoi","rating":"7/10","why":"Her first item (Sunfire/Iceborn or Black Cleaver) stacks even more field tankiness and healing while your first on-hit item hasn't yet tipped a fair duel — keep dodging E and farm."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Two on-hit items (BORK + Wit's End/Terminus) finally out-DPS her sustain in the open lane — Alpha Strike onto her off her tentacles, Wuju-shred her, and reset Highlander on the kill."}],"breakdown":{"early":"This is one of the cleanest losing early games in your champion pool. Her Tentacle (Q) and Test of Spirit (E) zone the entire wave, and your only safe play is farming with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos from outside slam range. The single most important fact: a landed Test of Spirit does NOT care that Alpha Strike makes you untargetable — the spirit lives on you and the tentacles slam on their own timer, so you cannot 'dodge' the vessel with Q. Walk into grab range to last-hit and you take a free E and lose the wave.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are still hers. Wuju Style true damage and Meditate come online, but Meditate is a trap here — it's a stationary channel and her tentacle slams interrupt it while she free-hits you, so you can't heal up inside her field. At 6, Highlander is a gank-dodge and a refresh tool, not a duel button; her Leap of Faith spawns the full tentacle ring and her healing simply eats your on-hit DPS. Do not contest the all-in — bait the E, sidestep the spirit, reset the wave, and ask your jungler to camp her since she's immobile.","late":"At two on-hit items (BORK + Wit's End or Terminus, into Kraken) the lane finally flips — but ONLY in the open side lane. Her tentacles are her entire power budget; pull her off them, Alpha Strike on, shred her armor with Wuju true damage, and your reset-on-kill Highlander grinds her down where the field can't help. Never re-enter a tentacle ring on an objective even when ahead.","wave":"Best wave: a wave pushed toward your tower so you farm Alpha Strike from max range and deny her tentacle real-estate near your turret. Worst wave: a frozen wave she anchors inside a ring of her own tentacles, where every trade happens in her damage field. Crash timing: shove and crash into her tower right before your jungler arrives so you can recall/roam, since you can't fight her in lane anyway.","cooldowns":"Track Test of Spirit (E) above all — it's a long cooldown (~16-12s) and is the only thing that turns the lane from 'lose' to 'unplayable.' When her E is down she has no way to rip your spirit, so that's your only window to step up or shove.","trading":"Never trade inside her tentacle field. The only profitable trade is Alpha Strike + Wuju autos onto her when she's stepped OFF her tentacles AND her E is on cooldown, then immediately disengage with Highlander move speed before the tentacles reach you.","spikes":"Her spikes: E available (every ~14s), level 6 Leap of Faith, and first tank item. Your spikes: level 6 Highlander (for survival/ganks, not dueling), and the real one — your second on-hit item, where DPS finally out-paces her heal.","feeding":"If you fall behind here it's catastrophic: she becomes an unkillable tentacle wall who out-sustains your whole team in fights, and a fed Illaoi 1v9s teamfights with her ult. Give up CS rather than deaths, freeze near tower, and play for objectives elsewhere instead of forcing the lane.","carry":"If you get ahead, your carry pattern is textbook Yi: Alpha Strike onto a squishy, true-damage shred, reset Highlander on the kill, repeat. But you only get ahead here by scaling and roaming, not by winning lane — your gold comes from her teammates, not from her.","difficulty":"It's 8/10 because every tool she has answers your kit: her field out-damages your early autos, her self-heal undoes your sustain, her slams ignore Alpha Strike's untargetability, and she's an AOE monster you can't burst before two items — a 43% win rate that reflects how rarely you get a clean window."},"focus":{"text":"Test of Spirit (E) — if she rips your spirit, you must run from your own tentacle slams, and Alpha Strike's untargetability does NOT remove the vessel. Never path into grab range, and only step up when her E is on cooldown.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm from the edge","d":"Last-hit with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos from outside her tentacle/grab range. Concede lane pressure and never walk in just to secure one minion."},{"t":"Only fight off her tentacles","d":"The single profitable engage is Alpha Strike onto her when she's stepped away from her tentacles AND her E is down — then disengage with Highlander before the slams land."},{"t":"Scale to two items","d":"Stall to BORK + Wit's End/Terminus, where your on-hit DPS finally out-paces her healing, and bring anti-heal (Executioner's/Mortal Reminder) to cut her sustain."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't trust untargetability","d":"Alpha Strike does NOT cleanse Test of Spirit — once vesseled, going untargetable doesn't stop the on-timer tentacle slams. Don't rely on Q to escape the spirit."},{"t":"Don't Meditate in her field","d":"Meditate is a stationary channel; her tentacle slams interrupt the heal and she free-hits you. Never channel W anywhere near her tentacles."},{"t":"Don't contest her 6 all-in","d":"Leap of Faith spawns a full tentacle ring and her healing eats your DPS — bait the E, sidestep the spirit, and reset the wave instead of fighting."}],"tradeGood":"Alpha Strike onto her when she's pulled off her tentacles and her Test of Spirit is on cooldown, Wuju-shred her with true damage, then peel off on Highlander move speed before the slams reach you.","tradeBad":"Any extended trade inside her tentacle field — especially walking up to auto or to Meditate, where the slams out-damage you and her self-heal erases the chunk.","ahead":"Leads here come from scaling and roaming, not from out-laning her. If you do get ahead, shove the wave with Alpha Strike, crash into her tower, and roam to snowball the rest of the map while your Highlander resets keep you healthy. In fights, ignore her entirely until she's pulled off her tentacles, then Alpha Strike a squishy, reset, and chain kills — never dive into her field for the pick.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Illaoi - Track: Test of Spirit (E) — if she rips your spirit, you must run from your own tentacle slams, and Alpha Strike's untargetability does NOT remove the vessel. Never path into grab range, and only step up when her E is on cooldown.. - Survive a miserable early lane by farming Alpha Strike off the wave from outside her tentacle range, then stall to two on-hit items (BORK/Kraken into Wit's End) and only ever fight her in the OPEN lane far from her tentacles, where your DPS finally out-paces her healing.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"One of Yi's worst lanes: her tentacle field out-damages and out-heals everything you can do before items, and even Alpha Strike's untargetability can't save you from her on-timer slams once she rips your spirit."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a hard-losing early lane by farming Alpha Strike from outside her tentacle range and never trading in her field, then scale to two on-hit items where your DPS out-paces her healing. You win by fighting her only in the open lane off her tentacles, and by getting your gold from her teammates rather than from her."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Illaoi owns levels 1-6 hard (field damage + sustain + on-timer slams beat your early kit); the lane only swings to you at your second on-hit item."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade ONLY when she's off her tentacles and Test of Spirit is on cooldown; back off and farm any other time, and never step up into her field for a single minion."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave on your side or pushed to her tower so you farm from max range; never let her freeze and anchor it inside a ring of her tentacles."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Critically, Alpha Strike's untargetability does NOT cleanse Test of Spirit — the vessel and tentacle slams hit on their own timer regardless of your blink; Meditate is interrupted by slams; her self-heal undoes your on-hit chunks."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo, Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve with Second Wind (to survive E poke and tentacle harass) and Bone Plating or Overgrowth. Second Wind over Conditioning is mandatory into her sustained early harass."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Teleport — you lose lane regardless, and TP lets you stay even on CS and use your scaling; Ignite is too greedy into a lane you can't kill early and her sustain out-heals it."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush an anti-heal component early (Executioner's Calling), then BORK as your core, into Kraken Slayer and Wit's End or Terminus for the on-hit/MR; Mortal Reminder later to keep cutting her healing. Take Plated Steelcaps vs her AD slams."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"There is no real lane all-in until two on-hit items, and even then ONLY when she's off her tentacles with E down — anywhere else her field and sustain win the fight."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"She's completely immobile, so she's a prime gank target — set up shoves and call your jungler to punish her lack of escape; conversely her Leap of Faith + tentacle field punishes enemy dives hard, so coordinate, don't solo-dive."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi error is trusting Alpha Strike to dodge her spirit/slams — it doesn't — and channeling Meditate near her tentacles to 'sustain through,' which just feeds free slam damage."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Freeze near tower, give CS over deaths, take Teleport value, and play for objectives and side-lane farm elsewhere; do not force a lane you mathematically cannot win pre-items."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If you get a lead, shove with Alpha Strike and roam — your reset Highlander snowballs the rest of the map far faster than grinding her wall, and in fights you only ever touch her once she's off her tentacles."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"HARD 8/10 — a 43% lane where her field out-damages, out-heals, and out-ranges your early kit, and even your untargetability can't save you; survive, scale, and win it off her tentacles or off the map."}]},"irelia":{"tldr":"A duelist mirror that comes down to itemization: I lose the early skirmishes to her Q-resets and E-stun, but once my on-hit spike lands the extended fight becomes mine — survive to first item and it's a coinflip I can carry.","winCon":"Farm safely behind Alpha Strike through levels 1-5, dodge her E-stun and Defiant Dance with Q's untargetable window, then hit my Kraken/BORK spike and turn every extended trade into a Wuju Style on-hit grind she can't out-sustain. Use Highlander resets to chain a kill once she commits her dash and stun.","enemyWin":"Irelia wins by punishing my weak 1-5 — she Q-resets through the wave for free poke, lands Flawless Duet to catch me the instant I land from Alpha Strike, and Defiant Dance eats my Q burst while healing. If she gets a lead before my first item she out-tempos me and shoves me under tower.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Irelia","rating":"6/10","why":"She can Q a low minion to reset and poke me with the dash damage while I have only short-range Wuju autos and no way to trade back at melee range level 1."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Irelia","rating":"6/10","why":"Her Ionian Fervor stacks ramp her attack speed fast, and with E charged she threatens a stun the moment I step up to last-hit, so I farm with Alpha Strike from a distance instead."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"My Wuju Style true damage comes online for a quick burst trade, but her Defiant Dance can soak it — whoever uses their cooldown first loses, so it's a standoff."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Meditate sustain lets me heal her Q-reset poke back to even, while her W heals her chunk back too — neither of us can build a lead through pure trades here."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Irelia","rating":"5/10","why":"Both of us spike at 6, but her Vanguard's Edge wall plus E-stun is a cleaner all-in than my Highlander, which only buys move/attack speed without burst or lockdown."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King turns my on-hit autos into sustained DPS that out-grinds her — if I dodge her E with Alpha Strike, the extended fight is mine."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"At two items my Wuju true damage plus on-hit shred out-DPS her resists, and Highlander resets let me chain through her after she blows Q-reset and stun on the first target."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Irelia. She uses Bladesurge to reset off low minions, dealing me chip damage I can't answer while I'm stuck with short-range Wuju autos and no burst. I have no safe step-up: if I walk to last-hit she charges Flawless Duet and threatens a stun, so I concede aggression and farm with Alpha Strike blinks from max range, taking the CS hit rather than the trade.","mid":"Levels 4-5 stabilize as Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain let me heal her poke back to even and threaten a short burst trade of my own — but her Defiant Dance can absorb that burst, so trades become a cooldown standoff. At 6 she gets the cleaner all-in: Vanguard's Edge to wall me in plus E-stun beats my Highlander, which only gives stats. I respect her 6 and don't fight without my jungler or my first item.","late":"At 2+ items the lane flips to me. Kraken/BORK plus Wuju Style means my on-hit DPS out-grinds her resists in any extended fight, and as long as I save Alpha Strike to dodge her E-stun, she can't lock me down long enough to burst me. Highlander resets let me chain through her once she's blown Q-reset and stun, and anti-heal shuts her Defiant Dance healing.","wave":"Best wave: a slow-push stack I freeze just outside tower so I farm with Alpha Strike untouched and deny her reset poke. Worst wave: a shoved wave under her tower early where her Q-resets through minions catch me for free and I can't disengage. Crash timing: crash the wave into her tower right as my first item completes so I can recall, spike, and return to a fresh lane on even CS.","cooldowns":"Track her E — Flawless Duet (the second blade stun). It's the only tool that locks me down after I land from Alpha Strike; if it's on cooldown, my all-in window is open. Also watch Defiant Dance (W) before dumping Q burst into her.","trading":"Short trades only until first item: step in with Wuju Style autos, eat one Q-reset, and walk before she charges E. Never extend into a fight where she can land both E blades. Post-item, I want the long fight — bait her E, dodge it with Alpha Strike, then auto her down through Highlander resets.","spikes":"Hers: level 6 (Vanguard's Edge + E all-in) and her first item once Ionian Fervor is maxed. Mine: level 6 Highlander for gank-dodging, then the real spike at Kraken/BORK first item where my on-hit DPS overtakes her, snowballing at 2+ items.","feeding":"If I fall behind, her Q-resets shove me under tower and she roams or freezes me out of farm. A fed Irelia with Trinity/Sundered Sky out-sustains and out-tempos my under-itemized on-hit, and her E-stun deletes me before Meditate matters. I lose the duelist race and the side lane.","carry":"If I'm ahead I become a 1v9 split-pusher: my on-hit shreds towers and any duelist who contests me, and Highlander's move speed plus resets let me chain kills across the map. I take side lane, force her to answer me, and let Alpha Strike dodge any collapse CC.","difficulty":"It's a true 5/10 EVEN because we're mirror-image duelists with opposite curves — she owns the early skirmish and I own the itemized fight. The skill expression is entirely in dodging her E with Q and surviving to my spike; misplay either and the 50% swings hard."},"focus":{"text":"Flawless Duet — her E. The two-blade stun is the hard CC that catches me the instant I land from Alpha Strike, since Q is my only escape. Save Q to dodge the blades or to break the stun setup; if her E is down, I can all-in freely.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike","d":"Levels 1-5, blink to her minions with Q to last-hit from range instead of walking into her E-stun threat. Conceding CS tempo beats eating her Q-reset poke at melee."},{"t":"Save Q for her E","d":"Alpha Strike's untargetable frames dodge Flawless Duet's blades. Bait her to charge E, then Q through it — a whiffed stun is a free all-in window for me."},{"t":"Buy anti-heal","d":"Bramble Vest or Executioner's Calling shuts down Defiant Dance and Sundered Sky healing, which is the only thing that lets her survive my extended on-hit DPS post-item."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't trade pre-6","d":"My early autos lose to her Q-reset tempo and ramped Ionian Fervor attack speed. Don't step up for a trade I can't win — farm and scale instead."},{"t":"Don't dump Q into her W","d":"Defiant Dance reduces and stores the damage you feed it, then heals her. Never burn Alpha Strike's burst while her W channel is active."},{"t":"Don't all-in into her E","d":"If Flawless Duet is up and I have no Q, her E-stun catches me out of every action and she resets through me. Wait for her E cooldown before committing Highlander."}],"tradeGood":"Post-first-item, bait her Flawless Duet, dodge both blades with Alpha Strike, then grind her down with Wuju Style on-hit autos through Highlander resets.","tradeBad":"A level 1-5 extended melee trade where I dump Q into her Defiant Dance and then eat a full Q-reset-into-E-stun with no escape up.","ahead":"Once I've got a kill or my first item lead, I take side lane and force her to duel me on my terms — my on-hit out-grinds her resists, so she either dies or gives up the wave. I use Highlander's move speed to dodge jungle collapses and chain resets across the map, and I keep anti-heal up so her Defiant Dance can't bail her out of a lost fight. Press the CS and plate lead into a tower so I out-scale her into the 2+ item window where I'm dominant.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Irelia - Track: Flawless Duet — her E. The two-blade stun is the hard CC that catches me the instant I land from Alpha Strike, since Q is my only escape. Save Q to dodge the blades or to break the stun setup; if her E is down, I can all-in freely.. - Farm safely behind Alpha Strike through levels 1-5, dodge her E-stun and Defiant Dance with Q's untargetable window, then hit my Kraken/BORK spike and turn every extended trade into a Wuju Style on-hit grind she can't out-sustain. Use Highlander resets to chain a kill once she commits her dash and stun.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A duelist mirror that comes down to itemization: I lose the early skirmishes to her Q-resets and E-stun, but once my on-hit spike lands the extended fight becomes mine — survive to first item and it's a coinflip I can carry."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive Irelia's level 1-5 skirmish dominance by farming with Alpha Strike and conceding aggression, then hit my Kraken/BORK on-hit spike and convert every extended fight with Wuju Style true damage. The lane is won by dodging her E-stun with Q and out-sustaining her into the itemized phase where my DPS and Highlander resets take over."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Irelia owns 1-2 (Q-reset poke), it's even 3-5 (Wuju + Meditate vs her W), she edges 6 (cleaner all-in), and I flip it at first item and dominate at 2+."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Pre-6: short Wuju-auto pokes only, walk before she charges E, never extend. Post-item: take the long fight, but only after baiting or confirming her E is down. Always keep Q in reserve to dodge Flawless Duet."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Freeze or slow-push just outside my tower early so her Q-resets can't reach me and I farm with Alpha Strike untouched. Crash the wave into her tower as my first item completes to recall, spike, and reset the lane even."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable frames dodge her Flawless Duet blades and her Bladesurge engage. Her Defiant Dance eats Q's burst and heals — never feed it. Wuju Style's true damage ignores the armor her passive and items give her. Highlander resets chain kills once she's used Q-reset and E."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (ramping attack speed and bonus range suits the on-hit grind and helps the long fight) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, and Coup de Grace; secondary Resolve with Conditioning/Overgrowth, or Bone Plating vs her early Q-reset poke. Take attack-speed shard, adaptive, and HP."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite to threaten the post-item all-in and cut her Defiant Dance healing for the kill; take Teleport instead if you want to play the scaling/side-lane game and stay safe through her strong early."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit spike, then Wit's End or Terminus into her mixed/AD profile. Build Bramble Vest/Executioner's anti-heal core against her W and Sundered Sky healing. Berserker's Greaves; Ninja Tabi if she's full-AD on-hit."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Only when her E (Flawless Duet) is on cooldown and I have Alpha Strike up — that's when she can't lock me down. Post-first-item with Highlander available, bait her dash-in, dodge with Q, and commit."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"My Highlander makes me hard to gank if I save Q for the dive, but pre-6 I'm gankable and her E-stun sets up easy ganks for her jungler. I want my jungler topside early to cover the weak window; a successful 2v2 post-6 snowballs me toward my spike."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players step up to last-hit at melee pre-6 and eat her E-stun-into-Q-reset, or they dump Alpha Strike into her Defiant Dance and lose the burst for nothing. Both throw the even lane to her early."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Farm with Alpha Strike under tower, take Teleport value, and scale — even a behind Yi snaps back at two items if you dodge her E. Don't contest waves you can't safely reach; group only when your on-hit comes online."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Take side lane, force her to duel me where my on-hit out-grinds her, and use Highlander's move speed plus resets to roam and chain kills. Keep anti-heal up and press towers — at 2+ items I out-DPS her and any single defender."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A genuine 50/50 duelist race: she owns the early, I own the itemized fight — dodge her E-stun, survive to first item, and the carry potential is mine."}]},"jax":{"tldr":"Jax dodges your whole on-hit kit with Counter Strike and stuns you out of every all-in, so you farm scared, dodge his E, and pray to out-scale at 2+ items.","winCon":"Survive a miserable early lane by farming with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, never trading into his E, and reach Kraken/BORK two items where your on-hit DPS plus Highlander resets can finally out-sustain and out-duel him in an extended fight. Pick up a kill through a jungle gank or by punishing his E whiff, then snowball before his Trinity/Steraks online makes the 1v1 unwinnable.","enemyWin":"Jax pops Counter Strike the instant you commit Alpha Strike or auto into him, eats your on-hit damage for free, then stuns and Q-W bursts you while you have no escape off cooldown. He just has to trade on his E timer and shove you out of XP range every wave; his Trinity Force/Steraks spike comes faster and harder than your first item, so he owns the entire lane until you have two completed items.","diff":"HARD","tone":"#ff5d6c","diffRating":"8/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Jax","rating":"6/10","why":"Jax has more base damage and a longer effective threat with Q gap-close, while your Alpha Strike at level 1 is a farm tool that resets into nothing if he simply walks at you."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Jax","rating":"7/10","why":"With Q plus W he can leap and burst you, and your only counterplay is Alpha Strike untargetability — but you have no follow-up damage to win the trade he forces."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Jax","rating":"7/10","why":"At level 3 his E Counter Strike comes online and hard-counters your autos: he dodges your on-hit hits and stuns you mid-Alpha-Strike-reset for a free trade."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Jax","rating":"6/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain stabilize your short trades, but Jax still wins any extended exchange by timing E to negate your auto windows."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Jax","rating":"6/10","why":"Both hit 6: Highlander lets you survive ganks and chase, but Jax's R grants huge bonus resists and on-hit magic damage that out-trades your unitemized DPS."},{"label":"First item","side":"Jax","rating":"7/10","why":"Jax's Trinity Force/Sheen spike lands before your Kraken or BORK completes, so his first-item all-in with E up still beats your first-item on-hit window."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Once Kraken plus BORK/Wit's End are online, your on-hit shred plus Highlander resets out-DPS him through an extended fight as long as you bait or wait out Counter Strike."}],"breakdown":{"early":"You are flatly behind levels 1-3. Jax has the gap-close (Q), the burst (W), and from level 3 the E Counter Strike that dodges your autos and stuns you mid-Alpha-Strike — the single worst thing that can happen to an on-hit champ. Do not contest the wave; use Alpha Strike on the caster minions to farm safely and only auto Jax when his E is on cooldown.","mid":"Levels 4-6 your Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain give you short trade windows, but Jax still owns the all-in because his E negates your auto-based damage on demand. Level 6 Highlander is for surviving ganks and dodging his commit, not for fighting him straight up — his R out-resists your unitemized on-hit damage.","late":"At 2+ items (Kraken + BORK/Wit's End/Terminus) the lane flips: your on-hit shred plus Highlander cooldown resets let you out-DPS and out-sustain him in a long fight. The catch is Counter Strike — bait it or wait it out, because an extended fight where his E is down is the only fight you win, and it's a fight you now win hard.","wave":"Best wave: a slow-push you can freeze just outside your tower so you out-farm safely and deny him all-in angles. Worst wave: a pushed wave that lets Jax Q onto you and trade with E up while you're exposed to his jungler. Crash timing: crash into his tower right before your item completes or before a known jungle path, then reset and return with a power spike to force the fight on your terms.","cooldowns":"Track Counter Strike (E) above all — it is the entire matchup. Never throw autos or commit Alpha Strike into an active or available E; only trade in the ~8-10s window after he uses it.","trading":"Short trade only when his E is down: walk up, land a Double Strike-empowered auto with Wuju Style active, then disengage before he can Q-reposition. Never start a trade you can't finish before his next Counter Strike.","spikes":"Jax spikes hardest at level 3 (E online), level 6 (R resists), and first item (Sheen/Trinity). Your only real spike is 2 completed on-hit items — everything before that is damage control.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Jax becomes an unkillable split-pusher who out-duels you 1v1 forever and uses Counter Strike to dodge your all-in even when you're itemized. Don't keep walking into the same E — farm side waves, ask for jungle help, and scale toward teamfights instead.","carry":"If you get ahead, you become a hyper-carry: Alpha Strike dodges his CC, your on-hit shreds his resists despite R, and Highlander resets chain you through the rest of the map. Group and force fights where his E only blanks one target's worth of your damage.","difficulty":"It's an 8/10 because Jax has a built-in answer to your exact win condition — Counter Strike negates auto-attack damage, which is all you do — plus the gap-close, the stun, and the faster item spike. You're behind from level 3 until you have two items."},"focus":{"text":"Counter Strike (E) — it dodges every auto-attack your entire kit is built on and stuns you out of Alpha Strike; only ever trade or all-in when it's on cooldown.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Bait or wait out his E","d":"Counter Strike negates all your auto damage and stuns you — only commit Alpha Strike or autos in the window after he's used or wasted it. This single rule decides the lane."},{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike early","d":"You lose levels 1-5 outright, so use Q on the wave to last-hit safely from range and concede aggression rather than feeding him a kill into his Trinity spike."},{"t":"Scale to two items","d":"Your win condition is Kraken plus BORK/Wit's End — keep CS even, take Doran's stacks for sustain, and don't risk dying before the lane flips at 2+ items."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't Alpha Strike into his E","d":"If you blink in while Counter Strike is up he dodges your hits and stuns you with no escape off cooldown — it's a free kill for him every time."},{"t":"Don't take extended trades pre-item","d":"Any long exchange before two items lets him E-negate your DPS and out-burst you with Q-W; only short-trade on his E cooldown."},{"t":"Don't push the wave","d":"Shoving lets Jax Q onto you and exposes you to ganks — and you can't escape a gank pre-6 without burning Alpha Strike, which leaves you defenseless to his stun."}],"tradeGood":"Walk up with Wuju Style active right after his Counter Strike goes on cooldown, land a Double Strike auto, and step out before he can Q-reposition.","tradeBad":"Alpha Strike into him while his E is up — he dodges all the on-hit damage and stuns you with no second escape, turning your engage into his free kill.","ahead":"If you steal a kill off a gank or an E whiff, snowball it immediately — buy your on-hit spike early and start forcing short trades on his E cooldown to deny his farm and item timings. Once you're itemized, Alpha Strike dodges his stun and your on-hit shred beats his R resists, so look to all-in any time his Counter Strike is down. Roam with Highlander's move speed to feed off other lanes and convert the lead before his Trinity/Steraks scaling catches up.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Jax - Track: Counter Strike (E) — it dodges every auto-attack your entire kit is built on and stuns you out of Alpha Strike; only ever trade or all-in when it's on cooldown.. - Survive a miserable early lane by farming with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, never trading into his E, and reach Kraken/BORK two items where your on-hit DPS plus Highlander resets can finally out-sustain and out-duel him in an extended fight. Pick up a kill through a jungle gank or by punishing his E whiff, then snowball before his Trinity/Steraks online makes the 1v1 unwinnable.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Jax dodges your whole on-hit kit with Counter Strike and stuns you out of every all-in, so you farm scared, dodge his E, and pray to out-scale at 2+ items."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing lane levels 1-6 by farming with Alpha Strike and never trading into Counter Strike, then reach two on-hit items where your DPS plus Highlander resets out-duel him in extended fights. The whole game is staying even in CS and gold until that 2-item window flips the matchup in your favor."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Jax owns levels 1 through first item (E at 3, R at 6, Trinity spike all in his favor); the lane only swings to you at 2+ completed on-hit items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade ONLY when Counter Strike is on cooldown — short auto with Wuju Style up, then leave. Back off completely whenever his E is available or his jungler is unknown."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave neutral or slow-pushed toward your side so you can freeze and out-farm safely; avoid shoving, which hands Jax Q-engage angles and gank setups. Crash only to reset into a power spike."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Counter Strike dodges your autos and Alpha Strike on-hits and stuns you — it hard-counters your kit; conversely Alpha Strike's untargetability can dodge his stun if you time the blink into his E cast, and Wuju Style true damage ignores the bonus armor his R provides."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the early attack-speed ramp into a frontloaded enemy, Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve with Second Wind and Overgrowth (or Bone Plating) to survive his level-3-to-6 trade pressure — take Second Wind specifically to heal through his poke."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Teleport — this is a survive-and-scale lane, so TP keeps you on XP after a forced back and gives map presence; Ignite is too greedy when you can't win the early all-in anyway."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer into Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit shred that beats his R resists, then Wit's End or Terminus since his R adds magic damage and you want MR; Plated Steelcaps vs his auto-and-Sheen AD, and a defensive third (Death's Dance/Steraks) if you're behind."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Only all-in after his Counter Strike is down AND you have at least one completed on-hit item — ideally two; pre-item, you have no all-in, just disengage."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're extremely gank-reliant here — a single early gank can buy you the kill that saves the lane, but you're also very gankable since Alpha Strike is your only escape; ward his jungle entrances and don't push into a missing enemy jungler."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players auto or Alpha Strike into an up Counter Strike and get dodged-and-stunned for a free death, or they try to fight Jax straight up before two items instead of accepting the scaling lane and farming."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Stop walking into his E — farm side waves with Alpha Strike, take what XP you can under tower, group with your team, and look for teamfights where his E only blanks one target instead of dueling him 1v1."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"With a lead, buy your on-hit spike early, all-in on every E cooldown, and use Highlander resets and move speed to roam and snowball other lanes before his Trinity/Steraks scaling stabilizes the 1v1."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"HARD 8/10 — Jax's Counter Strike is a built-in answer to your auto-reliant kit and he out-spikes you to two items; concede the early lane, dodge his E religiously, and scale to flip it at 2+ on-hit items."}]},"jayce":{"tldr":"A miserable early lane I just have to survive — Jayce pokes me off the wave with gate-Shock-Blast every CS, but once I hit Kraken/BORK I out-DPS his squishy frame and Alpha Strike erases his all-in.","winCon":"Concede levels 1-5: last-hit with Alpha Strike from max range, eat the chip, and never walk up for a \"fair\" trade. Reach my first on-hit item with even-ish CS, then use Highlander + Q to close the gap his combo can't kite anymore and out-sustain his poke with Meditate when I back off.","enemyWin":"Jayce wins by keeping me at hammer-then-cannon range forever — Acceleration Gate + Shock Blast and the Thundering Blow (E) knockback poke me below half every wave so I can't ever step up, then his Q-E-Q burst combo deletes me the moment I commit, all before I'm itemized.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"9/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Jayce","rating":"7/10","why":"Jayce opens Cannon-Q Shock Blast at range and chips me while I have only short autos and no way to answer — I just soak it and farm."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Jayce","rating":"7/10","why":"At 2 he can Acceleration-Gate his Shock Blast for the full-range accelerated orb, poking me every time I move up to last-hit."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Jayce","rating":"6/10","why":"His level-3 Q-E-Q (gate-Blast into Thundering Blow knockback into a second Blast) is a real burst combo I can't trade back into without Wuju Style true damage yet."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"My Wuju Style (E) true damage and Meditate (W) sustain come online so I survive his poke and punish him if he wastes Thundering Blow, but he still out-ranges me."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Highlander (R) gives me the move/attack speed and slow-immunity to finally close range, but his Q-E-Q burst still answers a naked commit, so it's a coin-flip on who used cooldowns first."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King flips extended fights — Alpha Strike dodges his Thundering Blow knockback and I out-DPS his zero-armor frame before he can re-poke."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At 2+ on-hit items I run him down with Highlander, untargetable-Q over his gate, and shred him in one rotation that resets R on the kill — he has no defensive layer to survive me."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are Jayce's lane, full stop — he sits at cannon range and his Acceleration-Gate Shock Blast hits me for free every time I walk up to CS, and I have nothing but short-range autos and an Alpha Strike that I'd rather save for last-hitting safely than for a trade. Do not contest. Farm whatever I can with Q from max range, take the poke, and ward for the gank he'll set up while I'm low.","mid":"Levels 4-6 I stabilize: Wuju Style (E) gives my autos true damage for real short trades, and Meditate (W) lets me heal off the poke between waves so his chip stops translating into a kill. At 6 Highlander gives me the speed and slow-immunity to close on him IF he's burned his Thundering Blow (E) knockback or his combo is down — but a naked all-in into a full Jayce rotation still loses, so I pick my window.","late":"At 2+ items the lane inverts hard. With Kraken/BORK plus Wit's End or Terminus my on-hit DPS out-races his burst, Alpha Strike makes me untargetable through his knockback, and Highlander resets on the kill so I chain into the rest of the map. He has zero defensive stats — once I'm on him in an extended fight he is dead.","wave":"Best wave: a slow-push that builds a big wave I can crash at 6, freezing him under tower so he can't poke me from range and I can all-in with Highlander up. Worst wave: a wave shoved into his tower early levels 1-3, where he zones me off CS with gate-Blast and I take free poke walking up. Crash timing: crash the wave right as Highlander (lvl 6) and my first on-hit item come online so I get a long recall, hit my power spike, and deny him the poke window between waves.","cooldowns":"Track his E, Thundering Blow — the knockback both interrupts my Alpha Strike approach and sets up his Q3 burst; if he uses it to push or to disengage, that's my window to commit.","trading":"Pre-6 I never initiate; I only punish a whiffed Shock Blast or a Thundering Blow used on the wave. Post-item I wait for his combo (Q-E-Q) to go on cooldown, then Alpha Strike in with Wuju Style active and force the extended fight he can't kite.","spikes":"Jayce spikes earliest: level 2-3 with Acceleration Gate online, and again at his first item (Eclipse) for poke amp. My spikes are later and bigger: level 6 Highlander, then first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK), then a hard 2-item flip to favoured-dominant.","feeding":"If I die early I'm a free poke target and a juicy gank — Jayce roams and shoves with gate-Blast while I'm too weak to contest. Falling behind here delays my item spike, which is the only thing that wins me the lane, so a bad early snowballs into total irrelevance until I farm back.","carry":"If I'm even or ahead at 2 items I'm one of the scariest duelists in the game — Highlander resets chain me through teamfights, Alpha Strike dodges priority CC, and Wuju Style true damage shreds squishies like Jayce regardless of armor. I take over side lane and skirmishes.","difficulty":"It's a 5/10 because the win rate is genuinely even: a brutal, must-respect early lane against one of the best melee-poke kits in the game, offset by one of the streakiest scaling curves — if I farm to items without dying, I simply out-scale him."},"focus":{"text":"Jayce's E, Thundering Blow — the knockback interrupts my Alpha Strike engage and is the trigger for his Q-E-Q burst combo; bait it out or only commit once it's down.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike from range","d":"Use Q to last-hit and pull back so I eat minimal poke walking into cannon-Q range; my whole early game is just surviving to items, not trading."},{"t":"Save Meditate for between waves","d":"Channel W out of his Shock Blast line to heal off his poke so his chip never adds up to a kill or a gankable health bar."},{"t":"Commit only after his combo is down","d":"Wait for his Thundering Blow (E) and Q-E-Q to go on cooldown, then Alpha Strike in with Wuju Style active — that's the only all-in that wins."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't walk up to CS into a charged gate-Q","d":"His Acceleration Gate + Shock Blast hits the full accelerated orb at range — sidestep the line or take it on minions, never your face."},{"t":"Don't Alpha Strike into his E knockback","d":"If he holds Thundering Blow, my untargetable blink ends and he knocks me back into a free Q3 burst; bait the E first."},{"t":"Don't force a fight before your first item","d":"Pre-Kraken/BORK I lose every fair trade to his burst — chasing a kill early just feeds his lead and his roams."}],"tradeGood":"Post-item, after he whiffs or spends Thundering Blow, Alpha Strike onto him with Wuju Style active and force an extended on-hit fight his squishy no-armor frame can't survive.","tradeBad":"Walking up to last-hit into a charged Acceleration-Gate Shock Blast at levels 1-3 and eating the full Q-E-Q burst for a single minion.","ahead":"Once I'm even or ahead I press with the side lane: shove the wave, force him to either give up CS to my range or get all-in'd with Highlander up. Use the R reset on a pick to immediately threaten his tower or rotate for a skirmish — my snowball is so steep that a single kill at 2 items lets me solo-carry the map while he can only poke from a fading lead.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Jayce - Track: Jayce's E, Thundering Blow — the knockback interrupts my Alpha Strike engage and is the trigger for his Q-E-Q burst combo; bait it out or only commit once it's down.. - Concede levels 1-5: last-hit with Alpha Strike from max range, eat the chip, and never walk up for a \"fair\" trade. Reach my first on-hit item with even-ish CS, then use Highlander + Q to close the gap his combo can't kite anymore and out-sustain his poke with Meditate when I back off.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A miserable early lane I just have to survive — Jayce pokes me off the wave with gate-Shock-Blast every CS, but once I hit Kraken/BORK I out-DPS his squishy frame and Alpha Strike erases his all-in."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Master Yi wins this lane by refusing the early game and farming to his on-hit item spike alive and roughly even on CS. Once Kraken/BORK comes online, Alpha Strike's untargetability beats Jayce's burst and on-hit DPS shreds his defenseless frame in any extended fight."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Jayce owns levels 1-3 hard, it's a skill coin-flip at 4-6, and Master Yi takes over decisively from first item onward — a classic streaky inversion that nets out EVEN."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Never initiate pre-6; only punish a whiffed Shock Blast or a Thundering Blow spent on the wave. Post-item, trade only after his Q-E-Q combo is on cooldown — then commit fully with Wuju Style up."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Don't shove into his tower early or you just hand him a free poke zone; aim to slow-push and crash a big wave at 6 / first item so you get the all-in window and a clean recall on your spike."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike (Q) goes untargetable through his Shock Blast and over his Acceleration Gate; Wuju Style (E) true damage ignores any armor he buys and shreds his squishy build; Meditate (W) out-sustains his lane poke; Highlander (R) slow-immunity beats his disengage and the kill-reset chains fights. His Thundering Blow (E) knockback is the one thing that interrupts my engage — respect it."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (faster on-hit stacking vs his pure-AD poke; Conqueror is fine into the harder-trade version) with Triumph and Legend: Alacrity, second tree Resolve (Conditioning/Second Wind to blunt his poke) or Precision Coup de Grace; Second Wind is the single best rune into Jayce's chip."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to convert my 2-item dominance into kills (and to counter his sustain-less, defenseless frame); take Teleport instead if you want to guarantee you farm back from a rough early and stay relevant."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King, then Wit's End (MR is wasted here since he's AD, so skip it — go Terminus for the armor-shred/MR self-buff against an AD bruiser-mage instead) and Berserker's Greaves; consider a defensive third like Death's Dance / Steraks since all his damage is physical and bursty."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Real all-ins start at level 6 with Highlander up AND his Thundering Blow (E) on cooldown, and become reliable at first item where Alpha Strike dodges his burst and out-DPS finishes him before he can re-poke."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"I'm extremely gankable early — Jayce sets up the dive by poking me low and shoving with gate-Blast, so I ward his fog and play for my own jungler to punish his over-extends; a single early gank in my favor flips the whole lane because of how hard I snowball."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi mistake here is trying to 'win' the early lane and walking into the gate-Q poke or all-inning pre-item — you almost always lose that, feed his roams, and delete your only win condition (scaling to items)."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If I'm behind, I freeze near my tower, farm with Alpha Strike, take Teleport value, and play purely for my item timings — Yi's curve is so steep that even a rough lane recovers the moment I hit 2 items, so just don't die again."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Ahead, I use Highlander resets to chain a lane kill into a tower or a roam, take over the side lane where his lack of defenses means he can never duel me, and force the map with Alpha Strike picks before his team has frontline."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"EVEN (51.83%) — a punishing early lane against elite melee-poke that I survive into a brutal scaling flip; respect levels 1-5, then take over from first item."}]},"karma":{"tldr":"Karma can chip me with Q poke early, but she has no hard lockdown to punish Alpha Strike, so once my on-hit items come online I run her down and she has nothing to stop it.","winCon":"Eat the early Q poke, farm safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, and survive to my first on-hit item (Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King). From there I use Alpha Strike to blink onto her through her RQ root and out-DPS her squishy enchanter body before her shield and slows matter.","enemyWin":"Karma wins by zoning me off the wave with Q poke and Mantra-empowered Q burst, keeping me out of range while she perma-shields and speeds herself away, so I arrive at my item spike at half health and behind on farm. If she lands RQ root the instant I'm out of Alpha Strike, her jungler collapses and I die before I can scale.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"4/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Karma","rating":"6/10","why":"Karma's Q out-ranges my autos and chunks me while I have nothing but Alpha Strike to close, so I just soak XP and concede the first wave."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Karma","rating":"6/10","why":"At 2 she has Q+E, shielding and speeding out of any Alpha Strike I throw while poking me down, so I can't commit yet."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"With Wuju Style up my Alpha Strike-into-Wuju autos finally trade back, but her Q poke keeps it even before I have sustain online."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Meditate out-sustains her Q poke and Wuju true damage lets me win short all-ins if she steps up to last-hit in my range."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander gives me the move speed and slow immunity to ignore her E shield-speed and run her down, plus it resets if I get the kill."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken/BORK on-hit DPS shreds her squishy enchanter body, and Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges her RQ root mid-blink so she can't peel me."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"With two items my extended-fight DPS plus Highlander resets erase her in a single Alpha Strike combo before her shields and slows can save her."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are Karma's. Her Q out-ranges everything I have and she'll poke me every time I walk up to last-hit, while my only gap-closer is Alpha Strike on a long early cooldown. Don't trade — farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, give up the first couple of CS if you must, and protect your health bar for the scaling fight to come.","mid":"Levels 4-6 stabilize the lane. Wuju Style's true damage and Meditate's sustain let me answer her poke and win short trades if she over-extends to farm. Level 6 Highlander is my first real spike — the move speed and slow immunity let me ignore her E shield-speed and stick to her, and a kill resets it to chain pressure.","late":"At 2+ items I flip the lane hard. Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King on-hit DPS melts her squishy enchanter body, and Alpha Strike's untargetability lets me dodge her RQ root and any incoming CC mid-combo. She has no way to peel a fed Yi — shields get out-DPS'd and her slows don't matter through Highlander.","wave":"Best wave: a wave pushing toward me so I farm under tower out of her Q range and deny her any pressure. Worst wave: a wave I'm shoved under her tower where she free-pokes me and her jungler can collapse on me with no escape. Crash timing: crash the wave just before my item spike completes so I can recall, buy, and return to a fresh wave with my power online.","cooldowns":"Track her Mantra (R) charge — Mantra-Q is the empowered poke/burst that actually hurts, and RQ root is the only thing that can pin me out of Alpha Strike. Bait or wait out her R before committing.","trading":"My trade pattern is patience then commitment: never auto-trade her Q poke early, just farm. Once I have Wuju Style and an item, I Alpha Strike in on a low-cooldown reset target, pop Wuju true damage, and force the extended fight where my DPS beats her shields — exactly the fight she can't survive.","spikes":"Her spikes are level 6 Mantra and any AP item that boosts her Q. My spikes are level 6 Highlander and especially my first on-hit item — that's the inflection point where the lane swings from hers to mine, and 2 items make me dominant.","feeding":"If I fall behind, her poke compounds and I get permanently zoned off CS, arriving at my item spike too late while she roams to help her team with shields and speed. A behind Yi who can't reach his items is dead weight, so I farm side lanes safely and wait for one isolated pick.","carry":"If I'm ahead, I'm a 1v9 — Alpha Strike dodges CC, Highlander chains resets through fights, and my on-hit DPS deletes her whole squishy backline, not just her. Use my lead to dive her in lane and then group to out-DPS every teamfight.","difficulty":"It's only a 4/10 because the early poke is annoying but not lethal — she has no hard CC to actually punish my Alpha Strike, no burst to one-shot me, and her enchanter body folds the moment I'm itemized. The whole difficulty is just surviving lane to scale."},"focus":{"text":"Her Mantra-empowered RQ root — it's the one ability that can pin me down out of Alpha Strike for her jungler or her own follow-up. Bait it or save Alpha Strike to break the tether, and the rest of her kit can't stop me.","letters":["R","Q"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm safe, scale up","d":"Concede the early lane and soak XP/CS with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos. Your whole win condition is reaching your first on-hit item with health to spare."},{"t":"Save Alpha Strike for her root","d":"Alpha Strike makes you untargetable mid-blink — time it to dodge her RQ root or any jungler CC, then commit. It's your only escape, so don't waste it pushing the wave when she has Mantra up."},{"t":"All-in after your item","d":"Once Kraken or BORK is online, force the extended fight. Alpha Strike in, Wuju true damage on, and out-DPS her shields before she can peel — she can't survive a fed Yi."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't trade autos early","d":"Walking up to auto her levels 1-3 just eats free Q poke and accomplishes nothing — your damage isn't online yet and you have no sustain to justify the trade."},{"t":"Don't Alpha Strike into her wave with R up","d":"Blinking in while she has Mantra means she RQ-roots you the second you're targetable again and her jungler collapses. Only commit when her root is on cooldown or baited."},{"t":"Don't dive her under tower behind","d":"If you're behind, her shields and self-peel plus tower turn a dive into a death. Farm side lanes and wait until your items let you delete her in one combo."}],"tradeGood":"After my first on-hit item, Alpha Strike onto her, pop Wuju Style true damage, and out-DPS her shield in an extended fight she can't kite out of with Highlander running.","tradeBad":"Walking up to auto-trade her levels 1-3 — I eat free Q poke with no sustain and no item DPS, doing nothing but feeding her lane lead.","ahead":"Once I'm ahead, Karma has zero tools to stop me — her shields get out-DPS'd, her slows are nullified by Highlander, and Alpha Strike dodges her root. Use the lead to dive her off the wave and deny her items, then snowball cross-map: my on-hit DPS plus CC-immune Alpha Strike lets me dive any squishy on her team. Reset Highlander on every kill to chain pick after pick.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Karma - Track: Her Mantra-empowered RQ root — it's the one ability that can pin me down out of Alpha Strike for her jungler or her own follow-up. Bait it or save Alpha Strike to break the tether, and the rest of her kit can't stop me.. - Eat the early Q poke, farm safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, and survive to my first on-hit item (Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King). From there I use Alpha Strike to blink onto her through her RQ root and out-DPS her squishy enchanter body before her shield and slows matter.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Karma can chip me with Q poke early, but she has no hard lockdown to punish Alpha Strike, so once my on-hit items come online I run her down and she has nothing to stop it."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"My win condition is surviving Karma's early Q poke to reach my first on-hit item, then forcing the extended fight where my DPS shreds her squishy enchanter body. Alpha Strike's untargetability neutralizes her only real answer — RQ root — so once I'm itemized she has nothing to peel me with."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Karma owns levels 1-2 with superior Q range and no commitment risk; the lane evens out at 3-5 as Wuju Style and Meditate come online, then flips firmly to me at level 6 Highlander and especially at my first on-hit item, becoming a stomp at 2 items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Never auto-trade levels 1-3 — just farm and eat the poke. Start trading at 4-5 only when she steps into my range to last-hit and I have Wuju Style up. From my first item onward, commit hard with Alpha Strike whenever her Mantra root is down."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Let the wave settle toward me early so I farm under tower out of her Q range and deny her free poke. Avoid being shoved under her turret where she pokes me freely and her jungler can collapse. Crash before my item spike completes so I recall, buy, and return with power online."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike makes me untargetable while blinking, so it dodges her RQ root and tether on reaction — the single most important interaction in the lane. Wuju Style's true damage ignores any defensive stat and chews through her shields; Meditate out-sustains her Q poke; Highlander's slow immunity ignores her E speed-peel so I stick to her."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the attack-speed ramp that maximizes on-hit DPS in extended fights (Conqueror is fine if you prefer the burst). Secondary Resolve with Conditioning/Overgrowth or Second Wind to laugh off her Q poke, plus the scaling-health and attack-speed shards; her damage is AP so a Magic Resist shard helps the lane."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to convert my scaling lead into kills and cut her shield/Meditate-style sustain healing. If you're worried about getting poked out and want a safer scaling path, Flash + Teleport keeps you even on waves, but Ignite is the higher-ceiling pick into a low-kill-pressure enchanter."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit spike, then Wit's End or Terminus — both add magic resist that directly counters her AP poke while boosting my DPS. Boots: Mercury's Treads or Plated, leaning Mercs for the magic-resist and tenacity vs her root. Add Blade of the Ruined King's % current-health if she ever builds bruisier."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"My real all-in windows open at level 6 with Highlander and become reliable at my first on-hit item. Commit only when her Mantra (R) is down — that's when she has no root to pin me and no empowered burst to trade back."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"This lane lives and dies on jungle pressure: Karma's RQ root is perfect gank setup, so respect her tether when I'm overextended and save Alpha Strike to escape it. On my side, my own jungler can dive her hard since she's squishy with no hard CC to peel for herself — call for a level-3 or 6 gank to snowball."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi mistake here is over-aggressing levels 1-3, walking up to auto-trade and getting chunked by Q for nothing before any damage is online. The second is blinking in with Alpha Strike while her Mantra root is up and getting pinned by her or her jungler."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If I'm behind, stop contesting her and farm side waves safely with Alpha Strike, never diving into her shield-and-tower setup. Wait for one isolated pick or a teamfight where I can flank a squishy — a single reset on Highlander can bring me right back into the game."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If I'm ahead, deny her items by diving her off the wave, then take my CC-immune on-hit threat to the rest of the map. Alpha Strike lets me dodge engage and dive any squishy; chaining Highlander resets through fights closes the game fast before her team can peel."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED, 4/10 difficulty — annoying early poke from an enchanter with no hard lockdown, but Alpha Strike dodges her root and my on-hit scaling deletes her the moment I'm itemized."}]},"kassadin":{"tldr":"Survive Kassadin's pokey-but-meleed early, then once I hit my on-hit spike I run him down through his Q shield before he ever reaches the 2-item scaling that owns me.","winCon":"Farm safe with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos levels 1-3, then from level 6 onward use Highlander and my first on-hit item to perma-pressure Kassadin before he stacks Rod and Catalyst — every kill I get on him is a kill he can't scale into. I want this game ended by the 2-item mark, because after that Riftwalk kites me and his shield eats my burst.","enemyWin":"Kassadin wins by playing for time: his Q magic shield blanks my Wuju on-hit and silences me out of Alpha Strike resets, and once he has Rod/Lich + Riftwalk stacks he R's away every time I commit, then turns and one-shots me in the mid-game. If he survives my early pressure even, the lane is lost on the scaling curve.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"4/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Kassadin","rating":"6/10","why":"At level 1 his Null Sphere Q out-ranges my autos and his passive magic shield soaks my poke, so he last-hits safely while I have no Wuju Style yet to threaten him."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Level 2 is a wash — if I get E or W first I can short-trade, but his Q silence still shuts off my Alpha Strike, so neither of us commits."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"At level 3 with Q, W and a point in Wuju Style I can Alpha Strike in, eat a few true-damage autos and Meditate off his Q poke, out-sustaining his weak melee form."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Levels 4-5 my Wuju Style true damage ignores the armor he can't build and out-trades his auto-attacks while Meditate refunds his Q chunk; he's still pre-Riftwalk and can't disengage."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Level 6 Highlander gives me the move/attack speed and slow-immunity to stick to him for a kill before he has the gold for Catalyst, denying his scaling at its most vulnerable point."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"My first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) spikes my DPS so hard I can burst him through the Q shield and Alpha-Strike-dodge his return Riftwalk to chase the reset."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Kassadin","rating":"7/10","why":"At 2+ items Kassadin flips it: Rod-stacked Riftwalk lets him blink away every time I Alpha Strike in, his shield greatly reduces my burst, and his ult combo deletes me before Meditate can save me."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Kassadin's range — his Null Sphere Q out-pokes my short melee autos and the silence on it cancels my Alpha Strike, so I don't try to fight, I farm. I use Alpha Strike on the caster minions to last-hit safely from his Q, and W Meditate to heal back the chip. I respect that he's harmless to my tower but annoying to my health bar, and I just stack CS until Wuju Style and level 6 arrive.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are where I take over. Wuju Style's bonus true damage out-trades his autos (he can't build armor against it), Meditate sustains through his Q rotations, and at 6 Highlander's speed and slow-immunity lets me stick to him for a real kill while he's still pre-Catalyst and squishy. This is the exact window where killing him matters most — every death delays his scaling.","late":"At 2+ items the matchup inverts. A Riftwalk stacked off Rod of Ages / Lich Bane lets him blink out the instant I Alpha Strike in, his passive magic shield soaks most of my on-hit burst, and his Q-W-R combo can one-shot me before Meditate channels. If the game reaches this stage even, I'm now the underdog and should group/split rather than 1v1 him.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push that crashes into his tower so I deny CS and zone him off the wave under turret. Worst wave: a wave shoved into MY tower early, which hands the safe Kassadin free farm and a free recall to rush Catalyst. Crash timing: crash the wave right before level 6 so I'm on top of him with a full minion advantage the moment Highlander comes up.","cooldowns":"Track Riftwalk (R) cooldown above all — once it's down he has no escape from my Alpha Strike chase; pre-6 track his Null Sphere (Q) since that silence is the only thing that interrupts my engage.","trading":"My trade is: walk up only when his Q is on cooldown, E Wuju Style on, Alpha Strike in for the on-hit + reset, auto twice, and Meditate or back off before his Q comes back up. Never auto-walk into a charged Q.","spikes":"My spikes: level 6 Highlander and my first on-hit item (Kraken/BotRK). His spikes: level 6 Riftwalk, then Catalyst/Rod completion and especially the 2-item mark where his Riftwalk stacking kicks in.","feeding":"If I fall behind, Kassadin's scaling means he snowballs harder than almost anyone — a fed Kassadin is a mid-game 1v9. I freeze near my tower, farm with Alpha Strike from max range, and wait for jungle help rather than forcing a fight I'll lose to his shield-and-blink.","carry":"If I'm ahead I never let him stabilize: I roam with Highlander's speed to feed off other lanes, keep denying his CS, and use my on-hit DPS to take towers and objectives fast, ending before his 2-item scaling spike ever comes online.","difficulty":"It's only 4/10 to play because the lane phase genuinely favors me — I out-sustain and out-trade his weak melee form. The difficulty is entirely the clock: I must convert the early-to-mid lead into a closed game, because his late-game scaling and Riftwalk kite are a hard counter to my reset pattern."},"focus":{"text":"Riftwalk — his stacking blink is the one ability that breaks my Alpha Strike chase-and-reset pattern, so I always all-in when it's on cooldown and respect it when it's up.","letters":["R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Q early","d":"Use Alpha Strike on the minion wave to last-hit from outside his Null Sphere range levels 1-3; concede the poke and just hit your CS and level breakpoints."},{"t":"All-in on Riftwalk cooldown","d":"From level 6, commit your Highlander all-in only when his R is down — he has no other escape, so that's a guaranteed kill window before he scales."},{"t":"Rush your on-hit spike and end","d":"Build Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King fast, snowball the lane, and force the game to close before his 2-item Riftwalk-stacking window arrives."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't walk into a charged Q","d":"Null Sphere silences and shields — if you Alpha Strike into an up Q you get silenced mid-reset and eat free poke; only engage after he's spent it."},{"t":"Don't try to 1v1 him at 2 items","d":"Once Riftwalk is stacked off Rod/Lich he blinks out of every engage and his shield eats your burst — group or split instead of forcing the solo fight."},{"t":"Don't waste Meditate on poke when you could be killing","d":"Pre-6, sustaining through Q is fine, but don't burn your whole W tempo healing chip when the real play is pressuring him off CS and denying his scaling."}],"tradeGood":"Wait out his Null Sphere, then E Wuju Style on and Alpha Strike in for a quick on-hit burst-and-reset, autoing twice before stepping back out of his Q range.","tradeBad":"Auto-walking up while his Q is up, getting silenced out of Alpha Strike and chunked, or chasing him at 2 items into a stacked Riftwalk turnaround.","ahead":"When I'm ahead I treat the clock as my ally turned weapon — I deny every CS I can so his already-slow scaling never catches up, and I use Highlander's movement speed to roam and snowball other lanes between waves. I take towers and the first drakes/heralds with my on-hit DPS to translate the lead into objectives, because a Kassadin who falls behind in farm is harmless for ten more minutes. The goal is always to end the game in the window where I'm strong and before his 2-item spike lets him kite and one-shot.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Kassadin - Track: Riftwalk — his stacking blink is the one ability that breaks my Alpha Strike chase-and-reset pattern, so I always all-in when it's on cooldown and respect it when it's up.. - Farm safe with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos levels 1-3, then from level 6 onward use Highlander and my first on-hit item to perma-pressure Kassadin before he stacks Rod and Catalyst — every kill I get on him is a kill he can't scale into. I want this game ended by the 2-item mark, because after that Riftwalk kites me and his shield eats my burst.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Survive Kassadin's pokey-but-meleed early, then once I hit my on-hit spike I run him down through his Q shield before he ever reaches the 2-item scaling that owns me."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"I win this lane by out-trading and out-sustaining Kassadin's weak melee form from levels 3 through my first item, converting that into kills and CS denial that stall his scaling. The whole plan is to end the game before his 2-item Riftwalk-stacking window, because after that he kites my resets and his shield eats my burst."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Kassadin edges levels 1-2 with Q range, it's even at 2, then favor swings hard to me from level 3 through first item, before flipping back to him at 2+ items as Riftwalk comes online."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only when his Null Sphere is on cooldown — E on, Alpha Strike in, two autos, out; back off entirely when Q is up (silence cancels my engage) and never extend a fight past the point his Riftwalk can disengage and turn."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Slow-push and crash into his tower to deny CS and zone him; avoid shoving into my own tower, which hands the safe Kassadin free farm and recalls. Crash right before 6 so I'm on top of him when Highlander unlocks."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike makes me untargetable to dodge his Q-W-R burst, but his Null Sphere silence interrupts the engage if I mistime it; my Wuju Style true damage ignores armor he can't build, while his passive magic shield specifically soaks my magic-on-hit and his Riftwalk hard-counters my chase-and-reset."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo primary with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Coup de Grace; secondary Resolve (Conditioning/Overgrowth) or Sorcery (Celerity, Gathering Storm) for the scaling fight. Since he's AP, take Magic Resist and a Doran's Blade start to bully his early melee form."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite — this is a lane I want to win early, and Ignite gives me the kill pressure at 6 and cuts any Meditate-style sustain on his side; take Flash to dodge his ult-combo engage."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first for the on-hit spike, then Wit's End is excellent here for the MR and magic on-hit against his AP, into Terminus for resist-shred; Mercury's Treads boots and a Maw/Hexdrinker component vs his burst."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Level 3-5 short trades when his Q is down, level 6 the instant Highlander unlocks and he's pre-Catalyst, and at first item when my DPS bursts him through the shield — always gated on his Riftwalk being on cooldown."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"My ganks are gold here: a Highlander all-in plus a jungler with hard CC kills Kassadin before he has Riftwalk stacks, and every kill denies his scaling. Equally, I'm gankable pre-6 since Alpha Strike is my only out, so I respect a missing enemy jungler."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi mistake is forcing early all-ins levels 1-2 into his Q range and getting silenced and chunked, then tilting; the other is failing to close the game and letting it reach the 2-item stage where Kassadin simply outscales and kites me."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If I'm behind I freeze near tower, farm with max-range Alpha Strike, buy MR early, and refuse the 1v1 — I wait for jungle collapses and scale on my own items rather than feeding his snowball."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If ahead I deny his CS relentlessly, roam with Highlander speed to snowball other lanes, and use on-hit DPS to take towers and early objectives so the game ends inside my strong window."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED (56.79% WR) — a clean lane-phase win for Master Yi that I must cash in before Kassadin's 2-item scaling and Riftwalk kite reclaim the game."}]},"kayle":{"tldr":"A scaling-mirror standoff: you out-DPS Kayle's awkward melee form on your first on-hit item, but every level she draws closer to the ranged-form, R-invuln carry who reclaims the game the moment she hits two items.","winCon":"Win the window between your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) and her second component — punish her short melee range and weak waveclear with Alpha Strike farming plus Wuju trades, then convert any pre-16 lead into towers and cross-map kills before her ranged form and Highlander invuln come online.","enemyWin":"Kayle survives your itemized window by playing safe behind her ranged-form auto-attacks and using R's invulnerability to deny your reset-snowball, then out-scales you at two items where her on-hit ranged DPS and waveclear simply do more from a range you can't close.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Both of you are melee and weak at level 1; neither wants to commit autos with no abilities, so it's a farm standoff she can't punish yet."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"With Wuju Style's bonus true damage you out-trade her stubby melee autos, and Alpha Strike resets your attack timer for an extra hit if she steps up to last-hit."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Pre-6 Kayle has no escape and her melee form does little; your Q + E short trade chunks her before she has any waveclear or range to answer."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Wuju Style and Meditate sustain let you sit on her and bully a champion who is still meleed and itemless, while you deny her the farm she desperately needs."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Your Highlander gives anti-gank mobility, but her level-6 ranged transformation (Form 1) finally lets her auto you from outside Alpha Strike range, neutralizing the bully window."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King spikes your on-hit DPS hard while she's still on one item; this is your last clean all-in window before she scales."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Kayle","rating":"7/10","why":"At two items Kayle's ranged-form on-hit DPS plus R invulnerability resets her in fights you'd otherwise win, and she kites you out of Alpha Strike range to reclaim the game."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are yours but not free — you're both melee, so this is one of the few lanes where you aren't auto-losing the early game. Use Wuju Style's true damage and Alpha Strike's attack-reset to win short trades and deny her CS, because every minion she misses delays the scaling that beats you. Don't over-extend for a kill you can't secure; her whole game plan is to survive to two items.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are your peak relative power: Meditate sustains through her chip, Wuju keeps trades in your favour, and she's still meleed and itemless. The instant she hits 6 and her ranged form unlocks she can auto you from outside Alpha Strike's leap range, so cash your lead into plates and a roam before that range advantage flips the lane.","late":"At 2+ items the lane belongs to Kayle. Her ranged on-hit form out-DPSes you from distance and R's invulnerability negates the exact reset-kill chains Highlander is built around. You stop solo-killing her and must instead group, split push the side she isn't on, and end before her 3-item ranged form takes over the map.","wave":"Best wave: a wave you can shove to deny her CS and zone her off the melee form before 6. Worst wave: a slow-pushing wave that lets her free-farm safely toward two items. Crash timing: crash the big wave just before you recall for your first on-hit item so you don't lose tempo on the spike.","cooldowns":"Track Divine Judgment (R) above all — her invulnerability is the only thing that survives your all-in; note when she ults so you can commit Highlander resets while it's down. Pre-6, watch her E (Starfire Spellblade) for the ranged poke and slow that lets her trade back.","trading":"Walk up with E Wuju Style active, Alpha Strike in for the attack-reset double true-damage hit, auto twice and disengage before her minions aggro — a short burst pattern her melee form can't answer. Avoid extended autoing once she's ranged.","spikes":"Your spikes: level 6 Highlander (anti-gank), and first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) where your DPS peaks vs her. Her spikes: level 6 (ranged form unlock), level 11 (rank 2 R, longer invuln), level 16 (final ranged form), and her two-item mark.","feeding":"If you fall behind, this lane collapses fast — a fed Kayle is exactly the ranged scaler you can't run down. Farm safely with Alpha Strike, rush Wit's End for her magic damage, and pivot to splitpushing a side lane rather than dueling her.","carry":"If ahead, you carry by ending early — take her tower, roam with Highlander's move speed to snowball other lanes and invade her jungler, and deny her sidelane farm so the game closes before her two-item ranged takeover.","difficulty":"It's only a 5/10 because, uniquely for you, the early game is even-to-favoured (she's melee too) instead of a death sentence — but the difficulty lives in discipline: you must convert a real lead in a tight window or the scaling inverts and she out-carries you."},"focus":{"text":"Kayle's R (Divine Judgment) — the few seconds of invulnerability hard-counter your Highlander reset chain; it lets her survive your all-in and turn a fight you were winning, so bait it before you commit your full combo.","letters":["R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Bully the melee form","d":"Levels 1-5 Kayle is a short-range meleer with no waveclear; sit on her with Wuju Style trades and Alpha Strike harass and starve her of the CS she needs to come online."},{"t":"Cash in before 16","d":"Convert every early lead into plates, towers and roams before her level-16 ranged form and her two-item spike; a lead that sits idle evaporates the moment she scales."},{"t":"Bait R before committing","d":"Don't dump your full E + Q + autos while Divine Judgment is up — poke her to force the invuln or wait it out, then all-in so your Highlander resets actually land the kill."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't slow-scale with her","d":"This is a race you lose if it goes even — passive farming hands Kayle the one thing she wants, time, and her two-item ranged form simply out-DPSes you from range."},{"t":"Don't all-in into her invuln","d":"Committing Alpha Strike and Wuju into an active Divine Judgment wastes your damage and your reset window; she walks away full and you're left exposed on cooldown."},{"t":"Don't chase the ranged form","d":"Post-16 chasing Kayle into her kite range pulls you out of Alpha Strike leap distance and onto her team; let her come to a fight on your terms instead."}],"tradeGood":"E Wuju Style on, walk up as she last-hits, Alpha Strike onto her for the attack-reset double-dip of true damage, then back off before minions aggro — a short trade she can't answer in melee form.","tradeBad":"A drawn-out all-in after level 16 or into an up Divine Judgment, where her R invuln eats your burst and her ranged autos out-sustain and out-range your Meditate.","ahead":"Press the lead immediately and spatially: take the tower the moment she has to recall from your early bullying, then use Highlander's move speed to roam mid or invade her jungler while she's stuck farming under tower. Every gold you take off the map is gold Kayle can't use to reach her scaling spike — deny her the side lane farm and end the game before two items, because a fed Kayle is the one enemy you can't simply run down later.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Kayle - Track: Kayle's R (Divine Judgment) — the few seconds of invulnerability hard-counter your Highlander reset chain; it lets her survive your all-in and turn a fight you were winning, so bait it before you commit your full combo.. - Win the window between your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) and her second component — punish her short melee range and weak waveclear with Alpha Strike farming plus Wuju trades, then convert any pre-16 lead into towers and cross-map kills before her ranged form and Highlander invuln come online.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A scaling-mirror standoff: you out-DPS Kayle's awkward melee form on your first on-hit item, but every level she draws closer to the ranged-form, R-invuln carry who reclaims the game the moment she hits two items."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Your win condition is tempo: this is a rare melee-vs-melee early for you, so bully Kayle's weak transformation phase and convert that pressure into objectives before level 16. You must close the game on your first-item snowball window, because if it reaches her two-item ranged form the matchup inverts."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Even at 1, yours from 2 through first item, flipping to Kayle's at level 6's ranged unlock and decisively hers at 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade aggressively with E up while she's meleed (levels 2-15); back off the instant her ranged form lets her auto from range or when Divine Judgment is available to negate your burst."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Push early to deny her CS and pressure her off the wave while she's weak, then shove and roam before 6; once her ranged waveclear comes online, freeze near your tower to deny her safe farm and force her to step into Alpha Strike range."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges nothing of Kayle's reliably (her E slow and ranged autos still land on exit), but it gives you the attack-reset and gap-close she can't punish in melee form; her Divine Judgment invuln is the single counter to your Highlander reset-kill chain, so it dictates when you commit."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (her low early threat lets the stacking attack speed ramp safely) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Sudden Impact + Treasure Hunter, or take Resolve (Conditioning/Overgrowth) if you want to out-scale her two-item window; runes are AD/on-hit so they don't shift vs her AP."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to convert your early melee dominance into kills and to cut her R-bought heal/time; take Teleport only if you specifically want to match her scaling and stay even in farm."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first for the on-hit spike that bursts her before two items, then Wit's End (its magic resist and on-hit shred is ideal vs her AP ranged form), Berserker's Greaves, and Terminus/Maw later for the MR and lifesteal to survive her scaling DPS."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"All-in from level 2 through your first item while she's meleed and her R is down; your hardest commit is right on the Kraken/BORK timing, the last moment your DPS clearly beats her single-item form."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Kayle is a free gank target pre-6 with no escape — call your jungler early and often, because a couple of early deaths set her scaling back enough to keep her out of her ranged-form spike; conversely she has no kill pressure on you, so you can play for tempo without fearing her ganking you."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players passively farm this 'even' lane and let Kayle free-scale, then act surprised when her two-item ranged form runs them down; the mistake is not exploiting the early melee window hard enough."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you fall behind, stop forcing the losing scaling race — farm safely with Alpha Strike, build Wit's End early for her magic damage, and look to splitpush the side she isn't defending rather than dueling her itemized form."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Snowball by ending fast: take her tower and roam with Highlander's speed to feed off the map, deny her sidelane farm, and force objectives and fights while she's still meleed so the game closes before her ranged-form takeover."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A true coin-flip (50.65%) scaling mirror — you own levels 2 through first item and must win there, because Kayle reclaims everything at two items and into the late game."}]},"kennen":{"tldr":"A ranged poke-kite that out-ranges your autos and whose R stun catches you the instant Alpha Strike ends — eat the chip, farm to your on-hit spike, and flip it after two items.","winCon":"Survive the early poke war by farming with Alpha Strike and Meditate, then once Kraken/BORK comes online use Wuju true damage and on-hit DPS to delete him in any fight where you dodge his Slicing Maelstrom with Q. Bait his R out, blink in untargetable, and burst him before he can reset the stun.","enemyWin":"Kennen pokes you down with Q/W from range you can't answer, holds his R until your Alpha Strike is on cooldown, then chains a full Slicing Maelstrom stun-lock that kills you before you can Meditate or escape. If he keeps you under half HP and out of his AA range all game, you never reach the fight where you win.","diff":"TRICKY","tone":"#ff8b3d","diffRating":"7/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Kennen","rating":"7/10","why":"Kennen's ranged Q poke chips you for free while your only level-1 tool is farming Alpha Strike at melee range."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Kennen","rating":"7/10","why":"With Q plus a W follow-up he stacks his passive toward an early stun, and you still have no E true damage or sustain to trade back."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Kennen","rating":"6/10","why":"His mark-stun off three Mark of the Storm procs threatens a kill, but your Alpha Strike can dodge the closing auto if you read it."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Kennen","rating":"6/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain stabilize your trades, but his energy kite still keeps you out of AA range and tops his health off."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's move speed and slow immunity let you stick to him through his W slow, and you can Alpha Strike the moment he commits Slicing Maelstrom."},{"label":"First item","side":"Skill","rating":"6/10","why":"Your first on-hit item lets you out-DPS him in a fight, but it comes down to whether you dodge his R stun with Q — land it and you win, eat it and you die."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"At Kraken plus BORK with Wit's End MR your on-hit burst and Highlander resets out-trade his AP DPS, and Wit's End shrugs his poke."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are Kennen's. He sits at range throwing Q (Thundering Shuriken) for free chip while your only option is to farm with Alpha Strike and concede every trade — your short range and lack of E true damage mean you simply can't reach him. Hold your Q for dodging his closing auto, not for engaging, and never walk up for a CS while he has three Mark of the Storm stacks ready.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you stabilize: Wuju Style adds true damage for short bursts and Meditate lets you heal off his poke at the wave. Level 6 is your first real claim — Highlander gives move speed and slow immunity to fight through his W slow, and you can save Alpha Strike to go untargetable the instant he casts Slicing Maelstrom. Bait the R before you commit.","late":"At 2+ items (Kraken/BORK + Wit's End) the lane flips. Your on-hit DPS and Highlander resets out-damage his AP, Wit's End's MR and magic damage on-hit hard-counter his poke, and a fight where you dodge his R with Q is a clean kill that snowballs into resets across the map.","wave":"Best wave: a slow-push you freeze just outside tower so he must walk into your Alpha Strike range to farm. Worst wave: a wave shoved onto you under no tower, where he zones you off CS with Q from max range. Crash timing: crash hard right before your first item back so you can recall, buy your on-hit spike, and return to a fresh wave you can fight on.","cooldowns":"Track his R (Slicing Maelstrom) above everything — it's a long cooldown, and once it's down you have a free window to all-in him with no stun-lock answer.","trading":"Never auto-trade into his range. Your only winning trade is reactive: dodge his engage or R with Alpha Strike, blink in untargetable, then dump Wuju autos and Double Strike while Highlander keeps you on him.","spikes":"Kennen spikes at 6 (R) and at his first AP item; you spike at 6 (Highlander), at your first on-hit item, and decisively at 2+ items where Wit's End answers his magic damage.","feeding":"If you fall behind, his Q poke zones you off the wave entirely and his R one-shots you in any skirmish — you become unkillable-to-uselessly-far-behind fast because your whole kit needs you alive and itemized to function.","carry":"If you get ahead, Highlander's kill-refresh lets you chain resets across lanes — take your lead, group with on-hit items, and Alpha Strike through his teammates' CC to reach and delete his carries.","difficulty":"It's a 7/10 because Kennen attacks the exact two things Yi has none of early: range and a CC answer. His R is point-and-click area lockdown that catches you after your one escape, so the whole lane is a scaling race you must survive, not win."},"focus":{"text":"Slicing Maelstrom (R) — his AOE stun is the only thing that beats your Alpha Strike escape; if it's up, he can chain-stun and kill you, so never commit until you've baited or dodged it.","letters":["R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Bait the R before committing","d":"Force or wait out Slicing Maelstrom, then all-in — once his R is down you have no lockdown to fear and your on-hit DPS wins the fight."},{"t":"Save Alpha Strike to dodge","d":"Hold Q as a defensive untargetable button against his engage and R cast, not as an engage tool; going untargetable mid-stun is your only escape."},{"t":"Rush Wit's End","d":"Buy Wit's End early in this lane — the MR shrugs his Q/W poke and the magic on-hit damage lets you out-trade him in the window you scale into."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't walk up to CS into Q","d":"Eating Thundering Shuriken for a minion stacks his Mark of the Storm toward a stun and bleeds the HP you need to survive — give up the CS and farm safely with Alpha Strike."},{"t":"Don't all-in while his R is up","d":"If Slicing Maelstrom is available he catches you the moment Q ends and chain-stuns you dead — that's the single trade that loses the lane."},{"t":"Don't fight at three Mark stacks","d":"With three passive stacks his next ability stuns you instantly, turning your engage into his free kill — back off until the marks expire."}],"tradeGood":"Bait his Slicing Maelstrom, Alpha Strike untargetable through it, then dump Wuju Style true-damage autos with Double Strike while Highlander keeps you glued to him.","tradeBad":"Walking up to auto-trade into his Q poke range while he holds three Mark of the Storm stacks and an available R.","ahead":"If you get a lead, freeze the wave just outside your range so he has to walk into Alpha Strike to farm, then punish every CS. Snowball with your on-hit spike and Highlander resets — once you have Kraken/BORK and Wit's End you out-DPS him through his own poke, and you can roam with R move speed to chain kills before he scales. Deny his items and the lane is permanently yours.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Kennen - Track: Slicing Maelstrom (R) — his AOE stun is the only thing that beats your Alpha Strike escape; if it's up, he can chain-stun and kill you, so never commit until you've baited or dodged it.. - Survive the early poke war by farming with Alpha Strike and Meditate, then once Kraken/BORK comes online use Wuju true damage and on-hit DPS to delete him in any fight where you dodge his Slicing Maelstrom with Q. Bait his R out, blink in untargetable, and burst him before he can reset the stun.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A ranged poke-kite that out-ranges your autos and whose R stun catches you the instant Alpha Strike ends — eat the chip, farm to your on-hit spike, and flip it after two items."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a poke-heavy early game by farming with Alpha Strike and healing with Meditate, then reach your first on-hit item where your DPS and Highlander resets out-trade his AP. The whole lane is a scaling race: you win every fight after two items where you dodge his Slicing Maelstrom with Q."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Kennen owns levels 1-5 with ranged poke and his level-6 R; favor swings to you at your first on-hit item and is decisively yours at 2+ items with Wit's End online."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Never initiate a trade into his Q range; only trade reactively after dodging his engage or R with Alpha Strike. Back off entirely whenever he has three Mark of the Storm stacks or an available Slicing Maelstrom."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Freeze just outside your Alpha Strike range so he must walk up to farm into your range; avoid shoving, which lets him poke you freely off CS under your tower. Crash before your first-item back to reset on a fresh wave."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability is your one answer to his Slicing Maelstrom — blink during his R cast to avoid the stun-lock. Meditate out-sustains his Q/W poke between trades, and Highlander's slow immunity ignores his W slow to let you stick to him."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the attack-speed ramp in extended fights (or Conqueror if you want trade staying power); secondary Resolve with Second Wind and Bone Plating to blunt his Q poke, plus the Magic Resist shard against his AP."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Teleport — Teleport keeps you even on a scaling lane you can't win early and lets you recover from poke recalls; take Ignite only if your jungler is camping for an early kill."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush an on-hit core of Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King, then prioritize Wit's End for the MR and magic on-hit against his AP; Mercury's Treads boots for tenacity vs his stun, and consider an early Hexdrinker/Maw if he's snowballing."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"All-in only when his Slicing Maelstrom is on cooldown and you have your first on-hit item — that's the window where you dodge or ignore his CC and out-DPS him. At 2+ items you can all-in on R cooldown nearly every wave."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're extremely gankable early since Alpha Strike is your only escape and his R sets up easy follow-up; ward and play safe. Your own jungler diving him is huge because Kennen has no escape once you reach him with Highlander."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players try to trade or all-in too early to 'win lane' and feed into his poke and R — this lane is survived, not won early. The other mistake is wasting Alpha Strike to engage instead of saving it to dodge his Slicing Maelstrom."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Farm under tower with Alpha Strike, take every TP recall to stay item-relevant, and avoid all skirmishes where his R can catch you. Scale to your 2+ item spike and let the game open up — your curve is steeper than his."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Freeze him off CS, punish his walk-ups with on-hit burst, and use Highlander's kill-refresh to chain resets across the map; press your item lead before his AP scaling catches up at three items."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"TRICKY (47.92% WR) — Kennen out-ranges and out-CCs you early, but bait his R, survive to your on-hit spike, and the 2+ item window is firmly yours."}]},"kled":{"tldr":"A weak-early, win-late skirmish: Kled's mounted Q-pull and Violent Tendencies bully you at levels 1-3, but once you hit Kraken/BORK you out-DPS Skaarl, dodge his all-in with Alpha Strike, and run him down before his late-game scaling reclaims it.","winCon":"Survive Kled's mounted early by farming with Alpha Strike from max range and never standing in his Bear Trap on a Rope line; once your first on-hit item is online, Wuju Style true damage and Highlander let you out-sustain his burst with Meditate, dodge his Chaaaaarge engage mid-blink, and burn through Skaarl's second health bar in an extended fight.","enemyWin":"Kled wins by landing Bear Trap on a Rope to drag you into mounted Violent Tendencies autos before level 6 and chunking you (or a remount) faster than you can scale, or by holding Chaaaaarge to all-in you the instant you commit Meditate. If he keeps you off CS and denies your item spike, his hard scaling carries the lane back at 2+ items.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"4/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Kled","rating":"6/10","why":"Mounted Kled with Bear Trap on a Rope (Q) and one Violent Tendencies stack out-trades your single Alpha Strike and bare autos — you have no Wuju Style or Highlander yet, so concede the level-1 push."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Kled","rating":"6/10","why":"His Q-pull into Violent Tendencies attack-speed autos still beats you; you only have Alpha Strike to last-hit from range and Meditate doesn't cover a full mounted burst, so keep your distance."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"With Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain online you can answer a short trade, but his Q-grab and Skaarl second health bar keep a straight fight even — bait his Q before committing."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Master Yi","rating":"5/10","why":"At 4-5 Wuju Style's true damage ignores any armor he builds and Meditate out-sustains his poke between Violent Tendencies windows, tilting short trades your way."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's bonus move/attack speed and slow immunity let you stick through his kite and dodge his Chaaaaarge (R) windup with a well-timed Alpha Strike, flipping the all-in."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King turns your on-hit DPS up sharply — you out-trade mounted Kled, shred Skaarl, and Alpha Strike resets your attack timer to chunk him through Violent Tendencies."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Kled","rating":"6/10","why":"Kled hard-scales: a remounted, itemized Kled keeps his recurring Q-engage and Chaaaaarge teamfight value, and his burst can drop you before Highlander resets — close the game before this window opens."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are Kled's lane to win. Mounted, he's a skirmish bully: Bear Trap on a Rope (Q) yanks you out of position into Violent Tendencies' attack-speed autos before you have Wuju Style, Meditate, or Highlander to answer. Do not walk up to CS in his face — last-hit with Alpha Strike from the back of the wave, which keeps you untargetable mid-blink, and accept losing a little CS rather than eating a Q-pull all-in.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are where the lane stabilizes for you. Wuju Style's bonus true damage ignores any early armor and Meditate's damage reduction plus heal lets you out-sustain his poke between his Violent Tendencies windows, so short trades start going even or your way. Level 6 Highlander is your real swing — the move/attack speed and slow immunity let you stick to him through his kite and use Alpha Strike to dodge his Chaaaaarge engage, turning his all-in into a kill on a dismounted Kled.","late":"At first item you flip ahead and at 2+ items you out-DPS him in any extended fight — Alpha Strike resets your attack timer and dodges his CC while you burn through Skaarl's second health bar, and Highlander chains resets off the kill. Respect that Kled is a hard scaler though: if you haven't closed by the time he remounts with items, his recurring Q-engage and Chaaaaarge reclaim relevance, so end the lane before that.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push you control so you fight on even or thin waves where his Q-pull into the minions hurts less and your Alpha Strike has fewer extra targets to scatter to. Worst wave: a big enemy wave crashing into you, which lets Kled Q-pull you into his caster minions and Violent Tendencies for a free chunk. Crash timing: shove and crash the wave just before your level 6 / first-item spike so you can recall, hit your item, and return with a tempo lead while denying him a dismount-reset bounce.","cooldowns":"Track Bear Trap on a Rope (Q) above all — it's his engage and his only hard initiation onto you. When his Q is down he has no way to force you, so that's your window to step up, last-hit freely, or all-in. Secondarily watch his remount timer (Skaarl returning) and Chaaaaarge (R) post-6.","trading":"Bait his Q first: dodge or sidestep Bear Trap on a Rope, then once it's on cooldown step in with Wuju Style true-damage autos and Alpha Strike to reset your attack timer. Never trade into a fresh Q while he's mounted and Violent Tendencies is up. After 6, use Highlander uptime to stick and Alpha Strike to dodge his Chaaaaarge mid-commit.","spikes":"Kled spikes at level 1-2 (mounted Q + Violent Tendencies) and on each remount. You spike at level 4-5 (Wuju Style + Meditate online), level 6 (Highlander), and hard at first item (Kraken / Blade of the Ruined King) where your on-hit DPS jumps past him; 2+ items is your peak unless he's remounted with items and scaled.","feeding":"If you fall behind, a fed mounted Kled chains Q-pulls and out-trades you through Meditate, and his remounts give him extra health bars you can't burn. Don't keep walking into the same Q — farm safe with Alpha Strike, give up the wave, and wait for your jungler or your item spike rather than forcing a trade you lose.","carry":"If you get ahead, you become a 1v9 on-hit hyper-carry: Alpha Strike dodges his CC and resets your timer, Wuju Style true damage shreds whatever armor he builds, and Highlander refreshes on kills so you chain pick-offs across the map. Press the lead by taking plates, crashing waves to recall into items, and roaming once Kled's Q is on cooldown.","difficulty":"It rates a 4/10 — FAVOURED but not free — because Kled genuinely owns the early levels and can deny your scaling with repeated Q-pull trades and remounts. The difficulty is patience: the lane is hard to throw only if you respect levels 1-3 and don't gift him the snowball before your items come online."},"focus":{"text":"Bear Trap on a Rope (Q) — his single-target grab/pull is his only way to lock you down and start his mounted Violent Tendencies burst; bait it out and the lane is yours, walk into it and you eat his whole all-in.","letters":["Q"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike","d":"Last-hit from the back of the wave with Q — it makes you untargetable mid-blink, dodges his poke, and resets your attack timer so you scale without eating a Bear Trap on a Rope pull."},{"t":"Bait the Q, then commit","d":"Sidestep or force out Bear Trap on a Rope first; once it's on cooldown Kled can't initiate, so that's when you step up with Wuju Style autos and Alpha Strike."},{"t":"Time Highlander to dodge Chaaaaarge","d":"Post-6, hold Alpha Strike to blink through his Chaaaaarge (R) engage and use Highlander's slow immunity to stick — his all-in becomes your kill on a dismounted Kled."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't CS in his face early","d":"Walking up to last-hit mounted Kled at levels 1-3 invites a Bear Trap on a Rope pull into Violent Tendencies autos you can't answer yet — give up the CS instead."},{"t":"Don't Meditate inside his all-in","d":"Channeling Meditate while his Q and Chaaaaarge are up just feeds him a free burst window — Meditate sustains poke, it does not survive a committed mounted all-in."},{"t":"Don't slow-play into his scaling","d":"Kled hard-scales and remounts give him extra health bars, so don't let the lane drift to 2+ items even — close it out on your first-item spike before he reclaims it."}],"tradeGood":"Bait out Bear Trap on a Rope, then once it's down step in with Wuju Style true-damage autos and Alpha Strike to reset your timer and chunk Skaarl while his Q can't pull you.","tradeBad":"Never trade into a fresh, mounted Kled with Bear Trap on a Rope up and Violent Tendencies stacking — his Q-pull into attack-speed autos out-bursts you before your items come online.","ahead":"Once you're ahead, weaponize your tempo: crash the wave to recall into your on-hit item, then return and all-in whenever his Q is on cooldown, using Alpha Strike to dodge his Chaaaaarge and Wuju Style to shred his armor. Highlander refreshes on every kill, so chain the reset into roams and dives across the map before Kled can remount and scale. Take plates and prio, then leverage your hyper-carry mid-game while he's still a one-trick early bully.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Kled - Track: Bear Trap on a Rope (Q) — his single-target grab/pull is his only way to lock you down and start his mounted Violent Tendencies burst; bait it out and the lane is yours, walk into it and you eat his whole all-in.. - Survive Kled's mounted early by farming with Alpha Strike from max range and never standing in his Bear Trap on a Rope line; once your first on-hit item is online, Wuju Style true damage and Highlander let you out-sustain his burst with Meditate, dodge his Chaaaaarge engage mid-blink, and burn through Skaarl's second health bar in an extended fight.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A weak-early, win-late skirmish: Kled's mounted Q-pull and Violent Tendencies bully you at levels 1-3, but once you hit Kraken/BORK you out-DPS Skaarl, dodge his all-in with Alpha Strike, and run him down before his late-game scaling reclaims it."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive Kled's mounted early by farming with Alpha Strike from range and refusing every Bear Trap on a Rope window, then flip the lane the moment your first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King) is online. From there your Wuju Style true damage, Meditate sustain, and Alpha Strike CC-dodge let you out-DPS him in extended fights and burn through Skaarl before his late scaling matters."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Kled owns 1-2 (mounted Q + Violent Tendencies), the lane goes even at 3-5 as Wuju Style and Meditate come online, you take 6 (Highlander) and spike hard at first item, then Kled reclaims relevance only at 2+ items if you let it go that long."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only after baiting out Bear Trap on a Rope; with his Q down he can't initiate, so step in with Wuju Style autos and Alpha Strike. Back off whenever Q is up and he's mounted with Violent Tendencies stacking — that's his trade, not yours."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep waves even or slow-push so his Q-pull has less value and Alpha Strike doesn't scatter onto extra minions; avoid letting a big wave crash on you. Crash just before your level 6 / first-item timing so you can recall, hit your spike, and return with a lead."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges his Chaaaaarge (R) engage and his poke if you time it on his commit; Wuju Style's true damage ignores any armor Kled itemizes; Meditate out-sustains his between-window poke but NOT a full mounted all-in; Highlander's slow immunity beats his kite so you stick for the kill."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (faster on-hit ramp to out-DPS his Violent Tendencies windows) — Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve with Conditioning and Overgrowth (or Second Wind into his poke) to survive the early; standard AS/adaptive/HP shards. Conqueror is the fallback if you want the extended-trade healing."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite for the kill pressure and anti-heal on his Skaarl-mounted sustain once you can all-in post-6; take Flash + Teleport instead if you expect to get bullied off the wave early and need to stabilize and match his remount tempo."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit spike that flips the lane, then Wit's End or Terminus into his physical-leaning damage for the extra MR/resist and on-hit; Berserker's Greaves; build Wuju Style around true damage so his armor is moot, and add a defensive third (Death's Dance / Maw) if he's fed."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You can all-in at level 6 once Highlander is up and his Bear Trap on a Rope is on cooldown and Skaarl is low/dismounted, and far more reliably at first item where your on-hit DPS out-trades him. Always start the all-in by dodging or baiting his Q, never into it."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're a weak, gankable early-laner here, so ping and respect ganks pre-6 — a Kled Q-pull plus jungler chains lethal CC onto you with Alpha Strike on cooldown. Once you have Highlander and an item you flip it: your jungler arriving while Kled's Q is down turns a dive into a free double, and Highlander's reset lets you snowball off it."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi error here is contesting CS in mounted Kled's face at level 1-2 and eating a Bear Trap on a Rope pull into Violent Tendencies, then trying to Meditate through the burst — which just feeds him. The other is slow-playing the scaling lane until 2+ items and letting his remount-plus-items spike reclaim it."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're behind, farm safe with Alpha Strike, concede waves rather than walking into repeat Q-pulls, and don't try to solo a fed mounted Kled. Wait for your item spike and jungle help, sidelane safely when his Q is down, and look to scale to the 2+ item window where your DPS still wins extended fights."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Crash waves to recall into your on-hit item, then all-in on every Q cooldown using Alpha Strike to dodge his engage; Highlander refreshes on kills so chain the reset into plates, roams, and dives. Close the game on your mid-game hyper-carry peak before Kled remounts and scales into relevance."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED, 4/10 difficulty — Kled bullies the early levels but Master Yi out-scales and out-DPSes him from first item onward; respect levels 1-3, hit your spike, and close before his late-game scaling reclaims the lane."}]},"ksante":{"tldr":"Survive K'Sante's lane-bully early without eating his Q knockup or getting pinned by R, then your on-hit item spike flips a coin-flip lane into a kill threat he can only answer by stripping his own resists.","winCon":"Farm safe with Alpha Strike levels 1-3, hold E Wuju Style's true damage for short trades once Meditate sustains you, then once Kraken/BORK is online dodge his Ntofo Q with Alpha Strike's untargetable blink and shred him through his own armor with on-hit true and percent-HP damage before he two-items into a real fighter.","enemyWin":"K'Sante wins by landing Ntofo Q knockup or W-dashing into a free trade you can't punish pre-6, and by saving R to strip his resists and isolate you the instant you commit Alpha Strike — once he's two-items he simply out-fights your on-hit DPS as a tank-duelist.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"K'Sante","rating":"6/10","why":"His Ntofo's Ferocity Q knockup and tanky base stats bully your short-range autos while you have only Alpha Strike for damage and no escape."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"K'Sante","rating":"6/10","why":"A second Q charge plus W's damage-block dash lets him walk into trades you can't answer before E Wuju Style or Meditate exist."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"K'Sante","rating":"5/10","why":"You stabilize on farm with Alpha Strike resets, but he still wins any extended auto exchange without your true damage online."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"E Wuju Style true damage plus Meditate sustain lets you win short trades, but his percent-HP passive and Q poke keep it even."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's slow immunity and move/attack speed let you ignore his Q slow-walk and dodge gank setups he relies on to all-in."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken/BORK on-hit plus E true damage shreds him through armor, and Alpha Strike goes untargetable through his R isolation attempt."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"K'Sante","rating":"6/10","why":"He two-items into a tank-fighter whose R-stripped form and sustained damage out-fight your on-hit kit unless you snowballed the early lane."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to K'Sante. His Ntofo's Ferocity Q outranges your autos and the empowered third cast knocks you up, while you have nothing but Alpha Strike for damage and zero escape if you over-extend. Farm with Q and Wuju autos, take the CS hits, and do not contest him — every all-in here is his.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are the inflection. E Wuju Style's bonus true damage and W Meditate sustain finally let you win short auto exchanges, and level 6 Highlander gives you slow immunity plus the speed to dodge the ganks he sets up with his Q slow. This is where the lane levels out to even.","late":"At 2+ items K'Sante reclaims the matchup. He builds into a genuine tank-duelist whose R strips his own resists for damage and isolates you, and his sustained fight output beats your on-hit DPS unless you converted the first-item window into a real lead.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push that lets you shove him under tower and roam/recall on your item spike timing. Worst wave: a frozen wave near his tower where his Q poke and a jungle gank can collapse on you with no escape. Crash timing: crash the wave just before your first on-hit item completes so you back, buy, and return on the spike with priority.","cooldowns":"Track his Ntofo's Ferocity Q charges and his R cooldown — Q knockup is his all-in initiation and R is the only tool that punishes your Alpha Strike commit.","trading":"Short trade: walk in with E Wuju Style active, get your on-hit autos plus a Double Strike, and step out before his Q comes back up. Never sit in an extended trade pre-item where his percent-HP passive and W block grind you down.","spikes":"His spikes: level 2 (second Q), level 6 (R isolation), and his first tank item. Your spikes: level 6 Highlander and your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK), which is the moment the lane flips toward you.","feeding":"If you fall behind, he two-items faster, his R deletes you in any skirmish, and you lose the only window (first item) where you out-damage him — the lane becomes unwinnable and you must farm side and scale.","carry":"If you hit your item spike ahead, use Alpha Strike to dodge his Q and R, out-DPS him through his own armor with E true damage, and reset Highlander off the kill to snowball before his tank scaling arrives.","difficulty":"It's a true 5/10 even lane: he bullies you early and out-scales you at 2+ items, but you own the level-6-to-first-item window cleanly, so the lane is decided by whether you convert that mid-game spike."},"focus":{"text":"His R isolation — it strips his own resists for damage and pins you the moment you commit Alpha Strike, and it's the one tool that turns your snowball window back against you.","letters":["R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Alpha Strike his R","d":"When he ults to isolate you, Alpha Strike goes untargetable mid-cast — blink through the windup to dodge the engage and reset your attack timer for the counter-fight."},{"t":"Hold E for the spike window","d":"Once your first on-hit item lands, open trades with E Wuju Style active so your true damage ignores his stacked armor and percent-HP tankiness."},{"t":"Use Highlander to dodge ganks","d":"At 6, Highlander's slow immunity nullifies the slow-walk setups he and his jungler rely on — pop it to escape collapses he can't otherwise punish."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't fight levels 1-3","d":"His Q knockup and tank base stats win every early all-in; eat the CS loss and farm with Alpha Strike instead of contesting."},{"t":"Don't Alpha Strike into his Q","d":"If you blink in and his Ntofo's Ferocity Q is up, the empowered knockup lands as you land — wait for it on cooldown before you commit."},{"t":"Don't extend past first item","d":"At 2+ items he out-fights you as a tank-duelist; never take a drawn-out fight in the late game where his R-strip damage and sustain beat your DPS."}],"tradeGood":"Step in with E Wuju Style up after his Q is on cooldown, land on-hit autos plus a Double Strike proc, and walk out before he can answer.","tradeBad":"An extended autoattack brawl before your first on-hit item, where his percent-HP passive, W block, and Q knockup grind you down with no true damage to punish his armor.","ahead":"Press your level-6-to-first-item window hard: Alpha Strike his Q and R to dodge his only answers, shred him through armor with E true damage, and reset Highlander off the kill to chain pressure. Deny his tank-item timings by shoving him under tower and forcing recalls so he never reaches the 2+ item state where he out-scales you. Snowball into other lanes with Highlander's speed before his late-game arrives.","loading":"- Master Yi vs K'Sante - Track: His R isolation — it strips his own resists for damage and pins you the moment you commit Alpha Strike, and it's the one tool that turns your snowball window back against you.. - Farm safe with Alpha Strike levels 1-3, hold E Wuju Style's true damage for short trades once Meditate sustains you, then once Kraken/BORK is online dodge his Ntofo Q with Alpha Strike's untargetable blink and shred him through his own armor with on-hit true and percent-HP damage before he two-items into a real fighter.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Survive K'Sante's lane-bully early without eating his Q knockup or getting pinned by R, then your on-hit item spike flips a coin-flip lane into a kill threat he can only answer by stripping his own resists."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing levels 1-3 by farming with Alpha Strike, then convert the level-6-to-first-item window where Highlander and on-hit damage flip the lane in your favor. Close it out before K'Sante reaches 2+ items, because that's the moment his tank-duelist scaling reclaims the matchup."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"K'Sante owns 1-3, the lane evens at 4-5, you take 6 through first item, and he reclaims it at 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only with E Wuju Style active and his Q on cooldown; back off the instant a trade goes long, since his percent-HP passive and W block win attrition."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Farm safe and even early to avoid his Q poke and gank windows, then slow-push and crash into tower around your item spike to gain priority and back on timing."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges his R isolation and Ntofo Q knockup; E Wuju Style's true damage ignores the armor his tank build and R-strip rely on; Highlander's slow immunity beats his Q slow."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo primary (he's a slow-attack-speed tank you want to out-DPS), with Triumph and Legend: Alacrity; secondary Resolve (Conditioning/Overgrowth) or Coup de Grace in Precision — take Bone Plating into his Q-W trade poke."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite to threaten kills in your first-item window and cut his lifesteal/heal; take Teleport instead if you'd rather scale safely through the rough early lane."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Open Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for percent-HP and on-hit shred, follow with Wit's End or Terminus for true/magic damage and resists; Berserker's Greaves, and value the Wit's End MR less here since he's primarily AD."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"All-in at level 6 once Highlander is up and again the moment your first on-hit item completes — those are the only windows where you reliably beat his tankiness."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"His Q slow and knockup make him a strong gank setup, so respect early ganks; your own jungler converts your level-6 spike into kills, and Highlander lets you dodge counter-ganks he sets up."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players over-trade levels 1-3 trying to fight a lane bully, burn Alpha Strike as damage instead of saving it to dodge his Q/R, and chase the fight into the late game where he out-scales them."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Farm side lane, use Alpha Strike purely to clear and escape, avoid every skirmish where his R can isolate you, and scale to a teamfight role where you flank rather than duel him."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Convert your first-item kill by resetting Highlander, denying his tank-item recalls under tower, and roaming with Highlander speed to spread your lead before his 2+ item scaling lands."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A genuine 5/10 even lane — K'Sante bullies you early and out-scales you late, but you cleanly own the level-6-to-first-item window, so it's won or lost on whether you cash that spike."}]},"lillia":{"tldr":"A coinflip kite-vs-scale lane: survive Lillia's pre-6 DOT poke and dodging-her-bounces, hit your on-hit spike, and you out-DPS her once she can't sleep-and-run forever.","winCon":"Use Alpha Strike to close the gap and reset your attack timer through her W/E kiting, then out-sustain her passive DOT with Meditate and grind to your first on-hit item; once you outscale her single-target burst, run her down with Highlander resets in any extended fight.","enemyWin":"Lillia kites you with W (Watch Out! Eep!) and E (Swirlseed) bounces, stacks her passive Dream Dust DOT so you can never sit still, and lands her R (Lullaby) to sleep you for a burst follow-up or a free disengage — if she keeps you at range and bleeds you with the DOT, you never get to use your autos.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Lillia","rating":"6/10","why":"Her E Swirlseed and passive DOT poke from range while your Q Alpha Strike on a single target barely scratches her and goes on a long cooldown."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Lillia","rating":"6/10","why":"She zones you off the wave with W swings and her DOT stacks faster than your auto cadence, and you still have no Wuju true damage online to punish."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"With E Wuju Style and W Meditate up you can sustain her DOT and trade short, but she can still W-kite away before you connect a full auto string."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Even trades — your Wuju true damage and Meditate heal answer her DOT, but she just disengages with W's movement speed when you commit."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Both hit power spikes: your R Highlander gives the move speed to chase through her kite, but her R Lullaby sleep can peel your engage or set up her own burst."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Your first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King) plus E true damage out-DPS her squishy AP frame faster than her DOT can race you."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"At 2+ items Alpha Strike dodges her Lullaby/Swirlseed and your on-hit shred kills her before her kite-and-DOT can out-tempo a Highlander-reset chase."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Lillia. Her E Swirlseed and passive Dream Dust DOT chip you from a range your short auto range can't answer, and committing Q Alpha Strike on a single target deals almost nothing while burning your only mobility tool for several seconds. Just farm with Wuju autos and last-hit Alpha Strikes, soak the poke, and don't try to win a level-1 or level-2 fight you can't reach.","mid":"Levels 4-6 stabilize you. Wuju Style's true damage and Meditate's channel heal let you out-sustain her DOT in short trades, and at 6 your Highlander move speed finally lets you stick through a W swing. But she also gets R Lullaby at 6 — a sleep that hard-stops your engage — so the lane is genuinely even here, traded blow for blow.","late":"At 2+ items you flip the lane. Your on-hit DPS (Kraken/BORK procs plus E true damage) burns her squishy AP frame faster than her DOT can race you, and Alpha Strike's untargetable window dodges her Lullaby and Swirlseed mid-cast. Highlander resets turn one pick into a chain, and she has no way to peel a fed Yi off her once you're on top.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push that lets you shove her under tower and deny her the room to W-kite while you free-farm to your item spike. Worst wave: a long open lane where she has full space to E-poke and W-disengage and stack DOT on you from max range. Crash timing: crash the wave just before your first on-hit item completes so you can recall, spike, and return without conceding plates.","cooldowns":"Track her R Lullaby above all — it's a long cooldown and a sleep that turns your all-in into a free kill on you; secondarily watch her W (Watch Out! Eep!) cooldown, the swing that gives her the burst and the movement speed to kite your commit.","trading":"Trade in bursts, not extended dances: walk up only when her E is on cooldown, Alpha Strike in to reset your attack timer, land a Double Strike Wuju auto string, then disengage before her DOT and W out-tempo you — never chase her through open ground where her kite wins.","spikes":"Your spikes: level 6 Highlander, and your first on-hit item where your DPS jumps. Her spikes: level 6 Lullaby (sleep setup/disengage) and any AP item that lets her DOT race your health bar.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Yi has no peel and no range — her DOT and W-kite will perma-zone you off the wave and she'll out-farm and out-roam you. Concede CS, hug tower, ping for jungle help, and scale; never force a fight from behind because her Lullaby just converts your desperation into a death.","carry":"If ahead, your snowball is brutal: Alpha Strike dodges her only defensive tools, your on-hit shred melts her squishy frame, and every Highlander reset extends your move-speed window to chase her across the map and snowball into 1v9 teamfights.","difficulty":"It's only a 5/10 because she's a kite-and-poke caster, not a hard-CC lockdown threat — her single sleep is dodgeable with Alpha Strike, and your scaling eventually trumps an off-meta AP toplaner who can't sustain her own poke. The danger is purely the weak, gankable early where her DOT and disengage stall your scaling."},"focus":{"text":"Lillia's R Lullaby — the sleep that hard-stops your all-in and sets up her burst or a clean disengage; bait it or dodge it with Alpha Strike's untargetable window before you commit.","letters":["R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm to your spike","d":"Concede the early lane — last-hit with Wuju autos and Alpha Strikes, soak the DOT, and rush your first on-hit item where you flip the matchup."},{"t":"Sustain with Meditate","d":"Channel W between trades to out-heal her passive Dream Dust DOT — her poke means nothing if you reset your health bar every wave."},{"t":"Dodge Lullaby with Q","d":"Time Alpha Strike's untargetable window to phase through her R sleep and E Swirlseed, then land your Wuju auto string while she's exposed."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't Q to engage early","d":"Burning Alpha Strike on a single target pre-item does almost no damage and leaves you with no escape for several seconds while her W-kite and DOT punish you."},{"t":"Don't chase through open ground","d":"Following her across open lane lets her W-kite, E-poke, and stack DOT on you indefinitely — only commit when her disengage is on cooldown."},{"t":"Don't all-in into Lullaby","d":"Forcing a fight while her R is up means she sleeps you mid-commit and turns your engage into your own death — bait it first."}],"tradeGood":"Walk up when her E and W are on cooldown, Alpha Strike in to reset your attack timer, land a Double Strike Wuju true-damage auto string, and peel off before her DOT races you.","tradeBad":"A long open-ground chase where she kites you with W movement speed, poke with E, and stacks her Dream Dust DOT while your autos never connect.","ahead":"Once you've got a kill or your item lead, Lillia has zero tools to peel you off — Alpha Strike dodges her Lullaby and Swirlseed, your on-hit shred melts her squishy AP frame, and Highlander resets chain your move-speed window. Press by shoving her under tower to deny W-kite space, then use your Highlander speed to roam and snowball other lanes, returning to crash plates. Every fight you win extends your reset chain into a 1v9.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Lillia - Track: Lillia's R Lullaby — the sleep that hard-stops your all-in and sets up her burst or a clean disengage; bait it or dodge it with Alpha Strike's untargetable window before you commit.. - Use Alpha Strike to close the gap and reset your attack timer through her W/E kiting, then out-sustain her passive DOT with Meditate and grind to your first on-hit item; once you outscale her single-target burst, run her down with Highlander resets in any extended fight.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A coinflip kite-vs-scale lane: survive Lillia's pre-6 DOT poke and dodging-her-bounces, hit your on-hit spike, and you out-DPS her once she can't sleep-and-run forever."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a weak, pokey early by farming with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos and sustaining her DOT with Meditate, then hit your first on-hit item and out-DPS her squishy frame. From there Alpha Strike dodges her sleep and your Highlander resets let you chain kills she can't kite away from."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Lillia owns 1-3 (DOT poke + kite), it's even 4-6 as Wuju/Meditate and Highlander vs Lullaby trade off, and Yi takes over hard from first item onward."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Only trade when her E Swirlseed and W are on cooldown — Q in, land a Double Strike auto string, leave; back off entirely whenever Lullaby is up or you're at range in open lane."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave short or slow-push her under tower to deny her the open-lane space she needs to W-kite and E-poke; avoid letting it sit in the middle where her DOT and disengage dominate."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable window phases through Lullaby's sleep and Swirlseed's projectile; Meditate out-heals her Dream Dust DOT; Wuju Style's true damage ignores any defensive AP stat she builds; Highlander's slow immunity answers her W-driven kite."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the on-hit attack-speed ramp that suits the grind to your item spike, with Triumph and either Legend: Alacrity or Tenacity; secondary Resolve (Conditioning/Second Wind for the DOT poke) or Precision Coup de Grace — Second Wind specifically eases her early Dream Dust chip."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ghost is standard for sticking through her kite, but Ignite is strong here for kill pressure on a squishy off-meta laner once you spike; Teleport only if you want to guarantee scaling from behind."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit spike that flips the lane, follow with Wit's End — its magic resist directly answers her AP DOT and W burst — then Terminus or Berserker's Greaves; lean Wit's End / Mercury's Treads against her magic damage."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"All-in only after first item, when her Lullaby is on cooldown, and ideally when her E/W are down — that's the window where your on-hit DPS plus a Highlander reset kills her before she can disengage."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're gankable early with no escape but Q, so play safe until your jungler shows — but a single successful gank snowballs you straight to your item spike; conversely her R can set up her own jungler's dive, so respect ganks while Lullaby is up."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players burn Alpha Strike to engage pre-item, do nothing, and get kited and DOT'd to death with no escape — and they chase her through open lane instead of waiting for her disengage to be down."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Hug tower, give up CS you can't safely take, ping for jungle pressure, and scale — never force a fight while behind because her Lullaby converts any desperate all-in into a free kill."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Shove her under tower to kill her kite space, use Highlander move speed to roam and chain kills with resets, crash plates between, and convert your on-hit DPS lead into 1v9 teamfight dominance."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"EVEN (52% Yi) — a scaling coinflip where you concede a pokey early to her kite and DOT, then out-DPS and out-reset her once your on-hit items come online."}]},"lucian":{"tldr":"Lucian pokes you off the wave with double-shots and dashes away from every Alpha Strike, so you eat a miserable, gankable early lane and just pray to survive to your on-hit item spike.","winCon":"Concede levels 1-5, farm safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos under tower, and survive to Kraken/Blade — then use Highlander's slow immunity and Q's untargetability to close the gap in extended fights once Lucian can't kite you anymore. Your only real path is scaling past lane, ideally with a jungler who punishes how far up Lucian shoves.","enemyWin":"Lucian sits at range, whittles you with passive double-shots and Q/W every time you walk up to CS, and E-dashes out the instant you Alpha Strike onto him — keeping you perma-low, denying farm, and setting up jungle ganks while you have no escape. If he gets a lead he simply out-ranges and bursts you before your on-hit DPS comes online.","diff":"HARD","tone":"#ff5d6c","diffRating":"8/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Lucian","rating":"7/10","why":"Lucian's range and passive double-shot let him auto you for free while you have no way to retaliate at level 1 without burning Q."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Lucian","rating":"7/10","why":"With Q (Piercing Light) up he pokes you off the wave, and Wuju Style isn't online yet so your autos can't trade back."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Lucian","rating":"8/10","why":"At level 3 Lucian has Q, W, and E — full dash-poke kit — and can punish every CS while you still have only Alpha Strike and weak autos."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Lucian","rating":"7/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain let you survive short trades, but Lucian's E-dash still cancels your Alpha Strike gap-close every time."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Lucian","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's slow immunity helps you dodge ganks and stick briefly, but Lucian's E plus double E-dash spacing still kites your one engage."},{"label":"First item","side":"Skill","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken/Blade on-hit DPS lets you win an extended all-in IF you land Alpha Strike when his E is down — but he usually holds E to deny exactly that."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"At 2+ items your on-hit shred plus Highlander resets out-DPS Lucian in any fight where you reach him, flipping the matchup hard if you survived lane."}],"breakdown":{"early":"This is the worst part of the lane for you. Lucian out-ranges you and his passive double-shot means every time you step up to last-hit, you trade one auto for two of his plus a Q. You have no escape but Alpha Strike, and burning it to farm leaves you naked to a gank. Just sit back, soak XP, and CS with Q when the cooldown is up.","mid":"Levels 4-6 stabilize slightly: Wuju Style's true damage and Meditate's sustain let you heal poke and take a short trade if Lucian whiffs an E. Level 6 Highlander is your first real tool — slow immunity to dodge ganks and a brief stick window — but Lucian's two E-charges still kite your single gap-close.","late":"At 2+ items (Kraken/Blade + Wit's End or Terminus) you flip the matchup: if you land Alpha Strike with his E down, your on-hit DPS and Highlander resets shred him before he can kite. The whole game is whether you reached this window even or behind.","wave":"Best wave: a wave frozen near your tower so Lucian has to over-extend into your jungler to poke you. Worst wave: a fast-pushing wave where Lucian shoves you under tower and zones you off CS and XP. Crash timing: only crash when your jungler is topside or Lucian has used E, so you don't get caught dashing into an empty lane with no escape up.","cooldowns":"Track Lucian's E (Relentless Pursuit) above all — it's both his escape from your Alpha Strike and his gap-close to poke. When E is down is your only safe window to walk up or all-in.","trading":"Lucian wins every neutral trade with range and double-shots; you only win if he wastes E aggressively or whiffs it, leaving him with no dash to kite your Alpha Strike + Wuju autos.","spikes":"Lucian spikes early at levels 2-3 and on his first crit/ADC item; you spike at level 6 (Highlander) and hard at Kraken/Blade, then dominate at 2+ items.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Lucian out-ranges and one-combos you (double Q-pass + double-shot) before your on-hit damage matters — you become useless and griefable, so play for cross-map farm and let your team make picks.","carry":"If you reach 2-3 items alive, you become a 1v9: Alpha Strike dodges his peel, Highlander resets chain you through teamfights, and on-hit true damage melts him and his frontline.","difficulty":"It's an 8/10 because Lucian attacks the exact two things Yi can't fix early — he has range you can't close and a dash that cancels your only escape — and he does it during the phase you're already weakest."},"focus":{"text":"Lucian's E (Relentless Pursuit) is the whole matchup — it's his escape from your Alpha Strike and his engage to poke. Only commit when his E is on cooldown.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Q, not autos","d":"Use Alpha Strike to safely last-hit from range and dodge his poke, but never burn it to chase — you need it up as your only escape from a gank."},{"t":"Commit only when his E is down","d":"Lucian's Relentless Pursuit dash kites your Alpha Strike; the only time your all-in lands is right after he uses E to engage or reposition."},{"t":"Scale and survive","d":"Concede the lane, hit Kraken/Blade alive, and look for sidelane and teamfight resets where your on-hit DPS beats his kite."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't Alpha Strike into his E","d":"If you blink onto Lucian while his E is up, he dashes away, you've burned your escape, and you're standing in the open with no follow-up and a gank incoming."},{"t":"Don't trade autos at level 1-3","d":"His passive double-shot and range mean every step-up costs you two autos plus a Q for one of yours — you just take free poke and shove yourself in."},{"t":"Don't over-push without vision","d":"A pushed lane against Lucian with no escape is a free kill for his jungler; ward and freeze instead of fighting for the wave."}],"tradeGood":"After Lucian burns E to engage or dodge, Alpha Strike onto him, pop Wuju Style for true damage, and ride Highlander to stick — now he has no dash to kite you.","tradeBad":"Walking up to auto-trade at levels 1-3, where his range plus passive double-shot guarantee you eat double the damage you deal and shove yourself under his control.","ahead":"If you somehow get ahead, force the sidelane where Lucian can't kite forever in a narrow space and your on-hit DPS plus Highlander resets punish any mistake. Track his E and all-in the moment it's down — once you're on him with Wuju Style true damage, he melts. Use your lead to push for plates and roam with Highlander's move speed since you out-tempo him in skirmishes.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Lucian - Track: Lucian's E (Relentless Pursuit) is the whole matchup — it's his escape from your Alpha Strike and his engage to poke. Only commit when his E is on cooldown.. - Concede levels 1-5, farm safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos under tower, and survive to Kraken/Blade — then use Highlander's slow immunity and Q's untargetability to close the gap in extended fights once Lucian can't kite you anymore. Your only real path is scaling past lane, ideally with a jungler who punishes how far up Lucian shoves.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Lucian pokes you off the wave with double-shots and dashes away from every Alpha Strike, so you eat a miserable, gankable early lane and just pray to survive to your on-hit item spike."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing early lane by farming with Alpha Strike under tower, then scale to your on-hit item spike where Highlander's slow immunity and Q's untargetability finally let you close the gap Lucian's range and dash deny you. Your win condition is reaching Kraken/Blade even-or-behind and converting the 2+ item window into a 1v9 reset machine."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Lucian owns levels 1-5 hard, the lane is roughly even at level 6 (Highlander) and first item, and flips to Yi-favoured only at 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Never trade autos before level 4; only commit Alpha Strike when his E is on cooldown; otherwise sit back, sustain poke with Meditate, and farm."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Freeze near your tower or keep the wave even so Lucian must over-extend to poke you — never shove into his side where his range and a gank punish your lack of escape."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike makes you untargetable to dodge his Q-pass and ganks, but his E (Relentless Pursuit) dash cancels your gap-close; Wuju Style adds true damage to beat any armor he buys; Meditate out-sustains his W/passive poke; Highlander's slow immunity ignores any slow from his items."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (faster on-hit ramp to survive and spike) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, and Last Stand; secondary Resolve (Second Wind + Overgrowth) to sustain his early poke, or Bone Plating if he runs you down."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Teleport is safest to recover from a lost lane and stay even in farm; take Ignite only if you're confident in a level-6 all-in window, but TP is the higher-percentage pick into a scaling ranged lane."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King, then Wit's End for MR and on-hit since Lucian is the AD threat but his burst is AD — Plated Steelcaps over Mercs, then Terminus; consider Death's Dance later for AD mitigation."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Only at level 6+ with Highlander up AND his E on cooldown — that's the lone window where Alpha Strike + Wuju Style can actually reach and kill him before he kites."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Your jungler is your lifeline: Lucian shoves and over-extends to poke, so a topside gank when he's pushed is your best source of a lead — equally, you're gankable with no escape if you push, so coordinate."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players burn Alpha Strike to farm or chase, then get caught with no escape and die to a gank — or they Alpha Strike into an up E and get kited for free."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Give up the lane entirely, farm safe waves with Q, take Teleport value, and play for cross-map and teamfight resets where your scaling beats his lane lead."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If you get a kill or hit 2 items first, force sidelane all-ins when his E is down and use Highlander resets to chain through his team — your DPS snowballs faster than his."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"HARD (45.48% WR) — a textbook ranged-kiter-vs-Yi lane you lose early and must scale out of; survive to 2+ items and you flip it, but most games are decided before you get there."}]},"malphite":{"tldr":"Malphite can poke you with Q and farm safe early, but he stacks armor against a true-damage on-hit duelist who out-sustains his W auto — once you hit your on-hit item this immobile tank can't kite you and folds in the extended fight, with only his R standing between him and a free reset.","winCon":"Concede the level 1-3 Q poke, farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, then spike at 6 and your first on-hit item: E Wuju Style true damage ignores his stacked armor, Meditate out-sustains his W-empowered auto, and you run him down once he blows R or you bait it.","enemyWin":"Malphite wins by never letting you stack — Q-slow poking you off CS, farming under tower behind his passive shield, and landing R as you commit Alpha Strike so his jungler arrives to delete you before Highlander can reset.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"4/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Malphite","rating":"6/10","why":"He starts Q and pokes you off the melee minions while your 125 range and no early E means you just take it and farm."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Malphite","rating":"6/10","why":"With Q + W up he can chunk you on a step-up auto and his passive shield eats your Alpha Strike chip, so you concede and last-hit."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"You stabilize as Wuju Style true damage comes online for short Q-into-auto pokes, but his Q-slow still kites your melee range."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Meditate now out-sustains his W-empowered auto poke and Wuju true damage starts ignoring his early armor components, flipping the trade math."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander gives you slow immunity that negates his Q-slow, but you must hold Alpha Strike's untargetable window to dodge his R rather than dump it for damage."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken/BORK on-hit plus E true damage shreds straight through his stacked armor, and immobile Malphite has no way to kite the chase once R is on cooldown."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At 2+ on-hit items you out-DPS his entire health bar through armor, and any kill resets Highlander to chain onto his team — he survives only to be a worse target than the squishies behind him."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are his. Malphite starts Q and pokes you whenever you step for a melee minion, and his W passive shield soaks the chip from your Alpha Strike, so there is no profitable trade. Just farm with Q on the caster line and Wuju autos, hold your wave, and accept that this is a scaling lane you are meant to lose early.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are where the lane turns. Wuju Style true damage starts cutting through his early armor components, Meditate out-sustains his single empowered W auto, and at 6 Highlander's slow immunity cancels the kiting value of his Q. Start taking short Q-edge-into-auto trades when his W is down, but do not over-commit before your item — his R can still flip a fight.","late":"At first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer or BORK) plus Wuju true damage, his stacked armor is meaningless and his immobility means he literally cannot escape the chase. At 2+ items you out-DPS his full health bar and every kill refreshes Highlander, letting you reset off him onto his carries. This is a hard-FAVOURED scaling endpoint.","wave":"Best wave: a slow freeze just outside your tower that forces Malphite to walk into your trade range to CS, or a stacked wave you crash on your item spike. Worst wave: shoved into his tower early, where he farms safely behind his shield and scales for free while your jungler can't path. Crash timing: crash hard the moment your first on-hit item completes so you trade tower plates and deny him farm during your spike.","cooldowns":"Track his R (Unstoppable Force) above all — it's a ~130/100s point-and-click knock-up that catches you out of Alpha Strike; secondarily watch his W (armor + empowered auto) so you only trade when it's down.","trading":"His trade is one Q-slow plus a W-empowered auto then back off; yours is to wait out that W auto, step up with E Wuju Style active, land Alpha Strike + a Double Strike auto so your true damage ignores his armor, then disengage with Highlander's move speed before his cooldowns return.","spikes":"His spikes: level 6 R, first armor item (Sunfire/Frozen Heart) frontline. Your spikes: level 6 Highlander, and far more decisively your first on-hit item where true damage + on-hit DPS makes his armor stacking worthless.","feeding":"If you fall behind, his R + jungle collapse is what kills you — you greed an Alpha Strike, he R's you on landing, and you die before Highlander resets. Then you're a weak early-laner with no item and he scales into an unkillable frontline.","carry":"If ahead, you become the textbook Yi snowball: on-hit + true damage erases his armor identity, Highlander resets chain you through his team, and Alpha Strike's untargetable frames dodge his one piece of CC. You side-lane uncontested and flank fights once R is down.","difficulty":"It's only 4/10 because the early Q poke is annoying and a well-timed R can still catch your Alpha Strike — but his armor-stacking tank identity is exactly what your true damage and on-hit kit are built to ignore, so it resolves FAVOURED."},"focus":{"text":"Malphite's R, Unstoppable Force — a point-and-click unstoppable dash and knock-up that catches you the instant Alpha Strike's untargetable window ends and sets up a jungle collapse; never commit your full combo until it's used or you've baited it.","letters":["R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Run E before you trade","d":"Activate Wuju Style so your autos and Alpha Strike deal bonus true damage — that's what turns his stacked armor into wet paper and is the entire reason this lane is favoured."},{"t":"Save Q for his R","d":"Alpha Strike makes you untargetable mid-cast, so hold it to dodge Unstoppable Force or bait the R out before you fully commit, then dump it for the chase."},{"t":"Scale, then crash on item","d":"Concede levels 1-3, farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, and look to crash and all-in the moment your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) finishes."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't brawl levels 1-3","d":"His Q-slow plus W-empowered auto and passive shield win every early trade; stepping up before Wuju true damage and Meditate are online just feeds him a lead."},{"t":"Don't dump Q into him at full HP","d":"Blowing Alpha Strike for chip leaves you with no escape — if he R's you with Q down, you eat the knock-up and the jungle gank with no reset."},{"t":"Don't ignore his jungler post-6","d":"His R is the perfect gank-setup CC; over-extending for a kill into a missing enemy jungle is how a winning Yi lane turns into a death and a reset for him."}],"tradeGood":"Wait out his W auto, flick on E Wuju Style, land Alpha Strike plus a Double Strike auto so your true damage ignores his armor, then peel off with Highlander's move speed before his Q and W come back.","tradeBad":"A level 1-3 extended trade where you eat a Q-slow and W auto into his passive shield, or dumping Alpha Strike for damage right before he lands R on you.","ahead":"Press the lead by crashing waves into his tower on your item spikes and forcing all-ins he can't kite — his armor is useless against your true damage and on-hit, so each fight refreshes Highlander and snowballs the next. Roam or side-lane with your move-speed steroid once his R is down, since he has zero tools to stop your Alpha Strike chase. Take his tower plates and turn the gold straight into your second on-hit item to lock the lane out.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Malphite - Track: Malphite's R, Unstoppable Force — a point-and-click unstoppable dash and knock-up that catches you the instant Alpha Strike's untargetable window ends and sets up a jungle collapse; never commit your full combo until it's used or you've baited it.. - Concede the level 1-3 Q poke, farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, then spike at 6 and your first on-hit item: E Wuju Style true damage ignores his stacked armor, Meditate out-sustains his W-empowered auto, and you run him down once he blows R or you bait it.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Malphite can poke you with Q and farm safe early, but he stacks armor against a true-damage on-hit duelist who out-sustains his W auto — once you hit your on-hit item this immobile tank can't kite you and folds in the extended fight, with only his R standing between him and a free reset."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a poke-heavy early lane by farming with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, then spike on Highlander and your first on-hit item. From there E Wuju Style true damage plus Kraken/BORK on-hit shred straight through his stacked armor while Meditate out-sustains his W, and his immobility means he can never escape or kite the chase."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Malphite-favoured 1-3 (Q poke), even at 4-5 as Wuju/Meditate come online, then it tilts to Master Yi at 6 (Highlander) and hard-FAVOURED from first on-hit item onward."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Don't trade levels 1-3; from 4 onward, trade only when his W is down — step in with E active, hit Alpha Strike + an auto, and leave before his cooldowns return. All-in freely once your first item is up and his R is on cooldown."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Slow-push or freeze just outside your tower early so he must walk into your range to CS; avoid shoving him under tower where he farms safe behind his shield. Crash the wave on your item spike to trade plates and deny his scaling."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"E Wuju Style true damage ignores his stacked armor — the core of the matchup. Alpha Strike's untargetable frames dodge his R knock-up. Meditate's damage reduction + heal out-sustains his W-empowered auto. Highlander's slow immunity cancels his Q-slow kiting. His passive shield only soaks early chip, not your itemized on-hit DPS."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (uncaps your attack speed for the on-hit chase and out-DPS) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve Conditioning + Overgrowth, or Second Wind into his Q poke. He's AP, so take the scaling-health/tenacity shards (HP, adaptive, MS or HP) rather than armor."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to convert your snowball and cut his durability when you all-in; take Flash + Teleport instead if you want to guarantee you survive the early poke phase and match his roams/scaling."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush an on-hit core — Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first, then Wit's End (he's AP, so the MR + on-hit magic is double value here) and Terminus for armor pen and resistances. Berserker's Greaves; build Wit's End/Maw-style MR over armor since his damage is magic, and Terminus shred handles whatever armor he stacks."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Level 6+ once Highlander is up and his W is down, and decisively the moment your first on-hit item completes — especially right after he uses R, when he has no CC and no way to escape your Alpha Strike chase."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"His R is a premium gank-setup, so post-6 his jungler is your real threat — ward up and don't over-extend with R available. Conversely, your own jungler converts this lane fast: any 2v2 you win the extended fight because his armor doesn't stop your true damage."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Trying to fight him levels 1-3 and falling behind, or dumping Alpha Strike for damage so you have no escape when his R lands — patience through the poke phase is the whole skill here."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Farm safely with Alpha Strike under tower, take Teleport, and stall to your item spike — even behind, your true damage and on-hit mean a single won fight at 2 items flips the game. Don't force trades; let his armor identity stay irrelevant."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Crash waves on your spikes, trade plates, reset Highlander off kills to chain onto his backline, and side-lane uncontested with your move-speed steroid once R is down. Buy your second on-hit item immediately to lock him out."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED, ~54% — a scaling lane where you eat early Q poke but his armor-stacking tank identity is exactly what your true damage and on-hit kit ignore; respect only his R."}]},"maokai":{"tldr":"A miserable scaling lane — Maokai's point-and-click W root catches you the instant Alpha Strike ends, his passive out-sustains Meditate, and he just survives until your items matter, so you farm, dodge ganks, and pray to scale.","winCon":"Concede the lane, farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, dodge every gank with Q, and reach two on-hit items (BORK + Wit's End/Terminus) where your sustained DPS finally out-grinds his tankiness in extended fights. Buy anti-heal (Executioner's into BORK) so his passive regen stops bailing him out.","enemyWin":"Maokai waits for your Alpha Strike to end, then point-and-click W roots you and Q knocks you back to lock down your only escape, letting him and his jungler delete you before you scale. His passive sustain refills faster than Meditate heals, so he wins every prolonged early trade and freezes you off farm.","diff":"HARD","tone":"#ff5d6c","diffRating":"8/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Maokai","rating":"6/10","why":"His passive heal and AA range out-trade your short reach; you have no Wuju true damage or escape yet beyond a long-cooldown Alpha Strike."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Maokai","rating":"6/10","why":"At 2 he has W root online before your kit functions — any auto-trade ends with you rooted and Q-knocked, eating sapling chip."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Maokai","rating":"7/10","why":"Full kit: W root catches you the moment Alpha Strike's untargetable blink ends, and his passive out-sustains anything Meditate restores."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Maokai","rating":"7/10","why":"Even with Wuju Style true damage and Meditate, his passive regen plus saplings mean your short trades net negative and he can freeze you off CS."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Maokai","rating":"7/10","why":"Highlander helps you dodge ganks, but his ult Nature's Grasp roots through it on landing and sets up a jungler to collect — his 6 is far scarier than yours."},{"label":"First item","side":"Maokai","rating":"6/10","why":"BORK/Kraken start to bite, but un-itemized he still out-tanks your on-hit and W-roots you out of any all-in before you finish him."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"With BORK + Wit's End/Terminus and anti-heal, your sustained on-hit finally shreds his health and Highlander resets carry the fight — provided you survived the early game."}],"breakdown":{"early":"You lose levels 1-3 outright. Maokai's passive heal-on-spell and longer effective range mean his autos and saplings out-trade your short reach while you have no Wuju true damage and only a long-cooldown Alpha Strike for safety. Farm with Q resets and Wuju autos on the wave, never on him, and accept that he can freeze you off CS.","mid":"At 4-5 Wuju Style and Meditate come online but his passive regen out-grinds your sustain, so short trades stay negative. Level 6 Highlander lets you dodge ganks, but his Nature's Grasp roots on landing and is built to chain with his jungler — your 6 is a defensive tool, his is a kill setup.","late":"This is the only window you own. With BORK + Wit's End or Terminus plus anti-heal, your sustained on-hit DPS finally out-paces his tankiness and Highlander resets let you chain through fights. If you reach this even on farm, you flip from prey to win condition.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push toward you so he must walk into Alpha Strike range to CS, letting you farm safely under tower. Worst wave: a frozen wave just outside your tower where his W root plus jungle gank delete you with no counterplay. Crash timing: only crash to reset and recall for your item spike, or right before your jungler arrives — never shove blind into his W and saplings.","cooldowns":"Track his W (Twisted Advance) above all — it's his only gap-close and the root that catches you out of Alpha Strike. If W is down, that's your single safe window to trade or farm aggressively; if it's up, give him nothing.","trading":"Trade only into a down W: Alpha Strike onto him to reset your attack timer, get a Wuju Style true-damage burst, and disengage before his passive heals it back. Never auto-walk in — every trade where W is up ends with you rooted, knocked back, and chunked.","spikes":"Maokai: levels 2-3 (full root pattern), level 6 Nature's Grasp, and his first tank item. Master Yi: level 6 Highlander for survival, but your real spikes are BORK first item and especially the 2-item on-hit window where the lane finally inverts.","feeding":"If you die once, his W root plus a single gank snowballs him into an unkillable frontline while you fall off the scaling clock entirely. Stop forcing, farm side waves safely with Q, ping his W cooldown for your team, and play for objectives rather than soloing a tank who out-sustains you.","carry":"If you reach two on-hit items alive, you don't carry through Maokai — you ignore him and use Alpha Strike to dodge his root and dive his carries, resetting Highlander on each kill to chain through the enemy team in extended fights.","difficulty":"8/10 because everything Maokai does answers your kit: point-and-click W beats your only escape, passive sustain beats Meditate, saplings zone your farm, and he simply has to survive — the one thing tanks do best — until you've scaled, which his early dominance is designed to prevent."},"focus":{"text":"Maokai's W (Twisted Advance) — the point-and-click dash-root that locks you down the instant Alpha Strike's untargetable window ends and sets up every gank. Bait it out or wait for it to be down before you commit to anything.","letters":["W"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Q, fight nothing","d":"Use Alpha Strike on the wave to last-hit and reset your attack timer while staying out of his range. Your job levels 1-9 is to reach two items alive, not to win lane."},{"t":"Save Q for his root","d":"Hold Alpha Strike as your dodge for Maokai's W and his jungler's CC — its untargetable blink is your only counterplay, so never burn it offensively when a gank is possible."},{"t":"Rush anti-heal","d":"Buy Executioner's Calling early and build into BORK. His passive sustain is what wins him the early lane, and grievous wounds is the single biggest swing you can make."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't extended-trade with W up","d":"Any auto fight while Twisted Advance is available ends with you rooted, Q-knocked, and eating saplings while his passive heals — only trade into a down W."},{"t":"Don't over-push into ganks","d":"A shoved wave plus his point-and-click root makes you the easiest gank target on the map; keep the wave central or on your side and ward his jungle entrances."},{"t":"Don't rely on Meditate to out-sustain him","d":"His passive regen refills faster than Meditate heals and the channel roots you in place for his W and gank — it's a panic button, not a trading tool here."}],"tradeGood":"Alpha Strike onto him only when his W is on cooldown, land a Wuju Style true-damage burst with a Double Strike proc, and disengage before his passive heals the chunk back.","tradeBad":"Walking up to auto-trade or channeling Meditate while his W is available — you get rooted, Q-knocked back, and bled out by saplings with no way to disengage.","ahead":"If you somehow get ahead, do not try to all-in Maokai himself — he's a tank who out-sustains you and your tempo is better spent elsewhere. Use the Highlander move speed to roam, crash waves and dive his squishier teammates, dodging his telegraphed W with Alpha Strike. Convert any lead into objectives and a faster path to your second on-hit item, which is the real source of your power in this game.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Maokai - Track: Maokai's W (Twisted Advance) — the point-and-click dash-root that locks you down the instant Alpha Strike's untargetable window ends and sets up every gank. Bait it out or wait for it to be down before you commit to anything.. - Concede the lane, farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, dodge every gank with Q, and reach two on-hit items (BORK + Wit's End/Terminus) where your sustained DPS finally out-grinds his tankiness in extended fights. Buy anti-heal (Executioner's into BORK) so his passive regen stops bailing him out.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A miserable scaling lane — Maokai's point-and-click W root catches you the instant Alpha Strike ends, his passive out-sustains Meditate, and he just survives until your items matter, so you farm, dodge ganks, and pray to scale."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing early lane by farming with Alpha Strike and conceding all aggression, then reach two on-hit items where your sustained DPS finally out-grinds his tankiness. The lane is won in the item shop and the extended late-game fight, never in the first ten minutes."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Maokai owns levels 1 through first-item hard; the lane only tilts toward you at the 2-item on-hit window, and only if you reached it alive."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade exclusively when his W (Twisted Advance) is on cooldown — Alpha Strike in, Wuju burst, leave. With W up, give him nothing and just farm; his passive sustain punishes every even trade."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave central or slow-pushing toward you so you farm safely and aren't a frozen gank target. Only crash to reset for an item back or right before your jungler arrives — never shove blindly into his root and saplings."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges his W root and ult only if timed on the cast — but his W is point-and-click, so once the blink ends he re-acquires and roots you. His Q knockback interrupts your approach and his passive regen out-paces Meditate. Highlander's slow-immunity does NOT stop his root."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (or Conqueror into his tankiness) primary with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve for Second Wind and Overgrowth to survive his poke and saplings. Take scaling health and the on-hit-friendly shards."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ghost or Exhaust over Ignite — Ignite's value is low against a tank with this much passive sustain, and you need the extra survivability/kiting tool to escape his root and ganks. Teleport is also fine to stay even in farm after recalls."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Executioner's Calling for grievous wounds, then Blade of the Ruined King as your first core item (its current-HP shred and on-hit answer his tankiness best), into Wit's End or Terminus for the magic-resist and sustained on-hit. Build Plated Steelcaps if his jungler is AD, plus a defensive third item like Death's Dance."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You realistically cannot all-in Maokai in lane before two items — he out-tanks and out-roots you. Your first true all-in window is BORK plus a second on-hit item, and even then prefer diving his carries over fighting him directly."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"This lane is brutal for ganks: his point-and-click W root guarantees CC for his jungler, so a single gank on a pushed wave can end your game. Ward both river entrances obsessively, hold Alpha Strike for the escape, and only fight 2v2 if his W is already down."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players try to out-trade or all-in Maokai early because he looks like an immobile tank — but his W root, Q knockback, and passive sustain hard-counter Yi's pre-item kit, and forcing fights just feeds his frontline and ends your scaling."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you fall behind, fully give up the lane: farm side waves with Q, never face-check, ping his W for your team, and play purely for the 2-item timing and objective fights. A farmed Yi is still a win condition; a fed-into-Maokai Yi is not."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If you get a lead, ignore Maokai and use Highlander's speed to roam, dive squishies with Alpha Strike, and rush your second on-hit item. Convert tempo into objectives — your snowball comes from out-scaling the map, not from killing the tank."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"HARD, 8/10 — Maokai's point-and-click root, passive sustain, and saplings counter every part of Yi's pre-item kit; concede early, scale to two on-hit items with anti-heal, and only then does the lane invert."}]},"mel":{"tldr":"Survive Mel's early Q poke, dodge her Solar Snare with Alpha Strike, and once you hit Kraken/BORK you Highlander onto her and delete a squishy mage who has zero hard lockdown.","winCon":"Farm safely under Mel's ranged Q poke to your first on-hit item, then E Wuju Style on and Alpha Strike straight through her W Solar Snare root so you reach her face — once Highlander is up you out-DPS and run down a 0-armor mage who can only stall, not stop you.","enemyWin":"Mel wins by chipping you out of XP/HP range with auto-attacking Q poke before you itemize and by timing her R Rebuttal to reflect your committed Alpha Strike + Wuju burst back into you, then walking away while her snare zone slows your reset.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"3/10","carryRating":"9/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Mel","rating":"6/10","why":"Mel's ranged Q out-ranges your auto and chips you while you have only Alpha Strike and no Wuju true damage yet."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Mel","rating":"5/10","why":"Her stacking Q poke still beats your short range, but you can Alpha Strike a minion to weave in a Double Strike auto for trade value."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"With Wuju Style unlocked your true-damage trade on her squishy frame roughly offsets her Q poke if you commit an Alpha-in."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage plus Meditate sustain lets you heal through her Q chip and win short all-ins on a mage with no escape."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity let you stick through her W snare-slow and reset cooldowns off the kill."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"Kraken Slayer / BORK on-hit shreds her low HP, and Alpha Strike's untargetable blink dodges both her snare and her R reflect window."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"9/10","why":"Two on-hit items plus E true damage delete a 0-armor mage in one Highlander reset chain she has no lockdown to interrupt."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are Mel's: her ranged Q auto-attack poke out-ranges you, and you have no Wuju true damage and only Alpha Strike for an escape, so you cannot trade profitably. Farm with Alpha Strike on the caster minions and last-hit with autos, eating chip rather than walking up. Buy early sustain (second Doran's / pots) so her Q can't shove you off the wave.","mid":"Levels 4-6 you stabilize hard. Max E Wuju Style for true damage that ignores her lack of armor, and use W Meditate after a trade to heal back the Q chip. At 6 Highlander is your first real fight button — its slow immunity means her W Solar Snare slow no longer kites you, and any kill refreshes it to chain.","late":"At 2+ items (Kraken Slayer + BORK/Wit's End) you are a 1v9 hyper-carry into her. She has no hard CC to peel a fed Yi: you E on, Alpha Strike through her R reflect and W root, and on-hit melts her squishy frame in under a Highlander window, resetting to her team.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push you can freeze just outside her tower so she has to walk up into Alpha-Strike range to farm. Worst wave: a wave shoved into your tower early, letting her Q poke you freely while you can't reach the minions. Crash timing: crash the wave into her tower right as your first on-hit item finishes so you can dive or zone her off the rebound.","cooldowns":"Track her W Solar Snare (the root/slow zone) and her R Rebuttal — those are the only tools that punish your Alpha Strike commit; her Q is just poke.","trading":"Trade only by E-ing on, Alpha Striking IN (not out) so the untargetable frames eat her Q/snare, landing a Double Strike auto, then Meditate to heal — never sit at range trading autos into her Q.","spikes":"Mel spikes at levels 1-3 and whenever R is up; you spike at 6 (Highlander), at first on-hit item, and overwhelmingly at 2 items.","feeding":"If you feed her early she snowballs poke into a permanent zone and her R becomes a hard counter to your all-in burst — but she's still squishy, so one good Alpha-in onto her after a JG gank flips it back fast.","carry":"Once ahead you don't need the lane — Highlander resets let you Alpha Strike sidelane creeps and roam, and you delete her or any squishy on sight in a 5v5 because she can't lock you down.","difficulty":"It's only a 3/10 because the early poke is annoying but Mel has no hard CC, no escape, and a squishy frame — everything that actually beats Yi (lockdown, kiting, armor) she lacks, so surviving to items is the whole game."},"focus":{"text":"Mel's W Solar Snare — the root/slow zone is the only thing that holds you still long enough for her or a ganking jungler to punish a committed Alpha Strike, so bait or Alpha-through it before you all-in. Respect her R Rebuttal reflecting your burst, but the snare is what kills you.","letters":["W","R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Alpha Strike INTO her","d":"Use Q's untargetable blink to close the gap through her snare and R window — you take zero damage during the dash and arrive in true-damage range."},{"t":"Max E and respect items","d":"Wuju Style true damage ignores her armorless squishy frame; just survive to Kraken/BORK and the lane flips permanently in your favor."},{"t":"Meditate after every trade","d":"W heals back her Q poke between waves so she can never chip you to a killable threshold before you itemize."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't auto-trade at range","d":"Standing in her Q range trading autos loses every time — her poke out-ranges you and you have no answer until you're on top of her."},{"t":"Don't Alpha into her active R","d":"Committing your full E+Alpha burst while Rebuttal is up reflects it back and can flip the all-in; wait the reflect out or bait it on a minion."},{"t":"Don't overstay vs ganks","d":"Pre-6 you only have Alpha Strike to escape, and her W snare sets up the jungler — back off if you don't see the enemy JG."}],"tradeGood":"E Wuju Style on, Alpha Strike directly into her to dodge the snare, land a Double Strike auto, and Meditate the Q chip — a one-sided true-damage burst she can't kite.","tradeBad":"Standing at auto range trading basics into her ranged Q, or blowing your full Alpha Strike combo while her R Rebuttal is up to reflect it.","ahead":"Once you've got a lead, freeze just out of her tower range so she has to walk into Alpha-Strike distance to farm, and punish every step forward. Use Highlander resets to Alpha-clear the sidelane and roam — she's too immobile to follow and too squishy to survive your return. In teamfights you simply Alpha Strike onto her through any peel and delete her before her R matters.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Mel - Track: Mel's W Solar Snare — the root/slow zone is the only thing that holds you still long enough for her or a ganking jungler to punish a committed Alpha Strike, so bait or Alpha-through it before you all-in. Respect her R Rebuttal reflecting your burst, but the snare is what kills you.. - Farm safely under Mel's ranged Q poke to your first on-hit item, then E Wuju Style on and Alpha Strike straight through her W Solar Snare root so you reach her face — once Highlander is up you out-DPS and run down a 0-armor mage who can only stall, not stop you.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Survive Mel's early Q poke, dodge her Solar Snare with Alpha Strike, and once you hit Kraken/BORK you Highlander onto her and delete a squishy mage who has zero hard lockdown."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Master Yi's win condition is to concede levels 1-3 to Mel's ranged Q poke, farm with Alpha Strike, and survive to his first on-hit item without giving a kill. From there Wuju Style true damage and Highlander's slow immunity let him Alpha Strike through her snare and out-DPS an armorless mage who has no hard CC to stop the reset chain."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Mel owns 1-3 (poke), it evens around 4-5 (Wuju + Meditate), and Yi takes 6 → first item → 2 items decisively as Highlander and on-hit come online."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only by Alpha-Striking IN to use the untargetable frames; never sit at range eating Q. Back off entirely if her R is up or you don't see the enemy jungler. Re-engage freely the moment Kraken/BORK finishes."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Hold the wave near the middle or slow-push to freeze outside her tower so she must step into Alpha range to farm. Avoid letting it shove to your tower where she pokes you off the minions; crash on your item spike to set up a dive."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable blink dodges her W Solar Snare and ducks her R Rebuttal reflect window if timed right. Wuju Style true damage ignores that she builds no armor; Highlander's slow immunity cancels her snare's kite; Meditate out-sustains her single-target Q poke."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (snowballs the on-hit DPS vs her squishy frame) → Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve Conditioning + Overgrowth for the early poke lane, or Sorcery Absolute Focus + Gathering Storm if you're confident surviving. Take the Health/AS/Armor shards — Armor is wasted vs AP, so run a Magic Resist shard instead."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to convert your item-spike all-ins into kills on a squishy with no escape; Teleport is acceptable only if you expect to get poked off the wave repeatedly and need to stay even in XP."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Open Doran's Blade + sustain. Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit spike, then Wit's End — its on-hit Magic Resist doubles as defense against her AP. Boots: Mercury's Treads to cut her snare-slow and any AP burst. Add Terminus later for the resist/shred; skip armor entirely vs Mel."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"All-in at 6 with Highlander up after she's used R, and decisively at first and second on-hit item. The cleanest windows are right after she wastes W or R on a wave, or when your jungler arrives to bait the snare."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Her W Solar Snare is a free setup for ganks pre-6, so ward and don't overextend without vision. After 6, the same gank flips: Highlander's slow immunity lets you ignore her snare and chase, so call your jungler to dive a squishy with no escape."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The big mistake is trying to win levels 1-3 by trading autos into her Q and getting chunked, or Alpha Striking OUT of a fight instead of IN — wasting the untargetable dodge frames and the on-hit value."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If behind, farm under tower with Alpha Strike, take MR/sustain, and play for scaling — she can't end the lane against you. One Alpha-in after a gank or one good item refunds the deficit because she stays squishy all game."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"When ahead, freeze her out of XP, use Highlander resets to roam and Alpha-clear sidelanes, and in fights blink onto her through any peel — she has no lockdown to stop a fed Yi from chaining resets across her whole team."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED 3/10 difficulty, 9/10 carry — a streaky early lane you survive into a free 1v9 once itemized, because Mel lacks every tool (CC, kite, armor) that actually beats Master Yi."}]},"mordekaiser":{"tldr":"A textbook scaling race: I get bullied off the wave early by Morde's E-into-isolated-Q, but once my on-hit comes online I out-DPS his shield and Alpha Strike dodges the realm-ending CC — survive to two items and the lane is mine.","winCon":"Concede the early, farm with Alpha Strike, and refuse the level 4-6 brawl his W shield-heal wins; once Kraken/BORK + Wit's End come online, out-DPS him in any extended fight, use Alpha Strike's untargetable blink to wait out Realm of Death's lockdown, and reset Highlander off the kill.","enemyWin":"Morde wins by closing the lane before I scale: E pull onto an isolated Q slam plus W sustain stomps my levels 1-5, and a well-timed Realm of Death drags me into a 1v1 where he steals my stats and his shield out-heals my pre-item on-hit before Wit's End ever cuts his AP.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Mordekaiser","rating":"6/10","why":"His single Q at full mana out-trades my low-base auto, and I have no Wuju true damage or Meditate yet to answer the poke."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Mordekaiser","rating":"6/10","why":"At 2 points his E knock-aside sets up the isolated-target Q bonus, and his W shield eats my Double Strike before I can punish."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Mordekaiser","rating":"6/10","why":"Full E-Q combo plus W sustain wins every short trade; my Alpha Strike only resets my swing, it doesn't out-damage his isolation slam yet."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain stabilize me for short E-tradebacks, but his W shield still out-heals a committed all-in."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Highlander answers his ganks and slow, but Realm of Death still wins the forced 1v1 since I have no item DPS to out-race his stolen-stat duel."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken/BORK on-hit plus Alpha Strike's untargetable frames to dodge the realm flip the duel — I out-DPS his shield faster than it heals."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"With Wit's End cutting his AP and on-hit stacked, I shred his W shield, Alpha Strike voids Realm of Death's burst, and Highlander resets snowball the kill."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Morde and you must accept it. His damage is his Q isolated slam — bonus damage when you're alone — and his E pull-and-knock sets that up, so do NOT get dragged off the wave where the lone-target bonus lands full. You have no Wuju true damage and no Meditate ranked yet, so your single Alpha Strike trade just loses to his Q+W. Last-hit with autos, use Alpha Strike to safely farm the back line, and concede CS over taking a slam you can't trade back.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are where he is most dangerous and where you must be most patient. Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain let you back off and reset rather than die, but his W shield still out-heals a full commit, so only trade when he wastes E on the wave. At 6 he gets Realm of Death; respect that he can press it the instant you over-extend. Highlander is your spike here too — it answers his ganks and slow immunity keeps you mobile — but it's a survival tool this stage, not a kill button.","late":"At first item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) the lane inverts. Your on-hit DPS now out-races his W shield's heal, and crucially Alpha Strike's untargetable blink lets you flicker out of Realm of Death's opening burst — bait the realm, Q as it lands, and out-sustain the duel he forced. At 2+ items with Wit's End shredding his MR and his AP, you win every extended fight and Highlander resets chain you across the map.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push you control near your tower so his E pull drags him toward your turret, not you off the wave. Worst wave: a wave shoved into his tower early — he freezes the lone-target Q on you with no escape but Q. Crash timing: crash the wave right before your first-item back so you reset on-hit power without conceding plates.","cooldowns":"Track his E (Death's Grasp pull) — it's his entire engage and isolation setup; when it's down he can't safely force the Q-slam trade. Past 6, track Realm of Death cooldown and never fight when you'd be caught in it without Alpha Strike up.","trading":"Pre-6: trade only when his E is on cooldown — without the pull he can't isolate his Q. Post-item: walk up, eat the E if you must, and Alpha Strike onto him; your ramped on-hit beats his shield heal in any fight longer than two seconds.","spikes":"His spikes: levels 2-3 (E+Q online), level 6 (Realm of Death), and Rylai's/Liandry's first item. Your spikes: level 6 Highlander for survival, then Kraken/BORK first item (DPS flip) and Wit's End second (his AP cut + shield shred).","feeding":"If you fall behind, he becomes a nightmare — a fed Morde's Realm of Death is a guaranteed 1v1 he wins, and your weak early gets exponentially worse. Give up the side lane, farm jungle camps and safe waves, and stall to your two-item power instead of forcing a fight from behind.","carry":"If you're ahead, your snowball is among the fastest in the game: Highlander resets let you Alpha Strike from kill to kill, and once Morde can't 1v1 you, his teamfight (he needs an isolated R target) collapses. Split-push him out and force him to answer you alone where you win.","difficulty":"It rates a 5/10 because the win rate is dead even (48.89%) — it's a clean scaling race with no unfightable mechanic. He owns five of seven stages but your two-item power is so dominant that the lane equalizes; the difficulty is purely the discipline to not die in the long early window."},"focus":{"text":"Realm of Death (R) — it drags you into an isolated 1v1 and steals your stats; before you have items it's a near-guaranteed loss, so it dictates when you can fight. The good news: Alpha Strike makes you untargetable, so timing Q into the realm's opening burst is the single most important play of the matchup.","letters":["R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Stay on the wave","d":"His Q slam only hurts when you're isolated, and his E exists to pull you off it. Last-hit hugging your minions so the lone-target bonus never lands full."},{"t":"Save Alpha Strike for his realm","d":"Once you hit 6 vs his 6, hold Q to blink untargetable through Realm of Death's opening burst — it's your only escape and it voids the worst of his forced duel."},{"t":"Scale to two items, then commit","d":"Kraken/BORK flips the DPS race and Wit's End cuts his AP and shreds his W shield. Don't force the lane until that on-hit is online — then you out-duel him anywhere."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't all-in before first item","d":"His W shield-heal out-sustains your single-ability pre-item trades; a level 3-5 commit dies to E-Q-W even with Meditate up."},{"t":"Don't get caught in the realm dry","d":"Eating Realm of Death with Alpha Strike on cooldown is a free kill for him — he steals your stats and his shield out-heals your raw autos. Never fight near his R without Q ready."},{"t":"Don't rely on Meditate to tank his combo","d":"Meditate's damage reduction is wasted channeling against his ability burst while he just walks up and slams — it's a sustain-between-trades tool, not a panic button mid-fight here."}],"tradeGood":"Post-first-item: bait his E, Alpha Strike onto him as it lands, and grind on-hit autos — your ramped DPS plus Wit's End shred beats his W shield in any fight past two seconds.","tradeBad":"A level 3-5 stand-and-fight after he lands E — his isolated Q plus W shield wins that exchange every time before your on-hit exists.","ahead":"Press it by split-pushing — Morde has no dash to escape you and his teamfight wants an isolated R target, so forcing him to answer you 1v1 is exactly where your itemized on-hit dominates. Use Highlander resets to roam and snowball other lanes between waves, and itemize Wit's End early to permanently neuter his shield and AP. Once he can't trade with you in lane, he's a stat-check you always win.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Mordekaiser - Track: Realm of Death (R) — it drags you into an isolated 1v1 and steals your stats; before you have items it's a near-guaranteed loss, so it dictates when you can fight. The good news: Alpha Strike makes you untargetable, so timing Q into the realm's opening burst is the single most important play of the matchup.. - Concede the early, farm with Alpha Strike, and refuse the level 4-6 brawl his W shield-heal wins; once Kraken/BORK + Wit's End come online, out-DPS him in any extended fight, use Alpha Strike's untargetable blink to wait out Realm of Death's lockdown, and reset Highlander off the kill.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A textbook scaling race: I get bullied off the wave early by Morde's E-into-isolated-Q, but once my on-hit comes online I out-DPS his shield and Alpha Strike dodges the realm-ending CC — survive to two items and the lane is mine."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive the brutal levels 1-5 by farming with Alpha Strike and never fighting off the wave, then reach your on-hit item spike where you out-DPS his W shield in extended fights. Use Alpha Strike's untargetable frames to neuter Realm of Death and let Highlander resets snowball the kill into a global lead."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Morde owns 1-5 (E-Q isolation + W shield), it goes even at 6 (Highlander vs Realm of Death), and flips hard to Yi from first item onward as on-hit out-races his sustain."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Pre-item: only trade when his E is on cooldown, and never stand in a full E-Q-W combo. Post-item: initiate freely — eat the E, Alpha Strike on, and DPS through his shield."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave slow-pushed near your side so his E pulls him toward your tower instead of dragging you out; avoid shoving it under his turret where he can freeze the isolated Q on you."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable blink dodges the opening burst of Realm of Death — the core defensive interaction. Wit's End cuts his AP and shreds his W shield. Meditate is for sustain between trades, not for tanking his ability burst mid-fight."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (his shield rewards sustained on-hit over burst) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve — Conditioning or Second Wind into his AP poke, plus the scaling HP and adaptive shards. Take Magic Resist shards vs his all-AP profile."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Teleport — you lose the early lane regardless, so TP keeps your CS even after a back and scales you safely to your item spike rather than gambling Ignite on a losing early."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first for the on-hit flip, Wit's End second is near-mandatory here (MR + shield/AP shred), then Terminus or Guinsoo. Build Mercury's Treads and consider a Maw/Hexdrinker against his all-AP burst and Realm of Death."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Realistically only from first item onward, and only with Alpha Strike up to answer his R. Before that, the only 'all-in' is punishing a whiffed E when Wuju Style and Meditate are ranked at 4-5 — and even then back off if his W shield is up."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Your early is gankable and Morde's E pull plus slow set up easy ganks against you — ward the river and play safe levels 1-6. Once you have Highlander, your jungler ganking him is lethal since he has no dash to escape your collapse."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Forcing trades before first item because the matchup is statistically even — it's even because of YOUR scaling, not your early. The other classic error is eating Realm of Death with Alpha Strike on cooldown."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Give up the side lane entirely, farm safe waves and jungle camps to hit two items, and avoid any spot where he can isolate his R on you. Let Wit's End and on-hit close the gap — your curve recovers harder than his does."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Split-push to force him into the 1v1 he loses, use Highlander resets to roam between waves, and rush Wit's End to permanently break his shield. He has no escape, so every time he answers you alone it's a kill."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A dead-even scaling race (48.89%) — Morde owns the long early, but Yi's two-item on-hit and Alpha Strike's realm-dodge make the late lane his; pure patience check, 5/10 to play."}]},"nasus":{"tldr":"You survive a soft early lane against a leveling Nasus, then your on-hit item spike turns him into farm — Alpha Strike dodges his W Wither and you out-DPS him before his Q stacks matter.","winCon":"Use Alpha Strike and Wuju autos to farm safely through levels 1-5, deny his Q stacks by trading when he last-hits, then hit your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) and run him down before he stacks into a late-game monster. Every kill on him is double value: it refreshes Highlander AND starves the one champion in the game who only scales by farming.","enemyWin":"If you AFK-farm and let him reach 200+ Q stacks, he Withers your attack speed to zero, walks onto you, and one-shots with stacked Siphoning Strike while his R lifesteal out-sustains your damage. He also wins every gank where W lands on you mid-Alpha-Strike-cooldown.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"3/10","carryRating":"9/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Nasus","rating":"6/10","why":"Level 1 with no items, your short range and lone Alpha Strike lose to a Q auto-cancel, so he can chunk you and start stacking uncontested."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"With E Wuju Style unlocked you can answer his Siphoning Strike auto-cancels with a quick true-damage trade, evening the lane."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Master Yi","rating":"5/10","why":"Level 3 you have Q+E+W: Alpha Strike in, Wuju true damage burst, Meditate the return, and his only answer is a non-leveled W."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Levels 4-5 Wuju Style true damage ignores his early armor and Meditate out-sustains his pre-R drain, so short trades favor you."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's attack speed and slow immunity let you ignore his W Wither slow component and chase him off the wave."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"Kraken Slayer / BORK on-hit shreds him faster than his Q stacks have scaled, and Alpha Strike makes you untargetable through his W cast."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Nasus","rating":"7/10","why":"If he free-farmed, his stacked Q plus R lifesteal and armor reclaim the duel — his Wither cripples your DPS and he out-sustains you at full build."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are the only window Nasus is favored: he has range parity on you, his Q auto-cancel hits harder than your base autos, and he wants to stack Siphoning Strike uncontested. Do not contest the first three waves for kills — farm with Alpha Strike and the occasional Wuju auto, and accept losing a little CS to deny him free stacks by stepping in when he goes for a Q last-hit. He has no kill pressure on you here unless his jungler shows.","mid":"At level 4 Wuju Style's true damage starts ignoring his armor and Meditate begins out-sustaining his pre-ult drain, so you can start taking short E-empowered trades. Level 6 Highlander is your turning point — the attack speed and slow immunity mean his W Wither barely slows your chase, and you can answer his aggression instead of conceding it.","late":"At 2+ items YOU spike first: Kraken/BORK on-hit melts his health bar faster than his Q has scaled, and you should be ending the game in this window. But if you let it go long and he free-farmed to 300+ stacks, this stage flips to Nasus — his stacked Q one-shots, R lifesteal out-heals your DPS, and his Wither shuts off your attack speed. Close before that.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push you control so you can deny his Q last-hits and step up for E trades. Worst wave: a fast-pushing wave that shoves into his tower, letting him free-farm stacks safely under turret. Crash timing: crash on level 6 and again on your first-item back so you can recall, spike, and return before he stacks through the window.","cooldowns":"Track W Wither (around 15s at rank 1) — it's his only kiting/peel tool and his entire gank setup; if it's down you can all-in freely, and you should bait it before committing Alpha Strike.","trading":"Trade in short E-Wuju-Style bursts: walk up when his Q is on cooldown or spent on a minion, land a true-damage auto sequence, and disengage before he can W you and auto-cancel back. Never sit in an extended slugfest pre-6 where his Q resets keep landing.","spikes":"Your spikes: level 6 Highlander, then first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK). His spikes: Q stack thresholds (~100, ~200 stacks) and 6 for R lifesteal/size — every minute you delay him is a stack he doesn't get.","feeding":"If you fall behind, his Wither plus stacked Q deletes you and he becomes unkillable with R lifesteal. A behind Yi vs a fed Nasus is one of the worst spots on the map — you can't out-DPS the lifesteal and can't escape the Wither slow without R up.","carry":"If ahead, you've denied the one champion who scales purely by farming — roam with Highlander's movement speed to snowball other lanes, and use your on-hit lead to solo-kill him whenever his W is down. Your reset-chaining in fights ends games fast.","difficulty":"It's a low-difficulty 3/10 because your scaling outpaces his stacking timeline and Alpha Strike answers his only disruptive tool (W) — the only way to lose is to AFK-farm and let him reach his stack power spike."},"focus":{"text":"W Wither — it slows your move AND attack speed to a crawl, which is the only thing that turns off your on-hit DPS and sets up his all-in or a gank. Bait it or save Alpha Strike to negate it.","letters":["W"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Deny his Q stacks","d":"Step up and trade when he winds up a Siphoning Strike last-hit; every stack you deny pushes his power spike out of the game. Starving Nasus is your real win condition."},{"t":"Alpha Strike through his W","d":"Time Q so you go untargetable as he casts Wither — you eat no slow, reset your attack timer, and come out of it still at full attack speed."},{"t":"End on your item spike","d":"Once Kraken or BORK comes online you out-DPS him hard — force fights and close the game in that window before his stacks catch up."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't AFK-farm the lane","d":"A passive Yi who lets Nasus free-stack hands him the one thing he needs to win — uncontested farm. Pressure him off CS, don't ignore him."},{"t":"Don't all-in while W is up","d":"If he hasn't used Wither, your attack speed gets gutted mid-fight; bait the W or wait for its cooldown before committing Alpha Strike."},{"t":"Don't let it go ultra-late even","d":"At full stacks his Q + R lifesteal reclaim the duel. Don't trust the 2+ item flip if he free-farmed — group and end instead of dueling a 400-stack Nasus."}],"tradeGood":"Walk up with E Wuju Style active right after he spends his Q on a minion, land a true-damage auto burst, and Meditate the chip back before his Wither comes off cooldown.","tradeBad":"A sustained toe-to-toe fight where his W Wither lands first — your attack speed and chase die, his Q resets keep chunking you, and you can't disengage through the slow.","ahead":"Pressing a lead here means roaming — Highlander's movement speed lets you snowball other lanes while Nasus is stuck farming, which compounds because he can't impact the map until he's stacked. Whenever his W is down, walk up and solo-kill him to deny even more stacks, and use your on-hit lead to take Herald/towers. Every plate and kill you take is tempo he can never get back.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Nasus - Track: W Wither — it slows your move AND attack speed to a crawl, which is the only thing that turns off your on-hit DPS and sets up his all-in or a gank. Bait it or save Alpha Strike to negate it.. - Use Alpha Strike and Wuju autos to farm safely through levels 1-5, deny his Q stacks by trading when he last-hits, then hit your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) and run him down before he stacks into a late-game monster. Every kill on him is double value: it refreshes Highlander AND starves the one champion in the game who only scales by farming.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"You survive a soft early lane against a leveling Nasus, then your on-hit item spike turns him into farm — Alpha Strike dodges his W Wither and you out-DPS him before his Q stacks matter."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive the soft levels 1-3 by farming with Alpha Strike instead of contesting, then spike on level 6 and your first on-hit item to out-DPS him before his Q stacks scale. The lane is a race between your itemization and his stacking — you win it by denying his farm and ending before late game."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Nasus edges 1-2, even at 3, Yi pulls ahead 4-5, owns 6 through first item, and only loses the 2+ item window if Nasus was allowed to free-farm to full stacks."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade in short E-empowered bursts when his Q is spent or W is down; back off the instant Wither lands or his Q is up for a reset. Never extended-fight pre-6."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Hold a slow push you control to deny his Q last-hits; avoid shoving him under tower where he free-stacks. Crash on your spike timings to recall and return ahead."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability lets you dodge his W Wither cast entirely, and the cast resets your attack timer; Wuju Style's true damage ignores the armor he builds; Meditate out-sustains his pre-R drain; Highlander's slow immunity negates Wither's slow on the chase."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (uptime to power your on-hit) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Sorcery Nimbus Cloak + Gathering Storm, or Resolve Conditioning vs his late-game burst. He's AD, so favor Alacrity over armor runes since you out-scale."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to convert your first-item spike into a solo kill and cut his R lifesteal with Grievous Wounds; Teleport is fine if you'd rather scale safely and not contest the soft early lane."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Open Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit spike that beats his stack timeline, then Wit's End or Terminus for sustained DPS and resists; rush Executioner's/Mortal Reminder antiheal to cut his R lifesteal, Berserker's Greaves, and a defensive third (Death's Dance / Maw) vs his stacked Q burst."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"All-in at level 6 with Highlander up and his W on cooldown, and again the moment your first on-hit item completes — those are your two clean kill windows before he's tanky."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Ganks are his best path to a lead because his W setting up the slow guarantees the kill if you've used Alpha Strike — ward your flank and hold Q as a gank-escape, not a poke tool. Your own jungler dives him easily since he has no escape and you provide the slow-immune chase."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi mistake here is treating it as a free lane and AFK-farming — that hands Nasus exactly the uncontested stacks he needs, turning a 3/10 lane into an unwinnable late game."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you fall behind, give up the duel entirely — farm side lanes with Highlander mobility, build antiheal early, and never 1v1 a stacked Nasus whose Wither shuts off your DPS; win through teamfight resets instead."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If ahead, roam to snowball other lanes and take objectives while he's stuck farming, solo-kill him whenever W is down, and end the game before his stack curve catches your item curve."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED, 54.9% — a 3/10 lane Yi wins by denying stacks and spiking first, losing only the ultra-late window to a free-farmed Nasus."}]},"nautilus":{"tldr":"A grindy even lane where Nautilus's chain-CC keeps you off him early, but once your on-hit items come online you out-DPS the tank and Alpha Strike dodges everything he throws.","winCon":"Farm safely through levels 1-5 with Alpha Strike and concede his early CC dominance, then hit your Kraken/BORK spike and use Alpha Strike's untargetability to phase through his Q hook and R Depth Charge while your on-hit true damage shreds his tank stack in the extended fight.","enemyWin":"Nautilus wins by chaining his passive root, Dredge Line hook, and Depth Charge knockup to lock you in place — every point-and-click CC catches you the instant Alpha Strike ends, and a jungler arriving on his hook turns the lockdown into a kill before you scale.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Nautilus","rating":"6/10","why":"Nautilus's tank base stats and passive root on his first auto beat your short range and one ability — you have no Q reset value off a single target and no Wuju true damage yet."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Nautilus","rating":"6/10","why":"With Dredge Line (Q) up he hooks you in and his passive root holds you for free autos, and you have no Meditate to sustain it back yet."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Nautilus","rating":"5/10","why":"You get Wuju Style (E) true damage and Meditate for short bursts, but his Riptide (E) AOE slow plus the passive root still keep you from sticking on him."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain let you trade shorts, but it comes down to whether you Alpha Strike his hook or eat it into a Riptide chain."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Highlander (R) gives you slow immunity to ignore his Riptide slow, but his Depth Charge (R) knockup answers your all-in — it's a read on who commits first."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King on-hit DPS now chunks his tank HP faster than he can lock you, and Wuju true damage ignores his armor stack."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"At 2+ items you out-DPS the tank outright — Alpha Strike phases his hook and Depth Charge, Highlander resets chain his deaths, and Meditate out-sustains his only-poke kit."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Nautilus and you have to accept it. His Staggering Blow passive roots you on his first auto, so any time you walk up to last-hit he can hook with Dredge Line (Q), pull you in, and root-auto you for free while your short range and lone Alpha Strike can't punish a tank. Farm with Alpha Strike on the wave from range, never stand in hook range at low HP, and treat every step forward as a chance for him to land Q into a jungler.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you stabilize as Wuju Style (E) true damage and Meditate (W) sustain come online, letting you take short trades and heal his poke back. Level 6 is the real swing: Highlander (R) gives slow immunity so his Riptide (E) slow can't kite you off, but his own Depth Charge (R) is a guaranteed single-target knockup that catches you the moment Alpha Strike ends. Don't all-in here unless his R is down — it's a coinflip read until your items arrive.","late":"At 2+ items the lane flips to you for good. Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King plus Wuju Style true damage out-DPS his tank stat line faster than his cooldowns can lock you, and Alpha Strike's untargetable window phases straight through his Q hook and Depth Charge. Highlander resets chain through any pick, and Meditate out-sustains a kit that's pure poke with no execute. A tank with no kite tools is exactly what you farm in the late side-lane 1v1.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push you control so you fight at your turret where his hook into a jungler is the riskiest play, not yours. Worst wave: a wave shoved into his turret early, where he hooks you under tower with passive-root and Riptide and a gank has nowhere to run. Crash timing: crash the wave just before your first-item spike so you reset, buy Kraken/BORK, and return to a freezing-range lane where his Q hook is your only threat to dodge.","cooldowns":"Track Dredge Line (Q hook) above all — it's his only engage and gap-closer, and on cooldown he is a stationary tank you walk onto; secondarily watch Depth Charge (R), the only CC Alpha Strike can't out-position.","trading":"Bait his Dredge Line hook or his Riptide first, then once they're down Alpha Strike onto him, Wuju-auto with true damage, and Meditate the chip back; never trade while his passive auto can root you into a full Riptide-hook-R chain.","spikes":"Yours: First item (Kraken/BORK) and 2+ items where on-hit melts his HP. His: levels 1-3 raw CC dominance and level 6 Depth Charge as the single tool that beats your all-in.","feeding":"If you die to a hook-gank you fall behind on the one thing that matters — items — and a fed Nautilus just becomes an unkillable CC bot who locks you for your team to clean up; play hyper-safe, farm with Alpha Strike from max range, and scale.","carry":"If you hit your item spike ahead, you don't just win lane — you become a 1v9 on-hit monster, using Alpha Strike to dodge enemy CC and Highlander resets to chain through the whole team while his tank body can only land one knockup.","difficulty":"It's a true 5/10: his chain-CC hard-counters your only-escape-is-Q identity early, but he brings zero kite and zero anti-heal, so your scaling reclaims the lane cleanly — the skill is surviving the hook phase, not winning it."},"focus":{"text":"Dredge Line (Q) — his hook is the only thing that catches you; it pulls you into passive-root range for a full Riptide and Depth Charge chain, and it's his sole gank-setup tool. Bait it or sidestep it and he's a stationary tank you farm.","letters":["Q"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike from range","d":"Use Q to clear caster minions and harass from outside hook range so you scale safely without ever feeding his Dredge Line a target."},{"t":"Dodge his hook with Alpha Strike","d":"When you do commit, time Alpha Strike's untargetable blink to phase his Q hook or Depth Charge knockup, then land on top of him with Wuju true damage up."},{"t":"Rush your on-hit spike","d":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King is the moment the lane flips — prioritize it, because Wuju true damage shreds his armor stack the instant you out-item him."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't step into hook range low","d":"Walking up to last-hit at low HP lets him Dredge Line you into a passive-root, Riptide, and a waiting jungler — the one way this even lane becomes a lost one."},{"t":"Don't all-in into his ult","d":"Depth Charge is a guaranteed single-target knockup that catches you after Alpha Strike ends; never commit your kit while his R is up unless you can dodge it."},{"t":"Don't trade through his passive root","d":"His first auto roots you — if you brawl in his auto range you get held in place for a full CC chain, so only fight after baiting his hook out."}],"tradeGood":"Bait his Dredge Line hook out, then Alpha Strike in with Wuju Style true damage active and Meditate the return chip — chunking the tank while his only engage is on cooldown.","tradeBad":"Walking into Dredge Line range at low HP and eating the hook into passive-root, Riptide, and Depth Charge — a full CC chain you can't Alpha Strike out of once it starts.","ahead":"Press a lead by forcing the side-lane 1v1 the moment your first item lands — a Nautilus with no kite can't escape your on-hit DPS once his hook is down, so bait it and all-in. Use the gold to rush your second on-hit item and snowball the scaling gap rather than diving his tower into a hook. Roam with Highlander's move speed to convert your lane lead into picks elsewhere, since your kit out-fights the rest of his squishier team harder than it out-farms him.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Nautilus - Track: Dredge Line (Q) — his hook is the only thing that catches you; it pulls you into passive-root range for a full Riptide and Depth Charge chain, and it's his sole gank-setup tool. Bait it or sidestep it and he's a stationary tank you farm.. - Farm safely through levels 1-5 with Alpha Strike and concede his early CC dominance, then hit your Kraken/BORK spike and use Alpha Strike's untargetability to phase through his Q hook and R Depth Charge while your on-hit true damage shreds his tank stack in the extended fight.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A grindy even lane where Nautilus's chain-CC keeps you off him early, but once your on-hit items come online you out-DPS the tank and Alpha Strike dodges everything he throws."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive the levels 1-5 CC phase by farming with Alpha Strike from outside Dredge Line range, then hit your Kraken/BORK spike and turn the tank into a free target. Your win condition is the extended fight at 2+ items where Wuju true damage out-DPSes his armor and Alpha Strike phases every piece of his lockdown."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Nautilus owns 1-3 on CC and tank stats, the lane evens out 4-6 as Wuju/Meditate/Highlander come online, and shifts hard to Master Yi from first item onward as on-hit DPS overtakes his tankiness."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only after his Dredge Line hook is on cooldown; back off entirely while his passive auto-root or Riptide are available, since a single landed auto chains into his full CC combo."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave slow-pushing or frozen near your side so his hook is the high-risk play, not yours; avoid shoving into his tower where a hook-gank has no escape route, and crash for your item spikes."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable window dodges Dredge Line and Depth Charge if timed; Highlander's slow immunity ignores his Riptide slow; Wuju Style true damage ignores his stacked armor; his Staggering Blow passive roots you to enable the chain — the whole matchup is your Q's i-frames versus his point-and-click CC."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for fastest on-hit ramp against a tank's HP pool, with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, and Last Stand or Cut Down (he stacks HP); secondary Resolve (Conditioning/Overgrowth) or Sorcery (Celerity/Waterwalking) — take Bone Plating into his auto-root pressure if you struggle early."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite to push your kill pressure once you out-item him and to deny a tank's natural sustain; take Flash plus Teleport instead if you want to scale safely and stay even through the hook phase rather than fighting for early kills."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first for on-hit shred of his tank HP, Wit's End or Terminus second versus a tank stacking resists, then Berserker's Greaves; he's AD/tank so prioritize raw DPS over defensive boots and lean Mercury's only if his team adds magic CC."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"All-in only when Dredge Line is on cooldown AND his Depth Charge is down — that's the gap where you Alpha Strike on, Wuju-shred him, and Meditate the chip; from first item onward those windows become kills."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"His Dredge Line is a perfect gank-setup tool, so his jungler swings this lane hard early — ward his hook approaches and play back until you have escape uptime; once you're itemized, his ganks matter less because you can Alpha Strike the collapse and Highlander out."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players walk into hook range to greed last-hits or try to win the level 1-3 trade — both feed his CC chain and a gank; the lane is a scaling exercise, not an early fight, so farm with Q and wait for items."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're behind, farm with Alpha Strike from max range, never contest a wave inside hook range, and stack on-hit items — you scale through almost any deficit, and a tank with no execute can't close you out, so just don't die to the hook."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If ahead, force the side-lane 1v1 to repeatedly bait and punish his hook, rush your second on-hit item, and use Highlander's move speed and reset to roam and snowball the rest of the map your kit dominates harder than the lane."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"An even 48.87% lane: Nautilus's chain-CC hard-counters your early identity, but his lack of kite and anti-heal hands the scaling, and the win, to Master Yi once your on-hit items come online."}]},"neeko":{"tldr":"A losing scaling race where Neeko's point-and-click E root plus AOE R stun catch you the instant Alpha Strike ends, killing you long before your on-hit items come online.","winCon":"Survive the first 8 levels by farming with Alpha Strike from max range, never overextending past river, and reach Kraken/BORK with full HP and even CS — then dodge her R stun with Q in fights and out-DPS her squishy body. You don't win this lane; you out-scale it, so the whole job is denying her the early picks that would end the game before you spike.","enemyWin":"Neeko lands E root point-blank (or off a Q poke) the moment your untargetable Alpha Strike resolves, then R AOE-stuns and bursts you while you're locked down, repeating it through a jungler. She also pokes you off the wave with Q so you can never trade or scale to your item spike.","diff":"HARD","tone":"#ff5d6c","diffRating":"8/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Neeko","rating":"7/10","why":"Neeko's Q poke and tankier base trades beat your level-1 short range; you have no E true damage or escape yet, so you can only walk up to last-hit and eat free Q chunks."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Neeko","rating":"7/10","why":"At 2 points she has Q+E and can root-poke you off the wave; your Alpha Strike still only blinks and resets autos but leaves you immobile and targetable the second it ends."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Neeko","rating":"7/10","why":"Her E root into Q combo deals real burst by level 3 while your Wuju Style true damage isn't online yet to punish her squishiness in a short trade."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Neeko","rating":"7/10","why":"Wuju Style and Meditate let you sustain Q poke, but any E root catches you flat and her R is one level away — you sustain, you don't trade favorably."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Neeko","rating":"8/10","why":"Neeko's R AOE stun + E root is a point-and-click kill on you the instant Alpha Strike resolves; Highlander's slow immunity doesn't break a stun or root, so this is her cleanest kill window."},{"label":"First item","side":"Neeko","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken/BORK spike your on-hit DPS so you can finally burst her squishy body — but only if you dodge R with Alpha Strike's untargetable frames; eat the stun and you still die first."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"With two on-hit items and Highlander resets you out-DPS her paper body in any fight where you Q her R/E; she stays a threat only if she lands first pick from fog before you commit."}],"breakdown":{"early":"You lose every level 1-3 trade: Neeko out-ranges you with Q poke, is tankier early, and her E root point-blanks you for a guaranteed punish. Alpha Strike makes you untargetable mid-blink but you're fully exposed the moment it ends, and you have no Wuju true damage online yet to make a short trade worth it. Walk up only to last-hit, take the poke, and concede the lane — surviving even is a win here.","mid":"Levels 4-5 Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain let you out-heal her Q poke, but a landed E root still chains into burst you can't answer. Level 6 is her power spike, not yours: R AOE stun + E is a point-and-click lockdown that kills you before Highlander matters, since the ult's slow immunity does nothing against stun or root. Hold Q purely as a CC-dodge here, not as a trade tool.","late":"At 2+ items (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King online) you finally out-DPS her squishy AP body and Highlander resets let you chain kills in teamfights. The entire fight hinges on saving Alpha Strike for the untargetable frames during her R cast — dodge the stun and she melts; eat it and you're still a free kill. Buy a QSS/Mercurial component the moment her lockdown is one-shotting you.","wave":"Best wave: slow-pushed toward you or frozen near your tower so you farm safely under turret and deny her any pick angle. Worst wave: a shoved wave near her tower or river where her E root plus a jungle gank traps you with only Alpha Strike to escape. Crash timing: only crash when she has backed or her R/E are down so you can recall or path to scuttle without being caught immobile.","cooldowns":"Track Neeko's E (Tangle-Barbs root) above all — it's the point-and-click that catches you after Alpha Strike — and her R (Pop! AOE stun) once she hits 6; if both are down she has no way to lock you, and that's your only safe trade window.","trading":"Short trade only when her E is on cooldown: Alpha Strike in, Wuju Style true-damage autos, then walk out before her Q poke resets. Never extend a trade hoping for a kill pre-item — she just E-roots and the trade flips. Most of the lane you simply farm and refuse to trade.","spikes":"Neeko spikes hard at level 6 (R stun lockdown) and with any Lich Bane/Liandry's first-item burst. You spike at level 6 only defensively (Highlander dodges ganks), then truly at first on-hit item and decisively at 2+ items — her spike comes first and is sharper in lane.","feeding":"If you fall behind, her R one-shots you through Alpha Strike if you mistime it, and she snowballs picks across the map with her clone disguise. A fed Neeko ends the game in the window before your items, so a deficit here is far more dangerous than a normal lane loss — play for CS and a late reset, not comebacks.","carry":"If you hit your item spike even, you become the win condition: split or group, force fights where you Q-dodge her R, and chain Highlander resets through her squishy team. Your carry ceiling is high precisely because she's so killable once you reach her.","difficulty":"It's 8/10 because she has point-and-click CC (E root) and AOE lockdown (R stun) that ignore your only defensive tool — Alpha Strike's untargetability ends the instant the blink does, and Highlander's slow immunity doesn't stop a stun or root. She out-ranges, out-trades, and out-picks you for the entire window before your items, which is exactly when junglers collapse on the weak early Yi."},"focus":{"text":"Neeko's R (Pop!) — the AOE stun that locks you the instant Alpha Strike's untargetable frames end, setting up a guaranteed kill before your items come online; save Q to dodge its cast.","letters":["R","E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike, concede the lane","d":"Use Q from max range to safe-farm and accept you lose the matchup pre-items; an even CS Yi at first item is a won game, an overextended dead Yi is a lost one."},{"t":"Save Q to dodge her R and E","d":"Treat Alpha Strike as a defensive untargetable button, not a damage tool — blink during her R (Pop!) cast or E throw so the stun/root whiffs, then commit."},{"t":"Buy QSS the second she one-shots you","d":"Mercurial Scimitar or a QSS component cleanses her R stun and E root, turning her lockdown kill into a fight you win with on-hit DPS."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't trade into a healthy E","d":"Her Tangle-Barbs root is point-and-click after your blink ends — if E is up and you walk in, the trade flips and she bursts you for free."},{"t":"Don't trust Alpha Strike to escape a gank","d":"It only blinks between nearby enemies and leaves you immobile and targetable on landing; with a jungler waiting she E-roots you the moment Q resolves."},{"t":"Don't push the wave without R/E tracked","d":"Shoving past river while her E or R is up plus jungle pressure is the exact pick she wants — you have no escape but Q and it won't save you from a stun."}],"tradeGood":"Alpha Strike in while her E is on cooldown, Wuju Style true-damage autos onto her squishy body, then walk out before her Q poke and root come back up.","tradeBad":"Walking up to trade while her E (Tangle-Barbs) is available — the root catches you flat the instant Alpha Strike ends and chains into burst you can't survive pre-item.","ahead":"If you get ahead, you've solved the lane: keep her shoved in and deny her any pick angle, since a behind Neeko can't burst you and her clone tricks stop working when she's too weak to follow up. Group or split to force fights where you Alpha-Strike-dodge her R, then chain Highlander resets through her paper-thin team. Press the tempo before she out-scales into a Lich Bane teamfight ult, because her R only gets more lethal the longer the game goes.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Neeko - Track: Neeko's R (Pop!) — the AOE stun that locks you the instant Alpha Strike's untargetable frames end, setting up a guaranteed kill before your items come online; save Q to dodge its cast.. - Survive the first 8 levels by farming with Alpha Strike from max range, never overextending past river, and reach Kraken/BORK with full HP and even CS — then dodge her R stun with Q in fights and out-DPS her squishy body. You don't win this lane; you out-scale it, so the whole job is denying her the early picks that would end the game before you spike.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A losing scaling race where Neeko's point-and-click E root plus AOE R stun catch you the instant Alpha Strike ends, killing you long before your on-hit items come online."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive the early lane even on CS by farming with Alpha Strike from range and never overextending into her E-root-plus-gank range, then reach Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King with full HP. From there you out-DPS her squishy AP body in any fight where you save Q to dodge her R stun, and Highlander resets let you snowball that single won fight into the game."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Neeko owns levels 1 through 6 (poke, root, then R lockdown); favor only crosses to you at first on-hit item and tilts decisively yours at 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only when her E (Tangle-Barbs) is on cooldown — Alpha Strike in, Wuju autos, leave. Back off entirely whenever E is up or she's level 6+ with R available, since her point-and-click CC flips any trade you start."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave slow-pushing to you or frozen near your tower so you farm safely and give her no pick window; never hard-shove past river without her R and E tracked and your jungler's position known, because your only escape is a blink that lands you immobile."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"The whole lane is Alpha Strike's untargetable frames versus her E root and R stun: you can blink-dodge the R (Pop!) cast and the E throw if timed right, but the instant the blink resolves you're targetable and immobile, and Highlander's slow immunity does NOT break a stun or root — so a landed E or R is a guaranteed punish. Meditate out-sustains her Q poke but does nothing against burst after a root."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (faster on-hit ramp to hit your item-spike DPS) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, and Last Stand or Coup de Grace; secondary Resolve with Conditioning/Overgrowth or Second Wind plus Bone Plating to survive her AP poke and root burst. Take Second Wind specifically to blunt her Q harass in lane."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ghost is standard for the scaling skirmisher, but vs a pick-mage who beats you early, Flash + Teleport is the safer pick to stay even on CS and recover after a lost trade; take Ignite only if you have a jungler set up to dive her before 6."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for your on-hit spike, then Wit's End for magic resist into her AP burst (doubles as DPS); build Mercurial Scimitar/QSS once her R stun and E root are one-shotting you, and take Mercury's Treads for the tenacity. Terminus is a strong third for the resist-shred-plus-MR profile against her."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You can only all-in when her E AND R are both on cooldown and you have an item online — then Alpha Strike in, Wuju true damage, and Highlander her down. Before items, there is effectively no all-in window for you; you survive, you don't dive."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"This is where the lane is lost: you're a weak, immobile early-laner and Neeko's E root sets up a free gank with only a blink to escape, so a ganking enemy jungler ends you. Demand your own jungler track hers and ward river religiously; if you fall behind to a dive, the game can be over before your spike."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players use Alpha Strike as an engage/damage tool and get rooted the instant it ends, or they overextend to farm and get picked by E-plus-jungler. The fix is treating Q purely as a defensive untargetable button and accepting a passive, even-CS lane until items."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Farm side lanes safely with Alpha Strike, never face-check her clone, and stack on-hit items to claw back your scaling. Avoid every fight where her R or E is up; your comeback is reaching 2+ items alive, not winning skirmishes while behind."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Once ahead, deny her any pick angle by keeping her shoved, then force objective fights where you dodge her R and reset Highlander through her team. Close before her late-game Lich Bane teamfight ult out-scales you — your snowball window is the item-spike midgame."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"HARD (45.35% WR): Neeko's point-and-click root and AOE stun beat your only escape and out-pick you for the entire pre-item window — survive even, save Q for her R, itemize QSS/MR, and your scaling does the rest."}]},"olaf":{"tldr":"A losing scaler-vs-bruiser lane: Olaf's axe-slow, lifesteal, and CC-immune Ragnarok let him run you down through every weak Yi window before your on-hit items ever come online.","winCon":"Survive — farm with Alpha Strike from max range, dodge his Undertow axes so he can't slow-and-chase, and refuse the all-in until you have Kraken/BORK plus anti-heal. Your only real path is to scale past lane and let a fed Olaf get kited by your team while you out-DPS the rest.","enemyWin":"Olaf walks you down with Undertow slows and Reckless Swing true damage before level 6, then at 6 pops Ragnarok to become CC-immune and unkillable-through-shields, chasing you through Alpha Strike and Highlander while Meditate can't out-sustain his lifesteal-fed true damage.","diff":"HARD","tone":"#ff5d6c","diffRating":"8/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Olaf","rating":"7/10","why":"Olaf's level-1 Undertow slow plus auto out-damages you before E Wuju Style or any item exists, and you have no escape but Q."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Olaf","rating":"7/10","why":"With a second point in Undertow he slows you on a missed-axe pickup and Reckless Swing chunks you with true damage you can't armor through."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Olaf","rating":"7/10","why":"He out-sustains your early Wuju autos with lifesteal and the axe slow means you can never disengage a trade you start."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Olaf","rating":"6/10","why":"Your Wuju Style true damage and Meditate come online, but his lifesteal plus Reckless Swing still wins the extended swing and he picks the trade by walking you down with the slow."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Olaf","rating":"8/10","why":"Ragnarok makes him CC-immune and deals true damage through shields — your Highlander can't outrun him and Alpha Strike's blink doesn't break his chase, so this is his hardest spike against you."},{"label":"First item","side":"Olaf","rating":"6/10","why":"His first bruiser item (Black Cleaver/Trinity) plus lifesteal still beats your Kraken/BORK first item in a straight duel since his true damage ignores any armor or defensive piece you bought."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"At two-plus on-hit items your Alpha Strike on-hit DPS finally out-races his sustain in a kited fight — but only if you space the Undertow and never duel him while Ragnarok is up."}],"breakdown":{"early":"This is one of your worst early lanes. Olaf has axe-slow and lifesteal from level 1 while you have short range, no escape but Alpha Strike, and almost no base damage — every walk-up trade he wins. Do not auto-trade; use Alpha Strike purely to last-hit and to blink out if he commits, and hold your wave near tower so a missed Undertow pickup doesn't let him slow-chase you to death.","mid":"Levels 4-5 your Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain let you contest short swaps, but his lifesteal plus Reckless Swing still wins the long fight, and the slow means he chooses every engagement. Level 6 is his peak against you, not yours — Ragnarok gives CC-immunity and true damage that ignores shields, so Highlander's move speed can't kite him out and Meditate's mitigation gets shredded. Concede the level-6 all-in.","late":"At two-plus on-hit items (Kraken/BORK into Wit's End or Terminus) you finally flip the duel — Alpha Strike's untargetable blink lets you reposition mid-fight and your on-hit DPS out-paces his sustain IF you keep spacing his Undertow and never fight inside his Ragnarok window. In teamfights you sidestep him entirely and farm the backline; dueling a fed Olaf 1v1 is still a coinflip you should avoid.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push that you can shove and then leave to recall for your on-hit spike. Worst wave: a frozen wave near his side where Undertow can slow you into a Reckless Swing all-in with no tower behind you. Crash timing: crash the wave just before your Kraken/BORK back so you reset on tempo and skip a dangerous shove-out where he can run you down.","cooldowns":"Track Ragnarok (R) above all — when it is down you can actually take a fight; when it is up you cannot CC-lock or outrun him. Secondarily watch Undertow (Q): if he misses the axe, its slow-pickup is gone and that's your only safe window to walk up or disengage.","trading":"His pattern is Undertow slow into walk-up autos and Reckless Swing; yours is to never start a sustained swap. Only trade when his axe is on cooldown and his R is down, and only with Wuju Style up — otherwise blink away with Alpha Strike and farm.","spikes":"Olaf spikes hardest at 6 (Ragnarok) and with his first bruiser item plus lifesteal; you spike at Kraken/BORK first item and decisively at two-plus on-hit items. The whole lane is a race between his level-6 dominance and your second-item flip.","feeding":"If you fall behind, a fed Olaf becomes nearly impossible to kite — his Ragnarok true damage and lifesteal let him dive your tower and survive. Stop trying to lane him: take camps, cross-map, and play for objectives where his single-target threat matters less.","carry":"If you somehow get ahead, you carry by refusing to facecheck him and instead splitting side lanes he can't catch you in, then teamfighting from angles where Alpha Strike dodges his engage. Your kill resets on Highlander chain through his squishies, never through him.","difficulty":"It's an 8/10 because Olaf attacks all three of your weaknesses at once: he has a slow to stop you kiting, true damage that ignores your only defensive tools, and a Ragnarok window that hard-counters Alpha Strike and Highlander — your two escape/chase buttons — exactly when you're weakest."},"focus":{"text":"Ragnarok (R) — it makes Olaf CC-immune and deals true damage that ignores shields and Meditate's mitigation, so he chases through your Alpha Strike blink and Highlander and you simply cannot win a fight while it's active.","letters":["R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike","d":"Use Q to last-hit from max range and to blink out of his walk-up — never to start a fight while he has Undertow and R available."},{"t":"Rush anti-heal","d":"Buy Executioner's/Bramble component early; his lifesteal undoes every trade you win, and without anti-heal you can't out-DPS his sustain even at two items."},{"t":"Respect the level-6 window","d":"When Ragnarok is up, concede the lane entirely — back off, farm safely, and only re-engage once you can confirm it's on cooldown."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't auto-trade early","d":"Levels 1-3 he wins every walk-up swap with axe-slow, lifesteal, and Reckless Swing true damage before your Wuju Style or items exist."},{"t":"Don't trust Alpha Strike as an escape into him","d":"The blink is short and untargetable for a moment, but his slow and Ragnarok let him re-stick instantly — Q out is a delay, not a getaway, while his R is up."},{"t":"Don't duel a fed Olaf 1v1 late","d":"Even at two items his Ragnarok true damage plus lifesteal can coinflip the fight; kite him with your team instead of stat-checking him."}],"tradeGood":"A short Alpha-Strike-and-Wuju-auto poke when his Undertow is on cooldown and Ragnarok is down, then blink away before his lifesteal swings the long fight.","tradeBad":"A standing toe-to-toe trade while he's slowed you with Undertow or has Ragnarok active — his true damage ignores your defenses and his lifesteal out-sustains Meditate.","ahead":"Pressing a lead here means denying him the duel, not winning it — shove and roam or take camps the moment his wave is dead, since a slow, dive-happy Olaf can't catch a Highlander-buffed Yi crossing the map. Use any kill's Highlander reset to chain onto his teammates, never onto Olaf himself. Build your second on-hit item fast so your two-item flip arrives before he snowballs his own bruiser core.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Olaf - Track: Ragnarok (R) — it makes Olaf CC-immune and deals true damage that ignores shields and Meditate's mitigation, so he chases through your Alpha Strike blink and Highlander and you simply cannot win a fight while it's active.. - Survive — farm with Alpha Strike from max range, dodge his Undertow axes so he can't slow-and-chase, and refuse the all-in until you have Kraken/BORK plus anti-heal. Your only real path is to scale past lane and let a fed Olaf get kited by your team while you out-DPS the rest.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A losing scaler-vs-bruiser lane: Olaf's axe-slow, lifesteal, and CC-immune Ragnarok let him run you down through every weak Yi window before your on-hit items ever come online."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Your win condition is to survive a brutal early lane by farming with Alpha Strike and conceding all aggression, then reach two on-hit items (Kraken/BORK into Wit's End or Terminus) with anti-heal up. From there you kite his Undertow, dodge fights inside Ragnarok, and out-DPS everyone except a fed Olaf himself."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Olaf owns levels 1 through 6 — his hardest spike is level 6 Ragnarok — and only at your two-plus-item window does favor finally tip to you, and only in a properly spaced fight."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only when both Undertow and Ragnarok are on cooldown and Wuju Style is up; otherwise blink out with Alpha Strike and farm. Never take a sustained swap — his lifesteal and true damage win every long fight."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Hold the wave near your tower early so a slow-chase has nowhere to take you, then slow-push and crash just before your item back to reset on tempo. Avoid freezing on his side where Undertow into Reckless Swing has no counterplay."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable blink dodges skillshots but does NOT break his Undertow slow or shake his chase while Ragnarok is up; Ragnarok's true damage ignores Meditate's damage reduction; his axe true damage and Reckless Swing ignore any armor or defensive item you build, so raw EHP doesn't save you."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the fastest on-hit ramp into his sustain duel; secondary Triumph and Legend: Alacrity, with Second Wind and either Bone Plating or Overgrowth in Resolve to survive his early walk-up and true-damage poke. Conqueror is the fallback if you want more raw bruiser staying power."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Teleport — you cannot win lane, so TP keeps you on level/item parity and lets you recover after concessions. Ignite is not worth it into a lane you're playing to scale out of."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first for the on-hit spike, then Wit's End (his Undertow/Ragnarok don't deal magic but Wit's helps vs the rest) or Terminus; anti-heal (Mortal Reminder line) is mandatory against his lifesteal. Armor doesn't help — his true damage ignores it — so favor on-hit DPS plus Bramble only for the anti-heal, not the armor."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You can only all-in at two-plus items, with anti-heal up, when Ragnarok is confirmed down and you've made him waste Undertow. Before that there is no clean all-in window against him."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You are extremely gankable pre-6 — Alpha Strike is your only out and the axe-slow holds you for the jungler, so ward his side aggressively. Conversely a gank to set you up is worth more here than in most lanes since you can't create your own lead; coordinate camps and dives for after you've itemized."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players treat Alpha Strike as an escape and walk up to trade, then get slow-chased and Reckless-Swung for committing into a lane they're meant to farm — and they duel Olaf inside Ragnarok thinking on-hit DPS stat-checks him, which it doesn't."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're losing, abandon the duel entirely: farm under tower with Alpha Strike, take jungle camps to stay even on items, TP to other lanes, and play purely for the late-game teamfight where you sidestep Olaf and shred his backline."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If you're ahead, never give it back in a coinflip duel — split push lanes he can't catch you in, chain Highlander resets through his squishies, and force objectives where his single-target slow is wasted on your team's frontline."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"HARD (37.8% WR, 8/10 difficulty): Olaf counters every Yi weakness at once — slow, true damage, and a CC-immune Ragnarok that beats Alpha Strike and Highlander — so play to survive and scale, not to win the lane."}]},"ornn":{"tldr":"Ornn pillars and walls you out of the early lane, but the second your on-hit items come online Alpha Strike dodges his CC and you out-DPS a tank who can't kite you.","winCon":"Survive a poke-y, shoved-in early lane by farming with Alpha Strike, then hit your first on-hit spike and use Q's untargetable frames to dodge his Brittle setup so you can out-sustain his damage through Meditate and shred him with Wuju Style true damage. Once you have two items you out-scale a self-itemizing tank who has no way to run you down.","enemyWin":"Ornn wins by abusing his range and Brittle early — landing E (Searing Charge) into a pillar to knock you up, then auto-resetting to detonate Brittle for a big chunk while you have no escape but a Q on cooldown. If he forces those trades before your items, or lands R (Call of the Forge God) double-knockup to chain CC you in a gank, you never reach your scaling window.","diff":"TRICKY","tone":"#ff8b3d","diffRating":"6/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Ornn","rating":"6/10","why":"Ornn out-ranges you with W (Bellows Breath) and pokes safely while your only level-1 tool is a single-target Alpha Strike that you can't afford to waste on him."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Ornn","rating":"6/10","why":"His E into pillar (Searing Charge) lets him knock you up and apply Brittle before you have Wuju Style true damage to punish back."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Ornn","rating":"6/10","why":"Ornn detonates Brittle with a W auto-reset for amplified damage and a slow, and you still lack the sustain or DPS to trade evenly at level 3."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Ornn","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain come online, so you can answer his pillar pokes with a short E-empowered burst and heal it back."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander gives you the move/attack speed and slow immunity to ignore his pillar slow and chase him down or dodge his gank setups."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King turns your on-hit DPS live, and Alpha Strike's untargetable frames let you blink through his E/R knockup."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At two items you melt a self-itemizing tank with on-hit %-health damage while Meditate out-sustains his single burst and Highlander resets refresh the fight."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Ornn — he has the range to poke you with W and the setup to knock you up with E into a pillar, then detonate Brittle with a W auto-reset for a chunk you can't trade back. Don't burn Alpha Strike trying to fight him; use it to last-hit and to clear the wave so you can't be pinned under tower. You are a farmer here, not a duelist.","mid":"Levels 4-5 stabilize as Wuju Style's true damage (which ignores his stacked armor) and Meditate's sustain let you answer his pokes and heal the chip. Level 6 is your first real swing: Highlander's slow immunity makes his pillar slow and Brittle-slow irrelevant, and the attack speed lets you trade or escape a gank far better than before.","late":"At two-plus items you flip the lane outright. Your on-hit build (Kraken/BORK %-health) shreds a tank who builds resistances but no real kill threat, Meditate out-sustains his single burst rotation, and every kill or assist refreshes Highlander to chain through the teamfight. He simply can't run you down or out-trade you anymore.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push you control so you can freeze just outside his pillar range and farm with Alpha Strike. Worst wave: a wave shoved onto you under tower where his E pillar pins you for a free Brittle detonation and a jungle gank. Crash timing: crash the wave just before your first-item back so you reset on a spike and return to a safe lane state.","cooldowns":"Track his E, Searing Charge (the pillar dash-knockup) — it's his only gap-closer and his Brittle setup; when it's down he cannot start a trade or chase you.","trading":"Pre-6 you lose the auto-trade because he out-ranges you and Brittle amplifies his damage — only step up with E (Wuju Style) active for a quick true-damage burst, then back off before he resets W. Post-items, walk him down with Highlander and Alpha Strike through his knockup, sustaining with Meditate.","spikes":"Ornn spikes at 2 (E+pillar Brittle combo) and at 6 (R double-knockup). You spike at 6 (Highlander) and decisively at first item and again at two items, where your on-hit DPS overtakes his tankiness.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Ornn's pillars and Brittle let his whole team chain-CC you out of every fight — you become a free target with one dodge (Q) and no other escape. Farm side lanes, hit your items late, and don't force.","carry":"If you get ahead, you become a 1v9 hyper-carry: Alpha Strike dodges the engage CC, Wuju Style true damage ignores everyone's armor, and Highlander resets let you chain through their backline while a lone Ornn can't peel a Yi who blinks out of his ultimate.","difficulty":"It's a 6/10 because the early lane is genuinely losing — his range, pillar knockup, and Brittle punish your weak levels 1-3 hard — but it never reaches HARD difficulty since he has zero kiting tools and you reliably reclaim 6 and the item windows; the danger is dying or falling behind before you scale, not the matchup being unwinnable."},"focus":{"text":"Ornn's E, Searing Charge — the dash that knocks you up off a pillar and sets up a Brittle detonation; it's his only gap-closer and the entire engine of his trades, so play around its cooldown and save Alpha Strike to blink out of the knockup.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Q, don't fight early","d":"Use Alpha Strike to safely last-hit and clear waves through levels 1-3 instead of contesting trades you lose to his range and Brittle."},{"t":"Dodge his CC with Alpha Strike","d":"Hold Q to blink untargetable through his E knockup or R double-knockup at the moment he commits, denying the Brittle detonation and his only lockdown."},{"t":"Build and rush on-hit %-health","d":"Get to your first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) fast — your whole win condition is scaling past a tank who can't kite you."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't waste Q on the wave near him","d":"If Alpha Strike is on cooldown you have no escape from his E or a gank, so never blink it into minions when he can knock you up."},{"t":"Don't auto-trade pre-6","d":"Standing to trade autos before items means eating a pillar knockup plus an amplified Brittle hit you can't answer — only step in with Wuju Style up for a quick burst."},{"t":"Don't fight in his pillar","d":"Avoid extended fights next to his Searing Charge terrain — the pillar gives him the dash, the knockup, and the slow that lets a tank stick to you."}],"tradeGood":"Flash or Alpha Strike through his E knockup once his pillar is down, then burst him with Wuju Style true damage and Double Strike while Meditate heals back any chip.","tradeBad":"A flat-footed auto-trade in his pillar range before items, where he knocks you up, detonates Brittle with a W reset, and you have no escape if Q is on cooldown.","ahead":"Press a lead by shoving him in with your faster clear and roaming on Highlander's bonus movement speed to snowball other lanes, since a lone Ornn can't punish your absence the way a duelist would. In lane, walk him down with Alpha Strike dodging his knockup and Wuju Style ignoring his armor — he can't itemize fast enough to out-tank true on-hit damage, and every kill resets Highlander to keep the pressure rolling.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Ornn - Track: Ornn's E, Searing Charge — the dash that knocks you up off a pillar and sets up a Brittle detonation; it's his only gap-closer and the entire engine of his trades, so play around its cooldown and save Alpha Strike to blink out of the knockup.. - Survive a poke-y, shoved-in early lane by farming with Alpha Strike, then hit your first on-hit spike and use Q's untargetable frames to dodge his Brittle setup so you can out-sustain his damage through Meditate and shred him with Wuju Style true damage. Once you have two items you out-scale a self-itemizing tank who has no way to run you down.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Ornn pillars and walls you out of the early lane, but the second your on-hit items come online Alpha Strike dodges his CC and you out-DPS a tank who can't kite you."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive Ornn's range-and-Brittle early by farming with Alpha Strike, then reach your first on-hit item and use Q's untargetable frames to dodge his E/R knockups so you out-DPS and out-sustain a tank who has no kiting tools. Wuju Style's true damage ignores his stacked armor and Meditate out-heals his single burst rotation, so the lane flips the moment you scale."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Ornn owns levels 1-3 with range and the pillar-Brittle combo, the lane evens at 4-5 as Wuju Style and Meditate come online, then favor swings to you at 6 (Highlander) and decisively at first and second item."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Back off all-auto trades pre-6; only step in with Wuju Style active for a quick true-damage burst and retreat before his W resets. After items, trade freely — walk him down with Highlander, blink his knockup with Alpha Strike, and sustain with Meditate."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave slow-pushing or frozen just outside his pillar range so you farm safely with Q and aren't pinned under tower; crash just before your first-item back to reset on a spike."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability is the whole matchup — it lets you blink through Searing Charge's knockup and Call of the Forge God's double-knockup, denying his Brittle detonation. Wuju Style's true damage bypasses the armor he stacks, and Highlander's slow immunity nullifies his pillar slow and Brittle slow."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo keystone with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand in Precision; secondary Resolve (Second Wind to ease his early poke, Overgrowth) — Second Wind specifically counters his level 1-3 chip. Shards: Attack Speed, Adaptive Force, Health."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite — Ignite's grievous wounds answers his own self-heal items and the kill pressure secures your scaling snowball; take Flash to cross his knockup or gap onto him after he commits E."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for %-health on-hit against his stacked health, then Wit's End or Terminus for true/magic on-hit to shred resistances; Plated Steelcaps into his AD, and Death's Dance or Sterak's Gage if you keep dying to his and the jungler's chunk."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You can genuinely all-in at 6 once Highlander makes his slows irrelevant, and especially after first item when Alpha Strike can dodge his knockup and your on-hit DPS out-races a tank's effective HP — pick the window right after his E is on cooldown."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Ganks are the real danger: Ornn's pillar knockup plus a follow-up CC chains you with only one Q to dodge, so ward his side and don't overextend pre-6; once you have Highlander you can blink the setup and even turn a botched gank with a reset."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi error here is treating the early lane like a winnable fight and burning Alpha Strike to trade — that leaves you with no escape from his E or a gank, and Brittle punishes the greed. Respect that you're a farmer until items."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're behind, abandon the duel — farm side waves, soak XP, and rush your on-hit spike; never force a fight where his pillar and Brittle let his team chain-CC a Yi with one dodge. Your curve is so steep that surviving to two items reclaims the game."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If ahead, shove and roam on Highlander's movement speed to spread the lead, then come back and walk him down with Alpha Strike through his knockup — kills reset Highlander to chain him and his jungler, and a self-itemizing Ornn can't out-tank your true on-hit damage."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"TRICKY 6/10 — Ornn edges a poke-and-Brittle early lane, but a Yi who farms patiently to his on-hit items dodges his CC with Alpha Strike and out-DPSes a kite-less tank from 6 onward."}]},"pantheon":{"tldr":"Pantheon bullies you off the wave for the entire early game and his point-and-click W stun catches you the instant Alpha Strike ends — you lose lane, then have to claw the game back at two items.","winCon":"Concede the early lane entirely — last-hit with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos under tower, dodge his all-ins, and just survive to your first on-hit item. Once Pantheon's spear and stun fall off and your Kraken/BORK come online, you out-DPS him in any extended fight and use the map to snowball, not the 1v1.","enemyWin":"Pantheon wins by spear-poking you (Q) every time you step for a CS, then all-in with W stun → Aegis-block your autos → empowered Q while you're locked, killing you before level 6 and repeatedly denying your farm so you never reach your item spikes. His R lets him roam and snowball other lanes while you're stuck.","diff":"HARD","tone":"#ff5d6c","diffRating":"8/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Pantheon","rating":"8/10","why":"His Q spear out-ranges your autos and his Aegis passive blocks the first hit of any retaliation, so you can't trade back at all and just eat free poke."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Pantheon","rating":"8/10","why":"With W point-and-click stun online he can lock you down and combo before you have any way to disengage — Alpha Strike isn't up reliably yet to dodge it."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Pantheon","rating":"9/10","why":"This is his cleanest kill level: empowered Q + W stun bursts you while his passive eats your Wuju autos, and you still have no escape but a long-cooldown Q."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Pantheon","rating":"7/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain let you survive short trades, but his combo still out-damages you and you cannot win an extended fight yet."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Pantheon","rating":"7/10","why":"Highlander lets you dodge ganks and disengage, but his level-6 spike and global R mean he out-tempos you and can leave to snowball elsewhere."},{"label":"First item","side":"Skill","rating":"6/10","why":"Your Kraken/BORK on-hit DPS arrives just as his spear starts falling off — Alpha Strike can now dodge his W stun if you time it, making the 1v1 genuinely close."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"With two on-hit items, Meditate out-sustains his poke and you out-DPS him in any extended fight, resetting Highlander on a kill to chain through his team."}],"breakdown":{"early":"You are flat-out losing levels 1-3 and there is no trade you can win. Pantheon's Q spear pokes you for free every time you walk up to last-hit, and his Aegis passive blocks the first auto of any retaliation, so even your Wuju-empowered autos get eaten. Hold the back of the wave, take CS with Alpha Strike when a minion would cost you HP, and accept you will give up some farm — staying alive is the whole job here.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you stabilize a little as Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain come online, so you can heal off his poke and answer a single trade — but his full combo still beats yours. Level 6 Highlander is your survival button, not a kill button: use the move speed and slow immunity to dodge his all-in and any gank, never to chase. Expect him to use his R to roam, so ping and respect the global.","late":"At two on-hit items the lane finally flips. Kraken/BORK + Wit's End or Terminus on-hit DPS shreds him, Meditate out-sustains his now-weak spear poke, and his early-game combo no longer one-shots you. In any extended fight you win, and a kill resets Highlander to let you chain through his team — this is the window you survived the early game to reach.","wave":"Best wave: a wave slow-pushing toward you so you can farm safely under tower and deny his all-in angle. Worst wave: a big wave you have to walk up into, where his spear poke and W stun punish every CS step. Crash timing: only crash for a recall or jungle reset — never shove into him pre-6 or you hand him the all-in he wants.","cooldowns":"Track his W stun above all — it's his all-in trigger; when it's down you can step up for CS, and you must save Alpha Strike or Highlander to answer it when it's up. Also watch his Q spear charge windup so you can sidestep the poke.","trading":"There is no clean trade for you before two items. His pattern is poke you with Q, wait for you to walk up, then W-stun → empowered Q → auto while his passive blocks your first hit back. Your counter-pattern is simply not to be in range — farm at max range and only commit once your items are online.","spikes":"Pantheon spikes hard at 1, 3, and 6 (W stun + empowered Q + global R). You spike at 6 for survival (Highlander) and decisively at first item, then again at two items where you become the favored duelist.","feeding":"If you fall behind, his early lead lets him perma-shove and roam with R while you're zoned off farm — the game can snowball away from your team fast. Cut your losses: farm safe under tower, ask your jungler to babysit, and stall until your items come online; do not try to force back a kill you can't win.","carry":"If you do get ahead here, you ignore the 1v1 entirely — push the wave, use Highlander's move speed to roam and pick off his squishies, and play for objectives. Your snowball is one of the highest in the game once Alpha Strike is dodging CC and resetting on kills.","difficulty":"It's an 8/10 because Pantheon attacks every one of your weaknesses at once: he out-ranges you (Q), point-and-click catches you the instant your only escape ends (W), and his passive negates your auto-reliant damage — all during the exact levels you're at your weakest. The 44.53% win rate reflects how often Yi simply never reaches his scaling."},"focus":{"text":"Pantheon's W is a point-and-click stun with no dodge — it's the trigger for his entire all-in and the one ability that catches you the moment Alpha Strike's untargetability ends. Never walk up while it's available.","letters":["W"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm at max range","d":"Use Alpha Strike to grab any minion that would cost you HP to walk up for, and last-hit from the back of the wave so his Q spear can't poke you for free."},{"t":"Save your escapes for his W","d":"Hold Alpha Strike's untargetable blink or Highlander's move speed specifically to answer his W stun all-in — these are the only tools that survive his combo."},{"t":"Stall to two items","d":"Your entire game plan is surviving to Kraken/BORK + a second on-hit item; once there, take extended fights and reset Highlander on kills to take over."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't walk up while W is up","d":"His point-and-click stun starts a combo you cannot survive early — if W is available, do not step into range for any CS or trade."},{"t":"Don't auto-trade into his passive","d":"His Aegis blocks the first hit of your retaliation, so trading autos with him pre-items is always a losing exchange even with Wuju Style up."},{"t":"Don't chase with Highlander","d":"Use R's move speed to escape and dodge, never to dive him — chasing into his W stun and empowered Q is exactly how you feed the early lead he wants."}],"tradeGood":"After two items, bait his W stun, dodge the follow-up with Alpha Strike, then re-engage with full on-hit DPS while Meditate out-sustains his weakened spear.","tradeBad":"Walking up to CS while his W is available and eating the W-stun → empowered Q combo with your autos negated by his passive — a guaranteed loss pre-items.","ahead":"A lead here means you stop dueling and start using the map: shove the wave, take Highlander's move speed across the river, and assassinate his squishier teammates while resetting your ult on every kill. Group for objectives where your on-hit DPS and Alpha Strike CC-dodge make you the strongest fighter on the field. Never re-enter a coinflip 1v1 with Pantheon when you can simply out-tempo his whole team instead.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Pantheon - Track: Pantheon's W is a point-and-click stun with no dodge — it's the trigger for his entire all-in and the one ability that catches you the moment Alpha Strike's untargetability ends. Never walk up while it's available.. - Concede the early lane entirely — last-hit with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos under tower, dodge his all-ins, and just survive to your first on-hit item. Once Pantheon's spear and stun fall off and your Kraken/BORK come online, you out-DPS him in any extended fight and use the map to snowball, not the 1v1.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Pantheon bullies you off the wave for the entire early game and his point-and-click W stun catches you the instant Alpha Strike ends — you lose lane, then have to claw the game back at two items."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a lost early lane by farming with Alpha Strike at max range and conceding all aggression, then reach your first two on-hit items. Once Kraken/BORK + Wit's End/Terminus are online your DPS and Meditate sustain flip the duel, and you snowball through resets rather than trying to win the 1v1 early."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Pantheon owns levels 1-6 (peaking at 3); the lane is even at first item and tilts to you at two items as his spear falls off and your on-hit comes online."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Don't trade at all pre-items — only step up for CS when his W stun is on cooldown. From first item on, you can answer single trades; from two items, bait his W, dodge with Alpha Strike, and commit to an extended fight."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Let the wave sit or slow-push toward you so you farm safely under tower and deny his all-in angle. Don't shove into him pre-6 — a frozen or slow wave near your tower is your safest state."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"The lane hinges on Alpha Strike's untargetability dodging his W stun and empowered Q; his Aegis passive blocking your first auto negates your retaliation; and Highlander's slow immunity + move speed letting you escape his all-in and ganks. Meditate out-sustains his poke once his spear scaling falls off."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the safer scaling attack speed in a lane you can't fight early; Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand (or Coup de Grace) in Precision. Secondary Resolve with Second Wind (huge vs his Q poke) and Bone Plating (eats his W-stun combo). Take armor shards vs his AD."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Teleport — Teleport to recover the farm and tempo you'll lose surviving the early lane, and to match his R global presence. Ignite is greedy here since you can't win the early all-in to use it."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for your spike, then Wit's End for the on-hit plus magic resist (you don't need it vs his AD — prefer a second on-hit) or Terminus for resistances and shred. Plated Steelcaps vs his auto/spear AD. Add Death's Dance or a Stridebreaker/defensive third if his team is AD-heavy."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You cannot all-in before first item, period. Your real all-in window is two items: bait or wait out his W, dodge with Alpha Strike, and commit when Meditate can out-sustain his poke and your on-hit out-damages him."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're extremely gankable early with only Q to escape, so ward his fog and play for your own jungler — a single successful gank with your CC-dodge follow-up can buy you the survival you need. Respect that his R lets him answer or counter-gank globally."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players try to trade autos or contest CS in range early, eating his W-stun combo into the passive block and feeding the lead that ends the game. The fix is patience: give up farm, stay alive, and trust your two-item spike."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Farm under tower, take every safe wave with Alpha Strike, ask your jungler to babysit, and stall for items — don't force a back you can't win. Use Teleport to stay even on farm and look for cross-map plays instead of the losing 1v1."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If you get ahead, stop dueling and use Highlander's move speed to roam and reset on his squishies, push waves, and take objectives — your snowball is among the highest in the game once Alpha Strike is dodging CC and chaining kills."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"HARD (8/10) — Pantheon stomps the early game and you only win by surviving to two items; lolalytics 44.53% confirms Yi rarely gets there cleanly."}]},"poppy":{"tldr":"A true coin-flip skirmish: Poppy's W shuts off my Alpha Strike escape and her wall-pin punishes a greedy in, but if I respect levels 1-6 and farm to my on-hit spike I out-DPS and out-sustain her every fight after.","winCon":"Survive Poppy's early lockdown by farming with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, never blowing Q into her face while W is up, then hit my first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) and win the extended fight where her single-target damage can't out-pace my DPS or Meditate sustain. Once I'm two items deep, I run her down, reset Highlander on the kill, and take over the map.","enemyWin":"Poppy wins by holding W to negate my Alpha Strike and Highlander dashes, then E-ing me into a wall for the stun so her jungler can collapse before I'm itemized, snowballing the weak-Yi window levels 1-6. If she gets a lead and itemizes Iceborn/Sunfire armor, she stays a sticky, unkillable peel-tank I can't burst through.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Poppy","rating":"7/10","why":"Poppy's Q knockup and higher base damage stomp my level-1 short range while I have no Wuju true damage or escape but Alpha Strike yet."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Poppy","rating":"6/10","why":"At 2 she has both Q poke and W ready to negate any Alpha Strike I throw, so I can only farm, not trade."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Poppy","rating":"6/10","why":"Level 3 she can full-combo E-wall-pin into Q for a long CC chain, and I still lack the sustain to survive an all-in."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"At 4-5 my Wuju Style true damage and Meditate healing come online for short Alpha-reset trades, but her W still blanks my engage if she holds it."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Highlander gives me slow-immunity and gank-dodging, but level-6 Poppy's R can knock me out of an all-in and reset the fight."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"At Kraken/BORK my on-hit DPS jumps and Wuju true damage cuts her armor, so once her W is on cooldown I out-trade her in any extended fight."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At 2+ items I out-DPS her single-target kit, Meditate out-sustains her poke, and Highlander resets let me chain-kill through her team."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are Poppy's: her Q knockup and stronger base damage beat my stubby auto range while I have no true damage and only Alpha Strike for an escape. Just farm — last-hit with autos, use Alpha Strike on the caster minions to push the timer when safe, and never throw Q at her with her W available because she can simply negate the dash and E-pin me into the wall. Stay near my tower side and let her shove if she wants; I don't lose anything by giving up early aggression.","mid":"At 4-5 I stabilize: Wuju Style's bonus true damage and Meditate's heal let me take a short trade if she steps up to last-hit and her W is on cooldown. Level 6 Highlander is my first real spike — slow-immunity and the move/attack speed let me dodge ganks and chase, but it does NOT beat her W or R, so I'm looking to survive and scale, not force kills. Track her W cooldown religiously; that single button decides whether I can engage at all.","late":"At 2+ items the lane flips hard in my favour. With Kraken/BORK plus Wit's End or Terminus my on-hit DPS shreds even an armor-stacking Poppy, Wuju true damage ignores her plate, and Meditate out-heals her single-target poke. I win every extended duel as long as I bait or wait out her W, and every kill resets Highlander to let me snowball into the map.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push that lets me freeze just outside my tower so she can't E-pin me into MY wall and a gank arrives behind me, not her. Worst wave: a wave shoved deep under HER tower where her E-into-wall stun plus a jungler means a free death before I'm itemized. Crash timing: crash the wave just before my item back (Kraken/BORK) or before a scuttle/objective fight so I reset on-spike and arrive with full HP and minions.","cooldowns":"Track Poppy's W (Steadfast Presence) above all — it negates every dash in my kit (Alpha Strike, Highlander movement) and grants her resist; only commit an all-in when it is on cooldown. Secondarily watch her E (Heroic Charge) so you never stand next to a wall when it's up.","trading":"Trade only when her W is down: walk up, auto-weave with Wuju Style active, and use Alpha Strike to reset my attack timer and apply double on-hit, then disengage before her Q/E come back. If W is up, do not commit — she eats the dash and pins you.","spikes":"My spikes: level 6 Highlander (gank survival), then first on-hit item (the real one), then 2 items where I take over. Her spikes: levels 1-3 raw stats, level 6 R for peel/displacement, and her first armor/Iceborn item which makes her a sticky peel-tank.","feeding":"If I fall behind, Poppy becomes a frontline peel-tank I literally cannot kill through her W and resists — I get kited and bursted in skirmishes. Stop forcing lane, farm side waves with Alpha Strike's safe last-hitting, and only group when I've caught back up on items; a fed Poppy doesn't 1v1 me but she perma-peels her carries away from me.","carry":"If I'm ahead, I'm one of the highest-snowball champs in the game: Highlander resets on kills/assists chain me through fights, my on-hit melts her squishies regardless of her W, and I use my move-speed to flank and delete backline rather than trading into her tanky front.","difficulty":"It's a 5/10 because the matchup is genuinely even — Poppy hard-counters my dash-based engage with one button and owns me levels 1-6, but I have a far higher ceiling and out-scale her completely once itemized. The skill is purely in not dying before my spike."},"focus":{"text":"Poppy's W, Steadfast Presence — it negates every dash in my kit (Alpha Strike and Highlander) and gives her resists, so it single-handedly decides whether I'm allowed to engage; her E wall-pin is the follow-up that kills me if I commit into it.","letters":["W","E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm to your on-hit spike","d":"Concede levels 1-6 and last-hit safely with autos and Alpha Strike; your entire game plan is arriving at Kraken/BORK alive, because you out-scale Poppy hard from there."},{"t":"Bait or wait out her W","d":"Only all-in when Steadfast Presence is on cooldown — make her use it on a fake step-in, then commit Alpha Strike into the real engage so the dash isn't negated."},{"t":"Stand away from walls","d":"When her E is up, never fight with a wall behind you; the wall-pin stun is what turns her poke into a kill, so position in open lane."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't Q into an up W","d":"Throwing Alpha Strike while she holds W wastes your only escape — she eats the untargetable blink for free and then E-pins you into the wall."},{"t":"Don't all-in before your item","d":"Pre-Kraken you lose every extended fight to her base stats and CC; forcing aggression levels 1-6 just feeds her the snowball she needs."},{"t":"Don't shove under her tower","d":"A deep wave gives her a free E-into-tower-wall stun plus a jungler gank — keep the wave central or frozen on your side."}],"tradeGood":"Walk up with Wuju Style active while her W is on cooldown, auto-weave a Double Strike, and Alpha Strike to reset my attack timer for double on-hit, then peel off before her Q and E come back.","tradeBad":"Never Alpha Strike into her while she's holding W and standing by a wall — she negates the dash, E-pins you for the stun, and Q-knocks you up for a free kill or jungle collapse.","ahead":"Pressing a lead means using my move-speed and Highlander resets, not raw dueling into her tanky kit. I roam to other lanes and objectives the moment I've shoved, since a fed Yi taking 3v3s and resetting on kills is worth far more than poking a peel-tank. In lane I deny her CS under tower and force her to choose between dying to my on-hit or giving up the wave entirely — but I always keep an eye on her W before I commit the kill.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Poppy - Track: Poppy's W, Steadfast Presence — it negates every dash in my kit (Alpha Strike and Highlander) and gives her resists, so it single-handedly decides whether I'm allowed to engage; her E wall-pin is the follow-up that kills me if I commit into it.. - Survive Poppy's early lockdown by farming with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, never blowing Q into her face while W is up, then hit my first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) and win the extended fight where her single-target damage can't out-pace my DPS or Meditate sustain. Once I'm two items deep, I run her down, reset Highlander on the kill, and take over the map.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A true coin-flip skirmish: Poppy's W shuts off my Alpha Strike escape and her wall-pin punishes a greedy in, but if I respect levels 1-6 and farm to my on-hit spike I out-DPS and out-sustain her every fight after."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive Poppy's level 1-6 lockdown by farming safely with Alpha Strike and never feeding her the dash-negate-into-wall-pin combo, then hit my first on-hit item where my DPS and Meditate sustain overwhelm her single-target damage. From two items I out-scale her completely and snowball through Highlander resets."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Poppy owns 1-3 (stats + CC), it's even at 4-6 (my Wuju/Meditate vs her W and R), and it swings to me at first item and hard to me at 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only when her W (Steadfast Presence) is on cooldown and no wall is behind me; weave Wuju autos with an Alpha Strike reset, then disengage. If W is up or her jungler is near, refuse the trade and just farm."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave central or freeze just outside my tower so she can't E-pin me into my own wall under a gank; avoid shoving deep under her turret pre-item. Crash on my item-back or before an objective so I arrive on-spike with full HP."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Her W negates Alpha Strike's blink and Highlander's movement, so it gates my entire engage; her E needs a wall to stun and her Q knockup interrupts my channel — Meditate can't be used mid-CC. My only safe play into an up W is to wait it out, since Alpha Strike's untargetability does NOT dodge a point-and-click E-charge once she's on top of me."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (faster on-hit ramp into her tankiness) > Triumph > Legend: Alacrity > Last Stand or Coup de Grace; secondary Resolve with Conditioning + Overgrowth for the early survivability against her CC, or Second Wind + Revitalize if she's poke-heavy. Conqueror is fine if you prefer the bonus AD, but Lethal Tempo carries the on-hit scaling better here."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to threaten the kill once I out-scale and to cut her sustain, but Flash + Teleport is the safer pick into an even lane where I want to scale and not get punished for a bad early back. Take TP if her jungler is gank-heavy."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit spike, then Wit's End (if she goes AP-bruiser/Iceborn) or Terminus for true/penetration through her armor; Berserker's Greaves, and consider Death's Dance or a Maw only if her team has the burst — otherwise stay full damage since Wuju true damage already ignores her plate."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"I can only all-in when her W is on cooldown AND I'm at first item or later — pre-item I have no all-in here. Post-Kraken, bait W, then commit Alpha Strike + Wuju + Highlander and reset on the kill."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"This lane is decided by junglers: Poppy's E-wall-pin plus a gank kills me before my spike, so I track her jungler harder than hers tracks me. My counterplay is Highlander at 6 to dodge ganks and a TP to recover; I want my own jungler topside early to deny her the snowball window."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi error here is throwing Alpha Strike at Poppy to trade or escape while her W is up — she negates it for free and you've handed her the kill. The second is forcing fights levels 1-6 instead of accepting you're weak and just farming to your item."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If I'm behind, stop dueling her — she becomes an unkillable peel-tank. Farm side waves with safe Alpha Strike last-hits, use Highlander move-speed to escape, and only re-engage the map once I've caught up on items; pick fights on HER carries, never on Poppy's front."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Ahead, I abuse Highlander kill-resets and move-speed to roam and take 3v3s rather than poke her tanky kit; my on-hit deletes her squishy teammates regardless of her W, and every reset chains me to the next target. Deny her CS under tower and snowball the map, not the 1v1."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A true 50/50 EVEN lane — Poppy's W hard-counters my dashes and owns me early, but I out-scale her decisively once itemized; win the lane by surviving to your spike, not by forcing it."}]},"quinn":{"tldr":"Quinn blinds and kites you off the wave early, but if you farm with Alpha Strike to your first on-hit item you flip her into a one-shot the second Highlander lets you stick.","winCon":"Concede the early levels, last-hit with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos to reach Kraken/Blade of the Ruined King without dying, then use Highlander's move/attack speed plus Alpha Strike's untargetable blink to close the gap her Harrier kite opens and delete her in two on-hit windows.","enemyWin":"Quinn wins by vaulting away every time you Alpha Strike in, blinding your autos during the trade so your on-hit damage whiffs, and poking you under tower with Harrier-empowered attacks so you can never farm even — keeping you off your item spikes long enough that her early lead outpaces your scaling.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Quinn","rating":"7/10","why":"Quinn's ranged autos plus Harrier proc outrange and out-poke your melee last-hits, and you have no answer but to soak it or Alpha Strike a minion to push out."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Quinn","rating":"7/10","why":"Her E vault knocks you back and blinds you, blanking your follow-up autos so any level-2 trade you start with Alpha Strike loses."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Quinn","rating":"6/10","why":"With Harrier kite and poke she controls the wave and zones your XP; your Q only resets attack speed off a target, so you still can't commit through her vault."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style's bonus true damage and Meditate's channel sustain start letting you out-trade her short bursts if she mispositions her blind."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity let you chase through her Harrier kite, but a clean E vault still resets the gap and ignores your slow-immune chase."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King on-hit DPS plus Alpha Strike going untargetable through her vault means one stick equals a kill if you bait E first."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At two on-hit items you out-DPS her squishy body in any extended fight and Highlander resets refresh your Q to chain-kill before she can reposition."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong entirely to Quinn. Her ranged autos with the Harrier mark out-poke your melee last-hits, and her E vault both knocks you out of attack range and blinds you, so any Alpha Strike engage gets blanked and punished. Just soak the wave, take CS with Alpha Strike when you can't walk up safely, and accept you will be down some HP — do not try to trade.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you stabilize: Wuju Style's true damage and Meditate's channel let you survive her poke and threaten a short trade if she throws E on cooldown. Level 6 Highlander is your first real tool — the move speed and slow immunity let you actually run her down through Harrier, but a saved vault still resets her, so the rule is bait E, then commit.","late":"At two on-hit items (Kraken/BORK plus Wit's End or Terminus) the lane is yours. You out-DPS her squishy frame in any sustained fight, Alpha Strike goes untargetable to dodge her vault on reaction, and a single kill resets Highlander to chain through her or her teammates. This is the streaky payoff her early lead is racing against.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push you can freeze just outside your tower so she has to walk into your Highlander range to last-hit. Worst wave: a wave shoved onto you under tower where her Harrier poke chunks you for every CS. Crash timing: crash the wave into her tower right before your first on-hit item completes so you can recall, buy, and return to a fresh lane already spiked.","cooldowns":"Track her E (Vault) cooldown above everything — it is her only escape from your all-in and her only hard blind on your autos. When E is down, that is your window; when it is up, never commit.","trading":"You never win a stat-check trade early; your trade is reactive — let her vault or poke, walk her E onto cooldown, then Alpha Strike in with Wuju Style active so your true damage and on-hit land before she can reposition.","spikes":"Quinn spikes at levels 1-3 and again whenever Harrier is up; you spike at 6 (Highlander) and decisively at first and second on-hit items. The lane's whole story is her early spike racing your item spikes.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Quinn roams with her passive move speed and snowballs the map while you are stuck farming — you become a useless melee that can't reach anyone. Play safe, match her recalls, and ping her roams so your team doesn't get caught by her tempo.","carry":"If you get ahead, you become an unkiteable on-hit monster — Alpha Strike dodges her CC, Highlander resets let you chain-fight, and you split or flank to delete her carries. Your snowball curve is one of the steepest in the game once the early hump is cleared.","difficulty":"It rates only 5/10 because despite a brutal early lane the matchup is genuinely EVEN (52%): Quinn cannot kill a respectful Yi outright, your scaling reliably reclaims the 2+ item window, and Alpha Strike's untargetable frames partially answer the one tool (vault) that defines her."},"focus":{"text":"Quinn's E (Vault) — it knocks you back out of attack range AND blinds your autos, so it simultaneously cancels your on-hit trade and is her only escape from your all-in; everything you do keys off whether it is up or down.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike","d":"Use Q to safely last-hit and shove from range when her Harrier poke makes walking up to melee CS too costly; it resets your attack timer on a struck target so you keep tempo without eating autos."},{"t":"Bait the vault, then commit","d":"Force or wait out her E before you all-in — once it is on cooldown she has no blind for your autos and no escape from Highlander, so that is your only real kill window."},{"t":"Race to your on-hit spike","d":"Prioritize a clean recall on Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King; the lane flips the instant your first on-hit item completes, so protect that timing over chasing kills early."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't Alpha Strike into her E","d":"If you blink in while her vault is up she just knocks you back and blinds your follow-up autos, wasting your only gap-closer and your trade — Q is not an engage tool when E is available."},{"t":"Don't channel Meditate in her poke range","d":"Standing still to heal in Harrier auto range just feeds her free poke; only Meditate when she is out of range or her wave can't reach you, or you'll heal less than she chunks."},{"t":"Don't chase across the wave early","d":"Her Harrier move speed and vault out-kite your level 1-6 chase; over-extending to catch her walks you into her poke and any roaming jungler while you have no Highlander to escape."}],"tradeGood":"Bait her E vault, then Alpha Strike in with Wuju Style active so your bonus true damage and on-hit land while she has no blind and no escape.","tradeBad":"Walking up to auto her at even HP while her vault is up — she blinds your attack and knocks you back, winning the trade for free.","ahead":"Once you're ahead, you become genuinely unkiteable: pop Highlander to run her down, Alpha Strike through her vault to go untargetable, and a single kill resets your cooldowns to chain-fight. Use that tempo to invade her side waves and shove for plates, then look to flank teamfights and delete her or her backline before they can peel — your snowball from this lane scales faster than her roam-based lead can answer.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Quinn - Track: Quinn's E (Vault) — it knocks you back out of attack range AND blinds your autos, so it simultaneously cancels your on-hit trade and is her only escape from your all-in; everything you do keys off whether it is up or down.. - Concede the early levels, last-hit with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos to reach Kraken/Blade of the Ruined King without dying, then use Highlander's move/attack speed plus Alpha Strike's untargetable blink to close the gap her Harrier kite opens and delete her in two on-hit windows.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Quinn blinds and kites you off the wave early, but if you farm with Alpha Strike to your first on-hit item you flip her into a one-shot the second Highlander lets you stick."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing levels 1-5 by farming with Alpha Strike instead of trading, then reach your first on-hit item without dying to her poke. From Kraken/BORK onward, Highlander plus Alpha Strike's untargetable frames let you close her Harrier kite and out-DPS her squishy frame, flipping the lane to FAVOURED."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Quinn owns 1-3 hard (poke + vault blind), it evens at 4-6 as Wuju/Meditate/Highlander come online, and shifts firmly to you at first and especially second on-hit item."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Never trade while her E is up; only commit after she vaults or poke-whiffs it. Reactive short trades with Wuju Style true damage are fine post-4; full all-ins only after 6 with E down or after your on-hit spike."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Don't fight the wave early — let it settle and freeze just outside your tower so she must step into Highlander range to CS. Pre-spike, slow-push and crash into her tower right before a recall so you return to a fresh lane already itemized."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable frames can dodge her E vault knockback and any incoming CC if timed on reaction; Wuju Style's true damage ignores armor for your trade; Meditate out-sustains her single-target poke but not while you're being auto'd. Her E blind is the hard counter — it makes your on-hit autos miss, so the whole lane is timing around it."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (ramping attack speed for on-hit) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve Conditioning + Overgrowth, or Second Wind + Bone Plating into her poke. Conqueror is the alternative if you want raw extended-fight damage, but Lethal Tempo is preferred to reach your attack-speed cap faster against a kiter."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite if you trust yourself to flip the lane and want post-6 kill pressure; Flash + Teleport is the safer pick here to recover from a rough early laning phase and match her roam tempo across the map."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King (BORK's % current-HP and self-heal is strong, Kraken's true-damage proc cuts her squish), then Berserker's Greaves, then Wit's End or Terminus for on-hit plus magic resist — note Quinn is AD, so prioritize armor in your third/defensive slot (Wit's End is value vs AP teams, not her specifically; consider a Steelcaps swap if she's the main threat)."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Level 6 with Highlander up and her E on cooldown is your first all-in; after that, any time her vault is down once you have your first on-hit item. Pre-6 with E up, you have no all-in — period."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Your jungler is huge here — a gank that catches her without vault (her only escape) converts your weak lane into a lead and a freeze. Conversely her vault and Harrier speed let her dodge most ganks, so coordinate to bait E first. Ward early because her poke means she'll have you low for the enemy jungler."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi error is forcing early Alpha Strike engages into her vault — you blink in, get blinded and knocked back, and lose the trade and your escape. The second is greeding CS in her poke range and dying to chip damage before you ever reach your item spike."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're behind, give up the lane gracefully: farm under tower with Alpha Strike, match her recalls, and ping her roams. You scale, she doesn't snowball you 1v1, so just hit your items and pivot to teamfights where your on-hit reset pattern still wins."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"When ahead, use Highlander tempo to invade her wave, take plates, and shove fast to roam yourself. In fights, Alpha Strike past her vault, kill a target to reset Highlander, and chain through her backline — your closing speed snowballs the map."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"EVEN (52%) — a brutal early lane you must survive, not win, that you reliably reclaim at your on-hit item spikes; respect the vault blind, race your items, and the scaling does the rest."}]},"renekton":{"tldr":"Renekton bullies you off every wave from levels 1-6 with his stun and fury combos, but if you farm safe with Alpha Strike and survive to your first on-hit item, you flip the lane and run him down once he falls off.","winCon":"Concede the early lane, freeze near your tower, and use Alpha Strike + Wuju Style autos to farm without eating his W stun, then hit Kraken/Blade of the Ruined King and turn every extended fight into an on-hit reset chain with Highlander. Your win condition is the back half of the game, not the lane itself.","enemyWin":"Renekton wins by abusing his early base damage and point-and-click W stun to all-in you at 2-3 fury bars before you have items, snowballing the kill into a tower and roams while you are still a weak farmer. If he gets a lead, his W stun catches you the instant Alpha Strike ends and he kills you before Wuju Style or Meditate matter.","diff":"TRICKY","tone":"#ff8b3d","diffRating":"7/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Renekton","rating":"7/10","why":"Renekton's level-1 base damage and slice-dash range out-trade your short-range autos, and you have no answer to a fury-empowered W stun."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Renekton","rating":"7/10","why":"At level 2 his W point-and-click stun locks you while he stacks fury, and your only escape is a single Alpha Strike on cooldown."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Renekton","rating":"8/10","why":"Level 3 is his cleanest all-in window — empowered W stun into E-Q follows you through the Alpha Strike blink and deletes you before Wuju Style true damage matters."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Renekton","rating":"6/10","why":"Levels 4-5 Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain let you survive short pokes, but he still wins any extended trade with empowered Cull the Meek lifesteal."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity let you dodge his gank setups and answer his all-in, and a single kill refreshes it to chain — your first real claim on the lane."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken/Blade of the Ruined King on-hit DPS plus Wuju true damage now out-trades his decaying fury combos in any fight he can't burst you in."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At 2+ items Renekton has fully fallen off — Alpha Strike dodges his W stun, Wuju shreds his armor, and Highlander resets let you run him down every fight."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are Renekton's lane, full stop. His base damage, slice-dash mobility, and a point-and-click W stun beat your short autos and one-charge Alpha Strike in every all-in. Do not trade — use Q to last-hit safely from outside his fury combo and accept losing CS rather than HP.","mid":"Levels 4-6 you stabilize but don't take over: Wuju Style bonus true damage and Meditate sustain let you eat poke and stay even on the wave, and level 6 Highlander is your first tool to dodge his all-in and a follow-up gank. You're surviving to scale, not winning the lane.","late":"At 2+ items the matchup inverts hard. Renekton's fury combo no longer one-shots you, and your Kraken/BORK on-hit plus Wuju true damage out-DPS him while Alpha Strike dodges the one W stun he has. Highlander resets turn a won fight into a roam that ends the game.","wave":"Best wave: a slow freeze just outside your tower so you farm with Alpha Strike and deny his all-in range. Worst wave: a wave shoved to his tower at level 3 where he empowers W and dives you off the Alpha Strike reset. Crash timing: only crash and recall after your first on-hit item completes so you reset on even HP and skip his strongest dive windows.","cooldowns":"Track his W (Ruthless Predator) — the empowered fury stun is his entire kill threat; if it's down you can safely Alpha Strike in to last-hit or to dodge a gank.","trading":"Pre-6 there is no good trade — he point-and-clicks the W stun and out-damages you, so you only auto-reset CS with Q. Post-item your trade is to bait his W, Alpha Strike through it, and Wuju-DPS him while it's on cooldown.","spikes":"His spikes are levels 1-3 and 6 with fury up; yours are level 6 Highlander, then hard at first item, then dominant at 2+ items — the classic crossover lane.","feeding":"If you die early Renekton snowballs his lead into your tower and you fall behind on the one thing you can't afford to lose — item timings — turning a survivable lane into an unwinnable one. Play for farm under tower and ping your jungler instead of forcing back.","carry":"Once ahead, your Highlander resets let you Alpha Strike from fight to fight across the map; you stop dueling Renekton and start using your on-hit DPS to delete his squishier carries and close before his team can peel.","difficulty":"It's a 7/10 because the entire early lane is conceded to a point-and-click bully who can kill you through your only escape, and one mistimed Alpha Strike or eaten W stun pre-item snowballs him hard enough to deny the scaling that is your whole game plan."},"focus":{"text":"His W, Ruthless Predator — the fury-empowered point-and-click stun. It locks you the moment Alpha Strike ends and sets up his entire kill combo; never commit while it's available.","letters":["W"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike","d":"Use Q to last-hit from outside his fury combo range so you scale without eating his W stun. Lost CS is recoverable; a death that denies your item spike is not."},{"t":"Bait the W, then commit","d":"Pre-item, only Alpha Strike in once his Ruthless Predator stun is on cooldown — that's your only safe window to trade or dodge a gank with Highlander up."},{"t":"Play for the scaling crossover","d":"Survive to your first on-hit item, then start taking the extended fights he can no longer burst you in, using Wuju true damage to shred his armor."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't all-in before items","d":"His base damage and empowered W stun win every level 1-3 trade — committing Alpha Strike into a full-fury Renekton just feeds him the lead that kills your scaling."},{"t":"Don't Alpha Strike with W stun up","d":"Renekton can point-and-click stun you the instant the blink ends and kill you before Wuju or Meditate matter — never burn your escape into an available Ruthless Predator."},{"t":"Don't greed the freeze when he has fury","d":"Standing in his combo range to deny a wave when he's sitting on 2-3 fury bars is exactly the dive he wants — give up the wave before you give up the kill."}],"tradeGood":"After his Ruthless Predator stun is on cooldown and you've itemized, Alpha Strike in, pop Wuju Style for armor-ignoring true damage, and out-DPS him while his fury decays.","tradeBad":"Any level 1-3 stand-and-trade — he point-and-click stuns you with empowered W and out-damages your short autos before Wuju Style or Meditate can sustain you.","ahead":"If you survive even and hit your item first, stop respecting him entirely — Alpha Strike dodges his W stun and your on-hit shreds him in any extended fight. Use Highlander resets off each kill to roam to the next lane rather than sitting top farming a beaten Renekton. Your job once ahead is to convert his fall-off into map pressure before his team can group to peel your dives.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Renekton - Track: His W, Ruthless Predator — the fury-empowered point-and-click stun. It locks you the moment Alpha Strike ends and sets up his entire kill combo; never commit while it's available.. - Concede the early lane, freeze near your tower, and use Alpha Strike + Wuju Style autos to farm without eating his W stun, then hit Kraken/Blade of the Ruined King and turn every extended fight into an on-hit reset chain with Highlander. Your win condition is the back half of the game, not the lane itself.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Renekton bullies you off every wave from levels 1-6 with his stun and fury combos, but if you farm safe with Alpha Strike and survive to your first on-hit item, you flip the lane and run him down once he falls off."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive Renekton's level 1-6 dominance by farming under tower with Alpha Strike and never eating his W stun, then flip the lane at your first on-hit item. Your whole game is the scaling crossover — concede the lane, win the game."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Renekton owns 1-5 (peak at 3), you claim level 6 with Highlander, then it tips fully to you at first item and you dominate at 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"No trades pre-item — only Q to last-hit. Post-item, only commit when his Ruthless Predator W is on cooldown, then Alpha Strike in and Wuju-DPS him."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Freeze just outside your tower so you farm safely and starve his all-in range; never shove into him at level 3 where he can empower W and dive your Alpha Strike reset."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike makes you untargetable to dodge his W stun and ult, but only if you blink while it's down — if W is up he stuns you the frame the blink ends. Wuju Style's true damage ignores the armor he'd otherwise stack, and Meditate out-sustains his decayed fury poke but not his empowered burst."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (faster on-hit ramp for the scaling fight), Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve with Second Wind + Overgrowth to survive his early poke. Take Conqueror only if you want more dueling weight, but Resolve secondary is non-negotiable into his early bully pattern."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Teleport — Ignite doesn't win you the early lane you're going to lose, and TP lets you farm safe, recover from a rough back, and stay even on items, which is the only thing that matters in this matchup."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first for the on-hit spike, then Wit's End vs his physical damage (it's also MR), Terminus or Death's Dance into his AD, Berserker's Greaves, and a defensive third like Maw or armor if he somehow stays ahead."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Only after your first item AND with his W on cooldown — pre-item there is no all-in window, and forcing one is the most common way this lane is lost."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're extremely gankable early since Alpha Strike is your only escape and he sets up the W stun for a dive — ward his fury timings and play for your own jungler to counter-gank once you have Highlander."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players trying to duel Renekton early because the champ 'snowballs' — you don't snowball this lane, you survive it; over-committing Alpha Strike pre-item feeds the exact lead that denies your scaling."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Farm under tower, take TP recalls to stay on item curve, give up the wave before the kill, and group with your team — your power is a teamfight item spike, not a 1v1 comeback against a fed Renekton."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Chain Highlander resets off kills to roam and snowball other lanes; once at 2+ items you out-DPS and dodge everything he has, so press your lead across the map instead of farming a dead lane."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"TRICKY (47.49% WR) — Renekton edges a brutal early lane, but survive to your on-hit items and the matchup flips hard in your favor; play to scale, not to win lane."}]},"riven":{"tldr":"A miserable scaling race where Riven kills you three times before your first item even comes online — survive, don't fight.","winCon":"Concede every level-1-through-5 trade, farm with Alpha Strike from max range, and stall the lane until your first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) lets Wuju Style true damage out-DPS her once her Q dashes and shield are on cooldown. You don't win lane — you survive it, hit 2+ items, and win the map with Highlander resets in skirmishes she can't reach.","enemyWin":"Riven walks up the instant your Alpha Strike or Flash is down, lands her third-Q stun into a full Q-W-E burst combo, and deletes you before Meditate can channel a single tick. She just has to deny you CS and zone you off the wave every cooldown cycle — your weak early base damage means you can't punish her even when she whiffs.","diff":"HARD","tone":"#ff5d6c","diffRating":"8/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Riven","rating":"7/10","why":"Riven's Q dashes and 290 range let her auto-Q poke you while your only level-1 tool, Alpha Strike, is a one-target farm blink that gives no escape value."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Riven","rating":"7/10","why":"At level 2 she takes a second Q charge and can chain two dashes into you for a free trade your low base damage can't answer."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Riven","rating":"8/10","why":"Level 3 Riven has Q-W-E online — her W stun catches you mid-Alpha-Strike on the way out and her shield eats the only return damage you have."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Riven","rating":"7/10","why":"Levels 4-5 Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain stabilize you for short trades, but her third-Q stun still wins any extended fight she commits to."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Riven","rating":"6/10","why":"Your Highlander at 6 finally lets you dodge her all-in with Alpha Strike's untargetable frames, but she has no ult to fear and still out-bursts you flat."},{"label":"First item","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) flips extended fights — if you bait her Q-W-E shield and Alpha Strike through the stun, Wuju autos out-DPS her; if she lands the combo clean she still kills you."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"At 2+ items Wuju Style true damage shreds her bruiser build and Highlander resets chain through her once Alpha Strike dodges the stun — but only if you survived to here."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are the worst part of this lane. Riven out-ranges you with her Q dashes, out-trades you with raw base damage, and your Alpha Strike does nothing defensively against a target sitting on top of you — it only blinks you between enemies, it doesn't reset her stun timer. Farm at max range, take the Wuju autos you can grab safely, and never contest a wave she's standing on. If she gets two early kills here, the lane is functionally over.","mid":"Levels 4-6 you stabilize slightly: Wuju Style's true damage and Meditate's sustain mean you survive short pokes and recover chunks. Level 6 Highlander is your first real defensive tool — its move speed and slow immunity let you reposition out of her combo, and Alpha Strike's untargetable frames can dodge the third-Q stun if you time the blink as she winds it up. Still don't start fights; you're buying time, not winning the lane.","late":"At 2+ items (Kraken/BORK into Wit's End or Terminus) the matchup inverts in extended fights. Riven is a burst-window bruiser — once her Q-W-E combo and shield are spent she has nothing, and Wuju Style true damage ignores her armor while Highlander refreshes off any kill or assist. If you can reach a side-lane 1v1 or a teamfight where she's already used her combo, you win it. Hard scalers don't reclaim this — Riven falls off, so the longer the game the better for you.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push into her tower so you can farm under plates and deny her the all-in space she needs. Worst wave: a fast-shoving wave that drags you to the middle of the lane where her three Q dashes have full engage range and you have no escape. Crash timing: crash the wave just before your first-item recall so you reset with Kraken/BORK and lose zero CS while she can't dive your plates.","cooldowns":"Track her third Q (the AOE stun) above everything — it's the only hard CC in her kit and it's what lands her full combo on you. Her Q stacks decay if she stops dashing, so bait the first two charges and step back before the third; once it's spent she has roughly 4 seconds of zero lockdown to walk up in.","trading":"Her pattern is dash-in, Q-W-E burst inside her combo window, then dash out on the empowered third Q or E. Your only good trade is AFTER she's blown that combo: Alpha Strike onto her, pop Wuju Style, and auto her down while her shield and dashes are on cooldown. Trading into a fresh combo is suicide.","spikes":"Riven spikes hardest at level 3 (full combo) and at her first bruiser item — that's her kill window. Your spikes are level 6 (Highlander defense) and your first on-hit completion, which is where the lane stops being a free kill for her.","feeding":"If you fall behind here you become unkillable-to-farm but irrelevant — a 0/3 Yi can't fight anyone and Riven roams to snowball other lanes. Stop trying to recover CS in lane, farm jungle camps and side waves safely, and don't show for fights until you have two items.","carry":"If you somehow get ahead, Yi's snowball is brutal: Highlander resets off kills, Alpha Strike's untargetability lets you dive past her peel, and Wuju true damage shreds anyone she's grouped with. One pick in a side lane becomes a chain of resets across the map.","difficulty":"It's an 8/10 because Riven has everything that beats Yi — point-and-click-adjacent burst, a hard stun to catch you after Alpha Strike, mobility to chase, and a kit that's strongest exactly when yours is weakest. The 36.88% win rate is real: you lose the lane by default and have to win the game in spite of it."},"focus":{"text":"Her third Q (Broken Wings) — the AOE knockup/stun that lands her entire Q-W-E burst on you. Bait the first two dashes, step back, and only walk up once that third charge is spent; getting stunned by it is what turns every trade into a death.","letters":["Q","W"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike at range","d":"Use Q to last-hit from outside her dash range so you never have to walk into the wave where her three Q charges can engage you. Grab the free Wuju autos only when she's animation-locked on a minion."},{"t":"Save Alpha Strike for her combo, not for waveclear","d":"Alpha Strike's untargetable frames are your only escape — time the blink as she winds up the third-Q stun or her W, and you dodge the lockdown that would otherwise kill you. Don't burn it on CS when she's looking to all-in."},{"t":"Scale and look for her empty window","d":"Your whole game is reaching 2+ items. Only ever fight her after she's blown Q-W-E and her shield — that's when Wuju true damage and Highlander resets flip the duel in your favor."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't trade into a fresh combo","d":"If her Q stacks are up and her shield is available, any trade you start she wins — she'll stun you mid-Alpha-Strike and burst you before Meditate channels. Wait her out."},{"t":"Don't Meditate in her face","d":"W Meditate roots you in a channel; Riven just walks up, lands her stun, and free-hits you out of it. Only channel when she's clearly out of dash range or recalling."},{"t":"Don't over-farm into a shove","d":"Letting the wave fast-push to mid-lane hands Riven the open space her three dashes need. Slow-push or hold near your tower so she can't all-in without diving plates."}],"tradeGood":"Alpha Strike onto her right after she's spent Q-W-E and her shield, pop Wuju Style, and auto her down while her dashes and stun are on cooldown.","tradeBad":"Walking up to last-hit while her third Q is charged — she dashes in, stuns you, and full-combos you before you can react.","ahead":"An ahead Yi turns this lane from a loss into a snowball engine. Once you have a kill and your first item, look to Alpha Strike past her shield in skirmishes — her peel is single-target burst, not lockdown, so Highlander's slow immunity carries you through it and every kill refreshes your ult to chain into the next fight. Roam to other lanes the moment she recalls; a fed Yi with Wuju true damage ends games far faster than a Riven who's fallen off her item spikes.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Riven - Track: Her third Q (Broken Wings) — the AOE knockup/stun that lands her entire Q-W-E burst on you. Bait the first two dashes, step back, and only walk up once that third charge is spent; getting stunned by it is what turns every trade into a death.. - Concede every level-1-through-5 trade, farm with Alpha Strike from max range, and stall the lane until your first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) lets Wuju Style true damage out-DPS her once her Q dashes and shield are on cooldown. You don't win lane — you survive it, hit 2+ items, and win the map with Highlander resets in skirmishes she can't reach.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A miserable scaling race where Riven kills you three times before your first item even comes online — survive, don't fight."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Master Yi cannot out-lane Riven — his win condition is survival and scaling, conceding all early aggression to reach his first on-hit item where Wuju Style true damage and Alpha Strike's untargetable frames let him win extended fights once her combo is spent. He wins the game, not the lane: hit 2+ items, find Riven after she's used Q-W-E, and chain Highlander resets through a kit that has nothing left."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Riven owns levels 1-5 hard, the gap narrows at 6 (Highlander defense) and your first item, and flips toward Yi only at 2+ items as Riven falls off and Wuju true damage shreds her."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Only trade after Riven has spent her third Q (stun) and shield; back off entirely while her Q stacks are charged or her shield is up. Bait the first two dashes, step out of range, then punish the ~4-second window where she has no lockdown."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave slow-pushing toward your side or freezing near your tower so Riven can't get the open mid-lane space her three dashes need. Farm under plates rather than contesting a wave she's standing on; crash just before your first-item back."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable frames can dodge Riven's third-Q stun and her W if you blink as she winds up — this is your single most important interaction, since the stun is what lands her full burst. Wuju Style's true damage ignores the armor in her bruiser build, and Highlander's slow immunity beats her E-dash chase. Note Meditate's channel roots you and is free combo bait for her — don't use it in range."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (faster on-hit ramp to survive trades and out-DPS once itemized) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, and Last Stand; secondary Resolve (Conditioning or Bone Plating into her AD burst) plus Second Wind for the early poke. Bone Plating specifically blunts her opening Q-W-E. Take Conqueror only if you want more raw extended-fight damage, but Bone Plating value is higher here."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Teleport — Ignite does nothing for a lane you can't win early, while TP lets you stay even on CS after her zoning shoves you off the wave and reach the map plays where you actually scale. Hold Flash strictly for her all-in, not for aggression."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first for the on-hit DPS spike, then Wit's End — its magic resist is wasted here but the attack speed and on-hit are core; better to go Terminus or an early Steel of legends/armor item like Frozen Heart-adjacent if her snowball is bad. Take Plated Steelcaps against her all-AD combo, and consider Death's Dance for the AD-burst mitigation if she's fed."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Almost never in lane before items. Your only true all-in window is after she's spent Q-W-E and her shield with her dashes down, ideally at level 6+ with Highlander up — Alpha Strike in, Wuju Style on, and burn her while she has no escape and no stun."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Riven is a strong dive partner and your early weakness makes you extremely gankable — ward the river side she pushes toward and play for your own jungler to camp her, since a Yi who gets one early kill flips the scaling math entirely. Track her flash; she'll burn it to secure a gank kill on you."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players try to trade back when Riven walks up, trusting Alpha Strike as an escape — but it only blinks between enemies and doesn't break her stun, so they get caught and deleted. The other mistake is Meditating in her face and getting free-hit out of the channel. Respect that you lose every fair trade."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're behind, fully give up the lane: farm jungle camps and safe side waves, take TP plays to stay level, and don't show for any fight until you have two items. A 0/3 Yi is useless — your only value is reaching the point where Wuju true damage matters, so stall the game."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If ahead, Alpha Strike past her single-target peel in skirmishes, chain Highlander resets off every kill, and roam the instant she recalls. Wuju true damage means even a slightly-fed Yi shreds her whole team; close fast before her bruiser-item spikes mean anything."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"HARD (36.88% WR, 8/10 difficulty) — you lose this lane by default to Riven's burst and stun; survive to 2+ items and win the game instead of the matchup."}]},"rumble":{"tldr":"A 63% lane where Rumble's Flamespitter chips you for three weak levels, then your on-hit spike turns him into free Highlander resets the moment you survive to items.","winCon":"Concede the early flame chip and farm with Alpha Strike, then hit your first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) and Q onto Rumble to ignore his Electro Harpoon slow and out-DPS his sustained burn before he can overheat-and-kite. Wuju Style true damage shreds his low base resistances, and every kill resets Highlander to chain through his cooldowns.","enemyWin":"Rumble wins the first three levels outright by stacking Flamespitter on you while Scrap Shield and Electro Harpoon's slow kite you out of melee, denying CS and setting up a level-6 Equalizer + jungler dive before your items come online. If he keeps you off the wave and burns your Meditate with overheated DoT, you never reach the scaling that makes the lane 63%.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"4/10","carryRating":"9/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Rumble","rating":"7/10","why":"Flamespitter is a free sustained magic DoT on the cone and your short-range autos can't contest it — you have no E true damage or R yet, so you just eat chip and last-hit with Alpha Strike."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Rumble","rating":"6/10","why":"Electro Harpoon's slow plus Scrap Shield move speed let him kite your autos while Flamespitter ticks; Meditate can heal the chip but channeling it concedes the wave."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Rumble","rating":"6/10","why":"He still out-trades you in the open — Wuju Style true damage isn't enough yet to beat an overheated Flamespitter, so Alpha-strike the wave and avoid standing in his cone."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain come online for short Q-in trades, but a fresh Scrap Shield + Harpoon slow still lets him disengage — trade only on his shield cooldown."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander gives slow immunity that nullifies Electro Harpoon and the move speed to stick through his kite — pop it on his shield-down window and Alpha Strike dodges the Equalizer cast."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King on-hit plus Wuju true damage out-DPS his burn through his thin resistances; Alpha Strike's untargetable blink eats the Equalizer zone and resets your attack timer on him."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"9/10","why":"At two items you out-sustain Flamespitter with Meditate and run him down — Highlander resets on the kill, and slow immunity means Harpoon and Scrap Shield can't peel you off the chain."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Rumble and there is no way around it — Flamespitter is a sustained magic DoT painted on a cone, not an auto you can dodge, so your only counterplay is to last-hit at the edge of the cone with Alpha Strike and refuse to stand in it. Don't try to trade autos: his Scrap Shield absorbs your first hits and Electro Harpoon's slow lets him walk away while the burn keeps ticking. Use Meditate to heal off-wave chip between minions, accept the CS you'll lose, and just survive to your spike — every level you stay even on farm is a level closer to flipping the lane.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are where your sustain starts mattering: Wuju Style gives your autos bonus true damage that ignores his (low) resistances and Meditate out-heals Flamespitter chip if you don't get caught channeling. Take only short trades when his Scrap Shield is on cooldown — Q in, load Wuju autos, and disengage before he re-shields and re-slows. Level 6 Highlander is the turning point: the slow immunity hard-counters Electro Harpoon and the move speed lets you finally stick through his kite. Hold it for his shield-down window or to answer a gank.","late":"Past two on-hit items (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King into Wit's End / Terminus) the lane is yours and it isn't close — your DPS plus Wuju true damage shreds his thin AP-bruiser resistances faster than overheated Flamespitter can burn you, and Meditate sustains the rest. Alpha Strike's untargetability lets you blink through the Equalizer zone entirely, and Highlander resets on every kill so you chain through his long cooldowns. The only late danger is a teamfight where his Equalizer carpets a choke — pick him off in the side lane instead.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push that lets you shove him under tower and roam/recall on your item spike. Worst wave: a wave frozen near his tower where he free-pokes you with Flamespitter and a gank traps you in his cone. Crash timing: crash the wave just before your first on-hit item back so you reset, buy, and come back able to duel him with the slow-immune Highlander window up.","cooldowns":"Track Scrap Shield (W) — it's his only steroid and the move-speed source for his kite; every trade you take should land in the seconds it's on cooldown. Secondarily count Electro Harpoon charges, since the slow is what lets him peel you pre-6.","trading":"Your trade is: wait out Scrap Shield, Q (Alpha Strike) onto him to reset your attack timer and ignore the slow, then auto with Wuju Style true damage active and walk off before he re-shields. Never stand-and-trade in an active Flamespitter cone — his sustained DoT beats your short-range autos until you're itemized.","spikes":"Rumble's spikes: level 1 Flamespitter, level 6 Equalizer, and an overheated Flamespitter (Danger Zone) at any point. Your spikes: level 6 Highlander (slow immunity vs Harpoon), and decisively your first on-hit item — that's when the 63% starts and the lane inverts.","feeding":"If you fall behind, an overheated Flamespitter plus Equalizer can chunk you before you reach items, and a Rumble with a lead will perma-shove and deny your scaling. Don't keep face-checking his cone for CS — give up the wave, farm side, and ping for jungle help; your curve recovers the moment you complete one on-hit item.","carry":"Ahead, you're one of the streakiest snowballs in the game: every Rumble kill resets Highlander, shortens your other cooldowns, and lets you Alpha Strike into the next fight untargetable. Take the side lane to force 1v1s where his Equalizer does the least, and split-push him off the map — he can't 1v1 you once you're two items up.","difficulty":"It's only 4/10 because the hard part is purely surviving three flame-chip levels with no escape but Q — Rumble has no hard CC to lock you after Alpha Strike and no way to kite a slow-immune Highlander, so once you reach items the lane is mechanically easy and heavily in your favor."},"focus":{"text":"The Equalizer (R) — Rumble carpets the ground you want to stand on to duel, and an overheated Flamespitter under it can chunk you before items; time your Alpha Strike to blink through the zone untargetable rather than walking across it.","letters":["R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Q, don't trade","d":"Levels 1-3, last-hit with Alpha Strike from the edge of his Flamespitter cone and refuse auto exchanges — you cannot beat sustained flame DoT until you have an on-hit item."},{"t":"Trade on Scrap Shield cooldown","d":"His shield is his only steroid and his kite speed; Q in and load Wuju Style true damage only when W is down, then walk off before he re-shields and Harpoon-slows you."},{"t":"Save Highlander for slow immunity","d":"Level 6 R makes Electro Harpoon's slow useless and gives the speed to stick on him — pop it to commit a kill or to chase him out of his own kite, not randomly."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't stand in Flamespitter","d":"It's a sustained magic DoT on a cone, not an auto — Alpha Strike and Meditate don't make it whiff, so eating the cone just hands him the early lane for free."},{"t":"Don't walk across the Equalizer","d":"Crossing his R carpet, especially under an overheated Flamespitter, can delete your weak early HP bar — Alpha Strike through it untargetable or fight off the line."},{"t":"Don't Meditate mid-trade","d":"Channeling Meditate roots you in his cone and lets him free-cast Harpoon and re-stack the burn — heal with it off-wave, never as a trade button against him."}],"tradeGood":"Wait out Scrap Shield, Alpha Strike onto Rumble to reset your attack timer and ignore his slow, then auto him with Wuju Style true damage active and disengage before he re-shields.","tradeBad":"Standing in an active (or overheated) Flamespitter cone trying to out-auto him before your first on-hit item — his sustained burn beats your short range and you'll lose the HP race you can't yet win.","ahead":"Press a lead by forcing the side lane where his Equalizer does the least and your 1v1 is uncontested — once you're a kill or an item up, no Rumble survives an extended duel. Every kill resets Highlander and trims your cooldowns, so chain pressure across the map rather than grouping into his teamfight zoning. Build the on-hit lead into objectives: a slow-immune, untargetable Yi takes Drakes and dives backlines faster than Rumble can rotate a flame carpet to stop you.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Rumble - Track: The Equalizer (R) — Rumble carpets the ground you want to stand on to duel, and an overheated Flamespitter under it can chunk you before items; time your Alpha Strike to blink through the zone untargetable rather than walking across it.. - Concede the early flame chip and farm with Alpha Strike, then hit your first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) and Q onto Rumble to ignore his Electro Harpoon slow and out-DPS his sustained burn before he can overheat-and-kite. Wuju Style true damage shreds his low base resistances, and every kill resets Highlander to chain through his cooldowns.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A 63% lane where Rumble's Flamespitter chips you for three weak levels, then your on-hit spike turns him into free Highlander resets the moment you survive to items."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive the three flame-chip levels by farming with Alpha Strike and healing chip with Meditate, then hit your first on-hit item and Q onto Rumble to out-DPS his sustained burn through his thin resistances. Highlander's slow immunity nullifies his Electro Harpoon kite, so once you're itemized he has no tool to stop you running him down and resetting through his cooldowns."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Rumble owns 1-3 (Flamespitter chip, no E/R yet), it's even 4-5 as Wuju true damage and Meditate come online, and it flips hard to Yi from level 6 / first item onward — decisively yours at 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only when Scrap Shield is on cooldown: Q in, auto with Wuju Style active, leave before he re-shields. Back off entirely whenever Flamespitter is active on you or he's near the Danger Zone overheat — eat no free cone damage pre-item."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Pre-6, let the wave sit slightly toward you or last-hit at max range so you're not pinned in his cone for a gank. On your item spike, slow-push and crash so you can recall, complete the on-hit item, and return with the Highlander window to duel."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike is untargetable mid-blink, so it dodges the Equalizer cast and any jungler skillshot timed with his combo. Highlander's slow immunity hard-counters Electro Harpoon. The catch: Flamespitter is a magic DoT, not an attack, so neither Q nor Meditate makes it 'miss' — you can only avoid it by not standing in the cone. Wuju Style's true damage ignores his AP-bruiser resistances entirely."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (uncaps attack speed for the on-hit duel and helps you out-DPS his burn) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve — Conditioning or Second Wind (Second Wind is excellent vs his constant Flamespitter poke) plus Overgrowth. Take Magic Resist shards (he's full AP) and an HP shard for the weak early lane."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite if your jungler will help you punish his weak escape and you want the snowball kill pressure at 6. Take Teleport instead if he's perma-shoving you out of lane early — TP keeps you on the scaling track so you reach your item spike even after a rough start."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush an on-hit core — Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first, into Wit's End (the MR plus magic-shred is perfect against his full-AP burn) or Terminus; finish with attack speed and an on-hit third. Boots: Mercury's Treads for the magic-damage reduction and tenacity against any CC setting up his Equalizer. Add Maw of Malmortius later if he's fed for the magic shield."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Your real all-in is level 6 with Highlander up and his Scrap Shield down, and especially after your first on-hit item completes — that's where slow immunity plus on-hit DPS lets you stick and kill through his kite. Don't commit a full all-in onto a fresh Equalizer."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're gankable and weak early, so the lane swings on jungle proximity — a Rumble with jungle help can dive you under his Equalizer before items. Ward up pre-6 and play for your own jungler to punish his immobility; post-6 your Highlander mobility lets you escape or turn ganks that a fresh Rumble can't follow."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi error here is trying to contest the early lane — standing in Flamespitter to trade or burning Meditate as a panic button mid-cone. You can't win levels 1-3; respecting that and farming to your item spike is the entire matchup."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're behind, give up the wave and farm the side lane safely with Alpha Strike, take Teleport value, and avoid his cone entirely. Ward against the dive and let your team make plays while you catch up — one on-hit item still lets you re-enter the duel, since Rumble has no hard CC to permanently lock you."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Ahead, take the side lane to force 1v1s away from his Equalizer zoning, chain Highlander resets through kills, and convert the on-hit lead into Drakes and backline dives. Split-push him off the map — he cannot 1v1 a two-item Yi."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED, 63% — Rumble owns the first three flame-chip levels, but you have no hard CC to fear and a brutal on-hit spike; survive the early cone and the lane is decisively yours from item one."}]},"ryze":{"tldr":"Survive Ryze's level 1-5 root-poke, hit your first on-hit item, then Alpha Strike through his Q-E root chain and run him down before he becomes a raid boss.","winCon":"Farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos through his early poke, hit Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King, then use Highlander plus Q's untargetability to dodge his root combo and out-DPS him in melee range. Every kill resets Highlander and shaves your cooldowns, so chain him before his W shield and resets stack up.","enemyWin":"Ryze lands his Q-into-E (or W) root, kites you with spammy ranged poke, and chunks you out of lane before you itemize. If he scales to 2+ items uncaught, his raid-boss DPS and root chain reclaim the lane and win every extended fight.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"4/10","carryRating":"9/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Ryze","rating":"6/10","why":"Ryze pokes with Q from range while your only tool is Alpha Strike to farm the casters; he chunks you for free."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Ryze","rating":"6/10","why":"His level-2 Q-E gives him an early root combo and you have no Wuju true damage or Highlander to punish it yet."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"You can E Wuju Style and Q-reset onto him for a short burst, but his W root still walks you back; trades are roughly even."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Master Yi","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju true damage and Meditate sustain let you all-in a missed root; you out-trade him on cooldown windows."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity let you ride through his slow and Q-untarget his root, flipping short fights your way."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King on-hit DPS shreds his low base HP faster than his W shield and resets can answer."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Ryze","rating":"6/10","why":"If uncaught, Ryze's raid-boss scaling and rooted-target DPS reclaim the late game; force the win before his core completes."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Ryze. He pokes with Q from outside your range and you have no escape but Alpha Strike, so don't try to trade — last-hit with Q on the caster wave and Wuju autos on the melees. Eat the poke, hold your position, and never walk into a Q that can chain into his E or W root.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are your stabilization. Wuju Style's true damage ignores any MR/armor and Meditate sustains his poke, so you can answer a whiffed root with a Q-reset all-in. Level 6 Highlander is your real turning point — the attack speed, move speed, and slow immunity let you stick to him and dodge his root with Q's untargetability frames.","late":"At 2+ items you out-DPS Ryze in any extended melee fight: Alpha Strike dodges his root, on-hit shreds through his W shield, and every kill resets Highlander to chain. But Ryze is a hard scaler — if he reaches full build uncaught, his raid-boss damage and root chain reclaim fights, so close the game on your item spike.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push that traps Ryze under tower so he can't safely poke and you crash for a free recall after your item. Worst wave: a wave shoved into your tower under his ranged poke, where he zones you off CS for free. Crash timing: crash the wave right as your first on-hit item completes so you can recall, buy, and return on your spike with a fresh wave.","cooldowns":"Track his E (the root finisher) and W (point-blank root) — if either is on cooldown after a Q, that's your all-in window.","trading":"Eat poke while farming early; from level 6 wait for him to commit Q-E into the wave, then Q-reset + E Wuju Style onto him under Highlander and burst him before his shield and resets recover.","spikes":"Ryze spikes at level 6 and at Tear/Lost Chapter into Archangel's; you spike at level 6 Highlander and hard at first on-hit item (Kraken / Blade of the Ruined King).","feeding":"If you fall behind, Ryze out-ranges and out-roots you permanently — he pokes you off the wave, his ganks become free with the root, and you give up farm and tempo, deleting your scaling window.","carry":"Once ahead, your reset-snowball is brutal: catch Ryze with a Q after his root is down, kill him, refresh Highlander, and use the reduced cooldowns to take towers, dives, and cross-map fights before he comes back online.","difficulty":"It's only 4/10 because the lolalytics 62.75% win rate reflects how decisively you flip it post-item — the early poke and root are real, but they don't beat you hard enough to stop you scaling past him."},"focus":{"text":"His root chain — Q into E (or point-blank W) is the only thing that stops Alpha Strike from being your get-out; if you're rooted out of Q, his poke and follow-up delete you. Bait it before you commit.","letters":["E","W"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm, don't fight, early","d":"Use Alpha Strike to clear the caster wave and Wuju autos on melees while eating his poke; you have no level 1-3 trade, so just hit your item spike intact."},{"t":"Q through the root","d":"Time Alpha Strike's untargetability frames to dodge his E/W root the instant he commits, then land on top of him with Highlander active."},{"t":"All-in on his root cooldown","d":"After he whiffs or burns Q-E into the wave, that's your window — E Wuju Style true damage plus on-hit melts his low base HP before his shield and resets recover."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't walk into Q range pre-6","d":"His Q is a free poke that chains into a root; eating it for no reason just chunks you out of your scaling lane for nothing."},{"t":"Don't let him scale uncaught","d":"Ryze is a hard scaler — if you AFK-farm and let him hit Archangel's plus full build, his raid-boss DPS and root chain reclaim every late fight."},{"t":"Don't Meditate mid-combo","d":"Channeling Meditate inside his root or Q poke just feeds him free damage and locks you in place; only sustain when he's out of spells."}],"tradeGood":"Bait his Q-E root into the wave, Alpha Strike onto him as it whiffs, then E Wuju Style + on-hit autos under Highlander to burst him before his shield refreshes.","tradeBad":"Walking up to auto him while his root is up — he Q-E roots you, kites out of Alpha Strike range, and pokes you to death for free.","ahead":"Press by catching Ryze whenever his root is on cooldown — Q onto him, kill, and let Highlander reset shave your cooldowns so you can immediately threaten the next play. Use your tempo to take plates and roam, because a fed Yi cross-maps before Ryze scales. Deny his farm and items so his raid-boss late game never arrives.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Ryze - Track: His root chain — Q into E (or point-blank W) is the only thing that stops Alpha Strike from being your get-out; if you're rooted out of Q, his poke and follow-up delete you. Bait it before you commit.. - Farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos through his early poke, hit Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King, then use Highlander plus Q's untargetability to dodge his root combo and out-DPS him in melee range. Every kill resets Highlander and shaves your cooldowns, so chain him before his W shield and resets stack up.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Survive Ryze's level 1-5 root-poke, hit your first on-hit item, then Alpha Strike through his Q-E root chain and run him down before he becomes a raid boss."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a weak, pokey level 1-5 by farming with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, then hit Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King and use Highlander plus Q's untargetability to dodge Ryze's root and out-DPS him in melee. Every kill resets Highlander and reduces your cooldowns, so chain kills and end before his scaling completes."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Ryze owns 1-2 with Q poke and the early root, the lane evens out at 3-5 as Wuju and Meditate come online, and you take over from level 6 Highlander through first item — only the uncaught 2+ items window swings back to his scaling."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Don't trade levels 1-3 — just farm and eat poke. From 4 onward, only commit when his E/W root is on cooldown; Q-reset + Wuju Style burst, then disengage before his shield and resets recover."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Hold the wave near the middle or slow-push so Ryze can't safely poke you off CS; avoid letting it freeze under his tower where he zones you. Crash on your item spike to recall and return on your power."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges his Q/E/W root and any incoming damage during the blink; Wuju Style's true damage ignores his MR and shreds his low base HP; Highlander's slow immunity nullifies his kite; Meditate out-sustains his poke when he's out of spells."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (his MR is low and you want sustained on-hit stacking) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Coup de Grace; secondary Resolve (Conditioning/Overgrowth) or Sorcery (Celerity/Waterwalking) — take MR shard vs his AP poke and a second HP shard."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to convert your post-6 all-ins into kills and cut his W heal/shield value; take Teleport instead only if you expect to get poked off the wave repeatedly and need to reset onto your spike."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King, then Wit's End or Terminus for MR and on-hit to answer his AP — Wit's End in particular shreds his MR and sustains; Berserker's Greaves, and consider Mercury's Treads if his root chain is landing. Add Maw / Hexdrinker against his burst poke."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You can all-in from level 6 the moment his E/W root is down, and decisively at first on-hit item — Q-reset in, E Wuju Style, and out-DPS him before his shield and resets stabilize."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Your jungler is your early lifeline — a level 3-5 gank lets you escape his poke and snowball before scaling; conversely his root makes you extremely gankable, so ward his flanks and don't overstep when his jungler is unknown."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players try to trade or all-in too early into his root, get chained and kited, and fall behind — and then AFK-farm too passively and let Ryze scale uncaught. Respect 1-5, then punish hard."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If losing, give up nothing but farm — Alpha Strike the wave from max range, dodge his Q, never face-check his root, and group with your team where your on-hit DPS still matters even off an even CS lead."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"When ahead, catch him every time his root is on cooldown, reset Highlander off the kill, and convert the freed cooldowns into plates, dives, and cross-map roams before his raid-boss scaling arrives."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED (4/10 difficulty, 62.75% WR) — eat the early poke, hit your item, and Alpha Strike through his root to run down a scaler who can't kite you anymore."}]},"sejuani":{"tldr":"A brick wall: Sejuani's permafrost slows, point-and-click E stun, and AOE R lock you down the instant Alpha Strike ends, so you concede lane, farm safe, and try to outscale her into the late game.","winCon":"Survive the early game, hit your on-hit spike (Kraken/BORK into Wit's End), and only fight Sejuani once you can burst her health bar faster than she can stack Permafrost and reach R — ideally side-laning away from her CC chain rather than dueling her head-on. Use Alpha Strike to dodge her E stun cast, then commit only when Highlander is up to chain through her team.","enemyWin":"Sejuani slows you with auto-attack Permafrost stacks, lands her E stun the moment your Alpha Strike blink finishes, then walks you down or chains R to peel for her team — every hard-CC point she has answers your only escape. She wins by being unkiteable-in-reverse: you can't run her down without eating a full stun-and-slow chain that hands the trade to her jungler.","diff":"HARD","tone":"#ff5d6c","diffRating":"7/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Sejuani","rating":"6/10","why":"Sejuani's auto-attacks stack Permafrost to root/slow while your level-1 Alpha Strike does chip damage and no escape, so she controls the first wave."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Sejuani","rating":"6/10","why":"With W's percent-HP damage and Permafrost slow she out-trades your short autos; you have no Wuju true damage or Meditate yet to answer."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Sejuani","rating":"6/10","why":"Her E charges toward a stun off her own auto-attack stacks, catching you after any Alpha Strike before you have Highlander to dodge ganks."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Sejuani","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain stabilize your CS, but she's tanky enough that your short trades barely dent her and Permafrost still kites you off."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Sejuani","rating":"7/10","why":"Her R is a guaranteed AOE airborne+stun that totally negates Highlander's slow-immunity and your reset chain, locking you out of any fight she initiates."},{"label":"First item","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Kraken/BORK on-hit lets you melt her health, but she armor-stacks and her full CC chain (E stun into R) still wins any straight duel — you need her CC down to commit."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"At 2+ items your on-hit DPS plus Wit's End true damage shreds even a tanky Sejuani if you Alpha Strike past her E and Highlander-reset through the fight after her R is on cooldown."}],"breakdown":{"early":"You lose levels 1-3 outright. Sejuani's auto-attacks stack Permafrost, slowing then rooting you, while her W chunks a percent of your health and you have nothing but a short-range Alpha Strike that gives no escape. Just farm with Q on the casters, never walk up for an auto trade, and respect that any step forward is a free Permafrost stack toward her E stun.","mid":"Levels 4-6 you stabilize on CS as Wuju Style's true damage and Meditate's heal come online for the occasional short poke, but Sejuani is too tanky for your autos to matter and she still kites you with slows. Her level 6 R is the trap — it's a guaranteed AOE stun that completely ignores Highlander's slow immunity, so once she hits 6 you cannot fight her without flashing or baiting the ult first.","late":"At 2+ items (Kraken/BORK + Wit's End/Terminus) you finally out-DPS her in a vacuum — on-hit plus true damage shreds tank stats. But Sejuani never duels you alone late; she's a front-line peel tank, so your real job is to Alpha Strike past her E, kill her carries, and only touch Sejuani when her E and R are both down.","wave":"Best wave: a wave you can shove and roam from, or one frozen near your tower where she can't engage. Worst wave: a wave pushed into her side where she and her jungler can collapse and chain CC you off Permafrost stacks. Crash timing: crash the wave before her jungler's first clear path reaches top (around 3:15) so you reset and deny a Permafrost+gank setup, then look to slow-push and freeze after.","cooldowns":"Track her E (Arctic Assault stun) — it's her only point-and-click hard-CC that catches you out of Alpha Strike. If you bait or dodge the E cast, her trade and gank-setup collapse for its full cooldown.","trading":"Never auto-trade into her — she wins extended autos via Permafrost slow + W percent damage. Your only good trade is Alpha Strike onto her to proc on-hit and instantly back off before a Permafrost stack lands; anything longer hands her the stun window.","spikes":"Your spikes: level 6 Highlander (gank-dodging), Kraken/BORK first item, then 2+ items where you flip favoured. Her spikes: level 1 Permafrost pressure, level 6 R (hard negates your slow immunity), and any Frozen-Heart/armor item that blunts your on-hit.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Sejuani becomes an unkillable peel wall who perma-slows you and her R deletes your reset chain — you go from weak laner to useless teamfighter. A fed Sejuani means you literally cannot reach the backline without dying to the stun, so play sidelane and splitpush instead.","carry":"If you get ahead, you don't 1v1 Sejuani — you ignore her. Alpha Strike past her E, Highlander-reset through her squishies, and let your on-hit true damage erase her carries while her tankiness becomes irrelevant. Split-push to drag her away from her team and take her tower.","difficulty":"It's a 45% lane because Sejuani is the textbook anti-Yi: point-and-click slows that you can't dodge, an E stun that catches you the instant Alpha Strike's untargetability ends, and an AOE R that flat-out ignores Highlander's slow immunity. Every one of her tools answers your one escape, and she out-sustains your early chip while out-scaling your relevance into teamfights."},"focus":{"text":"Her R (Glacial Prison / Permafrost ult) — a guaranteed AOE airborne-and-stun that completely ignores Highlander's slow immunity and ends your reset chain; never commit to a fight while it's up.","letters":["R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm and scale, don't duel","d":"Concede the early lane entirely — use Alpha Strike to last-hit the caster wave and Wuju autos on melees, and accept you're a CS-and-XP bot until your first on-hit item."},{"t":"Dodge her E with Alpha Strike","d":"Time Alpha Strike's untargetability to eat her Arctic Assault stun cast — blinking through it wastes her only point-and-click lockdown and buys your whole trade window."},{"t":"Track her R before any commit","d":"Only all-in or chase once you've seen her ult go on cooldown; with R up, every fight risks an AOE stun that negates Highlander and gets you collapsed."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't take extended autos","d":"Standing in to trade basics feeds her Permafrost stacks and W percent damage — she out-sustains and out-slows you, then stuns and walks you down."},{"t":"Don't trust Highlander vs her R","d":"Highlander's slow immunity does nothing against her airborne+stun ultimate, so never engage thinking your R lets you fight through her — it doesn't."},{"t":"Don't push blind into a gank","d":"Permafrost-slowed and shoved up, you're the easiest gank in the game; over-extending into her jungler's path is how this lane goes from hard to lost."}],"tradeGood":"Alpha Strike in to proc on-hit, dodge her E cast with the blink, then immediately disengage before a Permafrost stack and slow can land.","tradeBad":"A stand-and-auto trade where she stacks Permafrost to slow you, chunks you with W's percent-HP damage, and lands E to walk you into her jungler.","ahead":"Pressing a lead means refusing to 1v1 the tank and instead weaponizing your scaling: shove and split-push to pull Sejuani away from her team, take her tower, and force her to choose between defending and grouping. In fights, Alpha Strike past her E and Highlander-reset through her squishies — your on-hit true damage makes her tankiness meaningless. Hold your all-in for when her E and R are both down, and let map pressure, not lane dueling, snowball the game.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Sejuani - Track: Her R (Glacial Prison / Permafrost ult) — a guaranteed AOE airborne-and-stun that completely ignores Highlander's slow immunity and ends your reset chain; never commit to a fight while it's up.. - Survive the early game, hit your on-hit spike (Kraken/BORK into Wit's End), and only fight Sejuani once you can burst her health bar faster than she can stack Permafrost and reach R — ideally side-laning away from her CC chain rather than dueling her head-on. Use Alpha Strike to dodge her E stun cast, then commit only when Highlander is up to chain through her team.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A brick wall: Sejuani's permafrost slows, point-and-click E stun, and AOE R lock you down the instant Alpha Strike ends, so you concede lane, farm safe, and try to outscale her into the late game."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"You don't beat Sejuani in lane — you survive her, farm to your on-hit spike, and outscale her into a hyper-carry she can't kite once you've itemized. Win the game by ignoring the tank, Alpha-Striking past her CC, and erasing her carries with on-hit true damage rather than ever taking a straight duel."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Sejuani owns levels 1-3 (Permafrost + W), trades at 4-5 once Wuju/Meditate are up, spikes hard again at 6 with R; you reach parity at first item and flip favoured-to-dominant only at 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only with an Alpha Strike in-and-out to proc on-hit and dodge her E; back off before any Permafrost stack lands. Never take extended autos — she wins every sustained exchange via slow plus W percent damage."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Early, freeze or hold near your tower so she can't engage off Permafrost; don't shove into her jungler. Once you have items and a wave state you control, shove and roam/split to drag her off her team rather than sitting in her CC range."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability can dodge her E stun cast and her R if timed; Highlander's slow immunity counters her Permafrost slows but does NOT counter her R's airborne+stun. Meditate out-sustains her early chip but is interrupted if she catches you, and Wit's End/BORK true damage is what makes her armor stacking irrelevant late."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the attack-speed ramp into her tankiness; Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand (or Coup if you want pick-off). Secondary Resolve — Conditioning + Overgrowth (or Second Wind into her poke) — to survive the early lane and her CC chain."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ghost is standard to chase past her slows and reposition after Alpha Strike; take Flash + Ignite only if your jungler camps top and you want kill pressure, but Ghost helps far more against her permafrost kiting."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King, then Wit's End or Terminus for the true/magic on-hit that ignores her armor stacking; Berserker's Greaves, and consider Mercury's Treads if her team adds CC. Add a defensive on-hit (Wit's End MR) since her damage and her supporting picks lean magic/CC."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You can only all-in when her E and R are both on cooldown and you have your first on-hit item — Alpha Strike in, burn her down with on-hit, and reset Highlander. Before 6 with her CC up, there is no clean all-in."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"This lane is gank-magnet territory: Permafrost slows you into the perfect setup, so a top-side jungler on her team often turns the lane lost. Play for your own jungler to counter-gank her overextension, and ward river religiously since you can't escape a collapse once slowed."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi error here is trying to duel Sejuani for the kill — walking up to auto-trade, eating Permafrost and the E stun, and dying to a gank. The second is committing through her R thinking Highlander saves you; it doesn't."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're behind, abandon the duel mindset entirely — farm safe, freeze near tower, and split-push side lanes where she can't reach you. Scale to your items, ward heavily, and only join fights once her E/R are spent on someone else."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Ahead, split-push to isolate her and take towers, then in fights Alpha Strike past her E and reset Highlander through her backline — her tankiness means nothing to your on-hit true damage. Use the map, not the lane, to close."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"HARD, 45% — Sejuani is the textbook anti-Yi with point-and-click slows, an E stun that catches you after Alpha Strike, and an R that ignores Highlander; concede lane, scale, and win by ignoring the tank."}]},"sett":{"tldr":"A grit-bruiser nightmare — Sett out-trades you with double-punch and W true damage every level, his E grab catches you the instant Alpha Strike ends, and his R suppress deletes you before you ever reach your on-hit spike.","winCon":"Survive: farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos from max range, never sit in his minion-wave grit, and stall the lane until Kraken/BORK comes online so you out-DPS him in a Highlander-reset extended fight. Your real win is post-laning — get to 2+ items even, then group and run people down while he's stuck as a single-target frontliner.","enemyWin":"Sett wins by walking up and auto-trading you into the ground levels 1-5, banking your poke into a W true-damage smash, then landing E to root you the moment your Alpha Strike untargetability drops and R-suppressing you into a 6+ all-in you cannot Meditate through.","diff":"HARD","tone":"#ff5d6c","diffRating":"8/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Sett","rating":"7/10","why":"His passive double-punch out-autos your low base damage and short range, and you have no escape but Q to disengage a bad auto-war."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Sett","rating":"7/10","why":"Two ranks of his right-hook auto chunk you while your Wuju Style isn't even online yet to fight back with true damage."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Sett","rating":"8/10","why":"Maxed Q on him plus a W smash banking your trade damage means he wins any extended auto-exchange decisively before you have Meditate sustain up."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Sett","rating":"7/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and short Meditate heals let you trade back briefly, but his grit shield and double-punch still favor him in a stand-still fight."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Sett","rating":"8/10","why":"His level-6 R suppress + W true-damage all-in flat-out kills you, and Meditate cannot out-heal a suppression burst combo while you're locked."},{"label":"First item","side":"Sett","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken/BORK closes the gap and your on-hit DPS spikes, but one E grab after your Alpha Strike still hands him the kill in lane."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"With two on-hit items you out-DPS his single-target kit in any extended fight, dodging his E and R cast windows with Alpha Strike and chaining Highlander resets."}],"breakdown":{"early":"This is a miserable level 1-3 for you. Sett's passive double-punch and right-hook auto out-trade your weak base damage and short range, and Wuju Style true damage isn't online yet so you have nothing to fight back with. Farm with Alpha Strike from outside auto range and Wuju-clear casters — do not stand in the wave and auto-war him, you lose every time.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you stabilize slightly: Wuju Style gives bonus true damage for short bursts and Meditate sustains you between trades, so you can answer a single committed auto and walk. But level 6 is a wall — his R is a point-and-click suppress that locks you out of Alpha Strike entirely and pairs with a W true-damage smash to delete you. You do not have a 6 spike that competes; Highlander is a chase/dodge tool, not a fight-winner yet here.","late":"At 2+ items (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King plus Wit's End/Terminus) the lane finally flips. Your on-hit DPS and attack-reset Alpha Strike out-damage his single-target bruiser kit in any extended fight, and you can use Q's untargetability to dodge his E grab and R cast, then Highlander-reset off the kill. The lane is lost on paper but the game isn't — you scale past him.","wave":"Best wave: a wave pushing toward you so you farm safely under tower with Alpha Strike and deny his grit-fueled all-in. Worst wave: a slow-push that traps you in the middle of the lane in his auto range with E and R up. Crash timing: crash the wave into his tower right before your jungler arrives or right before you recall on a Wuju spike, so you reset on even gold without giving him a free grab window.","cooldowns":"Track his E (grab/stun) above all — it's his only hard lockdown and the answer to your Alpha Strike untargetability; if it's down you can trade and disengage far more freely. Secondarily respect his W when he's banked a lot of your poke into it.","trading":"Never auto-war him in the wave. Your only good trade is a short Wuju-Style auto-and-Q-out once his E is on cooldown, then walk while Meditate ticks. His pattern is to bank your damage into W, walk up on double-punch, and look for E-into-R; if you're in range when E is up, you're trading on his terms and you lose.","spikes":"Sett spikes hard at 6 (R suppress all-in) and stays ahead through his first bruiser item. You spike at first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) and truly take over at 2+ items — that's the entire arc of this lane.","feeding":"If you fall behind, this gets ugly fast — a fed Sett W one-shot-smashes you and R locks you for the kill, and you have zero burst to answer. Concede the lane, farm side waves with Alpha Strike, and refuse every E-range interaction; your value is scaling, not the 2v2.","carry":"If you somehow get even or ahead, you carry by reaching 2+ items and turning every skirmish into a Highlander reset chain — Alpha Strike dodges the enemy's key cooldowns while your on-hit shreds, and you snowball off teamfights, not the lane itself.","difficulty":"It's 8/10 because Sett beats you at literally every lane stage from 1 through 6 — grit trades, true-damage W, and a point-and-click R suppress that hard-counters your only escape (Alpha Strike) — and you're a weak early laner who can't punish back until two items deep. The 38.73% win rate is real; you are surviving, not winning lane."},"focus":{"text":"Sett's E (Facebreaker) grab-stun is the ability that loses you the lane — it's a point-and-click root that catches you the instant Alpha Strike's untargetability ends and sets up his R suppress all-in. Always know if it's up before you walk into his range.","letters":["E","R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm from max range","d":"Use Alpha Strike to last-hit and Wuju-Style autos to clear casters from outside his double-punch auto range. Never stand in the wave to CS by hand against his grit trades."},{"t":"Hold Q to dodge his combo","d":"Save Alpha Strike to blink out the moment he commits E or R — the untargetability windows beat his grab and suppress cast if you time them, not for offense early."},{"t":"Play for 2 items","d":"Treat lane as pure survival until Kraken/BORK plus Wit's End or Terminus; that's when your on-hit DPS finally out-scales his single-target bruiser kit and the matchup flips."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't auto-war the wave","d":"His passive double-punch and right-hook out-trade your base damage every exchange levels 1-5; standing in to trade autos is how you feed a Sett."},{"t":"Don't get caught after Q","d":"The instant Alpha Strike ends you're targetable — if his E is up he grabs you, W-smashes, and R-suppresses you dead. Never blink in with E off cooldown."},{"t":"Don't trust Meditate vs his 6 all-in","d":"Meditate's damage reduction does nothing while you're suppressed by his R, and W's true damage ignores your sustain — do not channel into his ult combo."}],"tradeGood":"A quick Wuju-Style empowered auto plus immediate Alpha Strike out while his E is on cooldown, then walking to let Meditate heal — never a stand-still exchange.","tradeBad":"Standing in his auto range to trade basics while his E and W are up, letting him bank your damage into a true-damage smash and grab you into an all-in.","ahead":"If you get a lead here, do not waste it dueling Sett in lane where his E still beats you — convert it by shoving and roaming or invading with your jungler while Highlander's movement speed is up. Build your on-hit spike fast and force extended fights where Alpha Strike dodges his grab and your DPS outpaces his frontline. Your lead snowballs through teamfight resets, not by repeatedly walking into E range to prove a point.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Sett - Track: Sett's E (Facebreaker) grab-stun is the ability that loses you the lane — it's a point-and-click root that catches you the instant Alpha Strike's untargetability ends and sets up his R suppress all-in. Always know if it's up before you walk into his range.. - Survive: farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos from max range, never sit in his minion-wave grit, and stall the lane until Kraken/BORK comes online so you out-DPS him in a Highlander-reset extended fight. Your real win is post-laning — get to 2+ items even, then group and run people down while he's stuck as a single-target frontliner.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A grit-bruiser nightmare — Sett out-trades you with double-punch and W true damage every level, his E grab catches you the instant Alpha Strike ends, and his R suppress deletes you before you ever reach your on-hit spike."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Your win condition is not winning lane — it's surviving it. Farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos out of Sett's range, refuse every E-range trade, and reach Kraken/BORK plus a second on-hit item where your reset-chaining DPS finally out-scales his single-target bruiser kit."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Sett owns 1 through 6 hard (grit trades, then R all-in); you draw even-ish at first item and only take over decisively at 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only with a Wuju auto into an immediate Alpha Strike out while his E is down, then walk and let Meditate tick; back off entirely when E and W are up and never stand-still auto-war him."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave pushing toward you so you farm safely under tower and deny his grit-fueled all-in; only crash in before a recall or a jungle arrival, never get slow-pushed into the middle of the lane in his E range."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability can dodge his E grab and R suppress cast if timed, but the moment Q ends you're targetable — and his W true damage and R suppress both bypass Meditate (suppression cancels the channel entirely)."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the extended on-hit DPS, Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand (or Coup if you need waveclear safety); secondary Resolve with Conditioning/Overgrowth or Second Wind plus Bone Plating to survive his lane bullying. Tank shards: AS, adaptive, armor vs his AD."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Teleport — you cannot win lane, so TP lets you farm safe, scale, and join map plays; Ignite only if you have a confident jungler-assisted early and want to contest the 2v2."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King, then Wit's End or Terminus for on-hit plus resists; take Plated Steelcaps vs his AD autos, and consider Bramble Vest/Tabi-line armor early to blunt his trades. Add a Maw/Wit's End MR component only if his team skews AP."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You have no real all-in until 2+ items; before that, only commit when his E is on cooldown AND your jungler is present to peel his grab — otherwise it's a survival lane."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You are extremely gankable pre-6 with only Alpha Strike to escape, and Sett's E sets up ganks perfectly by rooting you for his jungler. Ward early and deep, and lean on your own jungler to contest the 2v2 since you lose the 1v1 outright."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi mistake here is treating Sett like an immobile juggernaut you can out-sustain — you can't; his W ignores your heal and his E hard-counters Alpha Strike. The second is Alpha-striking IN for offense and getting grabbed the frame it ends."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Concede the lane completely — farm side waves with Alpha Strike, never interact in E range, take every safe CS, and play for objectives and scaling. A behind Yi who keeps farming still out-scales a Sett; a behind Yi who keeps fighting feeds."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If you do get ahead, push and roam with Highlander's move speed rather than re-dueling him, build your on-hit spike fast, and snowball through teamfights where Alpha Strike dodges his cooldowns and your DPS resets chain kills."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"HARD — 8/10 difficulty, ~38.7% win rate; Sett beats you every lane stage 1-6, so survive, scale to 2 items, and carry from teamfights, not from lane."}]},"shen":{"tldr":"Shen taunts you out of every kill window and out-sustains your early autos — you scale, but he denies the lane until you have two items.","winCon":"Concede the early lane, farm with Alpha Strike, and survive to your first on-hit item where Wuju Style true damage shreds his armor and Meditate out-sustains his Q-empowered autos in extended fights. You don't kill Shen in lane — you out-scale into a duelist who chases his carries down once Highlander is up.","enemyWin":"Shen wins by walking you down with Shadow Dash taunt the instant you commit to a wave or Alpha Strike, blocking your reset auto with Spirit's Refuge, and using his global R to win every cross-map skirmish you can't contest. He just needs to deny you flat and let his team punish the map while you're a non-factor.","diff":"HARD","tone":"#ff5d6c","diffRating":"7/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Shen","rating":"6/10","why":"Shen's empowered Q out-trades your low-base autos and his passive shield negates your Double Strike chip — you have no kill pressure and can't escape a Shadow Dash with Q on cooldown."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Shen","rating":"6/10","why":"He gets W to block your reset auto and Q to win the short trade; you have only Wuju Style or Meditate at 2, never both, so any all-in he taunts you in goes his way."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Shen","rating":"7/10","why":"Three-point Shadow Dash with empowered Q is a hard gank-setup and burst window — without R you have no slow-immunity and Alpha Strike's cooldown is your only out."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Shen","rating":"6/10","why":"Wuju true damage and Meditate sustain stabilize you for short trades, but Spirit's Refuge still blanks your auto strings and you can't punish his short cooldowns yet."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Shen","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander gives you slow-immunity to ignore his slow, but he gets global R first — he can dive bot for a kill and out-tempo you, and his taunt still catches you post-Alpha."},{"label":"First item","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Kraken/BORK on-hit plus Wuju true damage starts beating his armor in an extended fight — but Meditate vs his sustain and Spirit's Refuge keep it a coin-flip if he taunts on cooldown."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"At two on-hit items Wuju Style's true damage ignores his stacked armor and Alpha Strike dodges Shadow Dash's animation — you out-DPS him and reset Highlander through the fight."}],"breakdown":{"early":"You are flatly behind levels 1-3 and there is nothing to contest. Shen's empowered Q out-damages your weak base autos, his passive shield eats your Double Strike chip, and Shadow Dash means any time you walk up to last-hit with melee range you risk a taunt-into-burst. Farm with Alpha Strike from max range, take Wuju autos only when his Q is on cooldown, and never trade into a Shadow Dash that's up.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you stabilize with Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain for short windows, but Spirit's Refuge (W) still blocks your auto strings so your trades are chip, not kills. At 6 you get Highlander for slow-immunity and gank-dodging, but Shen got global R first — expect him to ult bot for a kill and out-tempo you on the map while you farm.","late":"This is your lane. At two on-hit items (Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King plus Wit's End/Terminus) your Wuju Style true damage ignores Shen's stacked armor entirely, Alpha Strike untargets through Shadow Dash, and Meditate out-sustains his Q heal in a long fight. You flip from punching bag to the duelist who runs his carries down and resets Highlander off every kill.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push into him at two items so you can force an extended all-in where true damage and resets win. Worst wave: a wave shoved under his tower early — you walk into Shadow Dash range with no escape and feed a taunt-kill. Crash timing: crash on your item-spike recall so you reset on tempo, then freeze near your side until you out-scale his deny.","cooldowns":"Track Shadow Dash (E) above all — it's ~18s early and is the only thing that turns a neutral lane state into a death. Also note Spirit's Refuge (W) before you commit an auto string.","trading":"Early it's all chip and it favors him: he empowered-Q autos, you eat it. Don't trade — Alpha-farm. Post-item the pattern flips: bait the Shadow Dash, Q to untarget the follow-up, then Wuju-true-damage him down with on-hit while resets keep you topped.","spikes":"Shen spikes at 3 (full kit + gank threat), 6 (global R map pressure), and any armor item. You spike at first on-hit item and decisively at two items where true damage and Highlander resets take over.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Shen does nothing to you alone but his global R snowballs the rest of the map and you become a 0-impact farm bot. Give up plates, freeze for safety, and ask your jungler to babysit — a fed Yi recovers, a dead Yi does nothing.","carry":"If you get ahead, Highlander resets turn one pick into a rampage; Alpha Strike lets you dive past his frontline onto a carry, and Wuju true damage means his tankiness doesn't save them. You become the side-lane and teamfight win condition.","difficulty":"It's hard because Shen denies your entire scaling premise: point-and-click taunt catches you after your only escape, his W blanks your reset autos, his sustain trades with Meditate, and his global R means even a 'won' lane doesn't matter if you can't be everywhere he is."},"focus":{"text":"Shadow Dash — his point-and-click taunt is the one thing that turns this lane lethal: it locks you down after Alpha Strike, the only escape in your kit. Never be in its range with Q on cooldown.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Alpha-farm, don't fight","d":"Use Alpha Strike to last-hit from outside taunt range and concede the early lane entirely — your win condition is items, not kills, against Shen."},{"t":"Save Q for the taunt","d":"Keep Alpha Strike up as your answer to Shadow Dash; if he taunts and you have Q, blink out, but if Q is down and you're in his range you die."},{"t":"All-in only at two items","d":"Wait for your second on-hit item — then Wuju Style true damage ignores his armor and you can force the extended fight where resets and DPS win."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't walk into melee range early","d":"Last-hitting with autos at levels 1-3 puts you in Shadow Dash range with no escape — that's how you eat a taunt-into-burst and lose the lane on the spot."},{"t":"Don't auto into Spirit's Refuge","d":"His W blocks all your basic-attack damage including Double Strike and your reset auto, so committing an auto string while it's up is wasted and leaves you exposed."},{"t":"Don't chase a roaming Shen","d":"When he uses global R to help another lane, hard-shove and take plates/tower — never try to follow or duel him after, you can't match his map tempo."}],"tradeGood":"Post-two-items: bait the Shadow Dash, Alpha Strike to untarget the empowered-Q follow-up, then Wuju Style true-damage him down with on-hit autos while Highlander resets keep you healthy.","tradeBad":"Walking up to auto-trade at levels 1-3 with Shadow Dash up — he taunts you, empowered-Q's you, and you have no Q to escape and no items to win the fight.","ahead":"If you somehow get ahead, hard-shove every wave to deny Shen the farm he needs to scale, then take plates and roam with your item lead before his global R can equalize the map. Use Highlander's reset on any pick to snowball into a side-lane that he physically can't 1v1, and group only when your team can punish his global timer being down. Against Shen, pressing a lead means making the map move faster than his R can answer.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Shen - Track: Shadow Dash — his point-and-click taunt is the one thing that turns this lane lethal: it locks you down after Alpha Strike, the only escape in your kit. Never be in its range with Q on cooldown.. - Concede the early lane, farm with Alpha Strike, and survive to your first on-hit item where Wuju Style true damage shreds his armor and Meditate out-sustains his Q-empowered autos in extended fights. You don't kill Shen in lane — you out-scale into a duelist who chases his carries down once Highlander is up.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Shen taunts you out of every kill window and out-sustains your early autos — you scale, but he denies the lane until you have two items."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing early lane by farming with Alpha Strike out of Shadow Dash range, then out-scale to your two-item on-hit spike where Wuju Style true damage ignores his armor and Meditate out-sustains his Q. You never out-lane Shen — you out-item him and become the duelist who runs his carries down."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Shen owns 1-6 (empowered Q, W block, taunt, global R first); the lane is a coin-flip at your first item and flips to Yi-favoured only at two on-hit items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Don't trade autos before your first item — Alpha-farm only. After two items, bait Shadow Dash, Q the follow-up, and commit Wuju autos; back off any time his taunt is up and your Q is on cooldown."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Farm safe and even early so you're never shoved into his tower in taunt range; once you hit your item spike, slow-push to set up an extended all-in, and crash on recall to reset on tempo."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges Shadow Dash's follow-up and any incoming CC mid-blink; Spirit's Refuge (W) blocks your Double Strike and reset autos; Wuju Style's true damage ignores the armor he stacks; Meditate sustains through his empowered-Q chip."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (uncaps attack speed for the extended on-hit fight he forces you to win late) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve — Conditioning + Overgrowth for the armor/HP to survive his early empowered-Q poke. Run Second Wind if his chip is heavy."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite is fine if you want kill pressure post-item, but Teleport is the safer pick here — it lets you farm-recover from a deny lane and match his global R map presence so he can't out-tempo you cross-map."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Open Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit spike, then Wit's End or Terminus for true/magic on-hit that shreds his armor and adds MR vs his Q; Berserker's Greaves; build defensive (he's mostly physical, so a Steraks/Death's Dance round-out) and add anti-heal (Mortal Reminder) since Meditate-mirror duels reward cutting his Q sustain."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"You cannot truly all-in until two on-hit items are complete and his Shadow Dash is on cooldown — only then does the extended fight (true damage + Highlander resets) go your way; before that every all-in is his."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Shen's three-point Shadow Dash makes you extremely gankable pre-6 since Alpha Strike is your only escape — ward up and play back. Your own ganks are weak (no hard CC), so use your jungler defensively early and let Highlander's gank-dodge carry you to scaling."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players try to trade or all-in Shen early because he 'looks tanky and slow' — but his empowered Q, W block, and taunt mean every pre-item fight is his; the mistake is not respecting the deny and dying to a taunt with Q down."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Freeze near your tower, give up plates, and farm with Alpha Strike only; ask your jungler to babysit and avoid every Shadow Dash range. A behind Yi still scales — a dead one doesn't, so survive to items above all."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Press an item lead by hard-shoving to starve his scaling, taking plates and roaming before his global R equalizes, and using Highlander resets off every pick to become an unkillable side-laner he can't 1v1."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"HARD (44.2% WR) — Shen denies your whole scaling plan with taunt, W block, sustain, and a global ult; survive to two items and the lane flips, but getting there is the hardest part."}]},"singed":{"tldr":"A drain-tank with no lockdown can't punish your weak early or survive your itemized on-hit DPS — Wuju true damage shreds his tankiness and Alpha Strike dodges his Fling, so don't chase the proxy and you take this lane.","winCon":"Farm safely with Alpha Strike through his proxy poison, hit your first on-hit item (Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King) plus Wit's End for true/magic shred, then commit an extended fight where Wuju Style's true damage ignores his stacked HP and Meditate out-sustains his poison while you out-DPS him. Never run him down through his speed lane — make him fight you under your tower or at objectives where Highlander resets win the trade.","enemyWin":"Singed wins by refusing the 1v1 entirely — proxying your wave to deny CS, building a CDR/sustain lead, then using his huge move speed and Fling to flip you into his jungler or run the map while you flounder a weak early Yi. If you tilt-chase him through poison and minions, his Mega Adhesive slow plus a single Fling hands a kill to his team.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"4/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Singed","rating":"6/10","why":"Singed's W poison trail and proxy let him deny your CS while your level-1 short range and missing escape mean you just farm with Alpha Strike and concede space."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Singed","rating":"5/10","why":"His base sustain and poison tick out-trade your level-2 autos, and a Fling into his slow can set up an early jungle gank you can't yet dodge with Highlander."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"With Wuju Style online your true-damage autos start ignoring his early HP, but his poison-and-walk-away pattern keeps it a CS race rather than a fight."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage plus Meditate sustain let you out-trade his poison in short bursts, and Alpha Strike resets your attack timer for extra on-hit ticks he can't kite."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Highlander's move speed and slow immunity hard-counter Singed's whole identity — you ignore his Mega Adhesive slow and can finally stick to a champion who has no hard CC to escape."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK %HP) plus Wuju true damage melts his stacked HP faster than his poison drains you, and Alpha Strike goes untargetable through his Fling animation."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At Wit's End/Terminus plus a completed on-hit core you out-DPS the drain tank outright — his only answer was kiting and he can't, so an extended fight with Highlander resets is yours."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Singed owns levels 1-3 by default — not by fighting you, but by proxying your wave with his poison trail so you bleed CS and XP while a weak, escape-less Yi can't punish him. Use Alpha Strike to clear the chunks he leaves and Wuju autos to last-hit; do not walk into his poison to contest. Accept the slow start: this lane is about surviving to your spikes, not winning level 1.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are the turn. Wuju Style's true damage starts ignoring the HP he's stacking, Meditate lets you sit through poison ticks, and Level 6 Highlander makes his Mega Adhesive slow and Fling-into-gank setups far less scary — slow immunity is the exact tool that neuters his kit. Start taking short Wuju-buffed autos when his Fling is down.","late":"At 2+ items you flip the lane open. Kraken/BORK %HP plus Wit's End or Terminus shred a drain tank's effective HP, Wuju's true damage means his armor and stacks don't matter, and Alpha Strike goes untargetable through his Fling. In any extended fight you out-DPS him and Highlander refreshes on the kill — he simply has no lockdown to survive you.","wave":"Best wave: A slow push into his tower so he must either give the wave or fight you in your itemized window with no room to proxy. Worst wave: A wave shoved toward HIS tower that tempts you to dive through poison and Mega Adhesive for a kill you can't secure. Crash timing: Crash the wave on your first-item spike so you reset, buy your on-hit core, and return with a wave advantage before his next proxy.","cooldowns":"Track his W Fling cooldown above all — it's his only repositioning/peel tool and the setup for ganks. When Fling is down, that's your free window to commit Wuju autos. Also watch his Mega Adhesive (E) for the slow zone before you ever step forward.","trading":"Short, decisive: walk up only when his Fling is on cooldown, pop Wuju Style, land an Alpha Strike to reset your attack timer, get your two true-damage autos in, and back out before his poison out-ticks your health bar. Don't sit in poison trading auto-for-auto early — his sustain wins that.","spikes":"Yours: Level 6 Highlander (slow immunity vs his whole kit), first on-hit item, and Wit's End/Terminus completion. His: any tank/sustain item (Bami's/Demonic) that lets his poison out-tick you, plus the CDR that shortens his Fling — and a jungler arriving while his slow is up.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Singed roams and proxies the map with his speed, snowballing side lanes you can't catch up to. A behind Yi gives up the one thing that beats Singed: the itemized extended fight. Don't force it — farm jungle camps and side waves with Alpha Strike to recover the items that win the matchup.","carry":"Ahead, Wuju true damage plus on-hit %HP means you delete even a fed Singed, and Highlander resets turn one pick into a map-wide rampage. Use your speed to match his and collapse on him or his carries; a fed Yi into a no-CC drain tank is the cleanest snowball this champ gets.","difficulty":"It's only 4/10 because the hard part isn't the duel — it's the discipline. Singed never fights you fairly; the loss condition is you chasing him through poison and Mega Adhesive into his team. Respect the proxy, hit your items, and the actual combat is heavily yours."},"focus":{"text":"Singed's W Fling — it's his only repositioning and peel tool and the setup for every gank; when it's down he has nothing to stop you, but a Fling into his Mega Adhesive slow is how a single CC catches you after Alpha Strike.","letters":["W","E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike, never the proxy","d":"Use Q to clear the waves he leaves behind and last-hit safely instead of stepping into his poison trail. Conceding the early CS race is fine — your scaling is the win."},{"t":"Save Highlander for his slow","d":"Level 6 onward, Highlander's slow immunity ignores Mega Adhesive entirely. Pop it to stick to him or to walk out of a Fling-and-slow gank setup that would otherwise kill you."},{"t":"Force the extended fight at items","d":"Once you have an on-hit core plus Wit's End/Terminus, make him fight under your tower or at an objective where Wuju true damage and Highlander resets out-DPS his drain — he can't kite you there."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't chase him through poison","d":"His move speed plus poison trail and Mega Adhesive are built to bait you deep — a chase that looks winnable ends with a Fling into his jungler. If he runs, let him."},{"t":"Don't trade into Fling","d":"Stepping up while his W is available lets him flip you into his minions or team. Only commit autos when Fling is on cooldown."},{"t":"Don't skip anti-tank / anti-heal","d":"Without %HP and Wuju true damage, his stacked HP and drain sustain out-last your DPS. Building pure raw AD into a sustain tank throws your itemized advantage."}],"tradeGood":"Walk up while his Fling is on cooldown, pop Wuju Style, Alpha Strike to reset your attack timer, and land two true-damage autos that ignore his HP before backing out of poison range.","tradeBad":"Chasing him through his poison trail and Mega Adhesive slow for a kill, where his speed carries him to his jungler and a single Fling flips the fight.","ahead":"Press a lead by denying his proxy — slow-push waves into his tower so he can't reset the map with his speed, and punish every time his Fling is down with Wuju-buffed all-ins. Use Highlander's bonus speed to match his and to roam yourself, turning his uncatchable-map game against him. Once you're two items up, group for objectives where a no-CC drain tank simply cannot survive your true-damage on-hit DPS and Highlander resets.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Singed - Track: Singed's W Fling — it's his only repositioning and peel tool and the setup for every gank; when it's down he has nothing to stop you, but a Fling into his Mega Adhesive slow is how a single CC catches you after Alpha Strike.. - Farm safely with Alpha Strike through his proxy poison, hit your first on-hit item (Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King) plus Wit's End for true/magic shred, then commit an extended fight where Wuju Style's true damage ignores his stacked HP and Meditate out-sustains his poison while you out-DPS him. Never run him down through his speed lane — make him fight you under your tower or at objectives where Highlander resets win the trade.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A drain-tank with no lockdown can't punish your weak early or survive your itemized on-hit DPS — Wuju true damage shreds his tankiness and Alpha Strike dodges his Fling, so don't chase the proxy and you take this lane."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a weak, escape-less early lane by farming with Alpha Strike instead of contesting his proxy, then reach your on-hit item spike where Wuju Style's true damage ignores his stacked HP and Meditate out-sustains his poison. Win the extended fight he can't escape — he has no hard CC to punish you after Alpha Strike, so itemized Yi out-DPSes the drain tank and chains Highlander resets."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Singed edges 1-3 via proxy and poison, it evens out at 4-5 as Wuju true damage comes online, and it tilts hard to Yi from 6 (Highlander slow immunity) through first item and especially 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only when his W Fling is on cooldown: Wuju Style on, Alpha Strike to reset, two autos, out. Back off and farm when Fling is up, when you're standing in poison, or before level 6 against a Fling-into-gank setup."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Don't fight the proxy war — let him push and clear with Alpha Strike. Slow-push into his tower around your item spikes so he must fight or surrender the wave, and crash on your first-item back to return with tempo."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike makes you untargetable through his Fling and Mega Adhesive cast windows; Wuju Style's true damage bypasses the armor and HP a drain tank stacks; Meditate out-heals his poison ticks in a sustained fight; Highlander's slow immunity hard-counters Mega Adhesive, the one tool that sets up CC on you."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the on-hit attack-speed ramp that out-DPSes his sustain (Conqueror if you want the bonus AD and healing in extended fights); secondary Triumph + Legend: Alacrity, with Second Wind and Overgrowth in Resolve to blunt his poke poison since he's AP — take Magical Footwear or bone plating flex vs his magic damage."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite — Ignite's Grievous Wounds is the correct pick to cut his drain sustain in your all-in window and it secures the kills his lack of CC can't deny. Take Teleport only if you expect to be proxied off the map and need to match his split tempo."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush an on-hit core — Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for %HP shred — then Wit's End or Terminus for magic/armor shred and resist vs his AP poison; Berserker's Greaves for DPS, Mercury's/swap to Hexdrinker or Maw if his burst grows. Anti-heal (Mortal Reminder/Executioner's if needed) is essential into his drain."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"All-in at level 6 with Highlander up when his Fling is down, and any time after your first on-hit item if you can pin him for an extended fight under your tower or at an objective — that's where true damage plus resets win outright."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Pre-6 his Fling-plus-Mega-Adhesive can chain you for a gank, so ward his approach side and don't overextend without Highlander. After 6 your slow immunity and Alpha Strike untargetability make you very hard to collapse on; your own jungler can usually catch a Singed who has no escape if you ult to match his speed."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi error here is treating Singed like a kill — chasing him through poison and Mega Adhesive into his team, or trading auto-for-auto in his poison early where his sustain wins. The lane is won by farming to items and forcing the fight on your terms, not by out-running a champion built to be uncatchable."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're behind, stop contesting him — farm side waves and jungle camps with Alpha Strike to rebuild your on-hit core, since the itemized extended fight is the only thing that beats him. Play for objectives and let his split-push overextend him into a pick rather than dueling from a deficit."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Ahead, deny his proxy with slow-pushes, punish every Fling cooldown, and use Highlander's speed to match his roams and collapse on him. Two items up, group objectives where your true-damage on-hit DPS deletes a no-CC drain tank and every kill refreshes Highlander into the next."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED (54.55%): a no-lockdown drain tank can't punish your early or survive your itemized true-damage DPS — discipline against the proxy is the only thing standing between you and a clean win."}]},"sion":{"tldr":"Sion out-ranges, out-pokes, and out-scales you early, so you survive on Alpha Strike and farm until your on-hit items flip it — but he reclaims the lane the moment he's a full-tank frontline you can't burst.","winCon":"Concede the early to his Roar of the Slayer poke and charged Q, farm safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, and live to your Kraken/BORK spike where your on-hit DPS plus Highlander resets win extended side-lane fights. Claim Level 6 and the first-item window to take plates and snowball off his immobility before two tank items make him unkillable.","enemyWin":"Sion lands fully-charged Decimating Smash knockups and Roar of the Slayer armor-shred to chunk you before you itemize, then simply out-scales: Soul Furnace shield, ballooning resists, and his Glory in Death zombie second life turn him into a frontline your on-hit stalls out against.","diff":"TRICKY","tone":"#ff8b3d","diffRating":"6/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Sion","rating":"7/10","why":"A fully-charged Decimating Smash knockup plus point-and-click Roar of the Slayer poke chunk you, and Alpha Strike is your only answer — you just farm."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Sion","rating":"6/10","why":"His E armor-shred and Soul Furnace AoE out-trade your short-range autos before Wuju Style or Meditate are online to sustain it back."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Sion","rating":"6/10","why":"He out-ranges and out-pokes you with E into W while your only all-in is a telegraphed Alpha Strike he answers with a charged Q knockup."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Sion","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain stabilize your short trades, but his charged Q and shield still keep you off him."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's attack speed and slow immunity let you ride out his knockup window and out-DPS him as his Soul Furnace shield expires."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken Slayer/BORK on-hit plus Alpha Strike dodging his charged Q wins the extended duel his total immobility can't escape."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Sion","rating":"6/10","why":"Two tank items plus Glory in Death's zombie second life make him a frontline your on-hit DPS stalls out against once his armor is stacked."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Sion owns levels 1-3 outright. His Roar of the Slayer (E) is point-and-click poke that shreds your armor, and a fully-charged Decimating Smash (Q) knockup chunks you for free — you have no range and no escape but Alpha Strike, which you should never burn just to trade. Don't contest the wave melee; farm with Alpha Strike blinks and Wuju autos, dodge the charged Q with movement, and concede every aggressive trade until your kit comes online.","mid":"Levels 4-5 stabilize you as Wuju Style true damage and Meditate let you sustain short pokes back, but Sion still out-ranges you, so you're farming for 6, not fighting. Level 6 is your first claim on the lane: Highlander's attack speed and slow immunity let you survive his knockup-into-shield combo and out-DPS him right as Soul Furnace fades — force the trade only when his Q is on cooldown.","late":"At your first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) you spike hard: Alpha Strike goes untargetable through his charged Q, your %-health on-hit chews his tanky bars, and Highlander resets keep you in the fight. That's your one dominant window — abuse his immobility, take plates, and try to end. Once Sion finishes two tank items his resists plus Glory in Death's zombie second life make him a frontline you simply can't solo-burst; your on-hit ramp stalls on stacked armor and he reclaims it.","wave":"Best wave: a slow-pushed wave you can freeze just outside his tower, denying his E poke range while you farm to your item spike. Worst wave: a wave shoved into your tower under his Q-charge range where he zones you off CS and pokes with impunity. Crash timing: crash hard right as you hit Kraken/BORK and Highlander is up, so you trade plates and recall before his next tank item lands.","cooldowns":"Track Decimating Smash (Q) — the fully-charged knockup is his only hard CC and his only reliable burst; when it's down, you can step up and trade or all-in, and when it's up, you respect Alpha-Strike-dodge range or back off.","trading":"Pre-6 you lose every melee trade to his E-armor-shred plus W AoE, so don't take them — farm and sustain with Meditate. Post-item, bait or eat a non-charged Q, then Alpha Strike in, pop Wuju Style, and grind the extended trade his immobility can't walk out of.","spikes":"Sion's spikes: a fully-charged Q (every lane phase), Soul Furnace shield value, and especially two completed tank items. Your spikes: level 6 Highlander, then your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK), then 2+ items where you out-DPS most of the map — but he contests your 2-item window with full-tank resists.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Sion's E poke and charged Q zone you off the wave entirely and you fall further behind on items — the lane snowballs against you fast because you have no range to farm safely and your scaling is item-gated. Give the lane up, farm under tower with Alpha Strike, and look to the jungle/sidelane rather than int a 1v1 you can't win pre-item.","carry":"If you get ahead, you become a 1v9 split threat: Alpha Strike dodges his telegraphed engage, your on-hit melts even tanks over a few seconds, and every kill refreshes Highlander to chain through the map. Pressure a side lane he's too slow to rotate to and force him to choose between his tower and the rest of his team.","difficulty":"It's a 6/10 because Sion punishes your weak early relentlessly with point-and-click poke and a knockup you can't dodge without burning Alpha Strike, then contests your big 2-item window with the exact thing you struggle into — stacked armor and a tank with a second life. Your skill expression is patient farming and a clean item-spike timing, not lane dominance."},"focus":{"text":"His fully-charged Decimating Smash (Q): it's his only hard CC and his only real burst — a max-charge knockup chunks you and sets up everything. Bait it or dodge it with movement (or Alpha Strike untargetability), then punish the long cooldown.","letters":["Q"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm, don't fight, early","d":"Concede levels 1-3 to his E poke and charged Q. Use Alpha Strike and Wuju autos to last-hit safely and never trade into his armor-shred."},{"t":"Spike on item, then all-in","d":"Your real window is level 6 plus your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK). Alpha Strike dodges his charged Q and your on-hit grinds the extended trade his immobility can't escape."},{"t":"Save Alpha Strike to dodge his Q","d":"The untargetability frame on Alpha Strike can blank his fully-charged knockup. Time it as his engage, not as a poke tool you've already wasted."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't trade melee pre-item","d":"His Roar of the Slayer shreds your armor and Soul Furnace AoE chips you while you have no range and no sustain — you lose every short trade before Wuju Style and Meditate are online."},{"t":"Don't drag the game to full-tank Sion","d":"Two tank items plus his Glory in Death zombie second life make him a frontline your on-hit stalls on. Close on your item-spike lead; don't gamble on a late 5v5 he frontlines forever."},{"t":"Don't burn Alpha Strike to escape into nothing","d":"It's your only escape — if you blink out with his Q up and no second target to reset its cooldown, you're stranded for the knockup follow-up."}],"tradeGood":"Bait or eat his non-charged Q, then Alpha Strike in under Highlander with Wuju Style active and grind the extended on-hit trade his total immobility can't walk out of.","tradeBad":"Walking up to auto him at level 1-3 into a fully-charged Decimating Smash plus Roar of the Slayer armor-shred, with no item, no sustain, and Alpha Strike wasted.","ahead":"Press a lead by turning Sion's immobility into a death sentence in the side lane: shove with on-hit, take plates, and threaten an Alpha-Strike-dodge all-in he can only answer with a single charged Q. Every kill refreshes Highlander, so chain kills across the map and force him to defend his tower alone while you out-rotate his slow, telefragged engage. Build the snowball into objectives before his second tank item lands and his Glory in Death second life makes him a frontline again.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Sion - Track: His fully-charged Decimating Smash (Q): it's his only hard CC and his only real burst — a max-charge knockup chunks you and sets up everything. Bait it or dodge it with movement (or Alpha Strike untargetability), then punish the long cooldown.. - Concede the early to his Roar of the Slayer poke and charged Q, farm safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, and live to your Kraken/BORK spike where your on-hit DPS plus Highlander resets win extended side-lane fights. Claim Level 6 and the first-item window to take plates and snowball off his immobility before two tank items make him unkillable.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Sion out-ranges, out-pokes, and out-scales you early, so you survive on Alpha Strike and farm until your on-hit items flip it — but he reclaims the lane the moment he's a full-tank frontline you can't burst."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing early by farming with Alpha Strike and Meditate, then hit your level-6 plus first-on-hit-item spike where your DPS and Highlander resets win the extended duel his immobility can't escape. Convert that one window into plates and a side-lane snowball before two tank items make him unkillable."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Sion owns 1-5 (poke, charged Q, armor-shred); you claim 6 and your first-item window; he reclaims the 2+ item, full-tank frontline phase."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Pre-item: never trade — farm and sustain with Meditate, dodge the charged Q. Post-item: only commit when his Q is down, Alpha-Strike in, Wuju Style on, and grind the extended fight."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Slow-push or freeze just outside his E range early to farm safely; once you spike with Kraken/BORK and Highlander, crash the wave to take plates and recall before his next tank item."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability can dodge his fully-charged Decimating Smash knockup; Wuju Style true damage ignores the armor his Roar of the Slayer and tank items stack; Meditate out-sustains his Soul Furnace chip; Highlander's slow immunity ignores any slow attached to his engage."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (faster on-hit ramp to out-DPS through his shield) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Coup de Grace primary; Resolve secondary (Conditioning + Overgrowth, or Second Wind into his poke). Against this AD tank, take armor and tenacity shards."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ghost is fine to stick a champ who can't kite, but Ignite is the better pick here — it cuts his Soul Furnace/Meditate-style healing and converts your item-spike all-ins into kills; Flash to dodge or punish his charged Q."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Open Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for %-health on-hit to chew his tank bars, then Wit's End or Terminus for true/magic on-hit and resists; Mercury's Treads or Plated Steelcaps versus his AD/knockup; Mortal Reminder/anti-heal if the team is stacking sustain. Wuju Style true damage already helps shred his stacked armor."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Your only clean all-in windows are level 6 with Highlander up and his Q on cooldown, and again the moment your first on-hit item completes — outside those, you don't have the burst or range to commit."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're extremely gankable early since Alpha Strike is your only escape and Sion's charged Q sets up a free gank — ward his tri-bush and play safe until 6. With your own jungler, his immobility makes him trivial to collapse on; a single CC chain plus your on-hit deletes him."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players fight the early lane instead of farming it — trading into his armor-shred, wasting Alpha Strike to poke, then getting knocked up and killed; the matchup is won by patience and a clean item-spike timing, not lane aggression."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're behind, abandon the 1v1: farm under tower with Alpha Strike, never face-check his Q, and scale on jungle camps and side waves until your on-hit items come online and you can rejoin fights as a backline-diving threat."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If ahead, weaponize his slowness — split a side lane he can't rotate to, take plates and towers, and chain Highlander resets through skirmishes; close before his second tank item and Glory in Death restore his frontline."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"TRICKY (~45% WR): Sion edges a losing early and reclaims the full-tank late, but a disciplined Yi who farms to his on-hit spike owns level 6 and the first-item window — patience wins this lane, aggression loses it."}]},"swain":{"tldr":"A scaling race Yi wins: eat Swain's poke early, dodge his E with Alpha Strike, then out-DPS his drain once you hit Kraken/BORK and run him down before R can stack souls.","winCon":"Farm safely through levels 1-5 with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, never walking into E range, then once your first on-hit item is online use Q to phase through his E-root and burst him before Battle of the Immortals (R) can heal him back. Wit's End and your true-damage E shred his drain tankiness, and Highlander resets let you collapse the moment he commits.","enemyWin":"Swain wins if he lands E → W from max range to root-and-bomb you repeatedly, shoving you off the wave and starving your scaling, or if he catches your Alpha Strike landing point with the E pull and drains you out in his R AOE while a gank locks you down.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"4/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Swain","rating":"6/10","why":"Swain's Q poke and longer range out-trade your 125-range autos before Wuju Style or Meditate exist, so you can only last-hit."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Swain","rating":"5/10","why":"He out-damages you at range and threatens an early E → W root-bomb, while your only answer is to walk up for a CD-resetting Alpha Strike and back off."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"With Wuju Style up you can phase in with Q for a true-damage burst, but his W bomb plus a landed E still trades evenly if he respects your range."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Meditate sustains through his Q/W poke and Wuju Style's true damage lets short Q-in trades favor you when his E is on cooldown."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity let you stick to him and dodge his E-follow-up, turning his all-in attempts into your kills."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken Slayer or BORK on-hit plus Wuju true damage out-DPS his R drain, and Q untargetability dodges the E-pull that's his only lockdown."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At 2+ items with Wit's End shredding his AP and Highlander resetting, you delete him through his R before souls stack — he simply can't kite you."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Swain — his Q out-ranges your autos and a single E → W root-bomb chunks you for nothing in return. Do not contest; use Alpha Strike on the wave to farm safely and keep yourself out of E range (around 725 units). You're not trying to win these levels, only to reach 6 even.","mid":"Levels 4-6 you stabilize hard: Wuju Style's bonus true damage ignores the resistances his drain build leans on, and Meditate out-sustains his Q/W poke. Once you hit Highlander at 6, his slows mean nothing and you can finally punish a whiffed E — Q in, E-true-damage autos, R to chase, then disengage before his bomb detonates.","late":"At 2+ items you flip the lane: Kraken/BORK plus Wit's End out-DPS his R sustain, and Alpha Strike's untargetability lets you ignore his E entirely. He cannot kite you and his only escape is Flash, so any time his E is down he dies.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push into a freeze on your side so he has to walk past river into E range to CS, exposing him to your jungler. Worst wave: a wave shoved under his tower where his Q/W poke chunks you with no kill threat in return. Crash timing: crash the wave right as your first on-hit item completes so you reset, buy, and return with a thinned wave to set up a freeze.","cooldowns":"Track his E (Nevermove) — it's a slow-traveling skillshot on roughly a 12-13s cooldown early; when it's down he has no lockdown and you can all-in freely.","trading":"Trade only when his E is on cooldown: Q in (untargetable through any incoming root), land Wuju true-damage autos, and walk out before his W bomb arms. Never sit in his R aura trading autos for drain ticks — that math favors him.","spikes":"Swain spikes at 6 (R souls/heal) and on Liandry's/Rylai's for kiting poke; you spike at 6 (Highlander) and far harder at your first on-hit item, becoming dominant at two items with Wit's End.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Swain becomes a tanky drain bruiser who roots you out of every fight — but Yi's curve still bails you out: farm side lanes, hit three items, and Wit's End plus true damage lets you delete him even from a deficit. Never int an early Alpha Strike into his E.","carry":"Ahead, you don't 1v1 him — you split and force him to answer, then Q through his E and Highlander-reset off any pick to snowball the map; his immobility means he can never catch your splitting Yi.","difficulty":"It's only a 4/10 because his early poke and one E-root can punish a greedy Yi, but his total lack of mobility and your Q untargetability/true damage mean the lane is structurally yours the moment you itemize."},"focus":{"text":"Swain's E (Nevermove) — the slow-moving root that sets up his W bomb, his R drain, and any jungle gank. Side-step it or save Alpha Strike to phase through it; when it's down, he's defenseless and you can all-in.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Bait then dodge E","d":"Make him throw Nevermove, then use Alpha Strike's untargetability or a sidestep to dodge it; with his root down he has zero lockdown and you can collapse."},{"t":"Rush on-hit + Wit's End","d":"Kraken or BORK first, then Wit's End — its magic-resist and on-hit shred directly counters his AP drain and lets your true-damage E melt his sustain."},{"t":"Use Meditate on his poke","d":"Channel W to out-heal his Q and bomb chip; your sustain beats his pre-6 trade damage and keeps you healthy into your spike."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't fight in his R aura","d":"Never trade autos while standing in Battle of the Immortals — every tick heals him and stacks souls, turning a winnable duel into his comeback."},{"t":"Don't Q in onto a full-CD Swain","d":"If his E is up, Alpha Strike's reset can land you right next to his root-bomb-drain combo plus a gank — wait for E to be down."},{"t":"Don't force levels 1-3","d":"His Q out-ranges you and one E-root chunks you for free; contesting early just feeds him the lead his drain needs to out-scale your spike."}],"tradeGood":"Q in the instant his E is on cooldown, hit two Wuju-Style true-damage autos plus the Double Strike proc, and walk out before his W bomb detonates.","tradeBad":"Standing in his R drain aura auto-for-auto after eating an E-root — that's pure value for him and stacks the souls that win him the game.","ahead":"Pressing a lead, don't try to perma-zone an immobile mage who farms under tower — instead crash waves and roam/split, using Highlander resets off any kill to snowball other lanes. Q through his E every time he tries to peel for himself, and once you have two items he physically cannot kite or escape you, so dive him whenever his E is down. Force him to either give up CS to your freeze or walk into your jungler in river.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Swain - Track: Swain's E (Nevermove) — the slow-moving root that sets up his W bomb, his R drain, and any jungle gank. Side-step it or save Alpha Strike to phase through it; when it's down, he's defenseless and you can all-in.. - Farm safely through levels 1-5 with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, never walking into E range, then once your first on-hit item is online use Q to phase through his E-root and burst him before Battle of the Immortals (R) can heal him back. Wit's End and your true-damage E shred his drain tankiness, and Highlander resets let you collapse the moment he commits.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A scaling race Yi wins: eat Swain's poke early, dodge his E with Alpha Strike, then out-DPS his drain once you hit Kraken/BORK and run him down before R can stack souls."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive Swain's poke-heavy early with Meditate and Alpha Strike farming, then out-scale him to your first on-hit item where your true-damage DPS beats his drain sustain. Win every fight where his E is on cooldown by phasing in with Q and resetting Highlander."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Swain edges 1-3, lane is even at 4-5, and Yi takes clear control from 6 → first item → dominant at two items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only when Nevermove (E) is down: Q in, Wuju autos, leave before the W bomb arms; back off entirely if his E is up or you're inside his R aura."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Freeze on your side of river so he must over-extend into E range to farm, exposing him to ganks; avoid shoving under his tower where his poke is free."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike makes you untargetable, dodging Swain's E-root, W-detonation lock, and the moment of his R cast; Wuju Style's true damage ignores the resistances his drain build stacks; Highlander's slow immunity nullifies his Rylai's/Frostfire kiting."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (or Conqueror) with Triumph and Legend: Alacrity; secondary Resolve (Second Wind + Overgrowth) to ease his AP poke, or Magical Footwear/Cosmic Insight; rune shards: AS, adaptive, magic-resist vs his AP."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to convert your first-item spike into kills and cut his R heal with Grievous Wounds; take Teleport instead only if you expect to get poked off the wave and need to recover tempo."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first, Wit's End second for magic resist + on-hit to counter his AP drain, then Terminus or Death's Dance; Mercury's Treads vs his root; add Maw/QSS if his combo plus a gank keeps locking you down."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"All-in once Highlander is up AND his E is on cooldown — strongest at your first on-hit item, near-guaranteed at two items where you out-DPS his R before souls stack."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Swain's E is a free setup for ganks, so ward river and don't push past lane center when his E is up; conversely, your safest play is baiting his E, then signaling your jungler since a rooted-out Swain has no escape from a Yi gank."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi error here is Q-ing in onto a full-cooldown Swain to 'start scaling' early — you land in his E-W-R combo and feed the drain mage the lead that lets him out-scale your item spike."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If behind, abandon the 1v1: farm side waves to three items, take Wit's End for the magic-resist swing, and only fight when his E whiffs — Yi's curve reclaims even a rough start once true damage and on-hit come online."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Ahead, crash and roam with Highlander resets rather than chasing an under-tower Swain; split-push to force him to answer, then Q through his E and dive him the instant his root is down."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED (57% WR): a scaling lane Yi loses early and wins decisively — respect the E-root, out-sustain the poke, and his immobility hands you the duel from first item on."}]},"sylas":{"tldr":"A weak-early on-hit carry against a self-healing AP bruiser whose E stun catches you out of Alpha Strike and whose R steals your Highlander — survive to your on-hit spike and the lane flips, but Sylas edges everything before then.","winCon":"Concede the early, farm safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos through his Q/W drain poke, then explode in extended fights once Kraken/Blade of the Ruined King comes online — Alpha Strike dodges his E chain-stun mid-fight while on-hit DPS out-races his self-heal. Use Highlander resets to chain kills the second you out-trade him.","enemyWin":"Sylas sustains through your pathetic levels 1-5 with Q/W drain-heal, lands his E chain-dash stun to lock you down the instant Alpha Strike ends, and steals your Highlander with R to turn your own scaling into his all-in. If he pokes you off the wave and denies your item timing, you never reach the window where you beat him.","diff":"TRICKY","tone":"#ff8b3d","diffRating":"6/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Sylas","rating":"7/10","why":"Sylas Q drain-heal out-trades your tiny level-1 auto range while you have only Alpha Strike for damage and no Highlander or Wuju true damage yet."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Sylas","rating":"7/10","why":"His second ability (E or W) gives him a stun or shield-heal advantage in any short exchange before your Wuju Style or Meditate exist."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Sylas","rating":"6/10","why":"With E chain-dash online he can stun you out of Alpha Strike's untargetable window the moment it ends, and his Q/W heal undoes your auto poke."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Sylas","rating":"6/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain stabilize you for short trades, but his drain-heal and E stun still edge any extended fight pre-6."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's attack speed, move speed and slow-immunity let you stick and dodge his E with Alpha Strike — but respect that his R can steal Highlander right back."},{"label":"First item","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King on-hit DPS now out-races his Q/W self-heal in a sustained fight, but a clean E stun + stolen Highlander can still flip it."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"At 2+ items your on-hit DPS plus Alpha Strike dodging his E shreds him faster than he heals, and Highlander resets chain kills through the fight."}],"breakdown":{"early":"You are nearly helpless levels 1-3: short auto range, no escape but Alpha Strike, and no true damage yet, while Sylas Q/W drain-heals through any poke you land. Just farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, take CS, and never sit in his Q range. Any extended early trade feeds his heal and his E setup.","mid":"Levels 4-5 Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain let you contest short trades, but his E chain-stun and drain still edge them. Level 6 is your first real spike — Highlander's speed and slow-immunity let you stick or disengage and Alpha-Strike his E — but he hits 6 too, and his R can outright steal your Highlander.","late":"At 2+ items (Kraken/BORK plus Wit's End or Terminus) you flip FAVOURED: on-hit DPS out-races his self-heal in any sustained fight, Alpha Strike dodges his E mid-fight, and Highlander resets let you chain through him and his team. This is the window the whole lane is built to reach.","wave":"Best wave: a slow-push you can crash and freeze just past river so you farm safely out of his Q range and deny his all-in angle. Worst wave: a wave shoved under his tower early, where he Q/W-pokes you off the minions and sets up an E-stun all-in or a jungle dive. Crash timing: crash the wave just before your item completes so you can recall, spike, and return to a freeze without losing tempo.","cooldowns":"Track his E chain-dash (the stun) above all — it is the only thing that reliably catches you after Alpha Strike; bait it or wait it out before you commit. Secondarily count his R, because it steals Highlander.","trading":"Trade only with a full Alpha Strike + Wuju Style auto burst when his E is down, then disengage before his Q/W out-heals it. Avoid auto-for-auto poke wars — his drain wins those. Post-6, force trades where you can Alpha Strike his E and let Highlander attack speed close it.","spikes":"Sylas spikes early-to-mid on his drain-heal and E-stun setup and again whenever he can steal your R. You spike at Level 6 (Highlander) and decisively at first item, going dominant at 2+ items.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Sylas out-heals and out-ranges you and his stolen Highlander snowballs — you become unkillable-target food. Stop trading, farm side lanes with Alpha Strike, and wait for a teamfight where your on-hit can dodge his E and erase a carry instead of dueling him.","carry":"If you get ahead, your on-hit DPS deletes him through his heal, Alpha Strike makes you immune during his E, and every Highlander reset lets you snowball across the map faster than his single-target kit can answer.","difficulty":"It is a 6/10 TRICKY because Sylas has exactly the two tools that punish you — point-and-click lockdown (E) that catches you out of Alpha Strike and an R that steals your win-condition ult — and he sustains through your weak early; but you out-scale him hard, so surviving to items is the whole skill check."},"focus":{"text":"His E chain-dash stun — it is the only point-and-click lockdown that reliably catches you the instant Alpha Strike's untargetable window ends; bait or dodge it before committing. Respect his R too, since it steals your Highlander.","letters":["E","R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike, not autos","d":"Use Alpha Strike on the wave to last-hit safely from outside his Q drain range, and concede CS rather than auto-trading into his heal levels 1-3."},{"t":"Save Alpha Strike for his E","d":"Hold Alpha Strike to go untargetable through his E chain-dash stun in fights — dodging that one ability is the difference between dying and out-DPSing him."},{"t":"Survive to your item spike","d":"The whole lane is a race to Kraken/Blade of the Ruined King; play safe, hit your timing, and the matchup flips from his favour to yours."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't auto-trade his drain","d":"Never get into an auto-for-auto poke war pre-6 — his Q/W drain-heal out-sustains your chip and feeds his all-in setup."},{"t":"Don't blow Alpha Strike to engage","d":"If you Alpha in to start a fight, his E is up to stun you the moment it ends — use Alpha Strike reactively to dodge his stun, not to commit."},{"t":"Don't ult into a Sylas with R up","d":"Popping Highlander when his R is available hands him your ultimate; bait his R or fight after it's gone before you commit yours."}],"tradeGood":"A reactive burst where you Alpha-Strike through his E chain-stun, land a full Wuju Style true-damage auto sequence, then disengage before his Q/W heals it back.","tradeBad":"A drawn-out auto-for-auto poke war pre-item where his drain-heal out-sustains you and his E sets up a lockdown all-in.","ahead":"If you reach your item spike ahead, hunt extended fights: bait his E, Alpha Strike through it, and let on-hit DPS out-race his heal while Highlander resets carry you to the next kill. Shove and roam with your Highlander speed to snowball other lanes faster than his single-target kit can punish, and itemize anti-heal (Kraken passive plus a Mortal Reminder if needed) to shut his sustain off entirely. Never duel him with his R up — make him use it, then collect.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Sylas - Track: His E chain-dash stun — it is the only point-and-click lockdown that reliably catches you the instant Alpha Strike's untargetable window ends; bait or dodge it before committing. Respect his R too, since it steals your Highlander.. - Concede the early, farm safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos through his Q/W drain poke, then explode in extended fights once Kraken/Blade of the Ruined King comes online — Alpha Strike dodges his E chain-stun mid-fight while on-hit DPS out-races his self-heal. Use Highlander resets to chain kills the second you out-trade him.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A weak-early on-hit carry against a self-healing AP bruiser whose E stun catches you out of Alpha Strike and whose R steals your Highlander — survive to your on-hit spike and the lane flips, but Sylas edges everything before then."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing early lane by farming with Alpha Strike and conceding aggression to Sylas's drain-heal, then win every extended fight once your on-hit items come online by dodging his E with Alpha Strike. Highlander resets turn one won fight into a snowball he can't single-target his way out of."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Sylas owns 1-5 on drain-heal and E-stun, you claim 6 on Highlander (respecting his R theft), it's a coin-flip at first item, and you go FAVOURED-to-dominant at 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only with a reactive Alpha Strike + Wuju Style burst when his E is down, then disengage before his heal recovers it; back off entirely from any auto-for-auto exchange pre-6."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave slow-pushing toward you or frozen just past river so you farm out of his Q range and deny his E-stun all-in and dive angle; only shove when you've spiked on an item."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable blink dodges his E chain-dash stun and his Q drain damage; his R steals your Highlander, so the ult-vs-ult timing is the lane's core read — never pop yours while his R is up."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (best vs an AP bruiser you want to out-DPS), Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve with Conditioning or Second Wind to weather his Q/W poke; Conqueror is fine if you prefer the sustained-fight ramp."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite to cut his Q/W drain-heal and secure kills once you out-trade him; take Teleport only if you're being denied hard and need to scale safely back to lane."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Open Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit spike, follow with Wit's End or Terminus for magic resist into his AP, then boots (Mercury's Treads vs his E stun and AP); prioritize anti-heal effects to shut off his drain."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Only all-in at 6+ when his E and ideally his R are on cooldown — that's when you can Alpha Strike his stun, out-DPS his heal, and reset Highlander; before items, you have no real all-in."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're highly gankable pre-6 because Alpha Strike is your only out and his E can hold you for the gank — ward river and play short; post-6 Highlander's speed and slow-immunity let you dodge ganks and even punish his jungler in a 2v2 if you can Alpha their CC."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players Alpha Strike in to start fights and get E-stunned the instant it ends, or they pop Highlander into an available Sylas R and hand him their ult — both throw the matchup you were built to win late."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're behind, stop dueling him entirely: farm side waves with Alpha Strike, group only for teamfights where you can flank and Alpha through his E onto a backline carry rather than face-tank his drain and stun."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"When ahead, force extended fights with anti-heal up, bait and dodge his E, and ride Highlander resets to roam and snowball other lanes faster than his single-target kit can answer."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"TRICKY 6/10 — Sylas's E stun and R theft punish your weak early, but survive to your on-hit items and you out-scale him hard; a clean lane race, not a lost one."}]},"tahmkench":{"tldr":"Tahm Kench's grey-health and percent-HP devour out-sustain my on-hit damage through laning, so I farm safe, dodge his tongue, and wait to flip the lane once my second item comes online.","winCon":"Survive the early game with Alpha Strike farming and Wuju autos, never eat a Q tongue-stun into a free trade, and reach Blade of the Ruined King plus a second on-hit item where percent-HP and lifesteal finally chew through his grey health. From there I out-DPS him in extended fights and use Highlander resets to roam off his side lane.","enemyWin":"Tahm Kench wins by landing Q tongue-stun to lock me after my Alpha Strike is on cooldown, then devouring or stat-checking me while his passive grey health and W reset every trade I try. He out-sustains my early all-ins and roams with R to snowball other lanes while I'm too weak to punish his absence.","diff":"TRICKY","tone":"#ff8b3d","diffRating":"6/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Tahm Kench","rating":"6/10","why":"His tongue Q stun threatens a free trade while my Alpha Strike is just a farm tool with no escape value yet at level 1."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Tahm Kench","rating":"6/10","why":"A landed Q lets him walk up and stat-check me before Wuju Style's true damage is available to punish him back."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Tahm Kench","rating":"6/10","why":"His grey-health passive regenerates any chip I land with autos, so I can't build a poke lead while he sits on percent-HP sustain."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"With Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain online I can match his grey-health regen in short trades, but a Q stun still flips any extended one."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's slow immunity and move speed let me dodge his gank setups and answer a tongue-pull, the first window where I'm not just reacting."},{"label":"First item","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Blade of the Ruined King's percent-HP on-hit starts cutting his grey health, but one item alone doesn't beat his full devour-and-sustain pattern yet."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"At two on-hit items my percent-HP DPS and lifesteal out-pace his grey-health regen, and Alpha Strike dodges his Q so he can't lock me in the fight."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Tahm Kench. His Q tongue-stun is the whole danger: if he lands it while my Alpha Strike is down, I have no escape and eat a full trade plus a possible jungler. My grey-health enemy regenerates anything I poke, so I don't try to win the lane early. I farm with Alpha Strike, last-hit with Wuju autos, and stay out of tongue range of the wave.","mid":"Levels 4-5 stabilize as Wuju Style's true damage ignores any armor he builds and Meditate lets me sit through his chip and reset. Level 6 is my first real window: Highlander's slow immunity and attack speed let me dodge his gank attempts and punish a missed Q. I can take short Wuju trades now but must still respect a fresh tongue.","late":"At 2+ items I flip the lane. Blade of the Ruined King plus a second on-hit item (Wit's End vs his AP utility, Terminus, or Kraken) means my percent-HP on-hit finally out-paces his grey-health regen, and lifesteal heals through his damage. Alpha Strike untargetability dodges his Q in the fight so he can't lock me, and Highlander resets let me chain a kill into a roam.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push you control so you can freeze just outside tongue range and deny him CS without overextending into a Q. Worst wave: a wave shoved to his tower where he can Q you onto the turret or set up a jungle collapse. Crash timing: crash the wave just before your 2+ item back so you reset on full health and return for the dive window with item advantage.","cooldowns":"Track his Q (Tongue Lash) cooldown above all — every aggressive step you take should be on a Q you just watched whiff or go on cooldown. Also note when his R is up, since a roam means he leaves lane and you can shove and follow or take plates.","trading":"Trade only when his Q is down: walk in with Wuju Style active, get your Double Strike proc and on-hit autos, and step out before he can re-engage. Never extend a trade into his grey health refilling — short, Q-baited Wuju bursts only until you have two items.","spikes":"His spikes are level 6 (R roam pressure) and any point he lands Q with jungler nearby. Mine are level 6 Highlander for dodging ganks, and decisively the 2+ item on-hit window where percent-HP beats grey health.","feeding":"If I fall behind, Tahm Kench becomes an unkillable percent-HP wall who roams freely with R and devours me on sight. I lose all-in pressure, can't punish his roams, and the enemy team gets a fed drain-tank frontline — concede CS and farm jungle camps to scale.","carry":"If I'm ahead, I hit two items first and the lane is mine: I out-DPS him 1v1, Alpha Strike dodges his Q, and Highlander resets turn a kill into a side-lane snowball. I leave lane to apply on-hit DPS to squishies the moment I have my reset condition.","difficulty":"It's a 6/10 because his Q tongue-stun is a hard-CC trap for a champion whose only escape is Alpha Strike, and his grey-health plus percent-HP sustain neutralizes my entire early damage pattern. It's not harder because he can't actually kill me fast and I out-scale him decisively once itemized."},"focus":{"text":"His Q tongue-stun — it's the one ability that catches me after Alpha Strike and turns a neutral lane into a free trade or a gank; respect its range and only commit when it's on cooldown.","letters":["Q"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Bait the tongue","d":"Stay just outside Q range and only step in to trade or all-in on a Q you've watched whiff or go on cooldown, since it's the only thing that locks you down."},{"t":"Farm to two items","d":"Concede the early lane and CS safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos until Blade of the Ruined King plus a second on-hit item lets percent-HP beat his grey health."},{"t":"Dodge Q with Alpha Strike","d":"In fights past level 6, save Alpha Strike to go untargetable through his tongue so he can't stun you mid-trade and stat-check you."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't poke his grey health","d":"Trying to chip him down early just feeds his passive regen and percent-HP sustain — your autos do nothing to his health bar until you have on-hit items."},{"t":"Don't get tongued onto his tower","d":"Never push so hard that he can Q you under turret or into a jungle collapse while your Alpha Strike escape is on cooldown."},{"t":"Don't ignore his R roams","d":"When his ultimate is up and he vanishes, don't keep farming blindly — ping it, shove, and follow or take plates rather than letting him snowball another lane."}],"tradeGood":"Walk in with Wuju Style active on a Q he just whiffed, land a Double Strike on-hit burst, and step out before his grey health refills or his tongue comes back up.","tradeBad":"Never commit an extended trade while his Q is up — a single tongue-stun after your Alpha Strike is down hands him a free fight and likely a gank.","ahead":"Once I'm ahead, I hit my 2+ item on-hit spike first and use it to fully take the lane: I out-DPS him in any extended fight, dodge his Q with Alpha Strike, and snowball Highlander resets into roams. I leave the side lane to apply percent-HP on-hit pressure to the enemy carries while he's too slow to follow. Every reset I get means another tower or another lane collapses before he can stabilize as a frontline.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Tahm Kench - Track: His Q tongue-stun — it's the one ability that catches me after Alpha Strike and turns a neutral lane into a free trade or a gank; respect its range and only commit when it's on cooldown.. - Survive the early game with Alpha Strike farming and Wuju autos, never eat a Q tongue-stun into a free trade, and reach Blade of the Ruined King plus a second on-hit item where percent-HP and lifesteal finally chew through his grey health. From there I out-DPS him in extended fights and use Highlander resets to roam off his side lane.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Tahm Kench's grey-health and percent-HP devour out-sustain my on-hit damage through laning, so I farm safe, dodge his tongue, and wait to flip the lane once my second item comes online."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"My win condition is to survive a sustain-favored early lane without eating a Q tongue-stun, then reach my 2+ on-hit item spike where percent-HP and lifesteal finally beat his grey health. From there I out-DPS him in extended fights, dodge his Q with Alpha Strike, and chain Highlander resets into roams."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Tahm Kench owns levels 1-3 (Q + grey-health sustain), the lane evens out at 4-6 as Wuju true damage and Highlander come online, and I take over decisively at 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only when his Q is on cooldown — short Wuju Style bursts in, out before grey health refills; back off entirely whenever his tongue is up or his jungler could collapse."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Freeze or slow-push just outside tongue range early to deny CS safely; once I have two items I can shove, dive, and follow his roams. Avoid hard-pushing into his tower where a Q can pull me in."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges his Q tongue-stun in a fight; Wuju Style's true damage ignores the armor and tankiness he stacks; Meditate sustains through his early chip but loses to his percent-HP devour, and Highlander's slow immunity beats his gank-setup peel."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (ramps attack speed for the on-hit scaling that beats grey health) with Triumph and Legend: Alacrity; secondary Resolve with Conditioning and Overgrowth, or Second Wind into his percent-HP poke. Grasp/Conqueror are off-pattern here."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite — the Ignite grievous wounds cuts his grey-health and Meditate-tier sustain and gives me kill pressure once I spike; take Teleport instead only if you're being pushed in hard and need to stay even in CS."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Blade of the Ruined King first for percent-HP that shreds his grey health, then Wit's End if he goes AP utility (or Terminus / Kraken into AD comps); Berserker's Greaves, and tabis/defensive third only if his team's damage demands it. Anti-heal component (Mortal Reminder line) is strong into his sustain."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"I can only all-in when his Q is on cooldown and my Alpha Strike is up to dodge a re-engage — realistically at level 6 with Highlander, and freely at 2+ items where my DPS out-paces his sustain."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"His Q tongue-stun makes me extremely gankable early, so I track his jungler and play short until 6; conversely, my own jungler can convert a baited Q into a free kill since Tahm has no hard escape, and post-6 Highlander lets me follow his R roams."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi mistake here is trying to win the early lane by poking him — every auto just feeds his grey-health regen, and overextending to do it gets you tongued and killed. Respect the sustain and farm to your spike."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If I'm behind, I stop contesting lane, farm jungle camps and side waves to scale, and only group when my on-hit items are online; never solo-commit into a fed percent-HP drain-tank who'll just devour me."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Ahead, I hit two items first, take the lane outright, and use Highlander resets to roam the on-hit DPS onto enemy carries before he can stabilize as a frontline — every reset closes another objective."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"TRICKY (48%): his Q and grey-health sustain edge the early lane, but I claim level 6 and decisively out-scale him at 2+ on-hit items."}]},"teemo":{"tldr":"A pure kite-versus-scaling race: Teemo's Blinding Dart blanks your autos and on-hit and shoves you off the wave early, but a single blind is all he gets before BORK and Highlander let you run a no-escape squishy down.","winCon":"Survive the blind-and-poke phase by farming with Alpha Strike from max range, then itemize on-hit (Blade of the Ruined King into Wit's End) and use Highlander's move/attack speed to close the gap and out-DPS him before he can re-blind. The lane is won the moment you reach him with E Wuju Style up and one item online — Teemo has no escape if you arrive at full health.","enemyWin":"Teemo wins by keeping you at range: blind your Alpha Strike or your committed E auto window so your whole combo deals nothing, kite back with passive/move-speed, and chip you down with E poison and Q before you ever touch him. If he zones your minions with shrooms and keeps you under XP/CS, you never reach the items that flip the lane.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Teemo","rating":"7/10","why":"His auto range and Blinding Dart let him poke you for free while your only level-1 tool is Alpha Strike, which he just blinds or walks out of."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Teemo","rating":"7/10","why":"With Move Quick and poison up he kites every step-up, and a single Blinding Dart turns your Q-reset auto window into zero damage."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Teemo","rating":"6/10","why":"E poison plus Q out-trades your short autos before Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain can stabilize the lane."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style's true damage and a Meditate channel finally let you out-sustain his poison, but he still controls range and blind timing."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Highlander's move and attack speed close his kite gap, but his Blinding Dart on a short cooldown can still blank your engage if mistimed."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Blade of the Ruined King's active slow plus Alpha Strike untargetability let you ignore one blind and shred a squishy with no escape."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"With BORK and Wit's End your on-hit DPS plus a Highlander reset run him down through any single blind — he has nothing to peel a fed skirmisher."}],"breakdown":{"early":"This is Teemo's phase, full stop. At levels 1-3 you have short range, low base damage, and only Alpha Strike, while he autos you from range and holds Blinding Dart to negate any auto you try to land. Do not try to trade — farm with Alpha Strike on the back minions and Wuju autos when his blind is on cooldown, and accept that you will eat poison chip. The one rule: never burn Q to engage him, because once you blink in he just blinds your follow-up and kites you while E poison ticks.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you stabilize — Wuju Style's true damage means his Magical Resist does nothing and Meditate can heal back a chunk of his poke between waves, so the bleed slows. Level 6 Highlander is your first real answer to his kite: the move and attack speed and slow immunity let you actually stick to him. But his Blinding Dart cooldown is shorter than your all-in is long, so a lone level-6 engage with no item still gets blinded mid-combo. Use 6 to dodge ganks and contest, not to force a kill yet.","late":"Once Blade of the Ruined King is online the lane flips. Its active slow plus the on-hit DPS, paired with Alpha Strike's untargetability to dodge ONE blind, lets you close and shred him — Teemo is a squishy with no escape, so reaching him at full HP is a kill. At Wit's End / Terminus and 2+ items you out-DPS him through any single Blinding Dart, and a kill resets Highlander to keep going. He has no recovery tool once you're fed.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push you can freeze just outside his tower, denying him CS and forcing him to walk into your Alpha Strike range to farm. Worst wave: a wave shoved into your tower under his shrooms and poison, where you take chip just to last-hit and can be dove. Crash timing: crash the wave just before your first-item back so you reset on full HP with BORK online and return to a freeze that pins him in kill range.","cooldowns":"Track Blinding Dart (Q) above all — it is the entire matchup. Its cooldown is your only window: when it is down, Teemo cannot stop your autos or Alpha Strike on-hit, so every engage must be timed to a Q he has already used. Secondarily note his shroom (R) placements in brush and on the wave.","trading":"Never trade into an up Blinding Dart. Your only good trade is engaging the instant after he blinds a minion or whiffs Q: Alpha Strike in, E Wuju Style true-damage autos, and BORK active to stop his kite. If his blind is up, you concede the trade and farm.","spikes":"His spikes are level 1 (auto range + blind dominance) and any point your blind is up. Yours are level 6 Highlander (sticking power), Blade of the Ruined King (the lane-flipping item — slow + on-hit + the survivability to eat one blind), and 2+ items where you out-DPS through a blind entirely.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Teemo zones your wave with shrooms, denies you XP, and you fall further off your item timings — the one thing that flips this lane. A behind Yi who never reaches BORK is permanently kited and pokes to death. Give up CS rather than dying, ask your jungler to clear shrooms and force him off the wave, and play for scaling.","carry":"If ahead, you snowball harder than almost any champ — a fed Yi with BORK and Highlander resets through fights, and Teemo cannot peel or kite a skirmisher who out-ranges his blind cooldown. Use your lead to roam with Highlander's speed, take towers, and turn side-lane pressure into 1v9 splits.","difficulty":"It is a 5/10 EVEN, not harder, because the matchup is two clean halves: he hard-owns the early lane through blind and kite, you hard-own the scaling once BORK and Highlander come online and his no-escape squishy body folds. The skill is purely in surviving the early bleed without falling off your item timer."},"focus":{"text":"Blinding Dart (Q) is the whole lane — it blanks your autos, your Alpha Strike on-hit, and your E Wuju Style true damage. Every engage must be timed to when it is on cooldown.","letters":["Q"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike","d":"Use Q to last-hit from range and stay safe while you scale; it lets you CS without walking into his auto-plus-blind poke before your items come online."},{"t":"Engage only on a used blind","d":"Watch Blinding Dart's cooldown and commit your Alpha Strike, E autos, and BORK active the instant after he blinds a minion or whiffs Q on you."},{"t":"Build BORK first and rush it","d":"Blade of the Ruined King is the lane-flipping spike — its active slow stops his kite and its on-hit shreds his low HP; getting it on time is your entire win condition."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't engage into an up Q","d":"If Blinding Dart is available, an all-in deals near-zero — he blinds your Wuju autos mid-combo and kites you out while poison ticks. Wait it out."},{"t":"Don't burn Alpha Strike to chase","d":"Q is your only escape; if you blink in and get blinded, you have no way out and his E poison plus Move Quick finish you. Save it to dodge his combo, not to chase a kill you can't secure."},{"t":"Don't fall off your item timer","d":"Never trade CS or HP for nothing early — if his shrooms and poke deny you the gold for BORK, you stay permanently kited and the EVEN lane becomes a losing one."}],"tradeGood":"Alpha Strike in the moment his Blinding Dart is on cooldown, pop E Wuju Style for true-damage autos and BORK active to stop his kite, and burst him before the blind comes back up.","tradeBad":"Engaging into an up Blinding Dart — he blanks your entire on-hit combo, kites you with Move Quick, and chips you to death with E poison for free.","ahead":"Press a lead by freezing the wave just outside his tower so he must walk into your Alpha Strike range to farm, denying him the CS and XP he needs to keep kiting. Use Highlander's bonus move speed to roam and snowball other lanes, since Teemo can't punish a short absence. Once you have BORK plus a kill or two, force the side lane — he has no tool to stop a fed skirmisher from running him down, and every kill resets Highlander to chain the next.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Teemo - Track: Blinding Dart (Q) is the whole lane — it blanks your autos, your Alpha Strike on-hit, and your E Wuju Style true damage. Every engage must be timed to when it is on cooldown.. - Survive the blind-and-poke phase by farming with Alpha Strike from max range, then itemize on-hit (Blade of the Ruined King into Wit's End) and use Highlander's move/attack speed to close the gap and out-DPS him before he can re-blind. The lane is won the moment you reach him with E Wuju Style up and one item online — Teemo has no escape if you arrive at full health.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A pure kite-versus-scaling race: Teemo's Blinding Dart blanks your autos and on-hit and shoves you off the wave early, but a single blind is all he gets before BORK and Highlander let you run a no-escape squishy down."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Your win condition is surviving the early blind-and-poke phase without falling off your item timer, then reaching the Blade of the Ruined King spike that lets you close on a no-escape squishy. Time every all-in to a Blinding Dart that is already on cooldown, dodge one blind with Alpha Strike's untargetability, and out-DPS him with on-hit before he can re-blind."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Teemo owns levels 1-3 hard (range plus blind), the lane levels out at 4-6 as Wuju Style true damage, Meditate, and Highlander come online, and you take over at first item through 2+ items where his no-escape body can't survive your on-hit reset."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only when Blinding Dart is down — then commit fully with Alpha Strike, E autos, and BORK active. If his blind is up, take no trade and farm; a blinded combo is a free poke for him."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Push to a freeze just outside his tower so he must step into Alpha Strike range to CS. Avoid letting the wave sit shoved into your tower under his shrooms where you take chip to last-hit. Crash before your first back to reset on full HP with BORK online."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Blinding Dart blanks your autos, your Alpha Strike on-hit, AND your E Wuju Style true damage — it is the core counter. Your counterplay is Alpha Strike's untargetability (it dodges his Q and any incoming auto during the blink) and the fact that one blind on a cooldown is not enough to stop a fully itemized on-hit combo. Meditate out-sustains his poison chip between trades."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the on-hit attack-speed ramp that powers your scaling, with Triumph and Legend: Alacrity primary; secondary Resolve with Second Wind (huge vs his poke and poison) and Overgrowth, or Conditioning. Second Wind is near-mandatory into Teemo's poison."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ghost is strong here to close his kite gap and run him down with Highlander, but Teleport is fully acceptable to stay on your item timer and recover from a bad early shove. Avoid Ignite — you have no early all-in to make it pay off into a ranged kiter."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Blade of the Ruined King (active slow plus on-hit is the lane-flipping spike), then Wit's End for the magic resist and on-hit magic damage that turns his AP poke into nothing while it shreds him. Kraken Slayer or Terminus after. Mercury's Treads for his magic poke and any CC. Consider an early Wit's End component for the MR if his poke is winning."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Only when Blinding Dart is on cooldown AND you have at least BORK online and are near full HP. Level 6 with Highlander gives you the sticking speed, but a no-item all-in still gets blinded mid-combo — wait for first item to make the engage stick."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"Teemo is immobile with no escape, so a gank is a near-guaranteed kill if your jungler arrives while his blind is committed or down — call for early pressure to break the kite lane. Beware his shrooms revealing the gank and slowing your jungler; clear vision in brush first. His own ganks are weak; the danger is being zoned, not dove."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi error here is forcing trades or all-ins into an up Blinding Dart and watching the whole combo deal nothing, then dying to poison while kited. The second mistake is chasing with Alpha Strike as an engage and having no escape when blinded. Discipline on the Q cooldown is everything."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If behind, give up CS rather than HP, take Second Wind value, and ask your jungler to clear shrooms and pressure him off the wave. Farm with Alpha Strike under tower, hit your BORK timing even if late, and remember the lane swings back the instant you out-scale — don't int trying to force it even."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If ahead, freeze him out of CS, roam with Highlander speed to snowball other lanes, and force side-lane duels where his no-escape body folds. Every kill resets Highlander and reduces your other cooldowns, so chain pressure and take towers before he can buy his way back to relevance."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A genuine 51.6% EVEN coinflip of two halves — Teemo blinds and kites you out of the early lane, but you scale through one blind into a 1v9 skirmisher the moment BORK and Highlander land; discipline on his Q cooldown and your item timer decides it."}]},"trundle":{"tldr":"A coin-flip drain-tank duel: Trundle out-bites you early and his Pillar walls your only escape after Alpha Strike, but once your on-hit items come online your true damage and resets out-DPS his sustain.","winCon":"Survive his early bite-bullying by farming with Alpha Strike, then spike on your first on-hit item (Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King) plus Wuju Style true damage — that combination shreds the bonus resistances his R hands him and out-paces his drain. Drag every fight long with Highlander resets so his single Subjugate heal can't keep up.","enemyWin":"Trundle wins by snowballing the levels 1-5 window where his Q bite steals your AD and out-sustains your weak base damage, then landing Pillar of Ice to cut off your Alpha Strike escape and let his jungler collapse. If he reaches a defensive spike with R-stolen resistances before you finish your first item, his drain-tank EHP outlasts your DPS.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Trundle","rating":"6/10","why":"His Q Chomp steals attack damage and out-trades your weak rank-1 autos, and you have no Wuju true damage or escape yet besides Alpha Strike."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Trundle","rating":"6/10","why":"He spikes hard at 2 points with bite plus a poke tool while your base damage is still flat — eat minions with Q instead of dueling."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Trundle","rating":"5/10","why":"Once you have E Wuju Style you can take a short true-damage trade, but his bite-steal still wins the all-in, so it stays his side by a hair."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Meditate sustain plus Wuju true damage lets you farm and trade evenly, but Pillar of Ice still threatens to wall your Q exit — neither owns it."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Highlander gives you slow-immunity to ignore Frozen Domain's zone and dodge ganks, but he also hits 6 for Subjugate, so the spike cancels out."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King plus Wuju true damage starts cutting through the bonus resistances his R grants — your on-hit DPS now wins extended fights."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"At two on-hit items your true-damage shred and Highlander resets out-DPS his single drain-heal, flipping you to favoured if you avoid his Pillar."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are his. Trundle's Q Chomp steals a chunk of your attack damage on every bite, so trading autos here is a losing exchange while you still have flat base damage and no Wuju Style true damage online. Just farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, concede the lane, and never stand to fight him in his own minions where his sustain tops back up.","mid":"At E (Wuju Style) you can finally take a short true-damage trade since his stolen-armor and the resistances he'll get from R don't reduce true damage, but his bite-steal still wins a committed all-in, so keep trades brief. Level 6 is the swing: Highlander's slow-immunity lets you walk straight through his Frozen Domain movespeed/attack-speed zone and ignore Pillar's slow, but he also gets Subjugate, so respect a jungler collapse and don't ego-fight into a 2v1.","late":"At 2+ items you flip favoured. Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King plus Wuju Style true damage chews through the bonus resistances Subjugate steals off you, and Highlander resets let you chain through extended fights his single drain-heal can't out-sustain. The only thing that loses you the fight now is eating a Pillar of Ice the instant you drop out of Alpha Strike.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push that lets you crash on his tower while he's pillar-walled away from CSing, so you can shove-and-roam with Highlander. Worst wave: a wave frozen near his side where he can Q-bite-bully you off CS and set up a Pillar gank. Crash timing: crash the big wave just before your first on-hit item completes so you can recall, spike, and return before he can freeze it back on you.","cooldowns":"Track Pillar of Ice (E) above all — it's a ~13-15s cooldown and it's the one tool that traps you after Alpha Strike drops you out of untargetability; if it's down, your all-in is far safer.","trading":"Short and item-gated: pre-6 only trade when his Q Chomp is on cooldown and you have Wuju Style up for true damage; never auto-for-auto into a fresh bite. Post-items, you want the long fight — engage with R up, Alpha Strike onto him to reset your attack timer, and let on-hit true damage out-grind his drain.","spikes":"His spikes are early (Q at 1-2, defensive resistances + heal from Subjugate at 6). Yours are level 6 Highlander (slow-immunity beats his entire kite-zone kit) and especially your first and second on-hit items where true damage ignores everything his R gives him.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Trundle becomes an unkillable drain-tank front line — his R steals YOUR resistances and heals off you in fights, so a fed Trundle is a nightmare for your whole team. Don't int trying to solo him; farm side waves with Alpha Strike, hit your item timings, and let your slow-but-real scaling claw back the 2-item window.","carry":"Ahead, you out-scale him into a 1v9 — push side lanes, force him to answer with Highlander mobility, and when teamfights break out Alpha Strike onto his carries (it makes you untargetable to dodge his Pillar and any peel) and reset Highlander off every kill to run the whole team down.","difficulty":"It rates a 5/10 because it's a true coin-flip (49.38%): he genuinely owns the first five levels with bite-steal and Pillar lockdown, but nothing in his kit hard-counters your scaling the way a blind or hard point-and-click stun would — your true damage cleanly answers his resistance theft, so skilled play around his Pillar and your item timings decides it."},"focus":{"text":"Pillar of Ice (E) — it's the only thing that catches you after Alpha Strike ends, walling and slowing you out of the kill or the escape; bait it or wait it out before every all-in.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Q, don't duel early","d":"Use Alpha Strike to clear safely and stack CS through levels 1-5 instead of auto-trading into his Q Chomp, which steals your attack damage every bite."},{"t":"Hold Alpha Strike for his Pillar","d":"Alpha Strike makes you untargetable mid-blink, so use it to phase through or right after a Pillar of Ice cast — don't blow it early and get walled when it's on cooldown."},{"t":"Let on-hit true damage do the work","d":"Once Wuju Style and Kraken/Blade are up, your true damage ignores the resistances Subjugate steals off you — stretch the fight long and reset Highlander to win it."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't auto-trade into a fresh Q","d":"Trading basics while his Q Chomp is up just feeds him your AD and his sustain — only commit autos when his bite is on cooldown and Wuju Style is active."},{"t":"Don't fight inside his minions","d":"Trundle drains and tops himself off through a wave, so an extended trade in his creeps is a fight you lose even when you're even on items."},{"t":"Don't ego-duel a fed Trundle","d":"If he's ahead, his R steals your resistances and heals off you mid-fight — don't 1v1 him from behind; farm to your item spikes and let teammates help collapse."}],"tradeGood":"With Highlander and your first on-hit item up, Alpha Strike onto him to reset your attack timer, then auto with Wuju Style active so true damage shreds through his stolen resistances in a fight you keep going long.","tradeBad":"A level 1-3 auto-for-auto into a fresh Q Chomp — his bite steals your AD and his drain out-sustains you while your base damage is still flat and Wuju Style isn't online.","ahead":"Press a lead by shoving the wave with your item-boosted clear and roaming on Highlander's bonus movespeed, forcing Trundle to either lose CS under tower or follow into a fight he loses post-items. In skirmishes, Alpha Strike onto his backline so you're untargetable through his Pillar and any peel, then chain Highlander resets off each kill to snowball the map. Push your true-damage advantage relentlessly — his only answer to your scaling is to end the game fast, so deny him tempo.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Trundle - Track: Pillar of Ice (E) — it's the only thing that catches you after Alpha Strike ends, walling and slowing you out of the kill or the escape; bait it or wait it out before every all-in.. - Survive his early bite-bullying by farming with Alpha Strike, then spike on your first on-hit item (Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King) plus Wuju Style true damage — that combination shreds the bonus resistances his R hands him and out-paces his drain. Drag every fight long with Highlander resets so his single Subjugate heal can't keep up.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A coin-flip drain-tank duel: Trundle out-bites you early and his Pillar walls your only escape after Alpha Strike, but once your on-hit items come online your true damage and resets out-DPS his sustain."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Concede the early lane and farm safely with Alpha Strike until your first on-hit item plus Wuju Style come online, because true damage ignores every resistance his Subjugate steals. From there, drag fights long with Highlander resets so his single drain-heal can't out-sustain your on-hit DPS."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Trundle owns 1-3 (bite-steal), it's even at 4-6 (Wuju true damage + Highlander slow-immunity answer his kite and Pillar), and you flip favoured at 1-2 on-hit items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Pre-6: only trade when his Q Chomp is on cooldown and Wuju Style is up, and keep it short. Post-items: take the long fight with R up; back off any time his Pillar of Ice is available and you've already used Alpha Strike."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Farm under tower while behind early; once you spike, slow-push to crash on his tower so a frozen wave can't be used to bite-bully you, and shove before recalls to come back on time for your item spike."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges his Pillar of Ice and lets you phase a fight; Highlander's slow-immunity nullifies Frozen Domain's zone and Pillar's slow; Wuju Style's true damage bypasses the bonus resistances Subjugate gives him; Meditate out-sustains his pre-6 poke but not his full drain in a long fight."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (uncapped attack speed scales your on-hit and Alpha Strike resets) > Triumph > Legend: Alacrity > Last Stand (or Coup if he plays passive); secondary Sorcery — Nimbus Cloak + Transcendence — or Resolve Conditioning vs his bite. He's AD, so favor armor in your situationals."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to punish his weak escape and cap his Subjugate self-heal during your item-spike all-ins; take Teleport instead if you expect to be bullied off lane early and want to stay even on CS for the scaling fight."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit spike, into Wit's End (the magic damage + his AD reduction helps vs his bite) or Terminus for armor-shred + resistances. Berserker's Greaves; build Death's Dance / armor situationally since he's all physical, and pick up anti-heal (Mortal Reminder line) to cap his R and W sustain."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Your real all-in is level 6+ with Highlander up and your first on-hit item complete, AND his Pillar of Ice on cooldown — that combination lets you ignore his slows, shred his resistances, and reset through the kill."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"This is the danger axis: Pillar of Ice into a gank cuts off your one escape, so ward his pathing and respect early collusion. Conversely, Highlander makes you an excellent counter-gank threat post-6 and lets you reset and snowball off a successful 2v2 — sync your fights with your own jungler."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players try to win the early levels by auto-trading into his Q Chomp and feed him AD and sustain, then panic-burn Alpha Strike before his Pillar so they get walled out of the escape — patience until your items, and holding Q for his E, is the whole matchup."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Farm side waves with Alpha Strike, avoid every solo fight (his R will heal off you and steal your resistances), and target your item timings — your scaling is slow but real, and the 2-item window reclaims the lane if you stay even on CS."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Shove and roam on Highlander's movespeed, force him to lose CS or fight post-items, and in teamfights Alpha Strike his carries to phase his Pillar, then chain Highlander resets to run the map before he can out-tank you."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A genuine 49.38% EVEN coin-flip — Trundle bullies the first five levels with bite-steal and Pillar lockdown, but your true damage cleanly answers his resistance theft and you flip favoured the moment your on-hit items come online; play around his Pillar and your spikes and the lane is yours."}]},"tryndamere":{"tldr":"A miserable melee mirror where Tryndamere out-spins you every level, his W slow kites your short range, and even when you win the fight Undying Rage steals the kill — survive, farm with Alpha Strike, and pray for jungle help.","winCon":"Concede every all-in until you have a full on-hit item (Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King) plus Wuju Style true damage online, then only fight Tryndamere when his W slow and E gap-close are both down and his Undying Rage is on cooldown. Your real win condition is roaming/teamfighting Highlander resets elsewhere on the map, not solo-killing a champion who literally cannot die for 5 seconds.","enemyWin":"Tryndamere stat-checks you levels 1-9 with crit spins and Bloodlust self-heal, perma-slows you with W so you can't trade evenly, and uses E to all-in or to disengage your Alpha Strike. Once he hits a Statikk/Collector-style crit spike he simply runs you down, and his R means any fight you \"win\" still ends with him alive at 1 HP and spinning away.","diff":"HARD","tone":"#ff5d6c","diffRating":"8/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Tryndamere","rating":"7/10","why":"His crit autos and W slow out-damage your short-range Wuju autos while you have only Alpha Strike and no escape, so you can't even contest CS aggressively."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Tryndamere","rating":"7/10","why":"With W slow plus a second point in his spin, he wins any auto exchange and you have no Meditate or Wuju true damage yet to answer."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Tryndamere","rating":"8/10","why":"Level 3 Tryndamere can E-in, W-slow, and spin you down before your Q reset and Double Strike passive can out-DPS his crit-heal sustain."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Tryndamere","rating":"7/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain stabilize you for short pokes, but his Bloodlust crit-heal still out-sustains anything short of a full commit."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Tryndamere","rating":"8/10","why":"You get Highlander for slow-immunity and gank-dodging, but he gets Undying Rage — the better level-6 spike, since he survives your full burst at 1 HP and spins away."},{"label":"First item","side":"Tryndamere","rating":"6/10","why":"Your Kraken/BORK on-hit spike closes the gap, but his crit item (Statikk/Collector) lands the same time and his R still denies you the kill on any all-in."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"At 2+ items your Alpha Strike DPS and Highlander resets can out-trade him in extended fights, but Undying Rage means you can only kill him if you bait R first — pure execution."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are pure damage control. Tryndamere's crit autos, W slow and Bloodlust self-heal beat your short-range Wuju autos in every exchange, and you have no escape but Alpha Strike (which he can just E onto you after). Farm with Q on the wave, take the chip, and do not contest him for last hits — every auto you walk up for is an auto plus a slow plus a crit back.","mid":"Levels 4-6 you stabilize slightly: Wuju Style adds true damage to your autos and Meditate lets you recover poke, so you can take short isolated trades when his W slow is on cooldown. But level 6 swings back to him — your Highlander is a chase/escape tool here, while his Undying Rage is an outright survival button that voids your kill pressure.","late":"At 2+ items (Kraken/BORK + Wit's End or Terminus) you finally out-DPS him in a sustained fight and Highlander resets let you chain through a teamfight. The catch never changes: solo, he can still pop R and spin away, so your power is best spent grouping and resetting off OTHER targets, not dueling the one champion built not to die.","wave":"Best wave: a wave frozen just outside your tower so his E-in over-extends him into your jungler. Worst wave: a wave shoved into his tower where he spin-resets, perma-slows you, and dives you under turret with R up. Crash timing: crash the wave right before your first back so you reset on item without giving him a free dive window while you're low.","cooldowns":"Track his W (Mocking Shout) slow above all — it is what makes you un-trade-able; trade only in the ~13s window when it is down.","trading":"His pattern is E-in or walk-up, W-slow you, spin until you leave; only take a trade when W is on cooldown and you can land a full Alpha Strike + Double Strike + Wuju burst and walk before he heals it back with Bloodlust.","spikes":"Your spikes: Kraken/BORK first item, then 2+ items. His spikes: level 6 Undying Rage and his first crit item — both arrive before your DPS does, which is why this is a HARD lane.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Tryndamere becomes a side-lane monster who 1v1s you forever and split-pushes through you; do not keep dueling him — give the side lane, farm safe waves with Q, and play for your team's other lanes.","carry":"If you do get ahead, you carry by abusing Highlander resets in fights and teleport flanks — never by chasing a low Tryndamere, since R turns your chase into his free reset.","difficulty":"It's 8/10 because he wins lane on stats, kites your short range with W, sustains through your poke with Bloodlust, AND has the one ability (Undying Rage) that hard-counters your entire reset-on-kill identity."},"focus":{"text":"Undying Rage (R) — for 5 seconds Tryndamere cannot drop below 1 HP, so it negates every kill you think you've earned; never commit your full Alpha Strike + Wuju burst and Flash into a Tryndamere who still has R, and never chase one who has popped it.","letters":["R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Q, not autos","d":"Use Alpha Strike to safely last-hit and chip the wave from range while staying untargetable — walking up for autos just eats a crit and a W slow."},{"t":"Trade only when his W is down","d":"Mocking Shout slow is what makes Yi un-tradeable here; the ~13s it's on cooldown is your only real window for a full on-hit burst."},{"t":"Bait Undying Rage before you commit","d":"Force or wait out his R before spending Alpha Strike + Flash + Highlander, or your 'kill' is just a free spin-away for him."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't all-in pre-2-items","d":"Until Kraken/BORK plus Wuju true damage are online, his crit-heal sustain wins every extended exchange — you simply lose the duel."},{"t":"Don't chase a low Tryndamere","d":"Undying Rage means a 1-HP Tryndamere is bait; chasing into his W slow and spin gets you killed and resets nothing for you."},{"t":"Don't Alpha Strike into his E","d":"He can E onto you the instant your untargetable Q ends and immediately W-slow you, so don't blow Q as an escape when his E is up."}],"tradeGood":"A short trade where you land a full Alpha Strike + Double Strike + Wuju Style true-damage burst while his W slow is on cooldown, then walk out before Bloodlust heals it back.","tradeBad":"A committed all-in with Flash and Highlander into a Tryndamere who still has Undying Rage up — you spend everything, he survives at 1 HP, W-slows you, and spins you down.","ahead":"If you somehow get ahead, do NOT try to keep solo-killing him — his R turns every chase into his reset. Instead use your lead to roam with Highlander's move speed and snowball other lanes, then come back and 2v1 him with your jungler so the kill actually sticks. Take Teleport flanks onto the map and let your DPS lead carry teamfights where Tryndamere can't just spin away from five people.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Tryndamere - Track: Undying Rage (R) — for 5 seconds Tryndamere cannot drop below 1 HP, so it negates every kill you think you've earned; never commit your full Alpha Strike + Wuju burst and Flash into a Tryndamere who still has R, and never chase one who has popped it.. - Concede every all-in until you have a full on-hit item (Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King) plus Wuju Style true damage online, then only fight Tryndamere when his W slow and E gap-close are both down and his Undying Rage is on cooldown. Your real win condition is roaming/teamfighting Highlander resets elsewhere on the map, not solo-killing a champion who literally cannot die for 5 seconds.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A miserable melee mirror where Tryndamere out-spins you every level, his W slow kites your short range, and even when you win the fight Undying Rage steals the kill — survive, farm with Alpha Strike, and pray for jungle help."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing early lane by farming with Alpha Strike and only trading when his W slow is down, then reach your Kraken/BORK + Wuju true-damage spike where you out-DPS him in extended fights. Because Undying Rage denies solo kills, your true win condition is converting that DPS into teamfight Highlander resets and map pressure, not into a 1v1 you can't finish."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Tryndamere owns levels 1-6 outright (crit + W slow + Bloodlust + Undying Rage); the lane only approaches even at your 2-item on-hit spike, and even then his R keeps it from ever flipping clearly in your favor."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only when Mocking Shout (W) is on cooldown and you can land a full Alpha Strike + Double Strike + Wuju burst; back off the instant he E-gap-closes or W-slows, and never extend a trade into his Bloodlust crit-heal window."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Hold the wave near your tower or freeze just out of his E range so a dive over-commits him to your jungler; only shove to reset on an item or to set up a recall, never to dive a champion who out-sustains you under his own turret."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges his spin damage briefly but NOT a follow-up E + W, and Highlander's slow-immunity ignores his W slow — but neither answers Undying Rage, which voids your whole reset-on-kill loop; Meditate's damage reduction helps eat spin chip but is interrupt-vulnerable while he autos you."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (he's an AD bruiser-duelist you must out-DPS, not burst) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve Conditioning + Overgrowth or Second Wind for the auto-attack poke; flat armor shard, scaling/flat HP, scaling HP — itemize toward surviving his sustained AD crit damage."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Teleport — Ignite does nothing into a champion with Undying Rage and Bloodlust self-heal, while Teleport keeps you on XP through a losing lane and lets you flank fights where your DPS actually matters."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first for on-hit DPS, then Wit's End (the MR is wasted here, so prefer Terminus or Death's Dance for armor + the spin's AD), Plated Steelcaps over his crit autos, and a defensive third (Death's Dance / Maw is overkill) to survive his sustained crit damage."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Only at 2+ items, only when his W slow AND Undying Rage are both on cooldown, and ideally with a jungler present — any all-in while R is up is a free reset for him."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"This is a gank-dependent lane: Tryndamere has no escape so a jungle gank when his R is down is your best source of a real kill, but his W slow makes him hard to collapse on once R is up, and your own Highlander-dodge only saves you if you keep Q for the gank, not as a poke tool."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi mistake here is committing the full Alpha Strike + Flash all-in into a healthy Tryndamere, eating Undying Rage, and dying to the W-slow spin-down — you traded everything for nothing because he literally can't die for 5 seconds."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're losing, stop dueling him entirely: farm safe waves with Q, take Teleport to other lanes, and let your team's leads carry — never keep feeding the one champion in the game built to 1v1 you forever."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If you're ahead, snowball through the MAP — roam with Highlander move speed, force objective fights where he can't spin away from five people, and only re-engage him in lane with a jungler so the kill sticks past his R."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"HARD (41.1% WR, 8/10 difficulty) — Tryndamere out-stats you all lane, kites your short range with W, sustains through your poke, and his Undying Rage hard-counters your reset identity; you don't beat him in lane, you out-scale and out-teamfight him on the map."}]},"urgot":{"tldr":"A miserable percent-HP grind where Urgot's shotgun legs out-DPS your on-hit and his Fear Beyond Death yanks you out of every Alpha Strike all-in.","winCon":"Survive a brutal early lane farming with Alpha Strike, never standing in his W-Purge channel, and rush your on-hit spike (Kraken/BORK) so you can punish him while his E (Disdain) flip is on cooldown. Your real win is scaling past lane to a 2+ item teamfight where you Q over his R-fear and reset Highlander on his squishies, not soloing the tank.","enemyWin":"Urgot walks you down with his shotgun-leg passive and W-Purge percent-max-HP shred that ignores how itemized you get, then lands E to flip you under tower and R (Fear Beyond Death) to fear-and-execute you the moment you commit Alpha Strike. He simply out-grinds your DPS in any standstill and denies you the scaling window.","diff":"HARD","tone":"#ff5d6c","diffRating":"8/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Urgot","rating":"7/10","why":"He autos for his Echoing Flames shotgun-leg passive (percent-max-HP physical) and Qs (Corrosive Charge) to slow you, while you have only Alpha Strike and low base damage to answer."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Urgot","rating":"7/10","why":"A second point in Q means his slow plus shotgun-leg autos chunk you, and Meditate sustain isn't online yet to recover the percent-HP poke."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Urgot","rating":"7/10","why":"At three points he can flip with E (Disdain) into his shotgun range and W-Purge you, and your Alpha Strike cooldown is too long to repeatedly dodge his sustained shred."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Urgot","rating":"6/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain stabilize you for short autos, but ranking W (Purge) lets him machine-gun the percent-HP legs and your growing HP only feeds them."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity let you dodge his Q-slow and contest, but his R (Fear Beyond Death) is also online to fear you mid-commit, so the window is even at best."},{"label":"First item","side":"Urgot","rating":"6/10","why":"Your Kraken/BORK on-hit spike comes online, but his first tank item plus percent-HP legs out-grind your DPS and his R still executes you out of the trade you set up."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Urgot","rating":"6/10","why":"Tanky Urgot's percent-max-HP shotgun legs ignore your durability and Meditate, and Fear Beyond Death fears-then-executes you out of any 1v1 you try to win."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are awful for you. Urgot just walks up and autos for his Echoing Flames shotgun-leg passive (percent-max-HP physical) and lands Q (Corrosive Charge) to slow you in place while you have nothing but Alpha Strike to answer, and your base damage is too low to trade back. Farm at the tip of Alpha Strike and with Wuju autos only when his Q is down, and never sit in his W-Purge channel hoping to out-auto him, you lose that race hard.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you finally have Wuju Style true damage and a bit of Meditate sustain to recover percent-HP poke, but Urgot ranking W (Purge) means the channel locks on and rapid-fires his legs, and your bigger HP only makes the procs hit harder. Level 6 Highlander is your one even-ish window: the move speed and slow immunity beat his Q-slow, but his R is up too, so don't treat 6 as a kill button the way you would into an immobile mage.","late":"At 2+ items you'd expect to flip favoured, but Urgot is the exception. He builds tank while his shotgun-leg passive deals percent-max-HP that doesn't care about your durability or Meditate, so the standstill DPS duel that beats most juggernauts stalls into a tank you can't burst, and Fear Beyond Death fears-then-executes you out of any kill you earn. Carry through teamfights and side-lane pressure on squishies, not by soloing him.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push where you freeze just outside his shotgun range and farm with Wuju autos, denying him E-flip angles. Worst wave: a wave shoved into your tower where he can E (Disdain) you into the turret and W-Purge you with no escape but a long Alpha Strike. Crash timing: crash level 6 to recall, buy your on-hit component, and return for the Highlander window rather than fighting on the slow push.","cooldowns":"Track his E (Disdain) flip above all and his R (Fear Beyond Death) at 6 — when Disdain is down he can't reposition you into his legs and tower, and that is your only safe all-in or escape window.","trading":"Short Alpha Strike-and-back trades only: blink in, apply on-hit, and disengage before his W-Purge locks on; never stand and auto-duel through his shotgun legs because percent-max-HP shred beats your raw DPS in any extended fight.","spikes":"Your spikes: level 6 Highlander, then first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK). His spikes: every W rank and his first tank item (Bramble/Frozen Heart), which both let his percent-HP legs out-grind your scaling.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Urgot snowballs into an unkillable percent-HP tank who deletes you on every E-flip; don't keep feeding him solo kills — give up CS, farm safe waves under tower, and play for jungle ganks and scaling instead.","carry":"If ahead, you don't win by killing Urgot — you win by shoving the wave with Alpha Strike and roaming/teamfighting, using Highlander resets on his squishier teammates while ignoring the tank you can't burst.","difficulty":"It's an 8/10 because the matchup attacks every Yi weakness at once: percent-max-HP that ignores armor and your durability, point-and-click lockdown (E flip, R fear) that catches you after Q, and a tank you can't burst even at full items, so your scaling fantasy never pays off in the 1v1."},"focus":{"text":"Fear Beyond Death (his R) — it fears you mid-Alpha-Strike then executes you below the HP threshold, turning every all-in you commit into a free kill for him; track its cooldown before you ever press your DPS into him.","letters":["R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike","d":"Use Q to last-hit and Wuju autos at max range so you avoid his shotgun-leg passive and Q-slow; concede early aggression and prioritize getting to your on-hit item spike."},{"t":"All-in only on his Disdain cooldown","d":"His E (Disdain) flip is his repositioning and your death sentence — commit Highlander and on-hit DPS only when Disdain is down so he can't yank you into his legs and tower."},{"t":"Scale and side-lane, don't solo him","d":"Build your on-hit spike to push waves and pressure the map; carry through teamfights resetting Highlander on his squishy carries, not by 1v1ing a percent-HP tank you can't burst."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Never sit in W-Purge","d":"Don't stand and auto-duel him while Purge channels onto you — its percent-max-HP shotgun-leg shred beats your raw on-hit DPS, and your bigger HP only feeds the procs."},{"t":"Don't treat 6 as a kill button","d":"Highlander beats his Q-slow but his R (Fear Beyond Death) is up at the same time; committing a full all-in at 6 just lets him fear-and-execute you out of it."},{"t":"Don't all-in into his legs and tower","d":"Never Alpha Strike onto him near his turret or when E is up — he flips you in, W-Purges, and the tower plus shotgun legs finish you before Highlander can reset."}],"tradeGood":"A short Alpha Strike blink-in to apply on-hit (and reset Q on him) followed by an immediate disengage with Highlander move speed, all while his E and W are on cooldown.","tradeBad":"A standstill auto-duel through his W-Purge channel and shotgun legs, where his percent-max-HP shred and R-execute beat your DPS every time.","ahead":"Even with a lead, don't expect to solo-kill Urgot — his percent-HP and tankiness make him a bad target. Press your advantage by shoving the wave with Alpha Strike to deny his farm, then roam or recall for your on-hit spike faster than him. In fights, use your gold lead to delete his squishy backline and chain Highlander resets, leaving the tank you can't burst to your team.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Urgot - Track: Fear Beyond Death (his R) — it fears you mid-Alpha-Strike then executes you below the HP threshold, turning every all-in you commit into a free kill for him; track its cooldown before you ever press your DPS into him.. - Survive a brutal early lane farming with Alpha Strike, never standing in his W-Purge channel, and rush your on-hit spike (Kraken/BORK) so you can punish him while his E (Disdain) flip is on cooldown. Your real win is scaling past lane to a 2+ item teamfight where you Q over his R-fear and reset Highlander on his squishies, not soloing the tank.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A miserable percent-HP grind where Urgot's shotgun legs out-DPS your on-hit and his Fear Beyond Death yanks you out of every Alpha Strike all-in."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive the early percent-HP poke by farming with Alpha Strike and never standing in his W-Purge, then rush your on-hit item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) and play for the map rather than the 1v1. Your win condition is reaching the 2+ item teamfight where you Q over his R-fear and reset Highlander on his carries, not out-grinding the tank in lane."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Urgot owns levels 1-5 outright, level 6 is a coin-flip with Highlander vs his R, and even at 2+ items he stays ahead in the 1v1 because percent-HP and tank stats beat your scaling."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only with short Alpha Strike-and-disengage bursts while his E (Disdain) and W (Purge) are down; back off the instant his W locks on, and never auto-duel him in a standstill where his shotgun legs grind you out."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave slow-pushing or frozen just outside his shotgun range so he can't E-flip you into tower; avoid letting the wave sit on your turret where Disdain plus the tower kills you, and crash at 6 to back for your on-hit component."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges his Q (Corrosive Charge) and can be timed to avoid the start of his R cast, Highlander's slow immunity ignores his Q-slow, and Meditate's damage reduction softens his autos — but none of it answers his percent-max-HP shotgun legs or a landed E (Disdain) flip, and his R (Fear Beyond Death) hard-counters any committed all-in."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the extended on-hit ramp into his tankiness, with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, and Last Stand; secondary Resolve with Second Wind (huge vs his percent-HP poke) and Overgrowth, or Bone Plating if you fear his E-flip burst."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Teleport — Ignite is wasted on a percent-HP tank you can't execute, and TP lets you farm safe, recall for your on-hit spike, and return to lane without bleeding tempo in a matchup you can't kill-pressure."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for on-hit (BORK's percent-HP helps vs his tank stats), then Wit's End or Terminus for resists and shred; take Mercury's Treads vs his R-fear and CC, and consider Bramble/anti-heal only if he goes bruiser, otherwise prioritize attack speed and a Maw/Steraks-tier survival item."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"The only real all-in is level 6 with Highlander up AND his E (Disdain) on cooldown AND his R unavailable — outside that exact overlap, every commit risks his fear-execute, so you mostly don't all-in this lane at all."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're extremely gankable pre-6 with only Alpha Strike to escape, so ward his flank and play for your own jungler — a gank that catches Urgot before he can E-flip away gives you the only clean kills you'll get, while his ganks plus his own CC chain easily kill you."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players treat this like a normal juggernaut matchup and try to scale into a 1v1 win at 2+ items — but Urgot's percent-HP and R-execute mean the scaling never flips, so the mistake is fighting him at all instead of farming, scaling, and carrying through teamfights."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If behind, give up CS freely, farm under tower with Wuju autos, ward both flanks, and avoid every E-flip range; let your jungler answer his pressure and focus on hitting your item spikes to be relevant in mid-game fights rather than reclaiming lane."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If ahead, shove with Alpha Strike to deny his farm, recall for your on-hit spike, then leave the tank and roam — convert the lead into kills on his squishy teammates with Highlander resets, taking objectives while your tempo lead lasts."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"HARD (8/10, ~38.5% WR): Urgot's percent-max-HP shotgun legs, E-flip, and Fear Beyond Death execute attack every Yi weakness, so farm it out, never solo him, and carry through scaling and teamfights."}]},"vayne":{"tldr":"Vayne kites you out of lane with tumble and condemn, but if you survive to Highlander and your first on-hit item you can run her down — until she reclaims the game at three items.","winCon":"Concede the early levels, farm safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, and survive to level 6 plus your first on-hit item (Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King) — then use Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity to close the gap and force an all-in before she gets two completed items.","enemyWin":"Vayne wins by never letting you touch her: tumble (Q) resets her attacks and breaks your Alpha Strike target, Condemn (E) walls you back the instant you commit, and Silver Bolts' percent-HP true damage shreds you as you scale, so if she hits her item curve untouched she out-DPSes you in every extended fight by three items.","diff":"TRICKY","tone":"#ff8b3d","diffRating":"7/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Vayne","rating":"7/10","why":"She auto-attacks you for free from range while your only tool is to Alpha Strike the wave; you have no way to trade back at level 1."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Vayne","rating":"7/10","why":"Her tumble-empowered auto plus a second skill point out-damages your short range, and you still can't safely step up to last-hit with autos."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Vayne","rating":"6/10","why":"With Wuju Style's true damage available you can punish a missed Condemn, but she still kites your every approach and any all-in needs Flash."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Vayne","rating":"6/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain stabilize your trades, but without Highlander she still resets distance with tumble faster than you can stick."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's bonus move/attack speed and slow immunity finally let you chase through her tumble and ignore her slow, turning a baited Condemn into a kill window."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King on-hit DPS plus Alpha Strike dodging her Condemn lets you out-trade her squishy frame in any fight where she's out of escapes."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Vayne","rating":"7/10","why":"At two-plus items her Silver Bolts percent-max-HP true damage and tumble-kite out-scale your on-hit build — she reclaims every drawn-out duel from here."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are pure survival: Vayne auto-attacks you for free from range and your short reach plus weak base damage means you can't trade back. Use Alpha Strike to farm safely from a distance and Wuju autos only when she's busy last-hitting. Never walk up for a melee CS into her tumble auto — you'll just eat free Silver Bolts stacks.","mid":"Levels 4-5 Wuju Style's bonus true damage and Meditate's channel-heal let you take short trades and out-sustain her poke between minions. Level 6 is your first real swing: Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity let you finally chase through a tumble, and if she burns Condemn on the wave you can Alpha Strike in and threaten a kill with Ignite.","late":"At your first on-hit item you spike hard — Alpha Strike dodges her Condemn, resets your attack timer, and your on-hit DPS out-trades her thin HP bar. But this is a borrowed window: once Vayne completes her second and third items, Silver Bolts' percent-max-HP true damage and her tumble kite out-scale you, and she reclaims every extended fight. Close the game in the 6-to-one-item window or she wins it.","wave":"Best wave: a slow-push you can freeze just outside your tower, denying her the long-range free autos and shrinking the space she needs to kite. Worst wave: a wide, shoved-in wave on open ground that lets her tumble-kite around minions and chip you with Silver Bolts. Crash timing: crash hard right as you hit level 6 or your first item so you can recall, then return on a wave that lets you all-in with Highlander up.","cooldowns":"Track Condemn (E) above all — it's an ~18s cooldown and her only hard disengage. When it's down she cannot push you off her, so your entire all-in is built around baiting or eating it on minions first.","trading":"You lose every auto-for-auto trade until level 6, so trade only on her cooldown gaps: bait Condemn, wait out her tumble, then Alpha Strike in with Wuju Style active and Highlander chasing. Outside those windows, take no trade and just farm.","spikes":"Your spikes: level 6 (Highlander) and your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK). Her spikes: level 2 (tumble + second auto), and decisively her second and third items where Silver Bolts true damage outscales your tankiness.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Vayne snowballs into an unkillable kiter — her Silver Bolts melt you regardless of armor and you can never catch her. Farm under tower with Alpha Strike, give up the lane, and look to use Highlander's reset chain in skirmishes elsewhere on the map instead of forcing a losing 1v1.","carry":"If you get ahead, you carry by abusing Highlander resets: every kill or assist refreshes its duration and slashes your other cooldowns, so a won fight lets you Alpha Strike into the next target untargetable, dodge their CC, and chain across the map. Group as the on-hit threat and force fights before Vayne completes her third item.","difficulty":"It's a 7/10 because Vayne counters your two defining weaknesses — she kites your short range with tumble and hard-disengages your only all-in with Condemn, and her percent-HP true damage ignores the tankiness you'd normally lean on, so even after you win the mid-game she out-scales you back."},"focus":{"text":"Condemn (E) — it knocks you back and stuns you against a wall, hard-cancelling your all-in; bait it or bat minimum never commit with your back to terrain, because a wall-stun ends the fight before Wuju Style and Highlander can do work.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike early","d":"Use Q to last-hit from outside her auto range instead of walking up for melee CS; it keeps you safe from free Silver Bolts stacks and resets your attack timer so you concede nothing in lane."},{"t":"All-in only after 6 with items","d":"Wait for Highlander plus your first on-hit item before committing — slow immunity beats her kite, Alpha Strike dodges Condemn, and Kraken/BORK gives you the DPS to actually kill her squishy frame."},{"t":"Bait Condemn before you dive","d":"Force or eat her E on the minion wave first; with it on cooldown she has no disengage and your Alpha Strike all-in connects cleanly."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't commit with your back to a wall","d":"Condemn into terrain stuns you and cancels everything; always position so a knockback sends you toward open ground, not into a wall-stun."},{"t":"Don't let her free-farm to three items","d":"Once Silver Bolts and two completed items come online her percent-HP true damage out-scales your build — pressure and close before that, don't play for a late 1v1."},{"t":"Don't chase her tumbles without Highlander","d":"Before level 6 you can't stick to her; chasing tumbles just feeds free autos and eats Condemn, so only pursue when Highlander's speed and slow immunity are up."}],"tradeGood":"Bait Condemn on the wave, wait out her tumble, then Alpha Strike in with Wuju Style true damage and Highlander chasing to lock her squishy frame into a one-sided all-in.","tradeBad":"Walking up to melee a minion under her tumble auto, eating free Silver Bolts stacks for a single CS with no way to trade back.","ahead":"Press a lead by abusing Highlander's reset economy: every kill or assist refreshes its duration and drops your other cooldowns, so chain Alpha Strikes from target to target, dodging CC and resetting your attack timer. Deny her item curve by repeat-crashing the wave and recalling on your spikes, and force objective fights in the 6-to-one-item window before her Silver Bolts come online. Group as the on-hit carry and end the game before she reaches her three-item scaling.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Vayne - Track: Condemn (E) — it knocks you back and stuns you against a wall, hard-cancelling your all-in; bait it or bat minimum never commit with your back to terrain, because a wall-stun ends the fight before Wuju Style and Highlander can do work.. - Concede the early levels, farm safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, and survive to level 6 plus your first on-hit item (Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King) — then use Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity to close the gap and force an all-in before she gets two completed items.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Vayne kites you out of lane with tumble and condemn, but if you survive to Highlander and your first on-hit item you can run her down — until she reclaims the game at three items."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing early lane by farming with Alpha Strike, then spike on Highlander plus your first on-hit item to close the gap her kite normally protects. Your entire win condition is forcing the all-in inside the level-6-to-one-item window, before Vayne's percent-HP true damage out-scales you."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Vayne owns levels 1-5 (free range autos, tumble, no answer from you), the favor flips to Yi at 6 and first item (Highlander slow immunity + on-hit DPS), then swings back to Vayne hard at two-plus items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Take no auto-for-auto trade before 6 — you lose all of them. After 6, trade only when Condemn is down and her tumble is on cooldown: bait the E, then Alpha Strike in with Wuju Style up. Back off the instant she has Condemn and a wall behind you."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Freeze or slow-push just outside your tower early to deny her the open ground and free range autos she needs to kite. Crash the wave on your spike (6 / first item) to recall, then return on a wave that lets you all-in with Highlander available — avoid shoving into open mid-lane where she tumble-kites freely."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike makes you untargetable mid-blink, so timing it through her Condemn dodges the knockback and stun entirely — this is the single most important interaction in the lane. Highlander's slow immunity ignores her slow effects and its speed lets you stick through tumble; Meditate's channel-heal out-sustains her early poke. Her Silver Bolts deal TRUE damage, so armor does nothing — Wuju Style's true damage is your mirror to that."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the bonus attack speed and extended range that helps you stick on-hit through her kite (Conqueror is the alternative for raw dueling). Secondaries: Triumph and Legend: Alacrity or Bloodline in Precision; Second Wind and Overgrowth (or Bone Plating) in Resolve to blunt her lane poke since her damage is true/physical, not burst AP."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite to convert your level-6 all-in into a kill before she out-scales — the lane is a race and Ignite gives you the kill pressure to win it. Take Teleport instead only if you're being hard-zoned off the wave and need to stay even in farm/XP rather than fight."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Open Doran's Blade plus components into Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King as your first on-hit spike, then Wit's End for the magic resist and on-hit if she pairs with AP, or Terminus for the resists and shred in extended fights. Take Mercury's Treads if her team adds CC, otherwise Berserker's Greaves; Vayne herself is true/physical so armor is largely wasted against her."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Your only real all-in windows are: level 6 with Highlander up and Ignite ready, and after your first on-hit item — both contingent on Condemn being down or baited and her not having a wall to stun you into. Outside those, you cannot win the 1v1."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"A gank is your best path to a lead since you can't win lane alone — call your jungler for the level-6 dive when Condemn is down, and Highlander's speed lets you follow up. Conversely, you're extremely gankable pre-6 (no escape but Q, low HP), so ward her tumble path and respect that her Condemn can also set up the enemy jungler's combo on you."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi mistake here is chasing tumbles and forcing trades before level 6 — you eat free Silver Bolts stacks and a Condemn for nothing. The second is committing an all-in with a wall behind you, handing her a free Condemn wall-stun that cancels your entire combo."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're behind, fully concede the lane: farm under tower with Alpha Strike, never contest her, and rely on Highlander's reset chain to contribute to skirmishes around objectives rather than a 1v1 you cannot win. Build a defensive on-hit item early and play for cross-map value."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If you're ahead, close fast — repeat-crash to deny her item gold, force objective fights inside your spike window, and abuse Highlander resets to chain-kill across teamfights with untargetable Alpha Strikes. Every fight you take must happen before she completes her third item."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"TRICKY (46.3%) — Vayne kites and disengages your weaknesses and out-scales you late, but a disciplined Yi who survives to Highlander and his first on-hit item owns a real mid-game kill window; win in that window or lose the game."}]},"vladimir":{"tldr":"Vladimir pools your Alpha Strike and Ignite while out-sustaining you for ten levels, but if you survive to your on-hit spike and dodge his all-in CC, you out-DPS him before he goes unkillable.","winCon":"Concede the early lane to Vladimir's E poke and Q drain, farm with Alpha Strike, then hit your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) and force a Highlander-reset all-in before two items when his damage is still front-loadable. You win by killing him in the 4-item window — the moment he finishes Liandry's/Rylai's plus Zhonya's he flips the lane back.","enemyWin":"Vladimir wins by poking you to half with E charges and his empowered Q before you itemize, then Sanguine Pool to dodge your committed Alpha Strike and walk away while you have no escape up. Past three items his AoE drain and Zhonya's make him unkillable in the extended fight your snowball depends on.","diff":"TRICKY","tone":"#ff8b3d","diffRating":"7/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Vladimir","rating":"6/10","why":"Vladimir's longer E and Q range chip you while your auto-range and base damage are too low to threaten anything level 1."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Vladimir","rating":"6/10","why":"His Transfusion (Q) heal off-cooldown out-sustains your last-hit autos, and you have no Wuju true damage yet to punish."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Vladimir","rating":"7/10","why":"A charged E into Q burst can chunk a third of your HP, and you still lack the kill threat to trade it back."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Vladimir","rating":"6/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain stabilize you, but his Q drain and E poke still control the trade tempo."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity let you stick for a sudden burst before his Sanguine Pool comes back up to dodge it."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"Kraken/BORK on-hit plus Wuju true damage out-DPS his pre-Zhonya's HP, and Highlander resets let you commit through his Pool's downtime."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Vladimir","rating":"7/10","why":"Once Vladimir finishes Liandry's/Rylai's and Zhonya's his AoE drain and stasis reclaim the unkillable late game your reset-chain can't out-pace."}],"breakdown":{"early":"You lose levels 1-3 outright. Vladimir out-ranges you with E and heals every Transfusion off you, so any auto-trade you start, he wins back through sustain. Don't walk up for an extended trade — last-hit with autos, use Alpha Strike on the caster minions to push only when you want priority, and accept that you'll be down some CS and HP. The goal of this phase is simply to reach level 6 alive and not feed his snowball.","mid":"Levels 4-5 you get Wuju Style true damage and Meditate, which lets you take short, decisive trades instead of bleeding out — E on, two autos, back off before his Q heals it back. Level 6 is your first real window: Highlander gives the move/attack speed and slow immunity to stick onto him and burst before Sanguine Pool resets. But Vladimir also spikes hard at 6 with his ult amplifying his whole combo, so respect that his all-in burst is real too.","late":"At 2+ items you have a genuine kill window: Kraken/BORK on-hit plus Wuju true damage out-races his pre-Zhonya's health bar, and you can dodge his pool-timed CC with Alpha Strike. Push your lead HERE. Once he completes Liandry's/Rylai's and Zhonya's, he becomes the unkillable AoE-drain teamfighter and reclaims the game — your reset chain can't out-sustain three items of healing plus a stasis.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push that crashes into his tower around level 6-7 so you can dive or zone him off the wave during your Highlander window. Worst wave: a wave shoved fast under YOUR tower early, where his E poke chips you freely while you can't trade back. Crash timing: crash the big wave just before your first item completes so you have CS and recall timing to come back even or ahead for the all-in.","cooldowns":"Track Sanguine Pool (W) above all — it's ~26-28s early and it eats your entire committed Alpha Strike+Highlander burst. Only all-in when you've baited or seen it used.","trading":"Short trades only until you itemize: Wuju Style on, Q-reset onto him, one or two on-hit autos, disengage before his Transfusion heals the difference. Never sit in his E-Q poke range trading autos straight up — his sustain wins the war of attrition every time pre-6.","spikes":"Yours: level 6 Highlander, then first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK), then 2 items. His: level 6 ult amp, then Liandry's/Rylai's, and the unkillable spike at Zhonya's plus a third item.","feeding":"If you fall behind, Vladimir scales into a 1v9 AP threat your team can't kill while you're a useless under-itemized melee. Play for jungle 2v2s and side-lane farm, hard-shove and roam to a winnable lane instead of forcing his lane, and DON'T int Flash trying to all-in through his Pool.","carry":"If ahead, your snowball is brutal: itemize on-hit fast, use Highlander resets to chain kills across the map, and end before Vladimir reaches his three-item unkillable timer. Every minute the game goes long favors him, so close it.","difficulty":"It's 7/10 because Vladimir attacks all three of your weaknesses at once — ranged poke that beats you pre-scale, Sanguine Pool that dodges your only commit tool, and a late game that out-scales even your hyper-carry curve. You have real windows, but they're narrow and bracketed by phases where he's simply better."},"focus":{"text":"Sanguine Pool (W) — it makes Vladimir untargetable, dodging your fully-committed Alpha Strike, Ignite, and Highlander burst; never all-in until it's on cooldown.","letters":["W"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Bait the Pool first","d":"Force or watch Vladimir burn Sanguine Pool (W) before you commit Alpha Strike and Highlander — his untargetable window negates your entire burst if you go in blind."},{"t":"All-in at your item spike","d":"Wait for your first on-hit item plus level 6, then look for the 2-item window where Wuju true damage and Kraken/BORK out-DPS his pre-Zhonya's HP bar."},{"t":"Short trade with Wuju up","d":"Trade only in quick bursts — E active on, Q-reset in, one or two autos, out — so you punish before his Transfusion heals the exchange back."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't poke-war pre-6","d":"Never sit trading autos in his E-Q range early; his drain sustain out-values every straight auto exchange and you just feed his snowball."},{"t":"Don't commit into Pool","d":"Don't blow Alpha Strike, Ignite, and Highlander while Sanguine Pool is up — he pools the damage and walks away with your cooldowns gone."},{"t":"Don't let it go late","d":"Don't slow-play a lead; past his three-item unkillable timer Vladimir's AoE drain and Zhonya's flip the game no matter how fed you were."}],"tradeGood":"After he's used Sanguine Pool, pop Wuju Style and Q-reset onto him for an on-hit burst, then disengage before his Transfusion ticks the heal back.","tradeBad":"A straight auto-trade in his E-Q poke range before level 6, where his drain sustain out-heals everything you deal.","ahead":"Snowball fast and snowball wide: rush your on-hit core, then use Highlander's kill-refresh to chain Alpha Strike resets across mid and bot before Vladimir comes online. Zone him off CS and XP in lane so his scaling never starts, and apply anti-heal (Executioner's/anti-heal item) into his sustain. Above all, close the game before his three-item unkillable timer — a fed Yi who lets Vlad reach 4 items has thrown the lead.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Vladimir - Track: Sanguine Pool (W) — it makes Vladimir untargetable, dodging your fully-committed Alpha Strike, Ignite, and Highlander burst; never all-in until it's on cooldown.. - Concede the early lane to Vladimir's E poke and Q drain, farm with Alpha Strike, then hit your first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) and force a Highlander-reset all-in before two items when his damage is still front-loadable. You win by killing him in the 4-item window — the moment he finishes Liandry's/Rylai's plus Zhonya's he flips the lane back.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Vladimir pools your Alpha Strike and Ignite while out-sustaining you for ten levels, but if you survive to your on-hit spike and dodge his all-in CC, you out-DPS him before he goes unkillable."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing early lane against Vladimir's poke and drain, then convert your level-6-plus-first-item window into kills using Highlander resets and on-hit DPS. You must win the game in the 2-item bracket — before Vladimir completes Liandry's/Rylai's and Zhonya's and becomes unkillable."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Vladimir owns 1-5 (poke + sustain), the lane swings to Yi at 6 and first item through 2 items (on-hit + Wuju true damage out-DPS), then flips back to Vladimir at 3+ items (unkillable AoE drain)."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only in short bursts with Wuju Style active and ideally after his Sanguine Pool is down; back off the instant his Transfusion is healing the trade back, and never enter an extended exchange in his E-Q range pre-6."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Don't fight for the push early — match his shove and farm safe; once you have items, slow-push to build a crashing wave for your level-6/2-item dive while denying him the freeze-poke setup under his tower."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike makes you untargetable mid-blink, so you can dodge his ult-empowered combo timing with it, but Sanguine Pool does the same FOR him — making him untargetable to dodge your committed Alpha Strike, Ignite, and autos; the lane is a contest of who burns their untargetability first."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (faster on-hit ramp into his squishy AP body) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve Second Wind + Overgrowth to blunt his E-Q poke, or Sorcery Absolute Focus + Gathering Storm if you trust your safety and want scaling."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite is standard for the kill pressure and to cut his drain healing in your level-6/item all-in; take Teleport instead only if you expect to get poked out repeatedly and need to stabilize CS and XP."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first for the on-hit DPS spike, into Wit's End/Terminus for the magic resist and on-hit vs his AP, then Mercury's Treads; add an anti-heal source (Executioner's components / Mortal Reminder isn't AP-relevant, so itemize Wit's End MR plus early Oblivion-style grievous if available) and consider an early Null-Magic Mantle vs his burst."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Your only true all-in windows are level 6 with Highlander up AND Sanguine Pool down, and the 2-item bracket where Kraken/BORK + Wuju true damage out-races his health bar — outside those, you don't have the burst to beat his pool and sustain."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're highly gankable pre-6 with only Alpha Strike to escape, so a roaming enemy jungler can snowball Vlad off your weak early; conversely your own jungler tipping a 2v2 in your favor gives you the kill that starts your reset-chain — coordinate a dive right as your first item completes."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi error here is committing the full Alpha Strike-Ignite-Highlander combo while Sanguine Pool is up, then dying with everything on cooldown — and the second is slow-playing a lead until Vladimir reaches his unkillable three-item timer."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If you're losing, stop forcing his lane: hard-shove, roam to winnable lanes, farm side waves to stay item-relevant, and never Flash-in through his Pool to chase a kill you can't secure — play for a late teamfight where your team peels CC for you."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If ahead, rush on-hit, use Highlander kill-refreshes to chain Alpha Strike resets across the map, zone Vlad off farm and XP so his scaling never starts, and end the game before his three-item unkillable spike."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"TRICKY (46.41% WR) — Vladimir edges the lane with poke, sustain, and his Pool, but Yi owns level 6 and the 2-item window; win it there or lose it to his scaling."}]},"volibear":{"tldr":"A weak, gankable early into Voli's bite-sustain flips once Yi itemizes — Alpha Strike dodges his E stun and on-hit shreds the tank, but his own dive scaling keeps it a true coinflip.","winCon":"Survive Voli's level 1-6 W-bite trades by farming with Alpha Strike, then hit your first on-hit item (Kraken or BORK) and use Q to go untargetable through his E stun so you out-DPS the tank in any extended fight and reset Highlander off the kill.","enemyWin":"Volibear lands the E (Hand of the God) stun the instant your Alpha Strike lands and you're stuck on the ground, then stacks W bites that heal off your missing HP and Q-dashes to chase, killing you before your on-hit ramps; if he gets one early lead his max-HP healing snowballs out of your reach.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Volibear","rating":"6/10","why":"Voli's W (Frenzied Maul) bite-and-recast heals off your missing HP, out-sustaining your weak base autos before Wuju Style exists."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Volibear","rating":"6/10","why":"His second W bite plus a basic chunks you while your Q only resets your attack timer — no trade pattern beats his sustain yet."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Volibear","rating":"6/10","why":"Voli's W double-bite heal and incoming Q dash punish any greedy CS step; you should farm with Alpha Strike from range, not auto-trade."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain come online, so short E-into-AA trades start to even out his W heal."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Your Highlander R answers his level-6 E-stun gank-and-dive with slow immunity, but his R tower-disable + shield matches it — neither owns the fight."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken/BORK on-hit plus Q going untargetable through his E stun means you out-DPS the tank in an extended brawl."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"At 2+ items your on-hit (Wit's End MR shred / Terminus) melts his stacked health faster than W can heal, and Highlander resets chain his death into a fight win."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Volibear. His W (Frenzied Maul) bites you and the recast heals proportionally to your missing HP, so every auto-trade you start, his bite-and-heal wins — and your only level-1 tools are short autos and an Alpha Strike that resets your attack timer but does little base damage. Concede the opener, hold near your wave, and farm with Q from max range so you never eat the W double-bite.","mid":"Levels 4-5 your Wuju Style true damage and Meditate channel-heal come online and the lane stabilizes into short trades. Level 6 is the pivotal beat: his E (Hand of the God) stun plus Q dash makes him a real gank-dive threat, but Highlander gives you move/attack speed and slow immunity to dodge or punish that exact play. Neither champ runs the other off the lane here — it's a skill stage about who respects the E.","late":"At 2+ items Master Yi flips to favoured. Kraken Slayer/BORK/Wit's End on-hit shreds even a stacked-health Volibear faster than W can heal, Alpha Strike's untargetable frames eat his E stun and reset on champ hits, and a single kill refreshes Highlander to chain through the next fight. Wit's End's MR and on-hit also answer his bruiser-tank brawl directly.","wave":"Best wave: a slow-push you can freeze just outside his tower once you out-scale, denying his W sustain free farm and setting a Q-reset all-in. Worst wave: a fast-shoving wave pre-6 that pins you under tower where his Q-dash + E stun + jungler collapse with no escape but Q. Crash timing: crash into his tower right before your first on-hit item back so you reset on-item and deny him the bounce.","cooldowns":"Track his E (Hand of the God) — it's the long-cooldown point-and-click stun that catches you the instant Alpha Strike lands and you're grounded. If E is down, your on-hit DPS wins; if it's up, never commit a Q until you've baited it.","trading":"Pre-6 you lose the auto-trade to W's bite-heal, so only trade with a Wuju-empowered burst when his W is on cooldown. Post-item you reverse it: Q in untargetable to dodge E, E on for true damage, and grind the on-hit DPS he can't kite or heal through.","spikes":"Volibear spikes at level 6 (E stun + R tower-disable dive) and off any early kill that feeds his max-HP healing. Master Yi spikes at level 6 (Highlander) and hard at first on-hit item, then dominates at 2+ items.","feeding":"If Yi falls behind, Voli's max-HP-based W healing and tankiness mean your un-itemized on-hit can't kill him — he becomes an unkillable diver who one-shots your backline. Farm side waves with Q, take Meditate-sustained safe CS, and scale; do not contest his health bar without items.","carry":"Ahead, Yi is one of the streakiest 1v9 curves in the game: Highlander resets let you chain kills across the map, Alpha Strike dodges the enemy's key CC mid-fight, and on-hit shreds tanks like Voli that the rest of your team can't. Press side lanes and force fights once you have item lead.","difficulty":"It rates 5/10 because the lane is genuinely even (51.67% WR): you're badly behind for six levels and must respect the E stun, but your scaling is so steep that surviving to two items flips it — the difficulty is patience and dodging one ability, not a fundamentally losing matchup."},"focus":{"text":"Volibear's E, Hand of the God — the point-and-click stun that lands the moment your Alpha Strike ends and you're grounded, setting up his W-bite + Q-dash kill. Never commit a Q until it's baited or down.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike","d":"Use Q from max range to last-hit and stay out of W-bite range pre-6; it resets your attack timer and keeps you healthy while you wait to scale."},{"t":"Bait the E stun first","d":"Before any all-in, force or wait out his E (Hand of the God); once it's on cooldown, Q in untargetable and your on-hit DPS out-trades the tank cleanly."},{"t":"Buy on-hit early","d":"Rush Kraken Slayer or BORK and add Wit's End vs his bruiser damage — percent/true-style on-hit is the only thing that kills a health-stacking, self-healing Volibear."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't auto-trade pre-6","d":"His W (Frenzied Maul) bite-and-recast heals off your missing HP and out-sustains your weak early autos every time — concede the opener, don't brawl into it."},{"t":"Don't Q into an up E","d":"If you blow Alpha Strike while his Hand of the God is available, you land grounded into a guaranteed stun, W bites, and a Q-dash chase that kills you."},{"t":"Don't fight him even when behind","d":"Without items his max-HP-scaling W heal makes him effectively unkillable; chasing his health bar just feeds the dive — split-farm and scale instead."}],"tradeGood":"Post-item, Q in untargetable to dodge his E stun, flick on Wuju Style for true damage, and grind on-hit DPS while Meditate eats his W bite — a trade his tank stats and heal can't answer.","tradeBad":"A level 1-3 stand-and-auto trade into his W double-bite, where his missing-HP heal wins the exchange before Wuju Style or your on-hit items exist.","ahead":"Once you have an item and kill lead, freeze just outside his tower to starve his W-sustain farm, then all-in when his E is down — Q untargetable, E for true damage, and reset Highlander off the kill. Use the refreshed R to roam and shred objectives or his backline, where your on-hit out-carries any tank he can build into. Keep snowballing through fights rather than dueling him 1v1 at full HP, since his healing closes even windows.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Volibear - Track: Volibear's E, Hand of the God — the point-and-click stun that lands the moment your Alpha Strike ends and you're grounded, setting up his W-bite + Q-dash kill. Never commit a Q until it's baited or down.. - Survive Voli's level 1-6 W-bite trades by farming with Alpha Strike, then hit your first on-hit item (Kraken or BORK) and use Q to go untargetable through his E stun so you out-DPS the tank in any extended fight and reset Highlander off the kill.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A weak, gankable early into Voli's bite-sustain flips once Yi itemizes — Alpha Strike dodges his E stun and on-hit shreds the tank, but his own dive scaling keeps it a true coinflip."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing level 1-6 against Voli's W-bite sustain by farming with Alpha Strike, then out-scale him at first on-hit item where Q dodges his E stun and on-hit shreds his health bar. The whole lane is a patience check: reach two items healthy and you flip from prey to predator."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Volibear owns 1-3 (W heal), it goes even at 4-6 (Wuju/Meditate/Highlander vs E-stun dive), and Master Yi takes over from first item onward, dominating at 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Pre-6: only trade with a Wuju-empowered burst when his W is on cooldown, otherwise farm from Q range. Post-item: bait E, then Q-in and grind on-hit; always disengage with Meditate if his jungler shows."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Farm safe and let waves come to you while weak; once itemized, slow-push and freeze just outside his tower to deny his W-sustain CS and set up an E-down all-in. Avoid shoving into a pin pre-6."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable frames dodge his E (Hand of the God) stun and W bite if timed on his cast; Highlander's slow immunity ignores his W slow; Wit's End's MR and on-hit answer his bruiser-tank brawl; Meditate out-sustains a single W bite but not his stacked double-bite early."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (or Conqueror vs his sustain brawl) — Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve with Conditioning/Overgrowth or Second Wind into his bite poke, plus attack-speed/adaptive/HP shards."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to punish his W heal in the all-in once you out-scale; take Flash + Teleport instead if you want to guarantee scaling safely through the weak early and answer his roam/dive."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first for on-hit, then Wit's End for MR and on-hit vs his bruiser damage, Terminus/BORK to shred his stacked health; Plated Steelcaps vs his AD autos, defensive third item into his dive."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Only all-in pre-6 if his W is down and you've already chunked him; the real window opens at first on-hit item with his E (Hand of the God) on cooldown and Highlander up to chase and reset."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"This lane is gank-decided — his E stun is a perfect setup for a jungler, and you have only Q to escape, so ward early and respect ganks while weak; once you have Highlander, your slow immunity and Q let you survive collapses he'd otherwise convert into a fed dive."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players try to trade or all-in too early and lose to W's missing-HP heal, then int into his level-6 E-dive; the fix is to accept a passive, scaling lane and not contest his health bar before two items."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Side-farm with Alpha Strike, take only Meditate-sustained safe CS, give up the lane state, and scale — never chase a self-healing tanky Voli without items, and look to flank fights with Q/Highlander resets rather than lane him."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Press the item lead: freeze to starve his sustain, all-in on E-down, then use Highlander resets to chain kills and roam — your on-hit carries objectives and shreds the tanks his team relies on."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"EVEN (51.67%): a six-level survival check that flips hard the moment Master Yi itemizes — dodge the E, out-scale the bite, and the tank becomes your favorite snack."}]},"warwick":{"tldr":"A pure scaling race where I'm a weak, suppress-bait early laner who flips to a 1v9 the second my on-hit items come online — survive Warwick's drain-fight prime and the lane is mine.","winCon":"Concede the early levels, farm safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, and respect his Infinite Duress until I hit Kraken/BORK — then out-DPS his drain in any extended fight and use Highlander resets to snowball off him. The lane is decided by whether I reach my first on-hit item with even CS, not by trading.","enemyWin":"Warwick wins by abusing levels 1-6 when his Q drain-heal and W move speed let him chase me off the wave and his anti-heal-proof sustain out-grinds my Meditate, then landing point-and-click R to suppress-lock me through Alpha Strike for a free kill (often with his jungler). If he gets me 2+ levels or kills down before my items, his lead holds because I never get to scale.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Warwick","rating":"6/10","why":"His base damage plus Eternal Hunger passive heal beats my low level-1 output, and I have no Wuju true damage or Meditate yet to contest an auto-war."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Warwick","rating":"6/10","why":"With Q Jaws of the Beast leap-heal and W Blood Hunt move speed he can stick to me, while my only escape is Alpha Strike on a long cooldown."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Warwick","rating":"5/10","why":"He out-sustains my short trades through his passive and Q heal; I farm with Alpha Strike resets instead of fighting and just survive the level-3 window."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain come online so I can answer short trades, but Primal Howl's fear still interrupts my Meditate channel — it's a cooldown-trade dance."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Warwick","rating":"6/10","why":"His level-6 Infinite Duress suppress locks me out of Alpha Strike entirely and is a guaranteed kill setup with jungle, while my Highlander only helps me dodge, not duel him."},{"label":"First item","side":"Skill","rating":"6/10","why":"My Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King on-hit spike starts beating his Q drain in a sustained fight, but he's still a tanky bruiser who can survive to R me."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At 2+ on-hit items my DPS out-paces his lifesteal heal, Alpha Strike dodges his R animation if timed, and Highlander resets let me chain-kill through him and his team."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Warwick and I play to not die. His Eternal Hunger passive heals every auto (harder when I'm low) and Q Jaws of the Beast is a leap that heals him, so any extended auto-war I lose and any chase he wins with W Blood Hunt move speed. I last-hit with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos from max range, never greed a caster minion under his nose, and treat every river-side bush as a gank-plus-R setup. My only escape is Q, so I keep it off cooldown for disengage, not poke.","mid":"Levels 4-6 I stabilize as Wuju Style's bonus true damage and Meditate sustain let me take short, defined trades and heal back his chip — but Primal Howl can fear-interrupt my Meditate, so I only channel when his E is down. Level 6 is his spike, not mine: Infinite Duress is a point-and-click suppress that ignores my Alpha Strike escape and is a free kill if his jungler is nearby. My Highlander at 6 is for dodging ganks and refreshing cooldowns, not for winning a straight duel yet.","late":"Once I have Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King into a second on-hit item (Wit's End vs his AP, Terminus, or Guinsoo), I flip the matchup. My on-hit DPS out-paces his lifesteal heal, Alpha Strike becomes untargetable mid-fight to dodge his R cast, and every kill resets Highlander so I chase the whole team. He stays relevant only as a tanky frontline R-bot — I make sure I'm not the one he R's.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push I can freeze just outside my turret, denying his Q-leap all-in and forcing him to walk into my jungler. Worst wave: a shoved wave near his turret where W Blood Hunt move speed plus a gank pins me with no Flash. Crash timing: crash on the back of your item spike (just before recall) so you reset on full health and return to a fresh frozen wave.","cooldowns":"Track R Infinite Duress above all — it's his only point-and-click answer to Alpha Strike and the whole reason he can kill me; also count Primal Howl (E) since its fear is what interrupts Meditate.","trading":"He wants long sustained trades where his passive + Q heal grind me down; I want nothing or a short Wuju-true-damage burst then walk. Pre-6 I auto only to deny, not to win; post-items I commit only when his R is on cooldown.","spikes":"Warwick spikes at level 6 (Infinite Duress) and again on Bloodletter's Curse / sustain items; I spike at first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) and become favoured-to-dominant at 2+ items.","feeding":"If I fall behind, his R plus W means I'm permanently catchable and I farm-starve under turret while he roams. The lane never recovers on its own — I have to scale off jungle camps and side waves instead of the lane, because a fed Warwick out-sustains my whole early kit.","carry":"If I'm ahead I take over the map: Highlander's reset-on-kill plus my on-hit DPS lets me dive backlines and chain-kill, and a dead Warwick removes the only enemy who could lock me down. I split-push to force him to me, then 1v1 him once I out-DPS his heal.","difficulty":"It's a true 5/10 EVEN: not mechanically hard, but a knife-edge scaling race. Warwick owns the first six levels and one R can end it, yet if I farm cleanly to two items I'm the stronger champion — execution is all about lane survival and R-tracking, not combos."},"focus":{"text":"R Infinite Duress — his point-and-click suppress leap. It ignores Alpha Strike (my only escape), locks me in place, and is a guaranteed kill if his jungler collapses. Never fight near a wall or in fog when his R is up, and save Flash to break the suppress window.","letters":["R"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike, don't trade","d":"Use Q to last-hit from range and reset its cooldown off minions; concede the early auto-war because his passive + Q heal beats my pre-item output every time."},{"t":"Scale to your on-hit spike","d":"Get to Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King with even CS — that's the exact moment the lane flips, so prioritize survival and farm over kills before then."},{"t":"Track and bait his R","d":"Hold Flash for Infinite Duress and only commit when his R is on cooldown; once itemized, time Alpha Strike's untargetable window to dodge his R cast."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't fight in extended trades early","d":"Long auto-wars feed his Eternal Hunger and Q drain-heal; he out-sustains my Meditate before I have Wuju true damage and items, so never stand and brawl pre-6."},{"t":"Don't Meditate into his Primal Howl","d":"His E fear interrupts my channel and wastes the heal — only Meditate when his Howl is down, or you hand him a free reset on the trade."},{"t":"Don't get caught with R and no Flash","d":"Once your Q is on cooldown and his R is up, you have zero escape from the suppress-lock; never push into his half of the lane or facecheck bushes in that state."}],"tradeGood":"Post-item, a short burst with Wuju Style true damage and an Alpha Strike reset while his R and Primal Howl are both on cooldown, then disengage before his passive heal stacks.","tradeBad":"A long, stand-still auto-war at levels 1-5 where his Eternal Hunger passive and Q Jaws of the Beast heal out-grind my chip and set up his R.","ahead":"If I get ahead I weaponize Highlander — every kill refreshes its duration and slashes my cooldowns, so I chain-fight across the map and dive his carries. I keep him from ever isolating me, split-push to drag him to a sidelane, and only 1v1 once my on-hit DPS clearly out-paces his lifesteal heal. A dead Warwick means the one champion who could suppress-lock me is gone, and I'm free to take over every fight.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Warwick - Track: R Infinite Duress — his point-and-click suppress leap. It ignores Alpha Strike (my only escape), locks me in place, and is a guaranteed kill if his jungler collapses. Never fight near a wall or in fog when his R is up, and save Flash to break the suppress window.. - Concede the early levels, farm safely with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos, and respect his Infinite Duress until I hit Kraken/BORK — then out-DPS his drain in any extended fight and use Highlander resets to snowball off him. The lane is decided by whether I reach my first on-hit item with even CS, not by trading.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A pure scaling race where I'm a weak, suppress-bait early laner who flips to a 1v9 the second my on-hit items come online — survive Warwick's drain-fight prime and the lane is mine."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing early lane by farming with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos while respecting Infinite Duress, then reach my first on-hit item with even CS. From Kraken/BORK onward my DPS out-paces his drain-heal and Highlander resets let me snowball through him and the map."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Warwick owns 1-3 (his sustain + chase), it goes even at 4-5 (Wuju true damage + Meditate), he spikes at 6 (R suppress), I draw at first item, and I take over hard at 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Pre-6: don't trade, only deny CS from max range. Levels 4-6: short Wuju bursts only when his Primal Howl is down. Post-items: commit fully only when his R is on cooldown, never while it's up and you lack Flash."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Freeze just outside your turret to deny his Q-leap all-in and force jungle help to you; avoid shoving into his turret where W Blood Hunt move speed plus a gank pins you. Crash on your item-spike recall to reset full and reform the freeze."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"His R Infinite Duress is point-and-click and bypasses Alpha Strike's untargetability if it's already cast, but once I'm in Q I'm immune to new targeting — so I dodge his R by blinking as he winds up. His Primal Howl fear interrupts my Meditate channel; his Q and passive heal counter my poke. My Wuju true damage ignores no armor he stacks because he builds bruiser, so it's pure DPS racing."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (uptime for the extended-fight scaling race) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, and Last Stand or Coup de Grace; secondary Resolve with Conditioning/Overgrowth or Second Wind to survive his lane chip. If he goes AP/on-hit Bloodletter, lean Bone Plating; against his sustain, Coup helps execute through his heal."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ghost is standard for the scaling skirmisher, but in THIS lane Flash + Ignite or Flash + Exhaust is strong — Ignite's Grievous Wounds chops his entire heal-based kit and helps secure early kills; take Teleport only if you want to guarantee scaling and answer his all-ins by backing safe."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first (BORK's % current-HP and heal-cut shine vs his bulk + sustain), then Wit's End if he's AP / Terminus or Guinsoo's for the on-hit stack. Berserker's Greaves; itemize Executioner's/Mortal Reminder component early to slash his drain-heal. Add a defensive on-hit (Wit's End MR) vs his magic damage build."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Pre-6 I have no all-in — I only ever disengage. My real all-in window opens at first on-hit item when his R is on cooldown, and becomes a guaranteed win at 2+ items where Alpha Strike dodges his cast and Highlander resets carry the fight."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"This lane is gank-defined: Warwick + jungler = a dead Yi because R guarantees the lockdown, so I ward river and play for my own jungler's counter-gank. My weak early means I want my jungler to leash and check on me twice before items; post-scaling I become the one who dives with the jungle."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic Yi mistake here is trying to 'win lane' — auto-warring early feeds his sustain and walks into R range. The other is Meditating reactively into his Primal Howl fear and wasting the heal. Play to scale, not to fight."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If behind, abandon the lane as a fighting space: farm side waves and jungle camps from max range with Alpha Strike, never face-check, and keep Flash for his R. Group only when you have two items — your comeback is item timers, not duels."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If ahead, use Highlander's kill-resets to chain fights and dive backlines, split-push to force Warwick to a sidelane, and 1v1 him only once your on-hit DPS clearly beats his heal. Remove him from fights first since he's the only enemy who can lock you."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A true EVEN (50.31%) scaling race: Warwick owns the first six levels and one R can decide it, but reach two on-hit items with even farm and Master Yi is the stronger, lane-flipping hyper-carry."}]},"wukong":{"tldr":"Wukong out-trades and all-ins me through every early level with Q armor-shred, dash and clone, but if I survive to my on-hit items and hit 6 I flip the extended fight — a real TRICKY lane that's mine after First item.","winCon":"Concede levels 1-5, farm safely with Alpha Strike and short Wuju autos, and never get caught by his E-Q armor-shred all-in. Once Kraken or BORK is online I out-DPS his bruiser stats in any extended fight — Highlander resets let me chain through his clone and snowball the map.","enemyWin":"Wukong wins by abusing levels 1-6: his Q shreds my armor, E gives him the gap-close I lack, and his R knockup is point-and-click lockdown that catches me the instant Alpha Strike ends. If he forces my Flash early or zones me off farm before my first item, my whole curve is delayed and he can repeat-kill.","diff":"TRICKY","tone":"#ff8b3d","diffRating":"6/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Wukong","rating":"7/10","why":"His level-1 base damage and Q armor-shred beat my short-range autos before I have Wuju Style or any escape but Q."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Wukong","rating":"7/10","why":"At 2 points he can E in and threaten an all-in while I still have no W sustain or true damage to answer."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Wukong","rating":"6/10","why":"He spikes hard at 3 — full Q-E combo plus passive armor-stacking out-trades me, and I'm still farming with Alpha Strike rather than fighting."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Wukong","rating":"6/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain come online for me, but his clone and E mobility still let him pick the trades and disengage."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander gives me slow-immunity and the move/attack speed to chase him past his E, and dodging his R knockup with Alpha Strike's untargetable window swings the 1v1."},{"label":"First item","side":"Skill","rating":"6/10","why":"My Kraken/BORK on-hit spike meets his bruiser item timing — whoever lands their key cooldown (his R knockup vs my Alpha Strike dodge) takes the fight."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"At 2+ items my on-hit DPS plus Highlander resets out-damage his armor stack, and I cleave the clone instantly instead of being baited by it."}],"breakdown":{"early":"This is Wukong's lane through level 3. His Q shreds my armor and his level-1 base damage simply beats my short-range autos, and unlike me he has E to close gaps and a clone to bait my Alpha Strike. I have no escape but Q and no Wuju true damage yet, so I farm passively with Alpha Strike pulses and concede every all-in — taking even a fair trade here loses because his armor-shred makes my autos chunk for nothing.","mid":"Levels 4-5 I stabilize as Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain let me take short, controlled trades, but he still owns the tempo with E mobility and the clone. Level 6 is my first real claim: Highlander's slow-immunity and bonus move/attack speed let me run him down through his E, and Alpha Strike's untargetable window can dodge his R knockup outright if I time it as he casts.","late":"At 2+ items I flip to favoured. My on-hit stack out-DPSes his armor-and-HP bruiser build, and every kill or assist refreshes Highlander and shaves my cooldowns so I chain through fights. His clone stops working on me because I have the DPS to delete the real Wukong before his R combo matters — I just have to commit Alpha Strike onto the right target.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push into him from level 6+ so I have a big wave to fight on once Highlander and my item are up. Worst wave: a wave shoved at MY tower levels 1-3, which lets him dive with E and Q armor-shred while I have no escape. Crash timing: crash the wave just before my first item completes so I can recall, buy Kraken/BORK, and come back on even minions with my spike online.","cooldowns":"Track his R (Cyclone) above all, then his E dash — if both are down he cannot all-in or escape, and that's my only safe window to commit Alpha Strike and Wuju autos.","trading":"He wants short E-Q-auto bursts that shred my armor and disengage before I can stack on-hits; I want long, sustained fights where Wuju true damage and Meditate let my DPS win the war of attrition. Don't trade on his terms early — wait until I can hold him in melee long enough for on-hit to compound.","spikes":"His spikes are level 3 (full combo + armor stacking) and his first bruiser item; mine are level 6 (Highlander) and especially my first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King), after which the lane inverts.","feeding":"If I die early he snowballs his bruiser stats and just out-stats me through my item timings, delaying the one window where I overtake him — and a fed Wukong R can chain-CC me out of my own all-in. Falling behind here is brutal because my whole identity is hitting a spike on time.","carry":"If I'm ahead I rush my second on-hit item, use Highlander resets to chain kills in skirmishes, and roam with my move speed — a fed Master Yi out of this lane is a 1v9 that his single R can't lock down forever.","difficulty":"It's a 6/10 because his entire early kit (armor-shred Q, gap-close E, knockup R, clone bait) is built to punish exactly my weaknesses — no early escape, armor-reliant durability, and a fight pattern that needs time to ramp. I lose the first five levels and only win if I farm cleanly to my spike."},"focus":{"text":"His R, Cyclone — the spinning knockup is point-and-click lockdown that catches me the instant my Alpha Strike untargetable window ends, so I must bait or dodge it before I commit. Watch his E too, since R usually follows the dash in.","letters":["R","E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm to your item spike","d":"Use Alpha Strike to last-hit safely and concede levels 1-5; your whole game is reaching Kraken/BORK with even CS, not winning early trades you can't win."},{"t":"Time Alpha Strike on his R","d":"Save Q for the moment he casts Cyclone — the untargetable blink dodges the knockup and resets your attack timer, turning his all-in into your kill window."},{"t":"Cleave the real Wukong, not the clone","d":"His W decoy bursts and runs; once you have on-hit DPS, identify and commit Alpha Strike onto the true target so you don't waste your damage on the dummy."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't trade into his Q","d":"His armor-shred makes your early autos hit for almost nothing while his combo chunks you — never take a short trade levels 1-3 where his Q is up."},{"t":"Don't burn Flash to his early all-in","d":"If he forces Flash with E-Q before 6 you lose your only second escape, and he'll repeat-dive you off your spike; just give the wave instead."},{"t":"Don't channel Meditate in his face","d":"Standing still to heal lets him reposition for a clean R knockup and continue the combo — only Meditate after you've broken line of sight or he's on cooldown."}],"tradeGood":"A post-6 extended fight where I dodge his Cyclone with Alpha Strike, then hold him in melee with Wuju true damage and Highlander speed until on-hit out-DPSes his armor.","tradeBad":"A level 1-3 short trade into his up Q, where armor-shred neuters my autos and his E-into-R can convert the poke straight into a kill.","ahead":"Press a lead by rushing my second on-hit item and forcing extended fights the instant his R is on cooldown — that's the window his clone and armor can't save him. Use Highlander's kill-refresh to chain skirmishes and roam mid/bot with my move speed, since a fed Master Yi snowballs the whole map faster than a bruiser Wukong can. Deny his comeback by tracking his recalls and shoving him off his item timings.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Wukong - Track: His R, Cyclone — the spinning knockup is point-and-click lockdown that catches me the instant my Alpha Strike untargetable window ends, so I must bait or dodge it before I commit. Watch his E too, since R usually follows the dash in.. - Concede levels 1-5, farm safely with Alpha Strike and short Wuju autos, and never get caught by his E-Q armor-shred all-in. Once Kraken or BORK is online I out-DPS his bruiser stats in any extended fight — Highlander resets let me chain through his clone and snowball the map.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Wukong out-trades and all-ins me through every early level with Q armor-shred, dash and clone, but if I survive to my on-hit items and hit 6 I flip the extended fight — a real TRICKY lane that's mine after First item."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive a losing early lane by farming with Alpha Strike and conceding all-ins, then hit my Kraken/BORK on-hit spike to invert the fight. From First item onward I out-DPS his bruiser stats and use Highlander resets to chain kills through his clone."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Wukong owns 1-5 (armor-shred Q, E gap-close, R lockdown); I claim 6 with Highlander and take firm control at First item and 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Back off whenever his Q or R is up early; only trade once I have Wuju Style online and a way to hold him in melee, and fully commit only after First item or when his R is down."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave neutral or slightly toward me early so he can't dive me under tower with E; from 6+ slow-push to build a fight wave, and crash before recalling to buy my on-hit spike on even CS."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable blink dodges his R Cyclone knockup and resets my attack timer; his W clone baits my Q, so I must commit on the real target; his Q armor-shred is answered by Wuju Style's true damage, which ignores the armor entirely."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo primary (he's a durable bruiser, so I want the ramping attack speed for extended on-hit fights) with Triumph and Legend: Alacrity; secondary Resolve with Conditioning/Overgrowth or Second Wind into his early poke. Build armor-leaning runes/shards since his pre-mit damage is AD."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite if I want to contest kills at 6 and answer his sustain, or Flash plus Teleport to stay even in CS through the weak early and recall safely onto my spike — TP is the safer pick in this TRICKY lane."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Open Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit spike, then Wit's End or Terminus to shred his resists and pad against his AD; Plated Steelcaps into his autos and Q, and consider Wit's End's MR is wasted here so favor the AD-defensive boots. He stacks armor, so Terminus/BORK %-current-HP and true-damage on-hit matter most."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Only all-in once I have Highlander up AND his R is on cooldown, ideally after First item — that's the single window where my sustained DPS beats his burst-and-disengage. Before 6 with his combo up, there is no real all-in for me."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"I'm extremely gankable pre-6 with no escape but Q, so ward his side and play for my own jungler to punish his over-extension; his E-Q-R combo makes a gank on me nearly guaranteed death, so a tracked enemy jungler should make me concede the wave entirely."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"The classic error is fighting Wukong levels 1-3 because Master Yi 'wants to be aggressive' — his armor-shred and combo simply win that, and the loss delays my spike. Patience to the item timing is the whole matchup."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If I'm losing, freeze near my tower, farm with Alpha Strike from max range, and refuse every trade until my item completes — then look to scale through teamfights rather than reclaim lane, since one good Highlander reset can erase the deficit."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"When ahead, rush my second on-hit item, force fights the moment his R is down, and use Highlander's move speed and cooldown refresh to chain kills and roam — close it before his bruiser scaling and clone tricks become relevant."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"TRICKY (47.51% WR) — Wukong owns the early lane with armor-shred and lockdown, but Master Yi survives to his on-hit spike and flips the 2+ items window; win it by farming patiently and timing Alpha Strike on Cyclone."}]},"yasuo":{"tldr":"A coin-flip skirmisher race: Yasuo bullies my squishy early with Q-poke and Windwall, but once I hit Kraken/BORK my Alpha Strike out-DPSes him in any extended fight — though his crit + Windwall reclaim the late game.","winCon":"Survive levels 1-5 by farming with Alpha Strike from outside his Q-tornado range, then hard-spike at Kraken Slayer/BORK and use Q to blink through his EQ knockup and out-on-hit him in a sustained fight, resetting Highlander off the kill. Treat it as a race: win the brawl in the first-item window before his second crit item lets his Windwall + R take over.","enemyWin":"Yasuo wins by poking me down with Q every time I walk up to last-hit, dashing onto me through the wave for an EQ knockup, and using Windwall to negate my engage — then out-crit-scaling me at 2+ items where his sustained crit DPS plus R knockup beats my on-hit.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Yasuo","rating":"6/10","why":"His Q tornado-charge poke out-ranges my short auto, and I have no escape but Alpha Strike, so he free-harasses every time I step up to CS."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Yasuo","rating":"6/10","why":"At 2 stacks he can E-Q onto me for a knockup while my Wuju Style true damage and Meditate aren't online yet to punish the commit."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"With E rank-2 Wuju Style true damage I can finally trade back if he dashes in, but his Q3 knockup still flips a greedy all-in — it's about who respects whom."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"My Meditate sustains his Q-poke chip while his Windwall isn't up to block my autos, so the lane stabilizes into a farm standoff."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's move/attack speed and slow-immunity lets me stick through his dashes and dodge a gank, and his level-6 R knockup is a follow-up tool, not a duel-winner."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"7/10","why":"At Kraken Slayer/BORK my on-hit + Alpha Strike (which becomes untargetable and resets my attack timer) out-DPSes him before he has the crit chance to spike back."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Yasuo","rating":"6/10","why":"With two crit items his sustained crit DPS plus Windwall blanking my autos and R knockup interrupting my combo lets the hard-scaler reclaim the duel."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Yasuo. My autos are short-range and my only escape is Alpha Strike, so when I walk up to last-hit he charges Q and pokes me, and once he has 2 flow stacks he can E off a minion straight into me for the EQ knockup. Don't contest — farm with Alpha Strike on the caster minions and Wuju autos on melees, give up CS rather than eat his poke, and never stand in his Windwall's shadow.","mid":"Levels 4-6 even it out. Wuju Style's bonus true damage means if he dashes in I can E and trade back through any armor he buys, and Meditate lets me out-sustain his Q chip so he can't poke me to death. Level 6 Highlander is my real stabilizer: the move speed, attack speed, and slow-immunity let me dodge ganks and stick to him, and it resets if I get a kill. He's still the one who decides whether to commit — bait his Windwall before you all-in.","late":"At first item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) I flip ahead — Alpha Strike goes untargetable, resets my attack timer, and my on-hit out-DPSes his single-item crit. That's my window to force the fight. But at 2+ items the hard-scaler reclaims it: his crit chance comes online, Windwall blanks my autos mid-fight, and his R knockup interrupts my combo. I must close the game in the first-item brawl, not let it go to his three-item teamfighting.","wave":"Best wave: a slow-push you build into him so a frozen-ish lane sits near your tower, denying his dash-in escape and setting a Highlander all-in. Worst wave: a big wave shoved at his tower — he Windwalls, E-dashes through it onto you, and you have no follow-up. Crash timing: crash just before your first-item back (Kraken/BORK) so you return with the item spike and tempo to all-in.","cooldowns":"Track his Windwall (W) — it's a 26s cooldown that blocks nothing of mine since I'm melee on-hit, so its real value to me is knowing when it's DOWN to all-in; and track his flow stacks/Q3, since that knockup is the only thing that catches me after Alpha Strike.","trading":"Short trades only: E on for Wuju true damage, auto twice, walk off before his Q comes back up. Never sit in an extended trade pre-item where his sustained crit chip and a follow-up Q3 out-damage my chip. Post-Kraken, flip it — once you engage, commit fully because Alpha Strike + on-hit wins the long fight.","spikes":"My spikes: level 6 Highlander, then first on-hit item (Kraken/BORK) — that's my peak relative window. His spikes: level 6 R as a follow-up, but his real spike is his SECOND crit item, which is where he overtakes me. The matchup is a race between my first-item brawl power and his two-item scaling.","feeding":"If I fall behind, his Q-poke and crit chip make every walk-up lethal and I lose all farm. Don't force it — Alpha Strike farm under tower, ping for jungle help, and scale on neutral camps; my curve is streaky, so even a rough lane can be rescued by hitting my item spike off camps and side-lane CS.","carry":"If I'm ahead I'm a 1v9 — Highlander chains resets, so I look for a pick on him or his jungler, take the kill, and snowball the refresh into towers and objectives. My Alpha Strike untargetability lets me dive through his team's CC; once itemized I out-DPS his whole side of the map in an extended fight.","difficulty":"It's a 5/10 because the lane is a genuine 50/50: he owns the early and the very late, I own the level-6-to-first-item window, and neither side hard-stomps. The skill is in surviving his poke phase without feeding, baiting his Windwall, and timing your all-in to your item spike — execution-heavy but winnable."},"focus":{"text":"His Q3 / Windwall combo — the tornado knockup is the ONLY thing that catches me after Alpha Strike, and Windwall down is your green light to all-in.","letters":["Q","W"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike","d":"Use Q to last-hit the caster minions safely and Wuju-auto the melees so you stay healthy through his poke phase instead of walking into Q range."},{"t":"Bait Windwall, then all-in","d":"Force him to W on a minion or a fake step, then commit — Windwall blocks nothing of yours, so your only job is to engage when it's already spent."},{"t":"Spike-time your all-in","d":"Hold your real all-in for level 6 + Kraken/BORK; that's the one window your on-hit clearly out-DPSes his single-item crit before he scales past you."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't trade pre-item","d":"Never sit in an extended brawl before your first item — his sustained crit chip plus a follow-up Q3 knockup out-damages your auto-trade every time."},{"t":"Don't Q into his knockup","d":"Alpha Strike is your only escape; if you blow it to engage and he lands Q3, you're knocked up with no out and he resets the fight on you."},{"t":"Don't let it go super-late","d":"At 2+ crit items he reclaims the duel — don't passively scale into his three-item power; close the game in your first-item window."}],"tradeGood":"E on for Wuju Style true damage, Alpha Strike in for the untargetable reset and double-strike autos right after he's used his dash and his Windwall — short, then disengage before his Q is back.","tradeBad":"A drawn-out melee brawl pre-Kraken where you eat his crit chip and a Q3 knockup mid-combo with no item spike to out-DPS him.","ahead":"Snowball through Highlander resets: look for a pick on him or his jungler, take the kill, and immediately use the cooldown refresh to take plates, the next camp, or a dive. Your Alpha Strike untargetability lets you flash-dive through his team's CC, and once you're a Kraken/BORK ahead you out-DPS his entire side of the map in any extended fight. Don't let him scale back — keep forcing fights while your item lead is biggest.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Yasuo - Track: His Q3 / Windwall combo — the tornado knockup is the ONLY thing that catches me after Alpha Strike, and Windwall down is your green light to all-in.. - Survive levels 1-5 by farming with Alpha Strike from outside his Q-tornado range, then hard-spike at Kraken Slayer/BORK and use Q to blink through his EQ knockup and out-on-hit him in a sustained fight, resetting Highlander off the kill. Treat it as a race: win the brawl in the first-item window before his second crit item lets his Windwall + R take over.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A coin-flip skirmisher race: Yasuo bullies my squishy early with Q-poke and Windwall, but once I hit Kraken/BORK my Alpha Strike out-DPSes him in any extended fight — though his crit + Windwall reclaim the late game."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive his early Q-poke by farming with Alpha Strike, then hard-spike at Kraken Slayer/BORK and out-on-hit him in an extended fight where Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges his commit. Win the race in the first-item window before his second crit item plus Windwall and R reclaim the late game."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Yasuo owns 1-3, it's even 4-6 as Wuju true damage and Highlander come online, Master Yi peaks at first item, then Yasuo retakes it at 2+ crit items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade short pre-item (E-auto-auto, walk off) and only when his Q is on cooldown; never extend a pre-Kraken brawl. After first item, fully commit any time his Windwall and dash are spent."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Slow-push and keep the lane near your side so he can't dash to safety and you can set Highlander all-ins; avoid shoving into his tower where he Windwalls and E-dashes the wave onto you. Crash just before your first-item back."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike goes untargetable to dodge his EQ knockup commit and resets my attack timer for an instant on-hit burst; Meditate out-sustains his Q-poke chip; Wuju Style's true damage ignores any armor he builds; his Windwall blocks none of my melee on-hit, so its only relevance is timing my all-in for when it's down."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (his crit-DPS race rewards your on-hit attack speed) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Sorcery Nimbus Cloak + Gathering Storm, or Resolve Conditioning if his crit chip is grinding you down. Conqueror is the safer alternative into his sustained damage."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to win the level-6/first-item all-in race and cut his crit healing; take Flash + Teleport instead if you expect to lose the early and want to scale back into lane or split-push."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first for the on-hit spike, into Wit's End or Terminus for his crit + on-hit pressure (Wit's End's MR is wasted — he's AD — so prioritize the AD/on-hit items and Terminus armor shred); finish with Berserker's Greaves, and consider a Bramble Vest/Randuin's component if his crit is out-trading you."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Level 6 with Highlander up and his Windwall down, and again the moment your first on-hit item completes — those are the only windows where you clearly out-DPS him; outside them, farm."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"His E-dash mobility makes him slippery to gank but his lane-shove means he over-extends; ping your jungler for a level-6 dive where Highlander follows up the kill. On defense, his Windwall and dash help him survive an enemy gank, so play to vision and don't get caught after using Alpha Strike."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players over-aggress in the early levels trying to 'duel' him and feed his flow-stacked EQ, then waste Alpha Strike as an engage instead of saving it to dodge his knockup — survive first, all-in on the item spike."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Farm with Alpha Strike under tower, freeze if you can, and scale on jungle camps and side-lane CS; your streaky curve means hitting your first item even while behind can flip the lane, so don't throw it forcing trades you can't win."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Chain Highlander resets — take a pick, refresh your cooldowns, and immediately convert it into plates, camps, or a dive; force fights while your item lead is largest, because his scaling shrinks your window every back."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A true 50/50 (50.78% / EVEN): Yasuo owns the early and the very late, Master Yi owns the level-6-to-first-item race — survive the poke, bait the Windwall, and all-in on your spike."}]},"yone":{"tldr":"Survive Yone's even early, hit your first on-hit item, and Alpha Strike through his Q-dashes to out-DPS a duelist who can't pin you down — this is a Master Yi-favored lane.","winCon":"Farm safe with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos through levels 1-3, then spike on Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King and use Q's untargetability to dodge his R knockup and W spirit-cleave so you out-sustain his trades with Meditate and out-DPS him in extended fights. Once Highlander is resetting on kills you run him down through his E rewind.","enemyWin":"Yone wins by trading early with Q-dash autos and his Q3 knockup while your kit is weak, then using E to rewind out of every all-in and scaling his own crit so the lane stays even long enough that he matches your two-item window.","diff":"FAVOURED","tone":"#3ddc97","diffRating":"4/10","carryRating":"9/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Yone","rating":"6/10","why":"Yone's Q-dash auto pattern and longer reach beat your short-range Wuju autos before you have items, so farm with Alpha Strike instead of contesting."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Yone","rating":"6/10","why":"His Q gives him a built-in gap-closer for free trades while your only out is a single Alpha Strike on cooldown, so he edges every short exchange."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style's bonus true damage comes online and Meditate sustains his Q-poke, so short trades even out even before your spike."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"With Wuju true damage and Meditate sustain you out-trade his pre-six poke and start matching his autos in a stand-up fight."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander's move/attack speed and slow immunity let you stick to him through Q-dashes and answer his R knockup by Alpha Striking the wind-up."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King jumps your on-hit DPS so an extended fight where you dodge his R with Q and shred his health flips hard in your favor."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At two items you out-DPS and reset Highlander through his E rewind faster than he can crit you down, owning every sustained fight."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Yone — his Q-dash lets him auto-and-reposition while your short range and lack of an escape beyond a single Alpha Strike mean you lose stand-up trades. Don't contest CS with autos; use Alpha Strike to last-hit and clear, soak XP, and keep your HP healthy. Track his Q stacks so you never eat the Q3 knockup while your Q is down.","mid":"Levels 4-5 even out as Wuju Style's bonus true damage and Meditate sustain let you answer his Q-poke and take short trades back. Level 6 is your turning point: Highlander's attack speed, move speed, and slow immunity let you stick onto him through his dashes, and you can Alpha Strike the moment he commits R to dodge the knockup entirely.","late":"At two items you are the duelist he can't escape — Kraken/BORK on-hit plus Wuju true damage out-DPS his crit, Meditate out-sustains his trades, and Highlander resets keep you topped and chasing through his E rewind. Any extended fight past this point is yours; only a clean disengage saves him.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push you control so you fight him on the wave at level 6+ with minions adding to your on-hit DPS. Worst wave: a wave shoved into your tower early, exposing you to his Q-dash trades and jungle ganks while you're weak. Crash timing: crash the wave just before your first-item back so you reset on your spike and return even or ahead in CS.","cooldowns":"Track Yone's E (Spirit Rewind) — it's his escape and his trade-safety; when it's down, that's your all-in window. Also count his Q stacks so the Q3 knockup never catches you mid-Alpha-Strike-cooldown.","trading":"Pre-six, don't trade — farm with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos. Post-six, bait his Q-dash and R, Alpha Strike to dodge the knockup, then chain Wuju autos with Highlander attack speed while Meditate covers any poke he lands.","spikes":"Yone spikes at level 6 (R) and on his first crit item; you spike harder at 6 (Highlander) and decisively on your first on-hit item, snowballing at two items.","feeding":"If you fall behind, his early lead plus crit scaling makes him a slippery carry — but his ceiling is lower than yours, so farm Alpha Strike side-lane, hit your items, and look to teamfight where his E only saves him, not his team.","carry":"Ahead, you become a 1v9 — sidelane to draw him, win the duel through his E with Highlander resets, then use the refreshed R cooldowns to roam and snowball other lanes.","difficulty":"Only 4/10 because the early lane is genuinely Yone-favored and a misplay into his Q3 or a gank can set your weak phase back — but the matchup is FAVOURED because once you itemize, his mobility can't out-DPS your on-hit reset pattern."},"focus":{"text":"Yone's R (Fate Sealed) knockup is the only thing that can lock you down for a follow-up — bait it or Alpha Strike its wind-up to go untargetable, and respect his E (Spirit Rewind) as his escape when you commit your all-in.","letters":["R","E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Q early","d":"Use Alpha Strike to last-hit and clear safely through levels 1-3 instead of trading autos — concede the weak phase and arrive at your item spike even in CS and full HP."},{"t":"Alpha Strike his R","d":"When Yone commits Fate Sealed, blink with Alpha Strike to go untargetable through the knockup, then turn and out-DPS him while his big cooldown is spent."},{"t":"All-in when his E is down","d":"His Spirit Rewind is his only escape — once it's on cooldown and you have an item, commit Highlander and chain Wuju autos to kill him before he can recover."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't trade autos pre-six","d":"His Q-dash and longer reach beat your short-range Wuju autos before items — eating early trades just feeds his crit scaling and invites a gank while you're weak."},{"t":"Don't waste Q as escape early","d":"Alpha Strike is your only out — burning it to chase a kill you can't secure leaves you with no answer to his Q3 knockup or a jungle collapse."},{"t":"Don't Meditate in his face","d":"Channeling Meditate next to Yone lets him walk up, Q-dash, and Q3 knockup you out of the channel — only sustain when you've created space or after he's used his gap-closer."}],"tradeGood":"Post-six, bait his Q-dash and R, Alpha Strike the knockup to go untargetable, then unload Wuju-true-damage autos under Highlander attack speed while Meditate covers his return poke.","tradeBad":"A level 1-3 stand-up auto trade where his Q-dash reach and free repositioning out-damage your short autos and stack his crit items.","ahead":"Ahead, sidelane to force Yone into a 1v1 he can't win — bait his E, dodge his R with Alpha Strike, and kill him through Highlander resets that refresh your cooldowns. Use those refreshed timers to shove and roam to other lanes, snowballing your on-hit lead across the map. Keep building on-hit (BORK/Wit's End) so even his teammates can't peel you off him.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Yone - Track: Yone's R (Fate Sealed) knockup is the only thing that can lock you down for a follow-up — bait it or Alpha Strike its wind-up to go untargetable, and respect his E (Spirit Rewind) as his escape when you commit your all-in.. - Farm safe with Alpha Strike and Wuju autos through levels 1-3, then spike on Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King and use Q's untargetability to dodge his R knockup and W spirit-cleave so you out-sustain his trades with Meditate and out-DPS him in extended fights. Once Highlander is resetting on kills you run him down through his E rewind.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Survive Yone's even early, hit your first on-hit item, and Alpha Strike through his Q-dashes to out-DPS a duelist who can't pin you down — this is a Master Yi-favored lane."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Master Yi survives Yone's Q-dash early by farming with Alpha Strike, then spikes on his first on-hit item and uses Q's untargetability to dodge Fate Sealed while Meditate out-sustains and Wuju true damage out-DPS his crit. Once Highlander is resetting on kills, he runs Yone down through Spirit Rewind in every extended fight."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Yone owns levels 1-3, the lane evens at 4-5, and Master Yi takes over from level 6 (Highlander) and decisively on his first on-hit item through two items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Never auto-trade pre-six; from level 6 trade only after baiting his Q-dash/R, Alpha-Striking the knockup, then chaining Wuju autos — back off when his E is up and your Q is on cooldown."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Farm safe and even early with Alpha Strike, then slow-push so you fight on the wave at your spike; crash before your first-item back so you reset on your power timing and avoid shoving into his Q-dash trades."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges Yone's R knockup and his W spirit-cleave; Highlander's slow immunity ignores any kite; Meditate out-sustains his Q-poke but must not be channeled inside his Q3 range; his E Spirit Rewind is the escape you must wait out before committing."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (uncapped attack speed to ramp through his dashes) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve Conditioning + Overgrowth for the early bully phase, or Bone Plating vs his Q-poke. Conqueror is the safer pick if you expect to grind extended trades."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to punish his even early into a kill window once you spike at six; take Teleport instead if you expect to lose the early phase and want to scale safely and match recalls."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for the on-hit spike, second item Wit's End (his W and crit are mixed, MR helps) or Terminus; Berserker's Greaves; Wit's End / Maw of Malmortius if his crit damage is snowballing, Plated Steelcaps only if you're getting kited by autos."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"All-in at level 6 once Highlander is up and his E is on cooldown, and again the moment your first on-hit item completes — Alpha Strike the R, burn him with Wuju autos, and reset Highlander on the kill."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're gankable in the weak early phase since Alpha Strike is your only escape — ward his entrances and don't overextend pre-six; once you have R and an item, a gank flips your way because Highlander lets you chase and reset through the dive."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players contest CS with autos too early and feed Yone's crit, or burn Alpha Strike chasing instead of saving it to dodge Fate Sealed — discipline in the weak phase is the whole matchup."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"If behind, farm Alpha Strike in the sidelane, skip risky trades, hit your item spikes, and pivot to teamfights where his E only saves himself — your on-hit DPS still out-scales his ceiling."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Ahead, take 1v1s in the sidelane through his E, kill him with Highlander resets, then use the refreshed cooldowns to roam and shut down other lanes before he can scale back."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"FAVOURED (58.82% WR) — a tough but losable early phase that flips hard the moment Master Yi itemizes, because Yone's mobility can't escape an on-hit hyper-carry who goes untargetable through his only lockdown."}]},"yorick":{"tldr":"A true coinflip splitpush race: I dodge his E mist-cage with Alpha Strike and out-DPS the ghoul swarm in a fair 1v1, but if his cage lands or his wave shoves me off he just out-zones and out-scales me in the side lane.","winCon":"Survive his early ghoul poke, hit my on-hit spike (Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King), then catch him without a fresh E mist-wall and use Alpha Strike to dodge the cage while my on-hit DPS burns through Maiden and ghouls faster than they chip me. I win by snowballing off Highlander resets onto the rest of the map before he can split a tower.","enemyWin":"Yorick lands E to cage me, raises the wall behind me, and lets Maiden plus the ghoul swarm zone me off the wave and grind me down while I'm trapped. He out-scales the lane: even when I'm ahead, his splitpush and Maiden waveclear reclaim the side lane the moment I leave it.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Yorick","rating":"6/10","why":"His autos out-range and out-poke mine, and a single E mist-cage at level 1 locks me for free harass before I have any combo to answer."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Yorick","rating":"6/10","why":"With Q empowering his auto and ghouls spawning from his passive graves, he out-trades me while I only have Alpha Strike and have to farm with it instead of fighting."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"My Wuju Style true damage comes online so I can punch back in a short Alpha-Strike-and-walk-away trade, but his E cage still flips any extended exchange in his favor."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Meditate sustains his ghoul chip and Wuju true damage makes my Alpha Strike trades sting, but his ghoul swarm matches my damage if I commit without dodging E first."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Highlander gives me slow-immunity to ignore his E slow and dodge-gank, but he gets Maiden of the Mist on R and the swarm jumps his sustained DPS to match my spike."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"My Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King on-hit lets Alpha Strike dodge the E cage and shred Maiden plus ghouls in a fair 1v1 faster than they grind me."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Yorick","rating":"6/10","why":"He reclaims the side lane: Maiden and ghoul waveclear plus his splitpush DPS out-pressure towers the moment I leave, even if I out-duel him in a straight fight."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 are Yorick's. His autos out-range mine, his passive graves spawn ghouls that swarm me whenever he lands a Q empowered auto, and a single E mist-cage traps me for free harass that I have no combo to answer yet. I don't fight here — I farm with Alpha Strike from a safe angle and use Wuju autos only to secure CS, conceding the wave rather than eating ghoul chip in a losing trade.","mid":"Levels 4-5 I stabilize as Wuju Style's bonus true damage and Meditate sustain come online — now an Alpha-Strike-in, true-damage-auto, and walk-away trade actually stings him and Meditate channels off the ghoul chip. Level 6 is my first real spike: Highlander's slow-immunity lets me ignore his E slow and dodge ganks, but he simultaneously gets Maiden of the Mist on his R, so the swarm's sustained DPS jumps to match mine. Stay even, don't commit without dodging E.","late":"At first item (Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King) the lane tips to me — my on-hit DPS finally burns through Maiden and the ghoul wall faster than they grind me, and Alpha Strike's untargetable blink dodges the E cage outright. But at 2+ items Yorick the SCALER reclaims it: his Maiden and ghoul waveclear plus raw splitpush DPS out-pressure towers the instant I leave the side lane, so I have to convert my duel edge into map pressure, not a tower-trading race I lose.","wave":"Best wave: a slow push into him so my ghoul-shredding on-hit DPS forces a fair 1v1 under my tower with Alpha Strike up to dodge E. Worst wave: a wave shoved onto his side where his E cage and wall trap me deep with Maiden and the swarm and no escape but Q. Crash timing: crash the wave at level 6 right as Highlander comes up so I reset, buy my on-hit spike, and return with item power before his Maiden snowballs the side lane.","cooldowns":"Track his E (Dark Procession) mist-cage above all — it's a ~16s cooldown and it's the only thing that stops Alpha Strike from kiting him; if he whiffs or it's down, that's my entire all-in window. Also note when his Maiden R is up, since the ghoul swarm doubles his fight DPS.","trading":"Short and on my terms: pre-6 I only Alpha-Strike a single empowered Wuju auto and walk before ghouls stack on me. Post-item I wait for him to throw E (or have it on cooldown), then Alpha Strike onto him to dodge the cage, Wuju-auto through Meditate sustain, and reset Highlander if it kills. Never sit in the mist field trading autos into his whole swarm.","spikes":"My spikes: level 4-5 (Wuju + Meditate), level 6 (Highlander), and especially first on-hit item where I out-duel the swarm. His spikes: level 1 E availability, level 6 Maiden of the Mist, and every item that pushes his splitpush — he out-scales me into the late game.","feeding":"If I fall behind, his ghoul swarm and Maiden snowball the side lane and I become a free splitpush victim — getting caged once while behind usually means death to the swarm. I farm under tower with Alpha Strike, let my jungler answer his split, and scale to my item spike instead of forcing trades I can't win.","carry":"If I'm ahead, Highlander resets are the engine — every kill or assist refreshes its move/attack speed and cuts my other cooldowns, so I leave the side lane and use that speed to chain-pick across the map. I out-DPS objectives and turn my duel edge into team fights before his pure-split clock catches up.","difficulty":"It's a 5/10 EVEN because the skill check is symmetrical: I have a clean answer to his core threat (Alpha Strike dodges the E cage) but he has a clean answer to my snowball (he out-scales and out-splits me). Whoever respects the other's pattern — me not over-committing into the swarm, him not whiffing E — wins, so it comes down to execution, not the matchup."},"focus":{"text":"His E (Dark Procession) mist-cage — it's the only thing that locks Alpha Strike out and traps me with Maiden and the ghoul swarm; bait or wait it out before every all-in. His W wall trap chains off it to seal the escape.","letters":["E","W"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Dodge E with Alpha Strike","d":"Save Alpha Strike's untargetable blink for the moment he throws his E mist-cage — blinking through it denies the trap and resets my attack timer onto him."},{"t":"Scale to your on-hit item","d":"Concede the level 1-3 lane and farm safely; the matchup flips the instant Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King lets you shred Maiden and ghouls in a fair 1v1."},{"t":"Force the duel, not the split","d":"You out-duel him 1v1 but lose the pure splitpush race — pull him into a straight fight under your tower or take your Highlander resets to the rest of the map."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't trade in the mist field","d":"Never sit auto-trading inside his ghoul swarm and Maiden — their combined DPS matches yours and his E will cage you mid-fight with no escape but a used Q."},{"t":"Don't all-in with E up","d":"If his E mist-cage is available and you haven't baited it, an all-in gets trapped and the swarm grinds you down; wait for it to be on cooldown."},{"t":"Don't try to out-split him","d":"Don't sit in the side lane trading towers — his Maiden and ghoul waveclear out-pressure you at 2+ items and you'll lose the map while winning the 1v1."}],"tradeGood":"Wait for his E to be thrown or on cooldown, Alpha Strike onto him to dodge the cage, Wuju-auto with true damage through his ghoul chip, and walk before the swarm restacks.","tradeBad":"Walking into the wave to auto-trade while his ghoul swarm and Maiden are up and his E is off cooldown — that's the cage-into-swarm death he wants.","ahead":"Once I'm ahead, I stop tower-trading in the side lane — that's his win condition, not mine — and use Highlander resets to roam. Every pick refreshes my move/attack speed and slashes my cooldowns, so I chain kills across the map and out-DPS objectives before his splitpush clock matters. My job is to end before his Maiden and items reclaim the scaling lead.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Yorick - Track: His E (Dark Procession) mist-cage — it's the only thing that locks Alpha Strike out and traps me with Maiden and the ghoul swarm; bait or wait it out before every all-in. His W wall trap chains off it to seal the escape.. - Survive his early ghoul poke, hit my on-hit spike (Kraken or Blade of the Ruined King), then catch him without a fresh E mist-wall and use Alpha Strike to dodge the cage while my on-hit DPS burns through Maiden and ghouls faster than they chip me. I win by snowballing off Highlander resets onto the rest of the map before he can split a tower.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A true coinflip splitpush race: I dodge his E mist-cage with Alpha Strike and out-DPS the ghoul swarm in a fair 1v1, but if his cage lands or his wave shoves me off he just out-zones and out-scales me in the side lane."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive Yorick's level 1-3 ghoul poke by farming with Alpha Strike, then hit my first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King) where my DPS out-burns Maiden and the swarm in a fair 1v1. From there I convert duel wins into map pressure via Highlander resets before his late-game splitpush out-scales me."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Yorick owns 1-3 (range, ghouls, E cage); even at 4-6 (my Wuju/Meditate and Highlander vs his Maiden); mine at first item (on-hit shreds the swarm); his again at 2+ items (he out-scales and out-splits)."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Trade only when his E mist-cage is down or already thrown: Alpha Strike in, one Wuju-empowered auto, walk. Back off entirely if his ghoul swarm and Maiden are up and E is available — that extended trade is his."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Slow-push to pull him into a fair 1v1 under my tower with Alpha Strike up. Never let the wave shove onto his side where E and his W wall trap me deep in the swarm. Crash at 6 to reset for my on-hit spike."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetable blink is the whole matchup — it dodges his E mist-cage and the W wall follow-up. Highlander's slow-immunity ignores his E slow and dodges his ganks. Meditate sustains the ghoul chip; Wuju Style's true damage ignores his bruiser armor and shreds Maiden."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (faster on-hit ramp to out-DPS the swarm) into Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Coup de Grace; secondary Resolve with Conditioning/Overgrowth, or Sorcery with Nimbus Cloak for the gank-dodge. He's AD, so prioritize armor shards and HP/scaling."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Ignite to push my snowball and anti-heal his Meditate-less but item-sustained splitpush; take Teleport instead if I want to match his side-lane pressure and reset for my item spike without losing tempo."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for on-hit that melts Maiden and ghouls, then Wit's End vs nothing here (he's AD) — go Terminus or Death's Dance for armor instead. Boots: Plated Steelcaps vs his auto and ghoul damage. Anti-heal (Mortal Reminder) is low priority since his sustain is mostly Maiden, not self-heal."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"All-in only when his E is on cooldown or whiffed AND I have my first on-hit item — that's when Alpha Strike dodges nothing because nothing's there to dodge, and my DPS out-races the swarm. Highlander up makes it a kill-and-reset window."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"My ganks are weak pre-6 (no hard CC, easy to E-cage and wall off the chaser), so I don't force early plays. Post-6 Highlander's slow-immunity makes me hard to gank back. His E cage is a strong counter-gank tool, so my jungler should dive only when it's down."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players over-commit into the ghoul swarm trying to fight at level 2-3 and get caged-and-killed, or they sit in the side lane trying to out-split a scaler they can't out-split. Concede early, scale, and take the fight to the map instead."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Farm under tower with Alpha Strike, never get caught by E while behind (one cage equals death to the swarm), and let my jungler answer his split. Scale to my on-hit item and pick my 1v1 spots rather than forcing the losing side-lane race."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Leave the side lane and use Highlander resets to roam — every kill refreshes my speed and cuts cooldowns, so I chain picks and take objectives before his Maiden and items reclaim the scaling edge. End the game before his pure-split clock runs out."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"A genuine 50/50 EVEN: I dodge his cage and out-duel him 1v1, he out-zones and out-scales me in the split — execution and wave control decide it, not the matchup."}]},"zac":{"tldr":"A weak early lane where Zac's slings and CC chunk me, but once my on-hit items come online Alpha Strike dodges his engage and I out-DPS a tank who can't kite me — patience wins it.","winCon":"Farm safely with Alpha Strike through the early bullying, hit my first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King), then save Q to become untargetable through his E sling or Q/W knock-up and out-sustain his passive blobs in an extended fight. Zac can't kite, so once I'm itemized every all-in he starts becomes my reset window with Highlander.","enemyWin":"Zac wins by abusing levels 1-5: he slings in with E, lands his Q knock and W, and chunks me with point-and-click CC before I can scale, then walks away on his passive blob heals. If he gets help from his jungler while my Q is on cooldown, his lockdown catches me with no escape and snowballs the lane.","diff":"EVEN","tone":"#e8b84b","diffRating":"5/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Zac","rating":"6/10","why":"Zac's longer auto range and passive blob sustain win the level-1 minion poke war while my Alpha Strike still has no reset target to make it safe."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Zac","rating":"6/10","why":"His point-and-click Q knock-up at level 2 chunks me before Wuju Style true damage is online, so I just farm and concede the trade."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Zac","rating":"5/10","why":"With E sling engage up he can all-in, but my Q can blink out of his follow-up — a genuine skill stage where dodging his W decides it."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain stabilize me into even short trades, but his CC still threatens any over-extension."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"Highlander answers his ganks and lets me chase, but Zac's level-6 R airborne can still flip a fight he commits to first."},{"label":"First item","side":"Master Yi","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken Slayer / BORK on-hit DPS shreds a tank with no kite, and Alpha Strike goes untargetable through his E sling to win the extended fight."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Master Yi","rating":"8/10","why":"At 2+ items I out-DPS his entire blob pool, dodge his CC with Q, and reset Highlander off any kill to chain through him repeatedly."}],"breakdown":{"early":"Levels 1-3 belong to Zac. His autos out-range mine, his passive blobs heal back any poke I land, and at level 2 his Q knock-up plus W chunk me before Wuju Style is online. Don't fight — farm with Alpha Strike on the caster minions, take only what I can hit-and-run, and accept I'm behind in lane priority until I get items.","mid":"Levels 4-6 I stabilize. Wuju Style's bonus true damage ignores his armor for short trades and Meditate out-sustains his blob heals if I disengage on the channel. At 6, Highlander gives me move speed and slow immunity to dodge ganks and answer his E engage — but never start the all-in unless his E sling is down.","late":"At 2+ items (Kraken/BORK plus Wit's End or Terminus) I flip to dominant. A tank with no kite tool cannot escape my on-hit DPS, Alpha Strike makes me untargetable through his E re-engage and R airborne, and Wuju true damage punishes his armor stacking. Every fight he starts becomes a Highlander reset for me.","wave":"Best wave: a short wave near my tower so his E sling has to dive plates to reach me and I farm safely with Q. Worst wave: a long wave pushed to his side where his E engage and a gank trap me with no escape. Crash timing: shove and crash only after my first on-hit item is complete, to take plates or recall on a tempo lead — never shove while behind early.","cooldowns":"Track his E (Elastic Slingshot) — it's his only gap-closer and engage; if it's down he cannot start a fight or punish my Q. Also watch his Q knock-up timing in the early levels.","trading":"Early: he initiates with E or point-and-click Q and wins; I refuse and farm. Mid: I trade only with Wuju Style active and Q held to disengage. Late: I bait or dodge his E with Q, then sit on him with on-hit autos while Meditate negates his returning blob heal.","spikes":"Zac spikes hardest at levels 2-5 and again at level 6 R. My spikes are level 6 Highlander, then a hard jump at first on-hit item, then dominant at 2+ items — the lane inverts cleanly around my item timings.","feeding":"If I die early to his E-gank, the lane snowballs fast because I scale on items I now can't afford — play ultra-safe, farm under tower with Q, and wait for my power spike rather than forcing back into his CC.","carry":"If I'm ahead, I'm one of the highest-snowball champions in the game: Highlander resets off kills let me chain through Zac and his team, and Alpha Strike's untargetability lets me dive a CC-heavy comp that should counter me.","difficulty":"It's a true 5/10 EVEN: Zac genuinely beats me early with range, CC, and sustain, but he's a kite-less tank who hard-loses the scaling fight to on-hit — the difficulty is purely surviving the early window without dying."},"focus":{"text":"Zac's E (Elastic Slingshot) — his only engage and gap-closer. If it's on cooldown he can't start a fight or punish me; bait it out, dodge it with Alpha Strike, then commit when he can't re-engage.","letters":["E"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Q early","d":"Use Alpha Strike to clear the caster minions safely from range while conceding the level 1-3 trades — don't try to out-poke a champion with blob sustain and longer autos."},{"t":"Save Q for his engage","d":"Hold Alpha Strike to blink untargetable through his E sling, Q knock-up, or R airborne instead of using it as raw damage — it's my only way out of his lockdown."},{"t":"Fight after first item","d":"Once Kraken/BORK is complete, force extended fights: a kite-less tank can't escape my on-hit DPS, and Wuju Style true damage ignores his armor."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't all-in early","d":"Never commit levels 1-5 — his E engage plus Q/W CC chunks me before Wuju Style and Highlander are online, and I have no escape once Q is used."},{"t":"Don't fight near his tower","d":"Avoid pushing a long wave where his E sling can dive me onto plates with jungle help and no path to safety."},{"t":"Don't burn Q for damage","d":"If I use Alpha Strike just to poke, I'm dead to his next E knock-up — keep it as my dodge tool until he's committed his engage."}],"tradeGood":"After his E sling is down, walk up with Wuju Style active and Q held, sit on him with on-hit autos while Meditate erases his blob heal, and reset Highlander if he dies.","tradeBad":"A level-2 brawl where he point-and-click Q knocks me up and W's me before Wuju Style or Q is available to answer.","ahead":"Press a lead by sitting on a short wave and crashing only after my item completes, denying Zac the farm he needs to stay relevant as a tank. Use Highlander's move speed to roam mid or invade his jungler once I out-DPS the map, and dive him freely with Alpha Strike untargetability since a behind, kite-less Zac has no answer to my reset chains. Turn every gank attempt on me into a free kill that refreshes Highlander.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Zac - Track: Zac's E (Elastic Slingshot) — his only engage and gap-closer. If it's on cooldown he can't start a fight or punish me; bait it out, dodge it with Alpha Strike, then commit when he can't re-engage.. - Farm safely with Alpha Strike through the early bullying, hit my first on-hit item (Kraken Slayer / Blade of the Ruined King), then save Q to become untargetable through his E sling or Q/W knock-up and out-sustain his passive blobs in an extended fight. Zac can't kite, so once I'm itemized every all-in he starts becomes my reset window with Highlander.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"A weak early lane where Zac's slings and CC chunk me, but once my on-hit items come online Alpha Strike dodges his engage and I out-DPS a tank who can't kite me — patience wins it."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Survive Zac's stronger levels 1-5 by farming with Alpha Strike and refusing trades, then hit my first on-hit item where the lane inverts. A kite-less tank cannot escape my on-hit DPS, so once itemized I use Q to dodge his CC and out-sustain his blobs in every extended fight."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Zac favored 1-5 (range, CC, blob sustain), even at 6 with Highlander, then Master Yi favored from first item onward and dominant at 2+ items."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Refuse all trades levels 1-3; trade only mid-game with Wuju Style up and Q held to disengage; from first item on, force extended fights but always after baiting his E sling."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Keep the wave short near my tower while behind so his E has to dive plates to reach me; only start crashing for plates or recall once my first on-hit item completes and I hold tempo."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike's untargetability dodges his E sling damage, Q knock-up, and R airborne; Wuju Style's true damage ignores his armor stacking; Meditate out-channels the heal his passive blobs return; Highlander's slow immunity beats his slows and resets off kills."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo (best for stacking on-hit attack speed vs a fat tank) with Triumph, Legend: Alacrity, Last Stand; secondary Resolve Conditioning + Overgrowth, or Bone Plating vs his early CC poke. Take Cut Down — Zac builds health."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash + Ignite to punish his low early mobility and deny his blob sustain in kill windows; take Teleport instead only if I expect to get bullied off the wave and need to scale safely."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King first (BORK shreds his health pool and slows his kite), then Wit's End or Terminus for on-hit plus magic resist into his AP damage; Plated Steelcaps if he's the main physical threat, Mercs vs his CC chain; finish with Guardian Angel or Death's Dance to survive diving him."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Only all-in after his E sling is on cooldown AND I have my first on-hit item — before that I have no kill pressure and no escape; at 2+ items I can all-in almost any time his E is down."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"His E engage plus a gank while my Q is down is the lane's biggest danger early, so ward his river and hug tower; once I'm itemized my own jungler converging gives me a clean kill because Zac can't peel a fed on-hit Yi off himself."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players try to out-trade Zac early and burn Alpha Strike for damage, then die with no escape to his E knock-up — the whole lane is about patience until items."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Farm under tower with Q, take only safe CS, build defensively (Steelcaps, Death's Dance), and wait for the 2+ item window where I out-scale him regardless of the early deficit."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"Deny his farm with a short wave, roam with Highlander move speed after kills, and dive his team with Alpha Strike untargetability — every reset chains me further ahead of a tank who can't keep up."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"EVEN 5/10 — a patience check where Zac owns the early lane but a kite-less tank hard-loses the on-hit scaling fight; survive to items and I win."}]},"ziggs":{"tldr":"Ziggs sits at max range lobbing Bouncing Bombs you can't answer, blows you off the wave before your on-hit spike, and turns the lane into a CS-starved poke war Master Yi almost never wins.","winCon":"Survive the poke and farm with Alpha Strike at max range without trading autos, then end the lane indirectly — roam with Highlander or hit your Kraken/BORK spike and force a sidelane all-in the moment he's caught with no Satchel and no flash. You don't out-lane Ziggs; you out-scale and out-roam him, so play for level 6+ pressure on the rest of the map rather than a kill on him.","enemyWin":"He pokes you below half with Bouncing Bombs and Hexplosive Minefield from a range you can never cross on foot, denies CS by zoning the wave, and the instant you walk up he Satchels himself away and resets the gap. Every chunk he lands delays your item spike, and a Liandry's Ziggs just sieges your tower and snipes you across the map with Mega Inferno Bomb.","diff":"HARD","tone":"#ff5d6c","diffRating":"8/10","carryRating":"8/10","phases":[{"label":"Level 1","side":"Ziggs","rating":"7/10","why":"He lobs Bouncing Bomb (Q) from a screen away while your only level-1 tool is Alpha Strike, which needs him in melee range you can't safely reach."},{"label":"Level 2","side":"Ziggs","rating":"7/10","why":"Hexplosive Minefield (E) zones your CS and walking up to last-hit eats free Q poke before you have Wuju Style or Meditate online."},{"label":"Level 3","side":"Ziggs","rating":"7/10","why":"Three points of poke versus your zero range means he chunks you for every caster minion you try to Alpha Strike onto."},{"label":"Levels 4-5","side":"Ziggs","rating":"6/10","why":"Wuju Style (E) true damage and Meditate (W) sustain stabilize you, but you still can't close on a champ who Satchels (W) himself away and out-ranges every step."},{"label":"Level 6","side":"Ziggs","rating":"6/10","why":"Highlander (R) finally lets you sprint a gap, but he holds Satchel Charge (W) to self-knockback the instant you commit and the dash leaves you in his minefield."},{"label":"First item","side":"Ziggs","rating":"6/10","why":"Kraken/BORK on-hit comes online, yet a Liandry's Ziggs out-ranges your spike and a single full rotation still bursts you before you stick to him."},{"label":"2+ items","side":"Skill","rating":"5/10","why":"At 2+ items your on-hit DPS finally one-shots him if you ever reach melee, but he siege-zones objectives and Mega Inferno Bomb (R) snipes you, so it lives or dies on whether you catch him with Satchel down."}],"breakdown":{"early":"This is one of your worst early lanes. You have no ranged tool — Alpha Strike only fires at enemies already in melee range — so Ziggs lobs Bouncing Bombs at you from outside your reach with zero risk and refreshes its cooldown on minion kills. Walking up to last-hit eats a free Q, and his Hexplosive Minefield zones the wave so you either miss CS or take poke. Farm at the very back of the wave, use Alpha Strike on minions only when his Q is on cooldown, and concede the lane — do NOT try to trade.","mid":"Levels 4-5 give you Wuju Style true damage and Meditate sustain, which lets you heal back some poke between waves, but it changes nothing about the range gap: he Satchel-knocks himself away the instant you approach. Level 6 Highlander is your first real tool to close distance, but it's not a gap-closer — he just self-knockbacks with Satchel and re-opens the range. Use 6 to roam or answer a gank, not to force him 1v1.","late":"At Kraken/BORK + a second item your on-hit DPS deletes him IF you ever touch him, so the entire game becomes a positioning puzzle: he's a max-range artillery mage who sieges your tower, zones every objective, and snipes you with Mega Inferno Bomb across the map. You win by flanking, by Highlander-running him down when his Satchel and Flash are down, or by being on the other side of the map taking objectives while he can't fight you.","wave":"Best wave: a slow-pushing wave that crashes into his tower so you can shove-and-roam or recall on the on-hit spike without taking free poke. Worst wave: a wave frozen near your tower in his minefield, where he free-pokes you for every CS. Crash timing: shove and crash into his tower at level 6 and on each item spike, then leave lane to roam with Highlander rather than sit and eat bombs.","cooldowns":"Track Satchel Charge (W) above all — it's both his self-peel knockback and his escape; if it's down, that's your only real all-in window. Also watch Bouncing Bomb (Q) cooldown to know when it's safe to walk up and farm.","trading":"There is no good auto trade — he never lets you in melee. The only 'trade' is dodging Bouncing Bombs by sidestepping while you Alpha Strike a minion to farm, then disengaging. You only ever commit when his Satchel is on cooldown.","spikes":"Ziggs spikes at level 1-2 (immediate range advantage), at 6 (Mega Inferno Bomb adds map pressure and execute), and at Liandry's first item (siege + DPS). You spike at 6 (Highlander mobility/anti-gank), Kraken or BORK first item, and hard at 2+ items where you out-DPS him in any reachable fight.","feeding":"If you fall behind you become a useless melee farmer who can't approach the wave — Ziggs perma-pokes and zones you off CS, you fall further behind on items, and your whole game evaporates because Yi behind has no agency. Avoid ALL poke, farm under tower with Alpha Strike, and ping your jungler that you can't trade.","carry":"If you get ahead, Highlander resets let you chain kills across the map — take your 2+ item spike to the sidelane or a teamfight flank, Alpha Strike onto a frontliner to become untargetable through his Mega Inferno Bomb, and run down the squishies he can't peel. You carry by leaving this lane, not by winning it.","difficulty":"It's an 8/10 because you have literally zero answer to ranged poke before you scale: no gap-closer to bridge his range, no CC to catch him, and Alpha Strike can't even target him from afar. He out-ranges you, out-zones your farm, and self-peels your only commit, so you eat a poke-starved lane and have to win the game elsewhere."},"focus":{"text":"Satchel Charge (W) — it's his self-knockback escape AND his minefield detonator; if you ever all-in, it must be on cooldown or he just peels himself away and re-opens the range. Secondary threat is Bouncing Bomb (Q) poke that denies your farm.","letters":["W","Q"]},"dosFull":[{"t":"Farm with Alpha Strike, never autos","d":"Use Alpha Strike on minions at max range when his Bouncing Bomb is on cooldown so you keep CS without ever walking into his poke; do not auto-trade a champ you can't reach."},{"t":"Play for level 6 roams, not a kill","d":"Use Highlander's move speed and the slow immunity to leave lane and pressure other lanes or answer ganks — your value is map presence, since you can't force Ziggs 1v1."},{"t":"Commit only when Satchel is down","d":"Track his Satchel Charge; the rare time it's on cooldown and you have Highlander up is the only window to Alpha Strike in and burst him before he self-peels."}],"dontsFull":[{"t":"Don't walk up to last-hit into his Q","d":"Stepping forward for CS while Bouncing Bomb is up just hands him free poke that delays your only path back into the game — your item spike."},{"t":"Don't sit in Hexplosive Minefield","d":"His E zones the wave and a follow-up bomb on the slow chunks you hard; respect the minefield as a no-go zone and farm from outside it."},{"t":"Don't Alpha Strike in without an out","d":"Blinking onto him with no Flash and his Satchel up leaves you stranded in artillery range as he knocks himself away and his jungler collapses — Q is your only escape and it's now on cooldown."}],"tradeGood":"Alpha Strike onto a minion to farm safely while sidestepping a Bouncing Bomb, taking zero damage and giving him nothing to poke.","tradeBad":"Walking into Bouncing Bomb range to auto him or contest a minion, eating free poke from a champ you can't reach and who can't be punished back.","ahead":"If you do get ahead, don't keep forcing the unwinnable lane — convert it on the map. Shove the wave with your on-hit spike, then Highlander-roam to a flank or a sidelane all-in where you Alpha Strike a frontliner, go untargetable through his Mega Inferno Bomb, and chain Highlander resets through the squishies he can't peel. Deny him farm by ending objectives fast so his Liandry's siege never comes online.","loading":"- Master Yi vs Ziggs - Track: Satchel Charge (W) — it's his self-knockback escape AND his minefield detonator; if you ever all-in, it must be on cooldown or he just peels himself away and re-opens the range. Secondary threat is Bouncing Bomb (Q) poke that denies your farm.. - Survive the poke and farm with Alpha Strike at max range without trading autos, then end the lane indirectly — roam with Highlander or hit your Kraken/BORK spike and force a sidelane all-in the moment he's caught with no Satchel and no flash. You don't out-lane Ziggs; you out-scale and out-roam him, so play for level 6+ pressure on the rest of the map rather than a kill on him.","report":[{"h":"TL;DR","t":"Ziggs sits at max range lobbing Bouncing Bombs you can't answer, blows you off the wave before your on-hit spike, and turns the lane into a CS-starved poke war Master Yi almost never wins."},{"h":"Core Lane Win Condition","t":"Master Yi does not out-lane Ziggs — he survives a brutal poke lane by farming with Alpha Strike at max range and refusing every auto trade, then wins the GAME by scaling to his Kraken/BORK on-hit spike and out-roaming him with Highlander. The lane is conceded; the win condition is reaching 2+ items even on CS and converting that into objectives and teamfight flanks where Ziggs can't kite you."},{"h":"Level Advantage Chart","t":"Ziggs owns 1-5 hard on pure range; level 6 narrows it as Highlander gives you mobility; favor only approaches even at 2+ items where your on-hit DPS one-shots him if you can ever touch him."},{"h":"Trading Rules","t":"Never auto-trade — you can't reach him. Only commit when his Satchel Charge is on cooldown and you have Highlander up; otherwise farm with Alpha Strike when his Bouncing Bomb is down and disengage."},{"h":"Wave Management","t":"Slow-push or shove and crash into his tower so you can recall on spikes and roam; never let the wave freeze near your tower inside his minefield where he free-pokes you off CS."},{"h":"Key Ability Interactions","t":"Alpha Strike makes you untargetable, which dodges his Mega Inferno Bomb and a telegraphed Bouncing Bomb if timed — but it needs a target in melee range, so it's a farm/burst tool here, not a gap-closer. His Satchel Charge self-knockback hard-counters your commit: even after you blink in, he peels himself away. Meditate out-sustains some bomb poke but does nothing about the range gap."},{"h":"Rune Setup","t":"Lethal Tempo for the sustained on-hit DPS you need to delete him the moment you reach melee; secondary Resolve with Second Wind (heavy poke matchup) and Bone Plating, or Conditioning, plus Overgrowth — take Second Wind specifically to mitigate his Bouncing Bomb chip."},{"h":"Summoner Spells","t":"Flash plus Teleport — this is a scaling/roam lane you can't kill in, so TP keeps you on XP/CS through poke recalls and lets you impact other lanes; take Ignite only if your jungler plans to dive him early, which is rare here."},{"h":"Itemization","t":"Rush Kraken Slayer or Blade of the Ruined King for your on-hit spike, then Wit's End — its MR and on-hit magic damage directly counters his entire AP poke profile. Take Mercury's Treads for the MR and to cut his E slow; Hexdrinker/Maw early if his poke is snowballing, and add Wit's End MR before extending your build."},{"h":"All-In Windows","t":"Only when his Satchel Charge is down and you have Highlander active — Alpha Strike in, Wuju Style true damage plus on-hit, and burst him before he can self-peel. Outside that exact window there is no all-in; he kites or knocks himself away every time."},{"h":"Jungle Interaction","t":"You're extremely gank-dependent here — call your jungler early because a gank that lands CC catches Ziggs out of position and is your best shot at a lead. Conversely his minefield and Satchel make HIM hard to gank, and his long range means he poke-zones you while his own jungler dives, so ward and respect collapses."},{"h":"Common Mistakes","t":"Yi players walk up to last-hit or try to 'win lane' by trading autos, eating poke that delays the item spike and feeds a champ who can't be punished; the fix is to accept the lane is lost, farm with Alpha Strike from max range, and play for scaling and roams."},{"h":"How to Play From Behind","t":"Farm only with Alpha Strike under tower, dodge every bomb, take Second Wind value, and avoid all poke; ping for jungle help, give up the lane gracefully, and ride your team to a 2-item state where you still spike hard even behind."},{"h":"How to Snowball","t":"If ahead, shove and roam with Highlander resets, take objectives to deny his Liandry's siege timing, and look for sidelane all-ins or teamfight flanks where you Alpha Strike a frontliner, go untargetable, and run down the carries he can't kite."},{"h":"Final Matchup Rating","t":"HARD (8/10 difficulty, 8/10 carry) — a near-unwinnable lane phase against pure artillery range; concede the lane, scale to your on-hit spike, and win the game by out-roaming and out-fighting him everywhere except in his poke range."}]}};
